111239bf-d3de-4c95-889d-d7d8392cdf2c Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 350 F.
111239bf-d3de-4c95-889d-d7d8392cdf2c Add the dry ingredients to a large mixing bowl and stir to combine.
111239bf-d3de-4c95-889d-d7d8392cdf2c In another mixing bowl or the bowl of a stand mixer, cream together the butter, sugar and molasses until light and fluffy. Do not over-cream and try to keep the butter mixture below 68 F.
111239bf-d3de-4c95-889d-d7d8392cdf2c When color lightens and the texture is a bit fluffy, add in cold eggs one at a time, incorporating the first before adding the second, then mixing only until the egg is absorbed.
111239bf-d3de-4c95-889d-d7d8392cdf2c Add dry ingredients and mix gently until just combined. Fold in chocolate chips and three quarters of the M&Ms.
111239bf-d3de-4c95-889d-d7d8392cdf2c Prepare a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with parchment or oil/butter.
111239bf-d3de-4c95-889d-d7d8392cdf2c Press the dough into the pan to a uniform thickness. Top with remaining M&Ms.
111239bf-d3de-4c95-889d-d7d8392cdf2c Bake at 350 F for 25 minutes. Remove and cool somewhat before cutting. Store sealed in a cool, dry place for up to five days.
d76661f6-ebd3-44af-a575-8d92d4ec9176 Gather the ingredients.
d76661f6-ebd3-44af-a575-8d92d4ec9176 Pre-heat the oven to 350 F.
d76661f6-ebd3-44af-a575-8d92d4ec9176 Cream together the butter and granulated sugar using a stand or hand mixer.
d76661f6-ebd3-44af-a575-8d92d4ec9176 Beat in the eggs and vanilla.
d76661f6-ebd3-44af-a575-8d92d4ec9176 In a separate bowl, sift together the all-purpose flour, baking powder, and salt.
d76661f6-ebd3-44af-a575-8d92d4ec9176 Stir the dry ingredients into the wet until fully incorporated.
d76661f6-ebd3-44af-a575-8d92d4ec9176 Stir in 3/4 of the rainbow sprinkles.
d76661f6-ebd3-44af-a575-8d92d4ec9176 Butter and flour an 8-inch square baking pan or line with parchment paper.
d76661f6-ebd3-44af-a575-8d92d4ec9176 Pour the batter into the pan, sprinkle on the remaining sprinkles, and bake in the oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
d76661f6-ebd3-44af-a575-8d92d4ec9176 Cool and cut into 9 or 12 slices.
d76661f6-ebd3-44af-a575-8d92d4ec9176 While the bars are cooling, add the chocolate chips to a small, microwavable bowl and melt for 30 to 60 seconds.
d76661f6-ebd3-44af-a575-8d92d4ec9176 Drizzle the melted chocolate over the baked bars.
4a0a58cf-6715-49ca-84a7-c0c8ae736829 Gather the ingredients.
4a0a58cf-6715-49ca-84a7-c0c8ae736829 Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. In the bowl of a food processor fitted with the S-shaped (sabatier) blade, combine 3/4 cup of the chilled butter, powdered sugar, and salt. Process until moist clumps begin to form.
4a0a58cf-6715-49ca-84a7-c0c8ae736829 Add the flour and egg, and pulse just until a dough forms
4a0a58cf-6715-49ca-84a7-c0c8ae736829 Press the dough onto bottom and 3/4 inch up the sides of a 13x9x2-inch baking pan. Bake until the crust is golden brown, about 22 minutes. Allow the crust to cool slightly on a wire rack. Maintain the oven temperature as you proceed through the next steps.
4a0a58cf-6715-49ca-84a7-c0c8ae736829 In a large saucepan, bring the brown sugar, honey, and remaining 3/4 cup of butter to a boil, stirring frequently. Boil for 2 minutes.
4a0a58cf-6715-49ca-84a7-c0c8ae736829 Remove the saucepan from the heat and add the vanilla extract. (The mixture will bubbly slightly when the vanilla is added.)
4a0a58cf-6715-49ca-84a7-c0c8ae736829 Add the pecans and stir to coat completely.
4a0a58cf-6715-49ca-84a7-c0c8ae736829 Pour the pecan filling onto prepared crust, spreading it out evenly. Return the pan to the 375 degree oven. Bake until filling thickens and bubbles all over, about 20 minutes.
4a0a58cf-6715-49ca-84a7-c0c8ae736829 Allow to cool completely on a wire rack. Cut into 2-inch squares.
a4c3bd77-1362-4533-8613-0bd0d1f2a125 Gather the ingredients.
a4c3bd77-1362-4533-8613-0bd0d1f2a125 Pre-heat the oven to 350 F.
a4c3bd77-1362-4533-8613-0bd0d1f2a125 Add the graham crackers to a food processor and pulse until you have crumbs. Add in the sugar and melted butter.
a4c3bd77-1362-4533-8613-0bd0d1f2a125 Press the graham cracker mixture into the bottom of an 8" x 8" square baking pan. Note that a glass pan works very well for this recipe.
a4c3bd77-1362-4533-8613-0bd0d1f2a125 Bake for 10 minutes and allow to cool slightly, while leaving the oven on.
a4c3bd77-1362-4533-8613-0bd0d1f2a125 For the lime filling: Add the egg yolks to a mixing bowl and, using a stand or hand mixer, beat for a few minutes until fluffy.
a4c3bd77-1362-4533-8613-0bd0d1f2a125 Mix in the sweetened condensed milk, lime juice, salt, and lime zest.
a4c3bd77-1362-4533-8613-0bd0d1f2a125 Pour the mixture into the graham cracker crust and return to the oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until set.
a4c3bd77-1362-4533-8613-0bd0d1f2a125 Cool to room temperature and then refrigerate for 4 hours.
a4c3bd77-1362-4533-8613-0bd0d1f2a125 Slice into bars and serve with a wedge of lime on top, if desired.
7d07f85a-13f3-4a5b-8552-e04eedab762e Gather the ingredients.
7d07f85a-13f3-4a5b-8552-e04eedab762e Grease a 9x13-inch baking pan with non-stick cooking spray.
7d07f85a-13f3-4a5b-8552-e04eedab762e In a medium-sized saucepan that is large enough to also fit the marshmallows, melt the butter.
7d07f85a-13f3-4a5b-8552-e04eedab762e Add the marshmallows, turn the heat to low, and stir until the marshmallows have completely melted. Don't leave the marshmallows unsupervised—they marshmallows will burn or brown very easily.
7d07f85a-13f3-4a5b-8552-e04eedab762e Stir in the cereal two cups at a time until they are thoroughly combined.
7d07f85a-13f3-4a5b-8552-e04eedab762e Press the Rice Krispies mixture into the greased baking pan. We recommend greasing your hands as well to prevent the mixture from sticking to fingers. Allow treats to cool and then cut into 12 rectangles.
7d07f85a-13f3-4a5b-8552-e04eedab762e Place a sheet of parchment paper over a baking sheet.
7d07f85a-13f3-4a5b-8552-e04eedab762e Put 1 cup of the colored candy melts into a mug. Microwave 30 seconds at a time until the candy has melted. Stir in the 1 to 2 teaspoons of oil until it is completely combined. Dip three of the rectangles into the candy, covering about 1/3 of each rectangle. Try dipping them both vertically and horizontally. Lay each rectangle onto the sheet of parchment paper. Arrange the candy eyes as you like onto the melted white chocolate. Experiment with different arrangements and different amounts of eyes.
7d07f85a-13f3-4a5b-8552-e04eedab762e Repeat with remaining color candy melts. Allow them to cool completely. Store Rice Krispie treats in an airtight container.
5877cfc4-a1b1-48d6-851e-6466462e28ee Gather your ingredients and preheat the oven to 300F.
5877cfc4-a1b1-48d6-851e-6466462e28ee Grab two oven-safe pans or dishes. Put the walnuts in one of the pans, and the wheat bran in the other, and put both pans in the oven. Toast the walnuts and the wheat bran until they’re a bit more brown and fragrant than before they went in, about 15 minutes.
5877cfc4-a1b1-48d6-851e-6466462e28ee While the nuts and bran are toasting, mash the bananas and the dates in a medium bowl. The dates may not mash very much — just get the mixture gooey.
5877cfc4-a1b1-48d6-851e-6466462e28ee Roughly chop the toasted walnuts. Add the chopped walnuts, the toasted bran, cinnamon and the salt to the bowl with the bananas and dates. Mix well.
5877cfc4-a1b1-48d6-851e-6466462e28ee Add the liquid egg whites and mix until well combined.
5877cfc4-a1b1-48d6-851e-6466462e28ee Place a piece of parchment paper into an 8x8 inch baking pan such that the paper covers the entire interior surface of the pan.
5877cfc4-a1b1-48d6-851e-6466462e28ee Pour the batter into the paper-covered pan and spread it evenly as best you can. It’s ok if there are a few odd folds.
5877cfc4-a1b1-48d6-851e-6466462e28ee Put the pan in the oven and bake for about one hour and ten minutes, or until the egg white is no longer making surface bubbles, and the surface of the bars is no longer shiny.
5877cfc4-a1b1-48d6-851e-6466462e28ee Remove the bars from the pan via the parchment and let them cool to room temperature before cutting to your desired size. Refrigerate and consume within one week.
c3ae884f-0a88-42a8-ad92-513ee3cf4a06 Gather the ingredients. Heat the oven to 350 F.
c3ae884f-0a88-42a8-ad92-513ee3cf4a06 Grease and flour a 9x13-inch baking pan.
c3ae884f-0a88-42a8-ad92-513ee3cf4a06 In a small bowl, lightly beat one large egg.
c3ae884f-0a88-42a8-ad92-513ee3cf4a06 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, combine the cake mix, butter, and the beaten egg. Beat on low speed until the butter is blended into the dry cake mix and the egg mixture and the crumbs begin to clump together. Stop mixing and pat the crumbs firmly into the bottom of the prepared baking pan.
c3ae884f-0a88-42a8-ad92-513ee3cf4a06 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the softened cream cheese until smooth. Add the confectioners' sugar and beat until the mixture is light and well blended. Beat in the remaining 3 large eggs. Continue beating until very smooth. Beat in the vanilla, if using.
c3ae884f-0a88-42a8-ad92-513ee3cf4a06 Pour the cream cheese batter over the first layer and spread to cover evenly.
c3ae884f-0a88-42a8-ad92-513ee3cf4a06 Bake the chess squares for 35 to 40 minutes, or until set and lightly browned.
c3ae884f-0a88-42a8-ad92-513ee3cf4a06 Cook on a rack and then cover the pan with foil or plastic wrap. Transfer the pan to the refrigerator to chill thoroughly before cutting. They are a little gooier if you cut them while they are still warm.
c3ae884f-0a88-42a8-ad92-513ee3cf4a06 This recipe makes about 24 (2-inch) bars. Store the bars in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
bcde78f4-2eaa-424f-93f7-524f46a3f7c1 Gather the ingredients.
bcde78f4-2eaa-424f-93f7-524f46a3f7c1 In the bowl of a food processor, pulse the dates, almonds and walnuts, until the largest chunks of nuts are the size of peppercorns or smaller.
bcde78f4-2eaa-424f-93f7-524f46a3f7c1 Scrape down the sides and add the almond butter and vanilla. Process until well combined and the mixture sticks together when pressed. Stop and scrape down the sides once or twice as needed.
bcde78f4-2eaa-424f-93f7-524f46a3f7c1 Line an 8-inch or 9-inch square baking pan with parchment paper. Dump out the mixture onto the paper and press into the pan until level.
bcde78f4-2eaa-424f-93f7-524f46a3f7c1 Refrigerate for an hour and then cut into bars with a sharp knife.
bcde78f4-2eaa-424f-93f7-524f46a3f7c1 Individually wrap each bar and store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks, or in the freezer for up to 2 months.
eac8b1a7-c074-4bca-916d-295bbc940994 Gather the ingredients.
eac8b1a7-c074-4bca-916d-295bbc940994 Preheat oven to 350 F.
eac8b1a7-c074-4bca-916d-295bbc940994 Put the butter in a 9-by-13-inch baking pan and put it in the oven until the butter has melted.
eac8b1a7-c074-4bca-916d-295bbc940994 Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over the melted butter.
eac8b1a7-c074-4bca-916d-295bbc940994 Spread the chocolate chips over the graham cracker crumbs then add a layer of butterscotch chips. Make sure the chips coat the entire layer of graham cracker crumbs.
eac8b1a7-c074-4bca-916d-295bbc940994 Sprinkle coconut over the butterscotch chips layer.
eac8b1a7-c074-4bca-916d-295bbc940994 Drizzle the sweetened condensed milk evenly over the top.
eac8b1a7-c074-4bca-916d-295bbc940994 Sprinkle with the chopped pecans.
eac8b1a7-c074-4bca-916d-295bbc940994 Bake in the preheated oven for about 25 to 30 minutes, until set and lightly browned.
eac8b1a7-c074-4bca-916d-295bbc940994 Cool the bars in the pan. Once cool, cut them into 1 1/2-inch squares.
eac8b1a7-c074-4bca-916d-295bbc940994 Serve and enjoy!
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 Gather the ingredients.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 Spray a 7-inch round baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Cut a sheet of parchment paper to fit into the bottom of the pan and spray it lightly.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the butter and sugar together until it is light and fluffy.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in the vanilla.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 In a separate bowl, combine the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt; blend thoroughly with a spoon or whisk. Add the dry ingredients to the first mixture and beat on low speed just until blended.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 With a spoon or spatula, fold in the chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 Spread the batter in the prepared pan and cover with foil.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 Add 1 1/2 cups of water to the Instant Pot inner pot and put a baking sling in the pot. (If you don't have a silicone sling make one by putting a trivet in the pot, and putting in a long, folded sheet of foil; this will make it easier to lift the pan out when the brownies are ready.) Place the pan on the trivet or sling.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 Secure the Instant Pot lid and ensure the steam release valve is in the sealing position. Choose the pressure cook function (or manual on older models), high pressure, and set the time to 40 minutes. When the time is up, let the pressure release naturally for 10 minutes. Carefully turn the valve to venting to release the remaining steam. Lift the pan of brownies out, remove the foil, and set them on a rack to cool.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 When the brownies are cool, prepare the chocolate ganache glaze. Place the semisweet chocolate in a bowl and set it aside. Pour the heavy cream into a saucepan. Place the pan over medium heat and bring the cream to a boil. Pour the cream over the semisweet chocolate; stir until the chocolate has melted and the mixture is smooth.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 Slide a knife around the side of the pan to loosen the brownies. Carefully remove the brownies to a plate.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 Spread the chocolate glaze mixture over the brownies, little some drip down the sides, if desired.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 Sprinkle chopped nuts over the wet glaze. Cool completely.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 Slice the brownies and serve.
1beee359-17b3-4c09-adec-ecb1d71f0253 Enjoy!
7ced325f-90e4-46c3-958e-bc1c928b21fc Gather the ingredients.
7ced325f-90e4-46c3-958e-bc1c928b21fc Preheat oven to 350°F. Spray a 13" x 9" pan with nonstick baking spray containing flour and set aside.
7ced325f-90e4-46c3-958e-bc1c928b21fc In a large bowl, combine butter and 1/2 cup peanut butter and mix well. Add sugar and brown sugar and beat. Then stir in the egg, milk, and vanilla.
7ced325f-90e4-46c3-958e-bc1c928b21fc Measure the flour carefully, and add to the batter along with baking soda and salt. Mix well.
7ced325f-90e4-46c3-958e-bc1c928b21fc Spread the dough in the prepared pan. Bake for 20-30 minutes or until the bars are just set and light golden brown. The dough will rise quite a bit at first, but then it will settle back down. When the bars are evenly colored, they are done baking.
7ced325f-90e4-46c3-958e-bc1c928b21fc When you take the bars out of the oven, immediately spread them with 1 cup of the peanut butter chips. You can use the type of chips that are swirled with chocolate if you'd like.
7ced325f-90e4-46c3-958e-bc1c928b21fc Put the bars on a cooling rack. You want the bars to be still warm before you add the chocolate and peanut butter chip frosting.
7ced325f-90e4-46c3-958e-bc1c928b21fc Then combine the chocolate chips and 1 cup of the remaining peanut butter chips in a small microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on high for 1 minute, remove and stir. Continue microwaving for 30 second intervals, stirring after each interval, until the mixture is smooth.
7ced325f-90e4-46c3-958e-bc1c928b21fc Pour this mixture over the bars and gently spread to coat. Let stand until set, then cut into bars to serve.
b06fab89-634a-471f-bc45-279c64503856 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line a 9-inch square baking pan with aluminum foil. Lightly grease the foil with vegetable oil.
b06fab89-634a-471f-bc45-279c64503856 Place 4 tablespoons vegetable oil, maple syrup, peanut butter, and brown sugar in a microwave-proof bowl or measuring cup. Microwave gently on low heat for 30 seconds or so, or until ingredients can be whisked together easily. Whisk in the vanilla and the salt.
b06fab89-634a-471f-bc45-279c64503856 Mix the oats and quinoa flakes together in a bowl. Coarsely chop the nuts and dried fruit, and stir them into the oat mixture. Stir in the chocolate chips.
b06fab89-634a-471f-bc45-279c64503856 Add the liquid mixture to the oat mixture and stir until the dry ingredients are well coated. The mixture should be sticky and should start to clump together. If it doesn't, and it seems dry and crumbly, add more maple syrup to achieve the desired consistency.
b06fab89-634a-471f-bc45-279c64503856 Press the mixture down firmly into a baking pan. Grease a small piece of aluminum foil and use it to compress the mixture down into the pan as smoothly and firmly as possible.
b06fab89-634a-471f-bc45-279c64503856 Place pan in the oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until grains appear toasted and smell fragrant. Remove from the oven and let cool for 10 minutes. Finish cooling pan in the refrigerator, and for best (least crumbly) results, wait until the mixture is well-chilled before cutting it into bars.
cbddffd7-9e22-4884-a256-0e2797283027 Heat the oven to 375 F.
cbddffd7-9e22-4884-a256-0e2797283027 Butter a 9-inch square baking pan.
cbddffd7-9e22-4884-a256-0e2797283027 Combine oats, flour, 3/4 cup of brown sugar, chopped pecans, salt, the baking soda, and the butter; mix until mixture is well blended and crumbly.
cbddffd7-9e22-4884-a256-0e2797283027 Reserve about 1 1/2 cups of the crumb mixture and press the other half into the prepared baking pan.
cbddffd7-9e22-4884-a256-0e2797283027 Bake the crust for 10 minutes.
cbddffd7-9e22-4884-a256-0e2797283027 Remove the crust to a rack and set aside.
9d31f62f-15ca-481a-8514-44698ec6ddb1 Gather the ingredients.
9d31f62f-15ca-481a-8514-44698ec6ddb1 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Grease a 13-inch x 9-inch pan and set aside.
9d31f62f-15ca-481a-8514-44698ec6ddb1 In a large bowl, combine the flour, oats, brown sugar, soda and salt and blend with a spoon until mixed. Add the melted butter and mix until crumbly. Reserve half of the crumb mixture (about 3 cups) for the topping. Press the remaining crumb mixture in the bottom of the prepared pan.
9d31f62f-15ca-481a-8514-44698ec6ddb1 In a small bowl, combine the caramels and cream. Heat in the microwave oven for 3 to 4 minutes on 50% power, stirring twice during cooking, until the caramels are melted and the mixture is smooth.
9d31f62f-15ca-481a-8514-44698ec6ddb1 Sprinkle the chocolate chips and pecans over the crust in the pan. Drizzle evenly with the melted caramel mixture and sprinkle with the reserved crumb mixture evenly to coat.
9d31f62f-15ca-481a-8514-44698ec6ddb1 Bake the bars for 18 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown and bubbling around the edges.
9d31f62f-15ca-481a-8514-44698ec6ddb1 Cool the bars for 1 to 2 hours on a wire rack or until completely cooled. Cut into bars, then store covered with foil at room temperature.
9d31f62f-15ca-481a-8514-44698ec6ddb1 Enjoy!
d2b8f1cb-5a78-49a5-927a-5081d9cd39cc Preheat the oven to 325°F.
d2b8f1cb-5a78-49a5-927a-5081d9cd39cc In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, 3/4 cup powdered sugar, and 3/4 cup melted butter; mix with a hand mixer or a spoon until crumbs form. Press the crumbs into the bottom and 1/2" up sides of a 9" x 13" pan.
d2b8f1cb-5a78-49a5-927a-5081d9cd39cc Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until the crust is just set.
d2b8f1cb-5a78-49a5-927a-5081d9cd39cc While the crust is in the oven, beat the eggs with electric mixer until they are very light and fluffy; this should take about 3 to 4 minutes. Gradually add the sugar, beating until the mixture is light yellow and thick. Beat in the baking powder, flour, 3/4 cup plus two tablespoons lemon juice, and the salt until combined.
d2b8f1cb-5a78-49a5-927a-5081d9cd39cc When the crust comes out of the oven, pour the filling over as soon as it is beaten together. Return the bars to the oven and bake for 25 to 35 minutes longer or until the filling is set and light golden brown on top. Let cool completely.
d2b8f1cb-5a78-49a5-927a-5081d9cd39cc In a small bowl, combine 2 cups powdered sugar, 1/4 cup melted butter and 1/4 cup lemon juice. Mix well with a wire whisk, then pour the frosting over the cooled bars. You can also sprinkle the bars with powdered sugar through a small sieve.
d2b8f1cb-5a78-49a5-927a-5081d9cd39cc Refrigerate the bars until cold, then cut into squares or rectangles to serve.
8926e868-23ea-4be7-baf6-3b6ecf1119f8 Gather the ingredients.
8926e868-23ea-4be7-baf6-3b6ecf1119f8 Heat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas Mark 4.
8926e868-23ea-4be7-baf6-3b6ecf1119f8 Use 1 teaspoon butter to grease a 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking pan and line the base with parchment paper. The smaller pan will yield thicker and chewier bars; the larger pan's flapjacks will be crispier and thinner.
8926e868-23ea-4be7-baf6-3b6ecf1119f8 Place the golden syrup and 6 ounces of butter into a large saucepan and heat gently, stirring well, until the butter has melted into the syrup.
8926e868-23ea-4be7-baf6-3b6ecf1119f8 Put the oats in a large bowl and add a pinch of salt and the optional ginger. Pour in the butter and syrup mixture and stir to coat the oats.
8926e868-23ea-4be7-baf6-3b6ecf1119f8 Transfer the mixture into the prepared baking pan and spread it out, making sure the surface is even.
8926e868-23ea-4be7-baf6-3b6ecf1119f8 Bake in the heated oven for about 25 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from the oven while the flapjack is still slightly soft; it will harden once it has cooled.
8926e868-23ea-4be7-baf6-3b6ecf1119f8 Place the pan on a wire cooling rack and cut the flapjack into squares, but leave in the tin until completely cooled.
8926e868-23ea-4be7-baf6-3b6ecf1119f8 The flapjack bars keep well stored in an airtight tin. Enjoy.
8400a65f-8edc-4368-b5ed-421193506d3d Crush the graham crackers into large crumbs or chunks in a ziplock bag or in a bowl. Set aside.
8400a65f-8edc-4368-b5ed-421193506d3d Grease a 9x9 inch pan with non-stick spray.
8400a65f-8edc-4368-b5ed-421193506d3d Heat the butter in a large saucepan. Make sure it is large enough to accommodate all of the marshmallows.
8400a65f-8edc-4368-b5ed-421193506d3d Add the marshmallows to the pan and turn down the heat to low. Stir frequently until the marshmallows have melted. Be careful not to let the marshmallows brown or burn.
8400a65f-8edc-4368-b5ed-421193506d3d Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the Rice Krispie cereal, slowly adding a few cups at a time.
8400a65f-8edc-4368-b5ed-421193506d3d Allow the mixture to cool very slightly, about 30 seconds to a minute. Stir in the graham cracker crumbs, chocolate chunks, and extra mini marshmallows until evenly distributed throughout the Rice Krispie mixture. If you add the chocolate before the treats have cooled slightly, then the chocolate will completely melt into the treats, changing the look and texture. If you wait too long for them to cool then you will not be able to stir in the chocolate chunks, marshmallows, and graham crackers.
8400a65f-8edc-4368-b5ed-421193506d3d Pour the mixture into the greased pan. Lightly grease your hands with non-stick spray and press the mixture evenly into the pan. Press in more mini marshmallows and chocolate chunks into the top of the treats if desired.
8400a65f-8edc-4368-b5ed-421193506d3d After the treats have completely cooled, cut them into squares or other desired shape. Store in an airtight container or place in plastic zip bags in the freezer.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Place the chocolate bar in the freezer for 30 minutes. Cold chocolate is easier to cut.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Grease a large glass with butter.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Set aside.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 In a large saucepan over medium-low heat, melt butter.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Reduce heat to low and add marshmallow cream.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Stir often until butter and creme are melted through and combined.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Remove from heat and add crisped rice cereal.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Carefully fold cereal into marshmallow mixture until well coated.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Transfer to greased dish.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Place a small about of butter on hands (this keeps the cereal mixture from sticking to you).
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Gently press into a glass pan, making sure to cereal is evenly distributes and is about 1 1/2 inches or so, thick.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Let cool for 15 minutes.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 While treats are cooling, chop 1/3 cup/80 mL of chocolate and set aside.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Place 1/2 cup/120 mL of salted caramel sauce into a small bowl.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Warm in the microwave oven for about 15 seconds.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Pour into a small resealable plastic bag.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Let out air and close.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Using scissors, make a small snip on the corner of the bag. This can get messy so make sure you have a few paper towels.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Drizzle salted caramel over top of marshmallow treats and top with chocolate.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Place into the refrigerator for 10 minutes.
1938e7ed-9995-43a6-8fa1-02fa02cf7f15 Then cut into equal-sized squares.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Gather the ingredients.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Butter a 10-by-15-inch jelly roll pan and set aside.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 In a large saucepan, melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips until smooth, stirring frequently.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stirring until mixture is melted and smooth.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Spread half of this melted chocolate mixture into the prepared pan and refrigerate.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Stir peanuts into remaining chocolate mixture in saucepan and set aside.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 In another large heavy saucepan, combine butter and light cream over medium heat, stirring until melted.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Stir in the pudding mix (make sure it's not instant pudding, but the kind that's cooked) and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens slightly. Do not let the mixture come to a boil.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Remove pan from heat and beat in powdered sugar, using a mixer. Then add vanilla and blend.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Let this mixture cool for 15 minutes.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Then spread pudding mixture over the solidified chocolate mixture in the jelly roll pan. I like to drop it onto the chocolate layer by small spoonfuls, then spread it gently using an offset spatula.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Chill the chocolate and pudding layers for 30 to 40 minutes until firm.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Then drop reserved chocolate and peanut mixture over pudding layer with a spoon and spread gently to cover.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Chill bars until firm, about 2 hours, then cut into bars. Store in refrigerator.
42400806-a166-4ab6-8b0c-176e25c954f4 Serve and enjoy!
2d39906b-b747-4dbe-97b7-bd5a55955e4a Gather the pumpkin bar ingredients.
2d39906b-b747-4dbe-97b7-bd5a55955e4a Grease and flour a 13x9-inch baking pan. Preheat oven to 350 F.
2d39906b-b747-4dbe-97b7-bd5a55955e4a Prepare the batter in a medium bowl by combining the flour, brown sugar, granulated sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt. Set aside.
2d39906b-b747-4dbe-97b7-bd5a55955e4a In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs, pumpkin, vanilla, and oil until well blended, scraping the bowl a few times.
2d39906b-b747-4dbe-97b7-bd5a55955e4a Stir in the dry ingredients into the wet just until blended.
2d39906b-b747-4dbe-97b7-bd5a55955e4a Spread batter into prepared baking pan.
2d39906b-b747-4dbe-97b7-bd5a55955e4a Gather the streusel topping ingredients.
2d39906b-b747-4dbe-97b7-bd5a55955e4a Make the streusel topping by combining the 3/4 cup flour, 1/3 cup brown sugar, and cinnamon in a medium bowl.
2d39906b-b747-4dbe-97b7-bd5a55955e4a Using a pastry blender, or forks, cut in the butter until crumbly and mix in the pecans.
2d39906b-b747-4dbe-97b7-bd5a55955e4a Sprinkle topping evenly over the pumpkin batter.
2d39906b-b747-4dbe-97b7-bd5a55955e4a Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until set. A toothpick inserted in the center should come out clean. Cool bars in the pan on a rack and cut in squares to serve.
46eff2e2-fcb1-4cc3-98e2-d5f8fda22b9f Preheat the oven to 375 F. Spray a 13" x 9" pan with a nonstick baking spray containing flour and set aside.
46eff2e2-fcb1-4cc3-98e2-d5f8fda22b9f Break the cookie dough into the pan and, using floured fingers, press into an even layer. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until just set. Cool the crust for 30 minutes.
46eff2e2-fcb1-4cc3-98e2-d5f8fda22b9f In a small microwave-safe bowl, combine the chocolate chips and 1/2 cup of the peanut butter. Microwave on high for 2 minutes; remove and stir. Continue to microwave for 30-second intervals, stirring after each interval, until mixture is melted and smooth. Pour the melted chocolate mixture over the cookie layer and refrigerate.
46eff2e2-fcb1-4cc3-98e2-d5f8fda22b9f Then, in a medium bowl, combine the softened butter and 1 cup peanut butter; beat until smooth. Add the powdered sugar, cream, and vanilla and beat until fluffy. You may need to add more powdered sugar or cream to reach the desired consistency.
46eff2e2-fcb1-4cc3-98e2-d5f8fda22b9f Spread the peanut butter cream over the chocolate layer and sprinkle with the peanuts; press in slightly so they stick to the frosting. Let the bars stand until set, then cut into squares to serve.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b Gather the ingredients and preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b Lightly grease a baking tin measuring roughly 8x8-inch/20x20-centimeter and at least 1 1/2-in/4-centimeter high. Line the bottom with greaseproof paper.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b Put the butter, caster sugar, and golden syrup into a large saucepan and slowly melt over a medium heat, taking care not to burn it.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b In a large, roomy baking bowl, combine the dried fruits, walnuts, ground almonds, spices, and both types of oats.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b Pour in the melted butter and sugars and stir well to make sure all of the ingredients are combined and covered with the sticky liquid. Add the brandy, if using, and stir again.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b Press the mixture into the greased baking tin, making sure it goes right into the corners and that, when finished, the surface is level.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Check the flapjack from time to time to make sure it is not cooking too fast. If it is over-browning too quickly, turn the heat down.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b Once baked, remove the tin from the oven and leave to cool for 10 minutes.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b When a little cooled, remove from the tin and cut into chunks or slices. Place the pieces onto a wire cooling rack and leave to completely cool.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b Meanwhile, break the chocolate into small pieces. Drop into a bowl and place over a pan of simmering, not boiling, water. Stir once it's melted, but take care to use a wooden spoon warm melted chocolate does not like a cold metal spoon.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b Dip the ends of the flapjack chunks into the chocolate with as much or as little as you wish.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b Place back onto the cooling rack and once all are done, pop the cooling rack into the fridge and leave for the chocolate to set.
a12c5494-5fcb-4cd8-81a6-37255ef4656b Serve and enjoy!
7b4fc930-eec4-47ae-8c49-fbc6b29e074f Heat the oven to 350 F.
7b4fc930-eec4-47ae-8c49-fbc6b29e074f Grease and flour a 9-by-13-by-2-inch baking pan.
7b4fc930-eec4-47ae-8c49-fbc6b29e074f In a bowl, combine cake mix, 6 tablespoons of the butter and 1 cup of the rolled oats. Reserve 1 cup of this for​ the crumb topping and set aside.
7b4fc930-eec4-47ae-8c49-fbc6b29e074f To remaining mixture in the bowl, add egg; mix well. Press into pan. Pour cherry filling over crust; spread to cover.
7b4fc930-eec4-47ae-8c49-fbc6b29e074f In​ a large bowl, add the reserved 1 cup crumb mixture, the remaining 1/4 cup oats, the remaining 2 tablespoons butter, the chopped pecans, and brown sugar. Mix well. Sprinkle over cherries.
7b4fc930-eec4-47ae-8c49-fbc6b29e074f Bake in the preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until the topping is lightly browned.
c8e3bde8-cafe-401b-99e1-de8b487f6219 Gather the ingredients.
c8e3bde8-cafe-401b-99e1-de8b487f6219 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Spray a 13x9-pan with nonstick baking spray containing flour and set aside.
c8e3bde8-cafe-401b-99e1-de8b487f6219 In a large bowl, combine both boxes of brownie mix, oil, water, and eggs. Mix with a wooden spoon until blended. Stir in 12-ounce batch of chopped candy bars.
c8e3bde8-cafe-401b-99e1-de8b487f6219 Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until brownies are set and crust is shiny. Don't overbake the brownies.
c8e3bde8-cafe-401b-99e1-de8b487f6219 Cool on a wire rack for 30 minutes.
c8e3bde8-cafe-401b-99e1-de8b487f6219 In a medium microwave-safe bowl, combine the chocolate chips and peanut butter. Microwave on high for 1 minute, remove, and stir. Continue microwaving for 30 second intervals, stirring after each interval, until mixture is smooth.
c8e3bde8-cafe-401b-99e1-de8b487f6219 Stir in the second batch of chopped candy bars and spoon and spread the frosting over the warm brownies.
c8e3bde8-cafe-401b-99e1-de8b487f6219 Let the brownies stand on the wire rack until set.
c8e3bde8-cafe-401b-99e1-de8b487f6219 Cut into bars and serve.
68465db1-4879-44fa-8660-23bc5033e9ab Line an 8x8 baking pan with aluminum foil and set aside.
68465db1-4879-44fa-8660-23bc5033e9ab Mix the melted butter, graham cracker crumbs, and powdered sugar together in a medium bowl. Mix in 3/4 cup of peanut butter. Spread mixture evenly into the bottom of the pan. Packing it in slightly with your hands.
68465db1-4879-44fa-8660-23bc5033e9ab Combine 2 tablespoons of peanut butter with the chocolate chips and melt in a microwave. Stir until smooth and pour evenly over the graham cracker crumb layer.
68465db1-4879-44fa-8660-23bc5033e9ab Refrigerate until firm, usually about 3 hours and allow to come to room temperature for 10 minutes before cutting. Serve chilled or at room temperature. ​
a8af5345-75c6-4e2d-8082-3f9ab18e2d72 Gather the ingredients.
a8af5345-75c6-4e2d-8082-3f9ab18e2d72 Heat the oven to 325 F (165 C/Gas 3). Grease and flour a 13-by-9-by-2-inch baking pan.
a8af5345-75c6-4e2d-8082-3f9ab18e2d72 In a bowl, combine the cake mix with 1 egg and the melted butter. Mix until well blended.
a8af5345-75c6-4e2d-8082-3f9ab18e2d72 Press into the prepared baking pan.
a8af5345-75c6-4e2d-8082-3f9ab18e2d72 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the confectioners' sugar with the cream cheese, vanilla. and the 3 remaining eggs until smooth.
a8af5345-75c6-4e2d-8082-3f9ab18e2d72 Pour about 2/3 of the topping mixture onto the cake mixture; sprinkle with crumbled cookies then pour remaining mixture evenly over crumbs.
a8af5345-75c6-4e2d-8082-3f9ab18e2d72 Bake in the preheated oven for about 50 to 60 minutes, or until topping is lightly browned.
a8af5345-75c6-4e2d-8082-3f9ab18e2d72 Cool thoroughly and cut into bars. Keep refrigerated.
5bda6113-cf21-43cb-95eb-3e8d249349d5 In a large skillet, roast sesame seeds over low heat until they start to pop. They should become fragrant after 4 or 5 minutes.
5bda6113-cf21-43cb-95eb-3e8d249349d5 Remove seeds from heat and reserve.
5bda6113-cf21-43cb-95eb-3e8d249349d5 In a medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, water, and honey over low heat.
5bda6113-cf21-43cb-95eb-3e8d249349d5 Stir often until sugar is melted, making sure that the syrup does not burn.
5bda6113-cf21-43cb-95eb-3e8d249349d5 Remove from heat when the syrup is thick (about 5-7 minutes).
5bda6113-cf21-43cb-95eb-3e8d249349d5 Immediately pour sesame seeds into syrup, mixing to combine.
5bda6113-cf21-43cb-95eb-3e8d249349d5 Spread the sesame seed and syrup mixture onto a cookie sheet that is either greased or lined with parchment paper.
5bda6113-cf21-43cb-95eb-3e8d249349d5 Place another piece of parchment paper on top and roll gently with a rolling pin to flatten the top of the candy.
5bda6113-cf21-43cb-95eb-3e8d249349d5 Let candy cool about 5 minutes and then cut with a sharp knife into 1-inch squares or smaller rectangles. (Grease the knife if you are having a hard time cutting through).
5bda6113-cf21-43cb-95eb-3e8d249349d5 Cool completely and enjoy or store in an airtight container.
db90a325-2726-41bc-8ca2-3a0b910b1ce1 Gather the ingredients.
db90a325-2726-41bc-8ca2-3a0b910b1ce1 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray an 8-inch square baking dish with cooking spray.​
db90a325-2726-41bc-8ca2-3a0b910b1ce1 In a large saucepan, melt butter over medium-low heat.
db90a325-2726-41bc-8ca2-3a0b910b1ce1 When butter is melted, remove pan from heat and add flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda and vanilla. Mix until well-combined.​
db90a325-2726-41bc-8ca2-3a0b910b1ce1 Set aside about one-third of the mixture. Press the remaining mixture into prepared pan.
db90a325-2726-41bc-8ca2-3a0b910b1ce1 Lay sliced Snickers bars over top, leaving a 1/4-inch border all the way around. Crumble remaining oat mixture over the sliced candy bars.​
db90a325-2726-41bc-8ca2-3a0b910b1ce1 Bake 25 minutes. Cool completely, then cut into squares.
db90a325-2726-41bc-8ca2-3a0b910b1ce1 Serve and enjoy!
1ce133d9-2bd7-42ef-83d1-7f6accc4e792 Grease a 9 x 13 baking dish with oil or butter, or spray with nonstick cooking spray.
1ce133d9-2bd7-42ef-83d1-7f6accc4e792 In a medium saucepan, heat the peanut butter, honey and coconut oil over medium-low heat, stirring or whisking until smooth and well-combined. Remove from the heat.
1ce133d9-2bd7-42ef-83d1-7f6accc4e792 Stir in the oats, chocolate chips, coconut, almonds, and vanilla, mixing well until the chocolate chips are completely melted.
1ce133d9-2bd7-42ef-83d1-7f6accc4e792 Pour the mixture into the prepared pan. Refrigerate until the bars are firm. Cut into squares or rectangles. Store the bars in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
318617f8-2648-4a48-bcb8-d9b6cdcc28a2 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
318617f8-2648-4a48-bcb8-d9b6cdcc28a2 Make the crust: In a medium bowl using an electric mixer, beat the butter, confectioners' sugar and vanilla until fluffy, about 1 minute. Gradually add the flour, beating until well combined and mixture holds together and forms a dough. Press the dough over the bottom of the prepared pan.
318617f8-2648-4a48-bcb8-d9b6cdcc28a2 Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until lightly golden and firm when touched.
318617f8-2648-4a48-bcb8-d9b6cdcc28a2 Make the topping: In a medium bowl using an electric mixer on medium-high speed, beat the eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder, lemon zest, and lemon juice until well blended. Pour the mixture over the crust.
318617f8-2648-4a48-bcb8-d9b6cdcc28a2 Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the filling is set.
318617f8-2648-4a48-bcb8-d9b6cdcc28a2 Cool the lemon bars completely in the pan set on a wire rack. Dust with confectioners' sugar before cutting into bars.
4d7d1ba2-7c24-4162-81dc-caa87c768cec Gather the ingredients.
4d7d1ba2-7c24-4162-81dc-caa87c768cec Preheat the oven to 350 F. Butter a 9-by-13-by-2-inch baking pan.
4d7d1ba2-7c24-4162-81dc-caa87c768cec In a bowl combine the sweetened condensed milk and peanut butter; stir to blend thoroughly and then set aside.
4d7d1ba2-7c24-4162-81dc-caa87c768cec In a large bowl combine brown sugar, flour, oatmeal, soda, salt, and butter. Mix well. (You can use a stand mixer with a paddle attachment to mix the crumbs or use your hands.)
4d7d1ba2-7c24-4162-81dc-caa87c768cec Pat 1/2 to 2/3 of the oat mixture in the bottom of the prepared baking pan. Use enough to cover the bottom of the pan. We used about 13 ounces of the mixture for the bottom of the pan, or slightly more than half.
4d7d1ba2-7c24-4162-81dc-caa87c768cec Drizzle the bottom layer evenly with peanut butter mixture. Sprinkle the chocolate chips over the peanut butter layer. Sprinkle the remaining oat crumbs evenly over the chocolate chips.
4d7d1ba2-7c24-4162-81dc-caa87c768cec Bake in the preheated oven for about 18 to 21 minutes. (Watch carefully and take care not to overbake. The edges will be browned and the top will be lightly browned.)
4d7d1ba2-7c24-4162-81dc-caa87c768cec Serve and enjoy!
7fe571b2-27fc-4f60-9372-8605ab153e52 Gather the ingredients.
7fe571b2-27fc-4f60-9372-8605ab153e52 Preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4
7fe571b2-27fc-4f60-9372-8605ab153e52 Butter a 23cm x 33cm / 9"x 13" deep baking tin really well. Line the base with a sheet of greaseproof paper.
7fe571b2-27fc-4f60-9372-8605ab153e52 Put the golden syrup and butter into a non-stick saucepan. Over a low heat, gently heat through until the butter has melted, do not boil. Stir well. It is always difficult to measure Golden syrup accurately but err on the more is better side. A little extra will not harm, too little and the flapjack will not set properly..
7fe571b2-27fc-4f60-9372-8605ab153e52 Put the oats, and nibs (keep back at least 12 for decoration) into a large baking bowl. Mix them together then pour over the melted butter and syrup. Stir really well to ensure all the oats are well coated.
7fe571b2-27fc-4f60-9372-8605ab153e52 Tip the mixture into the greased baking tin, spread evenly making sure the surface is level.
7fe571b2-27fc-4f60-9372-8605ab153e52 Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes then remove the tin and score (do not cut) the surface of the flapjack into 12 squares. Pop a chocolate nib into the centre of each square. Quickly return the tin to the oven and bake for a further 10 minutes or until golden brown but still slightly soft. They will harden as they cool.
7fe571b2-27fc-4f60-9372-8605ab153e52 Place the tin on a wire cooling rack and cut the flapjack into squares but leave in the tin until completely cold. Enjoy.
d4605b58-5145-46ab-8661-c42cdd9ba9c7 Gather the ingredients.
d4605b58-5145-46ab-8661-c42cdd9ba9c7 Preheat oven to 350 F. Arrange the graham crackers in a single layer in an ungreased 15x10x1-inch jelly roll pan.
d4605b58-5145-46ab-8661-c42cdd9ba9c7 Heat brown sugar and margarine to boiling; boil and stir for 1 minute.
d4605b58-5145-46ab-8661-c42cdd9ba9c7 Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
d4605b58-5145-46ab-8661-c42cdd9ba9c7 Pour over graham crackers, spreading evenly; sprinkle with pecans.
d4605b58-5145-46ab-8661-c42cdd9ba9c7 Bake until bubbly, about 8 to 10 minutes.
d4605b58-5145-46ab-8661-c42cdd9ba9c7 Cool slightly and cut into squares.
d4605b58-5145-46ab-8661-c42cdd9ba9c7 Serve and enjoy!
153180de-db5a-475a-bddc-eccd554eac70 Cream butter and sugars; blend in egg and vanilla.
153180de-db5a-475a-bddc-eccd554eac70 Stir in remaining ingredients.
153180de-db5a-475a-bddc-eccd554eac70 Spread batter in a greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
153180de-db5a-475a-bddc-eccd554eac70 Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
153180de-db5a-475a-bddc-eccd554eac70 Sift powdered sugar over bars or top with a confectioners' sugar icing.
36985edc-55a7-414d-af72-e4a2ec5823d4 Heat the oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4). Lightly butter a 10 x 15 x 1-inch sheet pan
36985edc-55a7-414d-af72-e4a2ec5823d4 In a large bowl, cream together 1 cup butter and brown sugar. Beat in eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
36985edc-55a7-414d-af72-e4a2ec5823d4 In another bowl combine the flour, baking soda, and 1 teaspoon salt; stir in oats. Stir dry ingredients into the creamed mixture until well blended; set aside.
36985edc-55a7-414d-af72-e4a2ec5823d4 Pat about three-quarters of the oat mixture into the bottom of the prepared sheet pan. Set aside the remaining oat mixture.
36985edc-55a7-414d-af72-e4a2ec5823d4 In a heavy saucepan over low heat combine the sweetened condensed milk, chocolate chips, 2 tablespoons butter, and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Stir until the chocolate chips have melted and the mixture is smooth. Stir in 2 teaspoons vanilla and pecans or walnuts.
36985edc-55a7-414d-af72-e4a2ec5823d4 Spread the filling mixture over bottom crust in the baking pan, and then crumble the remaining oat mixture evenly over the top.
36985edc-55a7-414d-af72-e4a2ec5823d4 Bake the bars in the preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool before cutting into squares.
cb62c123-5dea-4493-b8a8-11eb66b3dfd3 Gather the ingredients.
cb62c123-5dea-4493-b8a8-11eb66b3dfd3 Heat a large deep pan on the stove. Add the oats, nuts, and seed combination (do not add any fruit) and cook for 5 minutes, constantly stirring to toast the ingredients. Take care not to burn. The mixture should just be golden brown.
cb62c123-5dea-4493-b8a8-11eb66b3dfd3 Remove from the heat and leave to cool.
cb62c123-5dea-4493-b8a8-11eb66b3dfd3 Place the honey, dark brown sugar, and butter into a saucepan. Melt, these together on medium heat, to completely dissolve the sugar.
cb62c123-5dea-4493-b8a8-11eb66b3dfd3 Cook for a further 5 minutes on a low heat, again, taking care not to burn. Turn off the heat and keep to one side.
cb62c123-5dea-4493-b8a8-11eb66b3dfd3 Mix the toasted ingredients with the melted butter mixture and the fruit to form a stiffish dough.
cb62c123-5dea-4493-b8a8-11eb66b3dfd3 Grease an 8- x 8-inch square cake tin and line the bottom with a sheet of baking paper. Press the flapjack mixture firmly and evenly into the tin making sure to get into the corners.
cb62c123-5dea-4493-b8a8-11eb66b3dfd3 Cut out squares and rectangles in the flapjack, then place the tin in the fridge and leave for a couple of hours to set.
cb62c123-5dea-4493-b8a8-11eb66b3dfd3 The flapjack keeps well in an airtight tin.
cb62c123-5dea-4493-b8a8-11eb66b3dfd3 Enjoy!
aba1b39a-4848-4793-945f-d9460a6f3099 Gather the ingredients. Line a 9 x 13 baking pan with non-stick foil and set aside. Pre-heat the oven to 350 degrees F.
aba1b39a-4848-4793-945f-d9460a6f3099 To begin, make the chocolate chip cookie layer. In a large bowl combine the package of chocolate chip cookie mix, 1/2 cup of softened unsalted butter, and one egg. Mix well until moistened and combined.
aba1b39a-4848-4793-945f-d9460a6f3099 Press the chocolate chip cookie dough evenly into the bottom of the prepared pan.
aba1b39a-4848-4793-945f-d9460a6f3099 For the Oreo cookie layer, place the Double Stuf Oreo Cookies on top of the chocolate chip cookie dough. In order to cover the entire surface, you might need to cut some of the Oreo cookies in half when your reach the end. Save any remaining cookies from the package for garnish when serving.
aba1b39a-4848-4793-945f-d9460a6f3099 Next, prepare the fudge brownie layer. In a large bowl combine with package of fudge brownie mix with the vegetable oil, water, and eggs. Mix well until moistened and combined.
aba1b39a-4848-4793-945f-d9460a6f3099 Pour the fudge brownie mixture evenly over the Oreo cookie layer. The brownie batter will also fall in-between the cracks down to the cookie layer to fill in all the gaps.
aba1b39a-4848-4793-945f-d9460a6f3099 Bake at 350 F for 45 minutes, or until the brownie layer is set. Cool completely before cutting.
aba1b39a-4848-4793-945f-d9460a6f3099 To cut, lift the foil out of the pan and slide the brownies out on to a cutting board. Cut into 30 brownies.
aba1b39a-4848-4793-945f-d9460a6f3099 The brownies can be served plain, or a la mode with a scoop of vanilla ice cream and a drizzle of hot fudge sauce. If there are any remaining Oreos from the package, they can be cut in half and served on top as well.
91ba8ee6-7868-40e8-bcfe-f557d1e3db23 Gather the ingredients.
91ba8ee6-7868-40e8-bcfe-f557d1e3db23 Preheat the oven to 350 Fand grease a 9 x 9-inch pan with cooking spray or softened butter. Line the bottom with a piece of parchment paper.
91ba8ee6-7868-40e8-bcfe-f557d1e3db23 Place the butter and sugars in a large mixing bowl and whisk until fully incorporated.
91ba8ee6-7868-40e8-bcfe-f557d1e3db23 Add the eggs and yolk one at a time, whisking gently after each addition. Add the vanilla and gently whisk again.
91ba8ee6-7868-40e8-bcfe-f557d1e3db23 Add the miso and whisk until smooth.
91ba8ee6-7868-40e8-bcfe-f557d1e3db23 Whisk the flour, baking powder and salt together in a medium sized bowl. Add the chunks to the bowl and whisk again.
91ba8ee6-7868-40e8-bcfe-f557d1e3db23 Add the dry ingredients to the wet and using a rubber spatula, very gently fold the two together. Do not over-mix.
91ba8ee6-7868-40e8-bcfe-f557d1e3db23 Transfer the batter to the prepared pan and use a flexible spatula to smooth the top.
91ba8ee6-7868-40e8-bcfe-f557d1e3db23 Sprinkle the Maldon sea salt (if using) over the top of the blondies.
91ba8ee6-7868-40e8-bcfe-f557d1e3db23 Bake for about 35 to 38 minutes, until the top is browned and a toothpick comes out with a moist crumb or two.
91ba8ee6-7868-40e8-bcfe-f557d1e3db23 Let the blondies cool on a rack until room temp and slice and serve.
6659c264-96cf-4bb6-9ab0-00ca61468eac Gather the ingredients.
6659c264-96cf-4bb6-9ab0-00ca61468eac Preheat the oven to 325 F. Grease a 9x13 pan with non-stick cooking spray or softened butter and line with parchment.
6659c264-96cf-4bb6-9ab0-00ca61468eac Place the oil and butter in a large microwave-safe bowl and microwave on high in 30-second bursts until the butter melts.
6659c264-96cf-4bb6-9ab0-00ca61468eac Add the cocoa and espresso powders and whisk to combine. Add the sugars and whisk to combine. Add the eggs and vanilla, all at once, and whisk very gently until combined.
6659c264-96cf-4bb6-9ab0-00ca61468eac Sprinkle the flour and the salt over the batter and, using a rubber spatula, gently fold the dry into the wet until no visible flour remains.
6659c264-96cf-4bb6-9ab0-00ca61468eac Transfer the batter to the prepared pan, spread with an offset spatula, and sprinkle with the flaky sea salt, if using.
6659c264-96cf-4bb6-9ab0-00ca61468eac Bake for about 20 to 22 minutes, rotating the pan at the halfway point. The brownies are ready when a cake tester comes out with a few moist crumbs. Don't overbake.
6659c264-96cf-4bb6-9ab0-00ca61468eac Let the brownies cool on a rack until room temperature. If desired, freeze them briefly before cutting, as this makes for cleaner squares.
6659c264-96cf-4bb6-9ab0-00ca61468eac Serve with glasses of cold whole milk.
14c2bc79-4fb6-4258-9cb5-941528a2bc64 Gather the ingredients.
14c2bc79-4fb6-4258-9cb5-941528a2bc64 Pre-heat the oven to 350 F.
14c2bc79-4fb6-4258-9cb5-941528a2bc64 Cream together the butter and granulated sugar using a stand or hand mixer.
14c2bc79-4fb6-4258-9cb5-941528a2bc64 Beat in the eggs and vanilla.
14c2bc79-4fb6-4258-9cb5-941528a2bc64 In a separate bowl, sift together the all-purpose flour, baking powder, and salt.
14c2bc79-4fb6-4258-9cb5-941528a2bc64 Stir the dry ingredients into the wet until fully incorporated.
14c2bc79-4fb6-4258-9cb5-941528a2bc64 Stir in 3/4 of the rainbow sprinkles.
14c2bc79-4fb6-4258-9cb5-941528a2bc64 Butter and flour an 8-inch square baking pan or line with parchment paper.
14c2bc79-4fb6-4258-9cb5-941528a2bc64 Pour the batter into the pan, sprinkle on the remaining sprinkles, and bake in the oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
14c2bc79-4fb6-4258-9cb5-941528a2bc64 Cool and cut into 9 or 12 slices.
14c2bc79-4fb6-4258-9cb5-941528a2bc64 While the bars are cooling, add the chocolate chips to a small, microwavable bowl and melt for 30 to 60 seconds.
14c2bc79-4fb6-4258-9cb5-941528a2bc64 Drizzle the melted chocolate over the baked bars.
04808864-879c-4c0c-9632-b5a88d3cd429 Gather the ingredients.
04808864-879c-4c0c-9632-b5a88d3cd429 Preheat oven to 350 F and lightly grease an 8 x 12-inch baking dish with butter or cooking spray.
04808864-879c-4c0c-9632-b5a88d3cd429 In a large bowl add melted butter, coconut oil, and sugars and whisk well to combine.
04808864-879c-4c0c-9632-b5a88d3cd429 Add eggs, vanilla, vinegar, and food coloring and whisk well another minute, until the color is red throughout and fully combined.
04808864-879c-4c0c-9632-b5a88d3cd429 Sift flour, cocoa powder, and salt into the butter mixture.
04808864-879c-4c0c-9632-b5a88d3cd429 Gently fold the dry ingredients into the wet until no flour bits remain, careful not to overmix.
04808864-879c-4c0c-9632-b5a88d3cd429 Pour the batter into prepared pan and smooth the top.
04808864-879c-4c0c-9632-b5a88d3cd429 Bake for 25 to 28 minutes, or until the center no longer jiggles. Remove from the oven and allow to cool for 15 to 20 minutes before slicing.
e9030680-6fb3-4d65-b6b0-b62d136649ee Gather the ingredients. Heat the oven to 350 F. Grease an 8-inch square baking pan and set aside.
e9030680-6fb3-4d65-b6b0-b62d136649ee In a large bowl, combine the melted butter, sugar and vanilla extract.
e9030680-6fb3-4d65-b6b0-b62d136649ee Add the eggs and beat well to combine.
e9030680-6fb3-4d65-b6b0-b62d136649ee In another large bowl combine the flour, unsweetened cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt.
e9030680-6fb3-4d65-b6b0-b62d136649ee Gradually add the flour mixture to the egg mixture, beating until well blended.
e9030680-6fb3-4d65-b6b0-b62d136649ee Spread the brownie batter evenly into the prepared baking pan.
e9030680-6fb3-4d65-b6b0-b62d136649ee Sprinkle the chopped fresh strawberries evenly on top of the batter. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
e9030680-6fb3-4d65-b6b0-b62d136649ee Cool completely in the pan on a wire rack.
e9030680-6fb3-4d65-b6b0-b62d136649ee Once cooled, melt the white chocolate and drizzle over the brownies.
ed5ad5d4-651c-46b5-9a72-e9c0a362ef72 Gather the ingredients.
ed5ad5d4-651c-46b5-9a72-e9c0a362ef72 In a mixing bowl with a spout, whisk the oil, coffee, and vanilla, until combined.
ed5ad5d4-651c-46b5-9a72-e9c0a362ef72 Do the same with the sugar, cocoa, and finally, the flour, one at a time, whisking until fully incorporated. Stir in the salt.
ed5ad5d4-651c-46b5-9a72-e9c0a362ef72 Finally, stir in the chocolate chips.
ed5ad5d4-651c-46b5-9a72-e9c0a362ef72 Pour the batter into a standard 12-ounce mug.
ed5ad5d4-651c-46b5-9a72-e9c0a362ef72 Microwave on high for 1 to 2 minutes, depending on the wattage of your microwave.
ed5ad5d4-651c-46b5-9a72-e9c0a362ef72 Let cool slightly before enjoying.
e043eb56-263a-4eb9-8a6d-ec49333596ac Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line a 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with parchment paper.
e043eb56-263a-4eb9-8a6d-ec49333596ac Melt the butter in a heavy bottomed saucepan over medium heat. Continue cooking until the butter solids begin to brown and become fragrant. Remove from heat.
e043eb56-263a-4eb9-8a6d-ec49333596ac Add the flour, oats, salt, and baking powder to a large bowl and mix well.
e043eb56-263a-4eb9-8a6d-ec49333596ac Split the vanilla bean in half lengthwise. Scrape out the pulp and add it to a large mixing bowl. Add the brown butter, sugar, molasses, and cardamom. Combine well, then add the eggs and whisk until incorporated.
e043eb56-263a-4eb9-8a6d-ec49333596ac Add the dry ingredients to the wet, add the walnuts, and mix to incorporate.
e043eb56-263a-4eb9-8a6d-ec49333596ac Pour the batter into the parchment-lined pan. Bake for between 30 and 40 minutes, or until set in the center.
e043eb56-263a-4eb9-8a6d-ec49333596ac De-pan and cool before cutting.
7676ae50-01cd-4366-abce-9e1097717d25 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 325 F.
7676ae50-01cd-4366-abce-9e1097717d25 Add the sugar and butter to a bowl and microwave for 2 minutes or until the butter is melted. Whisk the butter and sugar mixture together until they are incorporated.
7676ae50-01cd-4366-abce-9e1097717d25 Once the butter mixture has cooled slightly, beat in the eggs, vanilla extract, peppermint extract, and cocoa powder. Beat until the mixture is smooth and glossy. You can do this with a whisk, hand-mixer, or in a stand mixer.
7676ae50-01cd-4366-abce-9e1097717d25 Stir together the flour, baking soda, cornstarch, and salt in a separate bowl.
7676ae50-01cd-4366-abce-9e1097717d25 Fold the flour mixture into the wet mixture until there are no more pockets of flour. Be careful not to over mix. Fold the chocolate chips into the batter.
7676ae50-01cd-4366-abce-9e1097717d25 Pour the batter into a parchment-lined 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Make sure the parchment paper hangs over a few inches above the edges of the baking pan. The brownies are topped with frosting so they will still be thick. Smooth the top of the batter.
7676ae50-01cd-4366-abce-9e1097717d25 Bake for 45 minutes on the center rack in the oven. Test for doneness by inserting a toothpick into the center of the brownies. The toothpick should come out sticky, but not runny.
7676ae50-01cd-4366-abce-9e1097717d25 While the brownies are cooling, prepare the ganache. Place the chocolate chips and heavy cream in a bowl. Place the bowl in the microwave and heat for one-minute intervals until the chocolate is completely melted and smooth. Whisk in between each interval.
7676ae50-01cd-4366-abce-9e1097717d25 Pour the ganache over the cooled brownies. Smooth the ganache with a rubber spatula. Top the ganache with the crushed peppermint sticks. Allow them to cool slightly to room temperature. You can also place them in the refrigerator or freezer to get them to cool quicker.
7676ae50-01cd-4366-abce-9e1097717d25 Remove the brownies from the pan by grabbing the parchment paper. Cut them into squares with a long chef's knife or a pizza cutter.
f1c54f4f-4cd2-4452-a257-8ff07065b011 Pre-heat the oven to 325 degrees F and butter and flour an 8" square baking pan.
f1c54f4f-4cd2-4452-a257-8ff07065b011 Add the butter and chocolate to a heat-proof bowl and set it over a pot of simmering water. Stir until melted and allow to cool slightly.
f1c54f4f-4cd2-4452-a257-8ff07065b011 Whisk the granulated sugar into the butter and chocolate mixture, then whisk in the eggs and vanilla.
f1c54f4f-4cd2-4452-a257-8ff07065b011 Sift together the all-purpose flour, baking powder and salt and stir into the chocolate batter.
f1c54f4f-4cd2-4452-a257-8ff07065b011 Make the peanut butter swirl filling by stirring together the melted butter, confectioners sugar, peanut butter and salt until smooth.
f1c54f4f-4cd2-4452-a257-8ff07065b011 Pour the chocolate batter into the prepared pan and spread out evenly. Drop tablespoons of peanut butter filling on top of the batter and use a butter knife or a long skewer to gently swirl the peanut butter filling into the batter. Do not mix all the way so that the pretty swirl pattern remains on top.
f1c54f4f-4cd2-4452-a257-8ff07065b011 Bake for about 35 to 40 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean. Let cool and cut into 9 squares. Note that you can add a cup of chocolate chips or peanut butter chips to the batter before baking, if you like.
d130f2a9-68d1-41a2-a1c8-22d5f5ae65a1 Gather the ingredients.
d130f2a9-68d1-41a2-a1c8-22d5f5ae65a1 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Lightly grease an 8-inch baking pan.
d130f2a9-68d1-41a2-a1c8-22d5f5ae65a1 In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, and salt. Set aside.
d130f2a9-68d1-41a2-a1c8-22d5f5ae65a1 In a large bowl, whisk together the brown sugar and melted butter until well mixed.
d130f2a9-68d1-41a2-a1c8-22d5f5ae65a1 Whisk in the egg and vanilla extract.
d130f2a9-68d1-41a2-a1c8-22d5f5ae65a1 Add the flour mixture to the wet ingredients, mixing just until the batter is well combined, and no streaks of flour remain.
d130f2a9-68d1-41a2-a1c8-22d5f5ae65a1 Fold in the chopped strawberries and rhubarb.
d130f2a9-68d1-41a2-a1c8-22d5f5ae65a1 Transfer the batter to the prepared pan, and smooth the top with a spatula.
d130f2a9-68d1-41a2-a1c8-22d5f5ae65a1 Bake in the preheated oven for 35 to 45 minutes, or until the blondies are set, and a tester inserted in the center comes out clean, or nearly so (the blondies may be slightly gooey).
d130f2a9-68d1-41a2-a1c8-22d5f5ae65a1 Place on a wire rack to cool before cutting into squares.
d130f2a9-68d1-41a2-a1c8-22d5f5ae65a1 Serve and enjoy!
65e8d9c7-d840-4590-8d61-1176138ce260 Gather the ingredients.
65e8d9c7-d840-4590-8d61-1176138ce260 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line a 9-inch square baking pan with nonstick foil or parchment paper, leaving a 2-inch overhang on at least 2 sides. Grease the foil.
65e8d9c7-d840-4590-8d61-1176138ce260 To make the cake, combine the coconut flour, cocoa powder, and salt in a medium bowl.
65e8d9c7-d840-4590-8d61-1176138ce260 In a large saucepan, gently melt the butter or coconut oil and the chopped chocolate, stirring constantly. Allow to cool for 5 minutes.
65e8d9c7-d840-4590-8d61-1176138ce260 Add the sugar and eggs to the pan and stir to combine.
65e8d9c7-d840-4590-8d61-1176138ce260 Add the coconut flour mixture to the pan and stir to combine.
65e8d9c7-d840-4590-8d61-1176138ce260 Pour the batter in to the prepared baking pan and bake until set, 30 to 35 minutes.
65e8d9c7-d840-4590-8d61-1176138ce260 Cool completely in the pan on a wire rack.
65e8d9c7-d840-4590-8d61-1176138ce260 To prepare the frosting, combine 1/2 cup of the powdered sugar, solid coconut oil, cocoa powder, milk, and vanilla extract. Whisk to combine. Slowing add the remaining powdered sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, until desired spreading consistency is achieved.
65e8d9c7-d840-4590-8d61-1176138ce260 Spread the frosting on top of the cooled brownies.
65e8d9c7-d840-4590-8d61-1176138ce260 Sprinkle with the unsweetened shredded coconut.
65e8d9c7-d840-4590-8d61-1176138ce260 Use the foil overhang to help lift the brownies out of the pan. Cut into squares.
f9edaa5a-6057-42a3-967c-d903f4a81a23 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F.
f9edaa5a-6057-42a3-967c-d903f4a81a23 Butter and flour a 9 x 13 baking pan or line with parchment paper or aluminum foil and spray with non-stick cooking spray. Be sure to leave a 2-inch overhang on at least two sides to make the brownie easy to remove from the pan.
f9edaa5a-6057-42a3-967c-d903f4a81a23 Whisk together the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt in a bowl and set aside.
f9edaa5a-6057-42a3-967c-d903f4a81a23 Melt the butter and chocolate chips in a bowl set over a pot of simmering water, stirring frequently. Let cool slightly and stir in the sugar, eggs, and vanilla.
f9edaa5a-6057-42a3-967c-d903f4a81a23 Add the flour mixture and stir to combine. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out with just a few crumbs. Let the brownies cool completely before removing from the pan and use the foil or parchment overhang to help lift them out.
f9edaa5a-6057-42a3-967c-d903f4a81a23 Make two horizontal slices across the brownie, then make diagonal cuts to create the triangular tree shapes.
f9edaa5a-6057-42a3-967c-d903f4a81a23 In a small bowl, stir together the vanilla frosting and green food coloring. Start with about 5 drops of green food coloring, stir, and see if you like the shade or if you want to add a few more drops to get a deeper green color.
f9edaa5a-6057-42a3-967c-d903f4a81a23 Spoon the colored frosting into a disposable piping bag and slip off the tip. You can also use a regular kitchen zip-top plastic bag. Squeeze the frosting in a zig-zag pattern over each brownie tree.
f9edaa5a-6057-42a3-967c-d903f4a81a23 Insert a pretzel stick into the widest part of each tree to create the trunk and then top with your favorite holiday sprinkles.
67111520-b468-40c9-bafe-174f922d891e Gather your ingredients.
67111520-b468-40c9-bafe-174f922d891e Preheat the oven to 325 F. Line a 8x8 inch baking pan with parchment paper. Cut the paper in a square that will fit in the bottom of the pan with four flaps on each side that will line the sides. You can do this by making a 90 degree cut at the corners where each side meets.
67111520-b468-40c9-bafe-174f922d891e Place the butter and sugar in a large, microwave-safe bowl. You will do most of the stirring in this bowl, so make sure to pick one that will fit all of the batter. Heat it in the microwave for 1 to 2 minutes. Remove it from the microwave and stir. We used a whisk, but you can also use a hand-mixer.
67111520-b468-40c9-bafe-174f922d891e Allow it to cool on the counter for a few minutes, then stir in the vanilla extract, cayenne pepper, ground cinnamon, and cocoa powder.
67111520-b468-40c9-bafe-174f922d891e Add in one egg at a time to the butter and sugar mixture, mixing after each addition.
67111520-b468-40c9-bafe-174f922d891e In another bowl whisk together the flour, baking soda, cornstarch, and salt.
67111520-b468-40c9-bafe-174f922d891e Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients. Mix until the flour mixture has been completely incorporated, but do not over-mix!
67111520-b468-40c9-bafe-174f922d891e Gently stir in the chocolate chips and chocolate bar chunks. If you are adding nuts, add them now as well.
67111520-b468-40c9-bafe-174f922d891e Pour the brownie batter into the prepared pan and smooth the top so that it is even.
67111520-b468-40c9-bafe-174f922d891e Allow the brownies to cool slightly in the pan and then lift the sides of the parchment paper to lift the brownies out of the pan.
67111520-b468-40c9-bafe-174f922d891e Cut the brownies when they have mostly cooled to get the cleanest cuts.
67111520-b468-40c9-bafe-174f922d891e Enjoy them with a cold glass of milk or a cup of Mexican Hot Chocolate!
09035d5e-0dc3-4f60-9e07-9fb33616e5fd Gather the ingredients.
09035d5e-0dc3-4f60-9e07-9fb33616e5fd Preheat the oven to 350 F. Lightly oil a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and set aside.
09035d5e-0dc3-4f60-9e07-9fb33616e5fd In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt until well mixed.
09035d5e-0dc3-4f60-9e07-9fb33616e5fd In another small mixing bowl, combine the mashed bananas, soy milk, canola oil, and vanilla extract.
09035d5e-0dc3-4f60-9e07-9fb33616e5fd Add the wet ingredients to the dry, mixing until just combined.
09035d5e-0dc3-4f60-9e07-9fb33616e5fd Fold in the dairy-free chocolate chips.
09035d5e-0dc3-4f60-9e07-9fb33616e5fd Pour the batter into the prepared pan.
09035d5e-0dc3-4f60-9e07-9fb33616e5fd Bake for 25 to 35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center emerges clean.
09035d5e-0dc3-4f60-9e07-9fb33616e5fd Allow brownies to cool completely on a wire cooling rack before cutting into squares and serving.
09035d5e-0dc3-4f60-9e07-9fb33616e5fd Serve and enjoy!
bbbf5922-7d50-45be-8ca7-fd152cad1aab Heat the oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4).
bbbf5922-7d50-45be-8ca7-fd152cad1aab Grease and flour an 8- or 9- inch square baking pan.
bbbf5922-7d50-45be-8ca7-fd152cad1aab In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat melted butter, brown sugar, and peanut butter until smooth and creamy.
bbbf5922-7d50-45be-8ca7-fd152cad1aab Beat in the egg and vanilla.
bbbf5922-7d50-45be-8ca7-fd152cad1aab Slowly beat in flour, soda, and baking powder.
bbbf5922-7d50-45be-8ca7-fd152cad1aab Fold in chocolate chips or a mixture of chocolate and peanut butter chips.
bbbf5922-7d50-45be-8ca7-fd152cad1aab Spread or pat evenly (mixture will be thick) in the baking pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until set. Don't overbake.
bbbf5922-7d50-45be-8ca7-fd152cad1aab Cool on a rack and then cut into bars or squares.
ac154f4d-8814-4273-8ab4-274d55dbec51 Gather the ingredients.
ac154f4d-8814-4273-8ab4-274d55dbec51 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Spray a 13x9-pan with nonstick baking spray containing flour and set aside.
ac154f4d-8814-4273-8ab4-274d55dbec51 In a large bowl, combine both boxes of brownie mix, oil, water, and eggs. Mix with a wooden spoon until blended. Stir in 12-ounce batch of chopped candy bars.
ac154f4d-8814-4273-8ab4-274d55dbec51 Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until brownies are set and crust is shiny. Don't overbake the brownies.
ac154f4d-8814-4273-8ab4-274d55dbec51 Cool on a wire rack for 30 minutes.
ac154f4d-8814-4273-8ab4-274d55dbec51 In a medium microwave-safe bowl, combine the chocolate chips and peanut butter. Microwave on high for 1 minute, remove, and stir. Continue microwaving for 30 second intervals, stirring after each interval, until mixture is smooth.
ac154f4d-8814-4273-8ab4-274d55dbec51 Stir in the second batch of chopped candy bars and spoon and spread the frosting over the warm brownies.
ac154f4d-8814-4273-8ab4-274d55dbec51 Let the brownies stand on the wire rack until set.
ac154f4d-8814-4273-8ab4-274d55dbec51 Cut into bars and serve.
77ed5d52-c0fb-42cc-973e-090e0c6f70c7 Gather the ingredients.
77ed5d52-c0fb-42cc-973e-090e0c6f70c7 Heat the oven to 350 F.
77ed5d52-c0fb-42cc-973e-090e0c6f70c7 Grease and flour a 6 x 6-inch baking dish or pan (or a 4 x 8-inch loaf pan).
77ed5d52-c0fb-42cc-973e-090e0c6f70c7 In a medium mixing bowl, combine the sugar, cocoa powder, flour, salt, and baking powder.
77ed5d52-c0fb-42cc-973e-090e0c6f70c7 Melt the butter in a small saucepan over low heat, cool, then whisk in egg and vanilla.
77ed5d52-c0fb-42cc-973e-090e0c6f70c7 Stir the liquid mixture into the dry mixture.
77ed5d52-c0fb-42cc-973e-090e0c6f70c7 Scrape into your prepared baking dish.
77ed5d52-c0fb-42cc-973e-090e0c6f70c7 Bake for 25 minutes.
77ed5d52-c0fb-42cc-973e-090e0c6f70c7 Allow to cool on a baking rack.
77ed5d52-c0fb-42cc-973e-090e0c6f70c7 Serve and enjoy!
6ff8d5fa-7728-46df-9baa-b07a4a058a89 Gather the ingredients. Heat oven to 325 F; grease and flour an 8-inch square baking pan. Line the pan with parchment paper, if desired.
6ff8d5fa-7728-46df-9baa-b07a4a058a89 Put the butter and chocolate in a saucepan and place it over low heat. Cook, stirring constantly until the butter and chocolate are melted. Turn the heat off and let the mixture cool slightly. Whisk the sugar and vanilla into the chocolate mixture.
6ff8d5fa-7728-46df-9baa-b07a4a058a89 Add the eggs, one at a time, whisking after each addition. Combine the flour, baking powder, and salt in a small bowl; stir to blend.
6ff8d5fa-7728-46df-9baa-b07a4a058a89 Stir the flour mixture into the chocolate batter mixture. Stir in the chopped nuts, if using, blending well.
6ff8d5fa-7728-46df-9baa-b07a4a058a89 Spread the batter in the prepared pan.
6ff8d5fa-7728-46df-9baa-b07a4a058a89 Bake the brownies in the preheated oven for about 25 minutes.
e34fbd60-e1ae-4247-a413-e8b3de927e5d Gather the ingredients.
e34fbd60-e1ae-4247-a413-e8b3de927e5d Preheat oven to 350 F. Grease and flour an 8-inch square baking pan.
e34fbd60-e1ae-4247-a413-e8b3de927e5d In a medium bowl, combine the flour with salt, baking soda, and baking powder. Whisk or stir to blend thoroughly.
e34fbd60-e1ae-4247-a413-e8b3de927e5d In a mixing bowl with electric mixer, beat the egg for 2 to 3 minutes, or until foamy.
e34fbd60-e1ae-4247-a413-e8b3de927e5d Add the brown sugar, melted butter, and vanilla; beat well.
e34fbd60-e1ae-4247-a413-e8b3de927e5d Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
e34fbd60-e1ae-4247-a413-e8b3de927e5d Fold the walnuts into the batter.
e34fbd60-e1ae-4247-a413-e8b3de927e5d Spoon the thick batter into the prepared baking pan and spread it evenly with a spatula.
e34fbd60-e1ae-4247-a413-e8b3de927e5d Bake in the preheated oven for about 20 to 24 minutes, or until browned and the top has formed a crust.
e34fbd60-e1ae-4247-a413-e8b3de927e5d Cut into 2-inch bars; cool in pan. The recipe makes about 16 walnut bars.
5e207000-51e4-493a-b332-6c6e0fb73c36 Gather the ingredients.
5e207000-51e4-493a-b332-6c6e0fb73c36 Grease and flour an 8-inch square baking pan.
5e207000-51e4-493a-b332-6c6e0fb73c36 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
5e207000-51e4-493a-b332-6c6e0fb73c36 In a bowl or on a sheet of wax paper, combine the flour, baking powder, soda, and salt. Set aside.
5e207000-51e4-493a-b332-6c6e0fb73c36 In a mixing bowl beat the melted butter with brown sugar until smooth.
5e207000-51e4-493a-b332-6c6e0fb73c36 Add the egg and vanilla and beat until well blended.
5e207000-51e4-493a-b332-6c6e0fb73c36 Stir in the flour mixture until blended.
5e207000-51e4-493a-b332-6c6e0fb73c36 Fold in the chips and nuts, if using.
5e207000-51e4-493a-b332-6c6e0fb73c36 Spread in the prepared pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until set and lightly browned.
5e207000-51e4-493a-b332-6c6e0fb73c36 Serve and enjoy!
cb8503b8-c20e-49f7-9643-558a64530d48 Gather the ingredients.
cb8503b8-c20e-49f7-9643-558a64530d48 Preheat oven to 350 F. Spray an 8-inch by 8-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
cb8503b8-c20e-49f7-9643-558a64530d48 Whisk flour, cocoa, baking powder, sugar, and salt in a small bowl.
cb8503b8-c20e-49f7-9643-558a64530d48 In a medium bowl, combine oil, applesauce, vanilla, egg, and egg whites.
cb8503b8-c20e-49f7-9643-558a64530d48 Gradually stir in dry ingredients to wet ingredients until well combined.
cb8503b8-c20e-49f7-9643-558a64530d48 Pour into baking pan and bake for 20 minutes, until sides pull away from the edge of the pan.
cb8503b8-c20e-49f7-9643-558a64530d48 Cool in pan and cut into 16 squares.
cb8503b8-c20e-49f7-9643-558a64530d48 Enjoy!
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Gather the ingredients.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Preheat the oven to 400 F and lightly grease an 11 by 17-inch sheet pan.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour and sugar.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b In a heavy saucepan over medium heat, combine the butter, shortening, coffee, and cocoa.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Stir constantly until heated to a boil.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Pour boiling mixture over the flour and sugar.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Add the buttermilk, eggs, baking soda, and vanilla. Mix well, using a wooden spoon or high-speed mixer.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Bake for about 20 minutes, or until a cake tester comes out clean.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Meanwhile, prepare the frosting by combining the butter, cocoa, and milk in a saucepan over medium heat.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Stir frequently until heated to a boil.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Mix in the powdered sugar and vanilla and stir until smooth.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Pour the warm frosting over the brownies as soon as they come out of the oven.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Cool and cut into squares.
69393810-bdc9-424c-870a-a07301e5d13b Serve and enjoy.
975b66d6-41fa-40fd-96bd-557b602ed23d Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line an 8x8x2-inch baking dish with parchment paper or foil. Butter the paper or foil. Set aside.
975b66d6-41fa-40fd-96bd-557b602ed23d In the top of a double boiler, or in a heatproof bowl set over a saucepan of gently simmering water, place the butter and chocolate. Stir frequently until the chocolate and butter are completely melted and smooth. Remove from the heat.
975b66d6-41fa-40fd-96bd-557b602ed23d In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the almond flour, sugar, cocoa powder, and tapioca starch.
975b66d6-41fa-40fd-96bd-557b602ed23d Add the dry ingredients to the melted chocolate mixture, and mix well to form a lump-free batter.
975b66d6-41fa-40fd-96bd-557b602ed23d Add the eggs and vanilla, and beat into the brownie batter. Fold in the chocolate chips if using.
975b66d6-41fa-40fd-96bd-557b602ed23d Pour the brownie batter into the prepared pan, using a spatula to smooth the top.
975b66d6-41fa-40fd-96bd-557b602ed23d Bake in the preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until the brownies are firm to the touch, and a tester inserted in the center of the pan comes out clean.
975b66d6-41fa-40fd-96bd-557b602ed23d Cool the brownies in their pan on a wire rack.
975b66d6-41fa-40fd-96bd-557b602ed23d When you are ready to serve them, invert the pan over a serving plate, remove the paper or foil, and turn right side up. Cut into squares and serve.
00c8274e-1bd0-4354-8ff8-89475f2966f6 In a 1-quart canning jar, layer the flour, baking powder, soda, and salt (a wide-mouth canning funnel makes this a little easier).
00c8274e-1bd0-4354-8ff8-89475f2966f6 Shake jar just slightly to level layer.
00c8274e-1bd0-4354-8ff8-89475f2966f6 Add half of the brown sugar, then half of the nuts and half of the chocolate chips.
00c8274e-1bd0-4354-8ff8-89475f2966f6 Repeat layers with remaining brown sugar, chocolate chips, and nuts.
14fe55d3-142d-4f3b-b4d4-2326404dd908 Heat the oven to 350 F.
14fe55d3-142d-4f3b-b4d4-2326404dd908 Coat a 13" x 9" pan with cooking spray. Then, line the pan with parchment paper leaving a 2-inch overhang on both sides of the pan. Press down the parchment paper so that it sticks to the pan. Coat again with cooking spray and add a second strip of parchment paper laying it in the opposite direction also with a 2-inch overhang. Press it down and coat it with cooking spray. Set aside.
14fe55d3-142d-4f3b-b4d4-2326404dd908 In a medium mixing bowl, sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt until well combined. Set aside.
14fe55d3-142d-4f3b-b4d4-2326404dd908 In a large mixing bowl, beat together the mashed avocado, soy milk, water, and vanilla extract. Add the dry ingredients, mixing until well combined.
14fe55d3-142d-4f3b-b4d4-2326404dd908 Pour into the prepared baking pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until the top is set and a toothpick inserted into the center emerges with only a few crumbs. Allow brownies to cool completely in the pan before cutting into squares and serving.
14fe55d3-142d-4f3b-b4d4-2326404dd908 After brownies have cooled, grip the paper overhangs and lift the brownies out of the pan and transfer to a cutting board. Use a serrated knife to cut the brownies into 12 to 16 pieces, then lift off the parchment and transfer to a serving dish.
93b97f7a-f7da-4219-992f-3d3cbb1dbb1c Preheat the oven to 350 F.
93b97f7a-f7da-4219-992f-3d3cbb1dbb1c Grease and flour an 8-by-8-inch baking pan.
93b97f7a-f7da-4219-992f-3d3cbb1dbb1c Peel and core the apples. Chop the apples finely.
93b97f7a-f7da-4219-992f-3d3cbb1dbb1c In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
93b97f7a-f7da-4219-992f-3d3cbb1dbb1c Add the egg and blend well. Add the vanilla and mix thoroughly.
93b97f7a-f7da-4219-992f-3d3cbb1dbb1c Add apples and pecans; stir until blended.
93b97f7a-f7da-4219-992f-3d3cbb1dbb1c In a bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt. Stir the dry ingredients into the first mixture.
93b97f7a-f7da-4219-992f-3d3cbb1dbb1c Spread the batter in the prepared baking pan.
93b97f7a-f7da-4219-992f-3d3cbb1dbb1c Bake in the preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until firm.
93b97f7a-f7da-4219-992f-3d3cbb1dbb1c Cool completely and sift confectioners' sugar over the brownies, if desired. Cut into squares for serving.
55b6d907-66e1-4dc3-8de0-b206eed5514c Gather the ingredients. Heat oven to 350 F and grease and flour a 9-inch square baking pan. Line the pan with greased parchment paper, if desired.
55b6d907-66e1-4dc3-8de0-b206eed5514c Melt chocolate and butter in a bowl or pan over simmering water, stirring until smooth and warm. Set aside to cool.
55b6d907-66e1-4dc3-8de0-b206eed5514c In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the eggs with the salt, sugar, and vanilla until the mixture is light in color and thickened.
55b6d907-66e1-4dc3-8de0-b206eed5514c Stir in the cooled, melted chocolate and butter mixture. Fold in the flour and walnuts.
