55b6d907-66e1-4dc3-8de0-b206eed5514c Spread the brownie batter in the prepared pan and bake for about 25 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out with a few moist crumbs when inserted in the center.
55b6d907-66e1-4dc3-8de0-b206eed5514c Remove the brownies to a rack and let them cool completely before cutting into squares.
2c02f824-1674-4658-85e3-8437f0184303 Gather the ingredients.
2c02f824-1674-4658-85e3-8437f0184303 Prepare and bake the brownies in a 9 x 9-inch pan according to the package directions. Use a 9 x 13 pan if you prefer thinner brownies.
2c02f824-1674-4658-85e3-8437f0184303 As soon as the baked brownies are removed from the oven, cool them off for 10 minutes before brushing them evenly with 1/4 cup of bourbon. Place the pan of brownies on a cooling rack and place both of them in the refrigerator.
2c02f824-1674-4658-85e3-8437f0184303 While the brownies are cooling off, make the buttercream icing by creaming the butter with the rum and powdered sugar. Mix until the sugar is fully incorporated into the butter mixture.
2c02f824-1674-4658-85e3-8437f0184303 Remove the brownies from the refrigerator and spread the rum icing evenly on the cooled brownies. Place the brownie pan back in the refrigerator.
2c02f824-1674-4658-85e3-8437f0184303 When the pan of brownies is cold, melt the chocolate chips with the shortening in a double bath. Drizzle all the chocolate on top of the brownies.
2c02f824-1674-4658-85e3-8437f0184303 Keep the brownies in the refrigerator until it's time to serve.
2c02f824-1674-4658-85e3-8437f0184303 Cut in squares and enjoy!
b001fab5-33c0-43fe-92e8-68b4b1653cb0 Heat the oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4). Grease and flour a 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
b001fab5-33c0-43fe-92e8-68b4b1653cb0 In a large bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda; blend in 1/3 cup melted butter. Add boiling water; stir until well blended. Stir in sugar, beaten eggs and remaining 1/3 cup butter. Stir in flour and salt.
b001fab5-33c0-43fe-92e8-68b4b1653cb0 Stir nuts and the chocolate chips into batter. Spread batter in the prepared baking pan. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until the brownies are firm and begin to pull away from sides of pan.
b001fab5-33c0-43fe-92e8-68b4b1653cb0 Cool before cutting into squares.
c5e9a4b9-aa55-46cc-a9b1-8d2ce95224d8 Gather the ingredients.
c5e9a4b9-aa55-46cc-a9b1-8d2ce95224d8 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Grease and flour a 7x11-inch baking pan.
c5e9a4b9-aa55-46cc-a9b1-8d2ce95224d8 In a large bowl, cream together the butter and brown sugar.
c5e9a4b9-aa55-46cc-a9b1-8d2ce95224d8 Add the egg and beat in until well combined.
c5e9a4b9-aa55-46cc-a9b1-8d2ce95224d8 In a separate medium bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
c5e9a4b9-aa55-46cc-a9b1-8d2ce95224d8 Add to creamed mixture incorporating until well combined.
c5e9a4b9-aa55-46cc-a9b1-8d2ce95224d8 Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
c5e9a4b9-aa55-46cc-a9b1-8d2ce95224d8 Spread the batter in the prepared pan.
c5e9a4b9-aa55-46cc-a9b1-8d2ce95224d8 Bake 20 to 25 minutes. These brown very quickly, so be sure to start checking at the 20-minute mark.
c5e9a4b9-aa55-46cc-a9b1-8d2ce95224d8 Serve and enjoy!
08e7d4c4-d670-48c5-b563-1b013b7be065 Gather the ingredients.
08e7d4c4-d670-48c5-b563-1b013b7be065 Preheat oven to 350 F.
08e7d4c4-d670-48c5-b563-1b013b7be065 Line mini-muffin pan or 9x13 pan with 48 miniature muffin cup liners. Lightly spray with cooking spray.
08e7d4c4-d670-48c5-b563-1b013b7be065 Fill cups 2/3 full with batter.
08e7d4c4-d670-48c5-b563-1b013b7be065 Bake half the time of regular brownie recipe or approximately from 12 to 20 minutes. Test with toothpick. Do not overcook brownies.
08e7d4c4-d670-48c5-b563-1b013b7be065 Allow to cool in the pan for 10 minutes. Remove for complete cooling on wire rack.
08e7d4c4-d670-48c5-b563-1b013b7be065 Serve and enjoy!
63ebfd2e-ddeb-4de8-8b8a-a2412362c911 Gather the ingredients.
63ebfd2e-ddeb-4de8-8b8a-a2412362c911 In a large bowl, beat the butter with the brown sugar and granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
63ebfd2e-ddeb-4de8-8b8a-a2412362c911 Stir in the melted chocolate and beat in the cocoa.
63ebfd2e-ddeb-4de8-8b8a-a2412362c911 Then beat in the eggs and vanilla until the mixture is fluffy. You can do this by hand or with a hand or stand mixer.
63ebfd2e-ddeb-4de8-8b8a-a2412362c911 Add the flour, baking soda, and salt to the bowl and mix just until a dough forms. Don't over beat this mixture or the cookies will be tough.
63ebfd2e-ddeb-4de8-8b8a-a2412362c911 Stir in the candies.
63ebfd2e-ddeb-4de8-8b8a-a2412362c911 Cover and chill the dough for 4 to 6 hours in the fridge.
63ebfd2e-ddeb-4de8-8b8a-a2412362c911 When you are ready to bake the cookies, preheat the oven to 350 F.
63ebfd2e-ddeb-4de8-8b8a-a2412362c911 Form the dough into round balls by tablespoons, about 1-inch in diameter, and place them onto ungreased cookie sheets. You can press more candies into the tops of the dough balls if you'd like.
63ebfd2e-ddeb-4de8-8b8a-a2412362c911 Bake the cookies for 8 to 11 minutes or until the cookies are set but still slightly soft.
63ebfd2e-ddeb-4de8-8b8a-a2412362c911 Let them cool on the cookie sheet for 2 minutes, then remove the cookies carefully, using a spatula, to a wire rack to cool completely.
63ebfd2e-ddeb-4de8-8b8a-a2412362c911 Serve and enjoy!
aacb70d7-d85b-4c5f-b0f8-1f574549bdf7 Gather the ingredients.
aacb70d7-d85b-4c5f-b0f8-1f574549bdf7 In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt until they are evenly mixed. Set this dry mixture aside.
aacb70d7-d85b-4c5f-b0f8-1f574549bdf7 Transfer the melted butter into a smaller bowl and add the cocoa powder. Stir together until they are combined and no lumps remain. In a measuring cup or bowl, mix the vanilla extract with the eggs, then whisk them into the cocoa-butter mixture.
aacb70d7-d85b-4c5f-b0f8-1f574549bdf7 Add this wet mixture to the dry flour mixture and mix thoroughly by hand with a rubber spatula. It might seem as if you need more liquid, but do not add any. Just keep folding and pressing until the mixture comes together. It will eventually reach the consistency of stiff brownie batter.
aacb70d7-d85b-4c5f-b0f8-1f574549bdf7 Fold in the chocolate chips. Refrigerate the dough for 30 minutes to firm it up.
aacb70d7-d85b-4c5f-b0f8-1f574549bdf7 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line two baking sheets with Silpat baking liners or parchment paper. (Alternatively, you can lightly grease them.)
aacb70d7-d85b-4c5f-b0f8-1f574549bdf7 Pour confectioners' sugar into a small bowl. Scoop the dough by teaspoons, roll into balls, and drop the balls into the powdered sugar, rolling them around to cover them completely. Place the sugared dough balls on prepared baking sheets 1 1/2 inches apart.
aacb70d7-d85b-4c5f-b0f8-1f574549bdf7 Bake the cookies for 12 to 15 minutes. The cookies will spread, puff up a bit, and form cracks. The longer you cook them, the more crispy they will become.
aacb70d7-d85b-4c5f-b0f8-1f574549bdf7 Let the cookies cool for 10 minutes on the cookie sheets before using a spatula to remove to racks and cool completely. Store in a covered container.
aacb70d7-d85b-4c5f-b0f8-1f574549bdf7 Enjoy!
2de45181-f3bd-4037-9a2c-326b8ed18565 Pre-heat oven to 350 F and lightly grease a baking pan.
2de45181-f3bd-4037-9a2c-326b8ed18565 Whisk together the oil, maple syrup, soy milk, and vanilla.
2de45181-f3bd-4037-9a2c-326b8ed18565 In a separate bowl, combine the flour, cocoa, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
2de45181-f3bd-4037-9a2c-326b8ed18565 Combine the dry ingredients with the wet ingredients and mix just to combine. Gently fold in the nuts and chocolate chips.
2de45181-f3bd-4037-9a2c-326b8ed18565 Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Cut into squares and enjoy your vegan chocolate chip brownies.
c4892c8b-6c12-4e69-a789-5d4d221bd215 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F.
c4892c8b-6c12-4e69-a789-5d4d221bd215 Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with a nonstick baking spray containing flour and set aside.
c4892c8b-6c12-4e69-a789-5d4d221bd215 In a large saucepan, combine the butter, oil, chocolate chips, and cocoa powder. Melt this mixture over low heat until smooth, stirring occasionally.
c4892c8b-6c12-4e69-a789-5d4d221bd215 Add the brown sugar and granulated sugar and beat well. Beat in the eggs until smooth, then stir in the vanilla.
c4892c8b-6c12-4e69-a789-5d4d221bd215 Add the flour, baking powder, and salt to the chocolate mixture and mix well.
c4892c8b-6c12-4e69-a789-5d4d221bd215 Spoon and spread the batter into the prepared pan. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until the brownies are just set and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs. Cool the brownies completely on a wire rack.
c4892c8b-6c12-4e69-a789-5d4d221bd215 When the brownies are cool, make the icing. Combine the cream cheese and butter in a medium bowl and beat well.
c4892c8b-6c12-4e69-a789-5d4d221bd215 Add the powdered sugar, 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
c4892c8b-6c12-4e69-a789-5d4d221bd215 Add the vanilla.
c4892c8b-6c12-4e69-a789-5d4d221bd215 Spread the frosting over the cooled brownies.
eebe53bf-beb1-49b3-b4b8-fbd4b5201be9 Melt the butter over a low heat.
eebe53bf-beb1-49b3-b4b8-fbd4b5201be9 Set the butter aside to cool.
eebe53bf-beb1-49b3-b4b8-fbd4b5201be9 Combine the cocoa powder, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a medium bowl.
eebe53bf-beb1-49b3-b4b8-fbd4b5201be9 Heat the oven to 350 F. Grease a 13x9 inch pan.
eebe53bf-beb1-49b3-b4b8-fbd4b5201be9 Beat the melted butter, sugar, vanilla eggs, sugar, and vanilla in a large bowl.
eebe53bf-beb1-49b3-b4b8-fbd4b5201be9 Slowly blend in the dry ingredients.
eebe53bf-beb1-49b3-b4b8-fbd4b5201be9 Beat until it is well combined.
eebe53bf-beb1-49b3-b4b8-fbd4b5201be9 Stir in the nuts and the chips.
eebe53bf-beb1-49b3-b4b8-fbd4b5201be9 Pour into the prepared pan.
eebe53bf-beb1-49b3-b4b8-fbd4b5201be9 Bake Mrs. Quinn's Easy Brownies for 20 to 22 minutes.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Gather the ingredients.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Spray a 13" x 9" pan with a nonstick baking spray containing flour and set aside.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 In a large saucepan, combine the sugar, brown sugar, 2/3 cup butter, and water.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Bring to a boil, stirring frequently; boil for 1 to 2 minutes or until the sugar is completely dissolved.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Remove the saucepan from the heat and add the chocolate chips; stir until melted.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Add the cocoa powder and vanilla.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Then beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Stir in the flour, baking powder, and salt.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Spoon the batter into the prepared pan.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until the brownies are just set. Do not over bake. Check for doneness by observing a dry and shiny crust. You can't use the toothpick test on these brownies because they are too creamy.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Cool the brownies completely on a wire rack.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Then make the frosting: In a medium microwave-safe bowl, combine 2 cups chocolate chips and peanut butter.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Microwave this mixture on medium power for 2 minutes or until the chips melted; stir well.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 If necessary, continue microwaving for 30-second intervals until the chocolate chips have melted.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Pour this mixture over the brownies and spread. Let stand until set.
4bf95ada-37ca-43f3-af2f-770f42301fe6 Serve and enjoy!
319f5537-f262-496f-b40a-9a081755fc09 Preheat oven to 350 F (or 325 F. for glass or dark metal pan). Grease a 9 x 13 pan.
319f5537-f262-496f-b40a-9a081755fc09 Melt chocolate and butter in a saucepan over low heat; set aside. In a mixer, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla at high speed for 10 minutes**. Blend in chocolate mixture, flour and salt until just mixed. Stir in the nuts. Pour into prepared pan.
319f5537-f262-496f-b40a-9a081755fc09 Bake Ultimate Brownies for 35 to 40 minutes. (Don't over bake.) Cool and frost if desired, but that is not necessary.
ed549ee8-fc9a-499e-a8c1-422c895f021b Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C.
ed549ee8-fc9a-499e-a8c1-422c895f021b Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Melt the dark or bittersweet chocolate in the microwave or the top of a double boiler. Set aside to cool.
ed549ee8-fc9a-499e-a8c1-422c895f021b In a large bowl, whisk together the sugar, olive oil, eggs, vanilla, and peppermint extract.
ed549ee8-fc9a-499e-a8c1-422c895f021b In another bowl, whisk together the flour, cocoa powder, and salt. Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients and stir until well combined.
ed549ee8-fc9a-499e-a8c1-422c895f021b Slowly add the melted chocolate, stirring constantly, until it is totally incorporated. Fold in the chocolate chips.
ed549ee8-fc9a-499e-a8c1-422c895f021b Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and smooth the top with a spatula. Bake in the preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes or the top is glossy and a tester inserted into the center of the brownies comes out clean.
ed549ee8-fc9a-499e-a8c1-422c895f021b Cool the brownies in their pan on a wire rack.
ed549ee8-fc9a-499e-a8c1-422c895f021b Dust with confectioners' sugar if desired. Cut into squares to serve.
ed549ee8-fc9a-499e-a8c1-422c895f021b Enjoy!
37d63116-6f4d-4ac3-8a49-9d7d94a6a4db Gather the ingredients.
37d63116-6f4d-4ac3-8a49-9d7d94a6a4db Pre-heat oven to 350 F.
37d63116-6f4d-4ac3-8a49-9d7d94a6a4db Melt together the 1 1/4 cups butter or margarine and add in the 3/4 cup of cocoa; mixing well to combine.
37d63116-6f4d-4ac3-8a49-9d7d94a6a4db Once the butter or margarine is melted, transfer to a mixing bowl if needed, then stir in the 2 cups sugar and blend in the 4 eggs, one at a time. Between each egg, beat well to fully incorporate.
37d63116-6f4d-4ac3-8a49-9d7d94a6a4db Once the eggs are all mixed in, add in the 2 teaspoons of vanilla extract and stir to combine well.
37d63116-6f4d-4ac3-8a49-9d7d94a6a4db Stir in the 1 1/2 cups of flour and the optional chopped nuts; mixing to fully combine well.
37d63116-6f4d-4ac3-8a49-9d7d94a6a4db Bake in a lightly greased 9x13 inch baking pan for 30 minutes in the preheated oven.
37d63116-6f4d-4ac3-8a49-9d7d94a6a4db Let your homemade brownies cool on a rack for about 20 to 30 minutes.
37d63116-6f4d-4ac3-8a49-9d7d94a6a4db Once your brownies are fully cooled, you can cut into 20 square pieces.
e2fac8c0-9ffe-410c-afe0-70a8b254eb1d Gather the ingredients.
e2fac8c0-9ffe-410c-afe0-70a8b254eb1d Preheat the oven to 350 F. Lightly coat an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with cooking spray and then set it aside.
e2fac8c0-9ffe-410c-afe0-70a8b254eb1d In a large bowl, sift together the flour, unsweetened cocoa, salt, baking powder, baking soda, and cinnamon until well mixed, then set the bowl aside.
e2fac8c0-9ffe-410c-afe0-70a8b254eb1d In a medium bowl, beat together the sugar, brown sugar, non-fat dry milk powder, egg white, applesauce, and vanilla with a spoon until well combined.​
e2fac8c0-9ffe-410c-afe0-70a8b254eb1d Stir the wet mixture into the dry mixture, mixing just until the ingredients are well moistened. Do not overmix.
e2fac8c0-9ffe-410c-afe0-70a8b254eb1d Spread the brownie batter evenly in the prepared baking pan and bake in the oven for 22 to 23 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center of your brownies comes out clean.
e2fac8c0-9ffe-410c-afe0-70a8b254eb1d Cool on a wire rack.
e2fac8c0-9ffe-410c-afe0-70a8b254eb1d If you're not planning on frosting your brownies, you can give them a light dusting with powdered sugar, if you'd like. Enjoy!
4d3fc08b-76ff-4a86-9d9d-7d114395db96 Gather the ingredients.
4d3fc08b-76ff-4a86-9d9d-7d114395db96 Spray a 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
4d3fc08b-76ff-4a86-9d9d-7d114395db96 Heat the sweetened condensed milk and unsweetened chocolate in a medium saucepan over medium-low heat until chocolate is melted and mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
4d3fc08b-76ff-4a86-9d9d-7d114395db96 Remove the pan from the heat, and stir in the graham cracker crumbs and half of the chopped walnuts.
4d3fc08b-76ff-4a86-9d9d-7d114395db96 Spread in the prepared pan. Top with the remaining walnuts.
4d3fc08b-76ff-4a86-9d9d-7d114395db96 Chill until firm, 3 to 4 hours.
4d3fc08b-76ff-4a86-9d9d-7d114395db96 Serve and enjoy.
855030cb-30f4-4bc3-825f-4df54181b1ec Preheat the oven to 350 F. Grease a 9 x13 baking dish and set aside.
855030cb-30f4-4bc3-825f-4df54181b1ec In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, and salt, mixing until well-combined. Set aside.
855030cb-30f4-4bc3-825f-4df54181b1ec In a large mixing bowl, use an electric hand mixer set to medium speed and beat the soy margarine with the brown sugar for about 3 to 4 minutes or until creamy and fluffy.
855030cb-30f4-4bc3-825f-4df54181b1ec Add the eggs, one at a time, while beating the mixture.
855030cb-30f4-4bc3-825f-4df54181b1ec Add the vanilla extract and beat until the mixture is smooth and creamy.
855030cb-30f4-4bc3-825f-4df54181b1ec Gradually beat in the flour mixture until well combined.
855030cb-30f4-4bc3-825f-4df54181b1ec Fold in the dairy-free chocolate chips.
855030cb-30f4-4bc3-825f-4df54181b1ec Spread the mixture into the prepared pan and bake for 20 to 30 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and a toothpick inserted into the center emerges clean. Allow blondies to cool completely in the pan on a wire cooling rack before cutting into squares and serving.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 Gather the ingredients.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 Preheat oven to 350 F.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick baking spray containing flour, or grease it using solid shortening and dust with flour.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 In a heavy saucepan, melt the butter over low heat.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 Remove from heat and stir in the brown sugar until blended.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 Add eggs and vanilla and beat until combined.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 Add the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt, and mix.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 Stir in nuts, if using, until blended.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 Spread the batter and spread it into the prepared pan.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until the brownies are just set when lightly touched with your finger.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 Cool on wire rack.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 Frost as desired and cut the brownies into squares to serve.
63bb4bc8-004b-4ed4-866d-028e6f725209 Enjoy!
045e70a7-0ae9-45a8-90ed-20ad6b4fb8c9 Gather the ingredients.
045e70a7-0ae9-45a8-90ed-20ad6b4fb8c9 Preheat your oven to 375 F.
045e70a7-0ae9-45a8-90ed-20ad6b4fb8c9 In a small bowl, mix together the flaxseed meal with the water and allow to rest until gelled, about 5 minutes.
045e70a7-0ae9-45a8-90ed-20ad6b4fb8c9 In a large bowl, cream together the margarine and sugar until the mixture is very smooth.
045e70a7-0ae9-45a8-90ed-20ad6b4fb8c9 Add in the prepared flax seed meal, vanilla extract, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
045e70a7-0ae9-45a8-90ed-20ad6b4fb8c9 Slowly blend in the cocoa powder, and then mix in the non-dairy milk.
045e70a7-0ae9-45a8-90ed-20ad6b4fb8c9 Next, incorporate the millet flour, buckwheat flour, and 1/3 cup almond flour until well blended.
045e70a7-0ae9-45a8-90ed-20ad6b4fb8c9 If you have been using an electric mixer, do the next step with your hands: Add in chocolate chips and about 1/4 cup more almond flour and mix until well incorporated. The dough will be stiff, and slightly crumbly, but you will be able to grab little sections and roll them into balls.
045e70a7-0ae9-45a8-90ed-20ad6b4fb8c9 Roll the dough into large walnut-sized balls (about 1 1/2 inches in diameter) and place onto an ungreased cookie sheet about two inches apart.
045e70a7-0ae9-45a8-90ed-20ad6b4fb8c9 Bake at 375 F on the middle rack of your oven for about 10 minutes, or until fragrant and crispy on the edges.
045e70a7-0ae9-45a8-90ed-20ad6b4fb8c9 Let cookies cool; be sure not to move the cookies from the cookie sheet until they are completely cool or they will fall apart.
045e70a7-0ae9-45a8-90ed-20ad6b4fb8c9 Melt additional chocolate chips and drizzle a little onto the top of each cookie. Dust lightly with cinnamon.
6eba53ae-636c-43dd-89e0-690143dae14b Preheat the oven to 375 F. Line a 9-inch by 13-inch baking pan with nonstick foil.
6eba53ae-636c-43dd-89e0-690143dae14b Dry Ingredient Mixture: In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, cocoa powder, and salt until evenly combined. Set aside.
6eba53ae-636c-43dd-89e0-690143dae14b Chocolate Mixture: Melt butter, bittersweet chocolate, and white chocolate chips in a double-boiler over very low heat, stirring constantly until melted. Remove from heat.
6eba53ae-636c-43dd-89e0-690143dae14b Mix the Eggs and Sugar: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar on high speed until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
6eba53ae-636c-43dd-89e0-690143dae14b Add melted chocolate mixture to the eggs and sugar mixture, beating until combined.
6eba53ae-636c-43dd-89e0-690143dae14b Beat the reserved dry ingredient mixture into the melted chocolate mixture. Whisk in the Guinness Stout beer by hand. The batter may seem a bit thin.
6eba53ae-636c-43dd-89e0-690143dae14b Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan. Drop semisweet chocolate chips evenly on top of batter (some will sink in).
6eba53ae-636c-43dd-89e0-690143dae14b Bake 25 to 30 minutes (oven temperatures vary) on center rack in the oven, until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
6eba53ae-636c-43dd-89e0-690143dae14b Let the brownies cool, uncovered, to room temperature.
c99be56b-f3a2-4fb5-834f-31ef884ba39e Pre-heat oven to 350 F and lightly grease a baking pan.
c99be56b-f3a2-4fb5-834f-31ef884ba39e In a blender or food processor, process the silken tofu, water, maple syrup, cocoa, oil, and vanilla until smooth.
c99be56b-f3a2-4fb5-834f-31ef884ba39e In a large bowl, mix together the remaining ingredients, except the nuts.
c99be56b-f3a2-4fb5-834f-31ef884ba39e Combine the dry ingredients with the wet ingredients, stirring well to combine. Gently fold in the walnuts.
c99be56b-f3a2-4fb5-834f-31ef884ba39e Pour the batter into the baking pan and bake for about 40 minutes.
54cdc13b-2aca-4571-9379-9772ce3ac3e5 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray a 9x13-inch pan with cooking spray.
54cdc13b-2aca-4571-9379-9772ce3ac3e5 Mix the brownie mix, oil, water, and eggs with a spatula or wooden spoon, about 50 strokes, until well-combined.
54cdc13b-2aca-4571-9379-9772ce3ac3e5 Spread brownie batter in prepared pan. Bake 23 minutes.
54cdc13b-2aca-4571-9379-9772ce3ac3e5 Remove brownies from oven. Sprinkle mini marshmallows, candy corn, and chocolate chips over brownies. Return to oven and bake another 5 to 8 minutes.
54cdc13b-2aca-4571-9379-9772ce3ac3e5 Let brownies cool completely before cutting into squares.
54cdc13b-2aca-4571-9379-9772ce3ac3e5 Serve and enjoy!
d48d6326-7de4-4bb5-b031-824ee574a9c1 Heat the oven to 350 F.
d48d6326-7de4-4bb5-b031-824ee574a9c1 Grease and flour two 8-inch square pans.
d48d6326-7de4-4bb5-b031-824ee574a9c1 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream the butter and sugar until fluffy. Stir in molasses and vanilla. Beat in eggs.
d48d6326-7de4-4bb5-b031-824ee574a9c1 In another bowl, combine the flour and baking soda; blend thoroughly.
d48d6326-7de4-4bb5-b031-824ee574a9c1 Add the flour mixture to the first mixture, blending well.
d48d6326-7de4-4bb5-b031-824ee574a9c1 Fold in chopped nuts.
d48d6326-7de4-4bb5-b031-824ee574a9c1 Spread batter in the prepared pans.
d48d6326-7de4-4bb5-b031-824ee574a9c1 Bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes.
d841f928-6777-4561-94f1-c971aac9eb8c Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 375 F. Prepare baking sheets by lining with parchment paper.
d841f928-6777-4561-94f1-c971aac9eb8c In a large bowl, combine the flour and baking soda. Set aside.
d841f928-6777-4561-94f1-c971aac9eb8c In a large mixer bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar, instant vanilla pudding mix, and vanilla. Beat until smooth and creamy.
d841f928-6777-4561-94f1-c971aac9eb8c Beat in the eggs until well combined.
d841f928-6777-4561-94f1-c971aac9eb8c Gradually add the flour mixture to the butter mixture.
d841f928-6777-4561-94f1-c971aac9eb8c Stir in the chocolate chips.
d841f928-6777-4561-94f1-c971aac9eb8c Drop by heaping spoonfuls about 2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheets. Bake in the preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
d841f928-6777-4561-94f1-c971aac9eb8c Cool on a wire rack. Store in an airtight container if not eating right away.
29f8f267-6ed8-44c9-a1aa-7b11c19e8c69 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 325 F. Line two rimmed baking sheets with parchment paper.
29f8f267-6ed8-44c9-a1aa-7b11c19e8c69 In a small bowl, whisk together the almond flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt.
29f8f267-6ed8-44c9-a1aa-7b11c19e8c69 Add the butter to a deep bowl and beat, using an electric mixer, until creamy, 30 to 60 seconds.
29f8f267-6ed8-44c9-a1aa-7b11c19e8c69 Add the sugar, and beat on medium speed until the mixture becomes creamy, 3 to 5 minutes.
29f8f267-6ed8-44c9-a1aa-7b11c19e8c69 Add the egg and vanilla. Beat until thickened and fluffy, about 2 minutes.
29f8f267-6ed8-44c9-a1aa-7b11c19e8c69 Add the almond flour mixture to the bowl, and with mixer on the lowest speed, mix until just blended. The dough will be very soft (no need to chill).
29f8f267-6ed8-44c9-a1aa-7b11c19e8c69 Stir in the chocolate chips.
29f8f267-6ed8-44c9-a1aa-7b11c19e8c69 Scoop the dough, 2 tablespoonfuls at a time (a cookie scoop is handy here) onto the prepared sheet pans 2 to 3-inches apart. Bake one tray at a time, until the cookies are barely golden around the edges, and still puffed in the center, 13–15 minutes.
29f8f267-6ed8-44c9-a1aa-7b11c19e8c69 Let cookies cool on the tray for 2 minutes (they’ll be too delicate to transfer right from the oven), then use a spatula to transfer to a wire rack and let cool completely.
a20a7748-c13a-44ef-bec2-20c23c33b463 Gather the ingredients.
a20a7748-c13a-44ef-bec2-20c23c33b463 Preheat oven to 350 F. Line cookie sheets with parchment paper.
a20a7748-c13a-44ef-bec2-20c23c33b463 In a large mixer bowl, beat the butter, granulated sugar, and brown sugar together until mixed.
a20a7748-c13a-44ef-bec2-20c23c33b463 Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
a20a7748-c13a-44ef-bec2-20c23c33b463 Beat in vanilla and water.
a20a7748-c13a-44ef-bec2-20c23c33b463 In a medium bowl, stir together the flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt.
a20a7748-c13a-44ef-bec2-20c23c33b463 Add the dry ingredients to the butter mixture and beat until combined.
a20a7748-c13a-44ef-bec2-20c23c33b463 Add the oatmeal, butterscotch morsels, Cornflakes, and walnuts; mix well.
a20a7748-c13a-44ef-bec2-20c23c33b463 Place heaping spoonfuls of batter, about 2-inches apart, onto prepared baking sheets. Gently press each cookie to flatten it slightly. Bake cookies until lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes.
a20a7748-c13a-44ef-bec2-20c23c33b463 Transfer to wire racks to cool completely.
a20a7748-c13a-44ef-bec2-20c23c33b463 Serve and enjoy!
05107035-3fb4-43f1-a931-fcd8be0d9f7c Gather the ingredients.
05107035-3fb4-43f1-a931-fcd8be0d9f7c Preheat the oven to 350 F. Lightly grease baking sheets or line them with parchment paper.
05107035-3fb4-43f1-a931-fcd8be0d9f7c Put the filling ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to low and simmer, stirring frequently, until the date mixture is thickened, about 5 to 7 minutes. Set the date filling aside to cool.
05107035-3fb4-43f1-a931-fcd8be0d9f7c In a mixing bowl, beat the butter with the sugar until light and fluffy with the help of an electric mixer. Add the egg, water, and vanilla extract. Beat until well blended.
05107035-3fb4-43f1-a931-fcd8be0d9f7c In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, and salt. Stir with a spoon or whisk to blend.
05107035-3fb4-43f1-a931-fcd8be0d9f7c Stir the flour mixture into the butter mixture until the dough is smooth, malleable, and well blended.
05107035-3fb4-43f1-a931-fcd8be0d9f7c Using a teaspoon, drop the cookie dough onto the prepared cookie sheets.
05107035-3fb4-43f1-a931-fcd8be0d9f7c Place about 1/2 teaspoon of the date mixture on the top of each drop cookie and then place a small dab of cookie dough on top of the date mixture to "close" the cookie.
05107035-3fb4-43f1-a931-fcd8be0d9f7c Bake the cookies in the preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
05107035-3fb4-43f1-a931-fcd8be0d9f7c Remove the cookies to racks to cool completely.
05107035-3fb4-43f1-a931-fcd8be0d9f7c Enjoy!
5ca4f75d-f972-47e4-8588-a17dbea73a1f Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
5ca4f75d-f972-47e4-8588-a17dbea73a1f In a small bowl, whisk together the coconut flour, baking powder, and salt.
5ca4f75d-f972-47e4-8588-a17dbea73a1f In a large mixing bowl, combine the butter and sugar and whisk to combine.
5ca4f75d-f972-47e4-8588-a17dbea73a1f Add the vanilla and coconut extract (if using) and whisk. Add the egg and yolk, whisking after each addition.
5ca4f75d-f972-47e4-8588-a17dbea73a1f Add the dry ingredients all at once and gently combine with a rubber spatula.
5ca4f75d-f972-47e4-8588-a17dbea73a1f Add the chocolate coconut and mix to combine.
5ca4f75d-f972-47e4-8588-a17dbea73a1f Using a 1 1/2 tablespoon cookie scoop or measuring spoons, place 12 mounds of dough onto the prepared sheet.
5ca4f75d-f972-47e4-8588-a17dbea73a1f Bake for 12 minutes, rotating at the halfway point. The cookies are ready when lightly browned around the edges. Once removed from the oven, flatten each cookie gently with a spatula.
5ca4f75d-f972-47e4-8588-a17dbea73a1f Let cool until easy to handle and them remove to a cooling rack. Repeat with the remaining dough.
4eae9b4e-37b0-4e14-95bb-0bacf9c98908 Gather the ingredients.
4eae9b4e-37b0-4e14-95bb-0bacf9c98908 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line baking sheets with parchment paper.
4eae9b4e-37b0-4e14-95bb-0bacf9c98908 Combine flour, baking soda, salt, and cream of tartar in a small bowl.
4eae9b4e-37b0-4e14-95bb-0bacf9c98908 Add butter to a deep bowl, and beat with a hand mixer, or the paddle attachment of a stand mixer, until creamy, 30 seconds.
4eae9b4e-37b0-4e14-95bb-0bacf9c98908 Add sugars, and beat until light and creamy, 3 to 5 minutes. Add egg and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy, 1 minute.
4eae9b4e-37b0-4e14-95bb-0bacf9c98908 Add flour mixture to the bowl. Mix until just incorporated, and there are no visible signs of flour. Stir in the sprinkles.
4eae9b4e-37b0-4e14-95bb-0bacf9c98908 Drop dough, 1 1/2 tablespoons at a time (a medium cookie scoop is good for this step), onto the prepared baking sheets, spacing the dough 2 inches apart.
4eae9b4e-37b0-4e14-95bb-0bacf9c98908 Bake, one sheet at a time (important for cookies to cook evenly), until the bottoms and edges are lightly browned and the tops look set but still soft and chewy in the center, 12 to 14 minutes.
4eae9b4e-37b0-4e14-95bb-0bacf9c98908 Let cookies cool on the baking sheets for 5 minutes, then transfer to wire racks to cool completely.
c371d573-d697-4a4a-b165-2908f86cc688 Gather the ingredients.
c371d573-d697-4a4a-b165-2908f86cc688 To make the gingerbread whoopie pies, pre-heat the oven to 350 F.
c371d573-d697-4a4a-b165-2908f86cc688 Add the egg and light brown sugar to a large bowl. Using a stand or hand mixer, beat until smooth and slightly lightened in color. Beat in the molasses, melted butter and vanilla extract.
c371d573-d697-4a4a-b165-2908f86cc688 In a separate bowl, sift together the all purpose flour, baking soda, ground cinnamon, ground ginger, ground nutmeg and salt.
c371d573-d697-4a4a-b165-2908f86cc688 Stir the dry ingredients into the wet batter.
c371d573-d697-4a4a-b165-2908f86cc688 Using a 1 ounce cookie scoop, scoop the batter onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper or a baking mat, and keep the scoops at least 2" apart because they will spread in the oven. You can use a couple of baking sheets or just work in batches, but you should end up with about 20 scoops.
c371d573-d697-4a4a-b165-2908f86cc688 Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Allow to cool thoroughly before handling.
c371d573-d697-4a4a-b165-2908f86cc688 To make the tahini cream filling, whisk together the marshmallow fluff, powdered sugar, melted butter, milk, sesame paste, vanilla and sea salt until smooth. Let sit for a few minutes while the whoopie pies cool to let the filling set and thicken a bit. This will help the filling stay put when you spread it between the two pies.
c371d573-d697-4a4a-b165-2908f86cc688 To assemble the whoopie pies, place about a tablespoon of tahini cream in between the bottoms of two of the cookies (use more if you want them thicker) and gently sandwich together.
c371d573-d697-4a4a-b165-2908f86cc688 Enjoy!
95ec6fa0-db01-4d1e-a4db-6ab6aecbf580 Gather the ingredients and preheat the oven to 325 F/165 C/Gas 3.
95ec6fa0-db01-4d1e-a4db-6ab6aecbf580 Grease a cookie sheet or line it with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat.
95ec6fa0-db01-4d1e-a4db-6ab6aecbf580 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the sugar and butter together until light and fluffy, about 3 to 4 minutes.
95ec6fa0-db01-4d1e-a4db-6ab6aecbf580 Beat in the eggs until well blended.
95ec6fa0-db01-4d1e-a4db-6ab6aecbf580 In another bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves. Stir or whisk the dry mixture to blend thoroughly.
95ec6fa0-db01-4d1e-a4db-6ab6aecbf580 Add the flour mixture to the egg mixture, beating on low speed until blended.
95ec6fa0-db01-4d1e-a4db-6ab6aecbf580 Stir in the milk. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
95ec6fa0-db01-4d1e-a4db-6ab6aecbf580 Drop the dough by spoonfuls onto the prepared cookie sheet. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until the cookies are lightly browned.
95ec6fa0-db01-4d1e-a4db-6ab6aecbf580 Let the cookies cool completely.
95ec6fa0-db01-4d1e-a4db-6ab6aecbf580 Serve and enjoy or store them in an airtight container.
92a8e8fd-3c12-45a8-acd1-bb9f8f27e0b3 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F and line 2 rimmed sheet pans with parchment paper.
92a8e8fd-3c12-45a8-acd1-bb9f8f27e0b3 Add the almond flour, cocoa powder, salt, and baking soda to a bowl. Whisk until thoroughly combined and set aside.
92a8e8fd-3c12-45a8-acd1-bb9f8f27e0b3 Cream the unsalted butter and sweetener using a hand mixer or stand mixer. Beat until lightened in color and fluffy.
92a8e8fd-3c12-45a8-acd1-bb9f8f27e0b3 Mix in the eggs and the vanilla extract.
92a8e8fd-3c12-45a8-acd1-bb9f8f27e0b3 Stir in the flour mixture, just until incorporated, then fold in the chocolate chips.
92a8e8fd-3c12-45a8-acd1-bb9f8f27e0b3 Scoop out approximately 1 1/2-ounce balls and place on 2 prepared sheet pans. Note that these cookies will spread a little, so keep them a couple of inches apart on the baking sheets.
92a8e8fd-3c12-45a8-acd1-bb9f8f27e0b3 Flatten the top of each cookie very slightly and sprinkle with a bit of sea salt.
92a8e8fd-3c12-45a8-acd1-bb9f8f27e0b3 Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until just set. The cookies will be very soft but will firm up slightly as they cool.
e760e491-7eba-4ea6-8a7d-579a9bd27bc1 Gather the ingredients.
e760e491-7eba-4ea6-8a7d-579a9bd27bc1 Heat oven to 325 F. Line baking sheets with parchment paper.
e760e491-7eba-4ea6-8a7d-579a9bd27bc1 Separate the egg and place the white and yolk in different bowls.
e760e491-7eba-4ea6-8a7d-579a9bd27bc1 In the bowl of an electric mixer at high speed, beat egg white until foamy-white and double in volume. Beat in 3 tablespoons of the sugar, 1 at a time, until firm peaks form.
e760e491-7eba-4ea6-8a7d-579a9bd27bc1 Beat egg yolk well in a medium-size bowl; beat in the remaining sugar until fluffy and light.
e760e491-7eba-4ea6-8a7d-579a9bd27bc1 Stir in baking powder, salt, vanilla, rolled oats, coconut, and melted butter.
e760e491-7eba-4ea6-8a7d-579a9bd27bc1 Fold in egg white meringue.
e760e491-7eba-4ea6-8a7d-579a9bd27bc1 Drop by small spoonfuls onto prepared baking sheets, at least 1 inch apart. Cookies will spread.
e760e491-7eba-4ea6-8a7d-579a9bd27bc1 Bake 15 minutes or until firm and lightly golden. Remove from cookie sheets; cool completely on wire racks.
e760e491-7eba-4ea6-8a7d-579a9bd27bc1 Store in tightly covered container. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.
07cbd56d-ae89-41e6-845c-e69b5f7d6fdb Gather the ingredients.
07cbd56d-ae89-41e6-845c-e69b5f7d6fdb Heat the oven to 325 F/165 C/Gas Mark 3.
07cbd56d-ae89-41e6-845c-e69b5f7d6fdb Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper or nonstick foil. Spray the paper or foil with nonstick cooking spray.
07cbd56d-ae89-41e6-845c-e69b5f7d6fdb In a bowl, combine the coconut, sweetened condensed milk, and vanilla extract; blend well.
07cbd56d-ae89-41e6-845c-e69b5f7d6fdb Grease or spray a teaspoon or cookie scoop.
07cbd56d-ae89-41e6-845c-e69b5f7d6fdb Drop mounds of the coconut mixture onto the prepared baking sheets, leaving about 1 1/2 inches between ​the cookies.
07cbd56d-ae89-41e6-845c-e69b5f7d6fdb Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned around the edges.
07cbd56d-ae89-41e6-845c-e69b5f7d6fdb Immediately remove the cookies to a rack to cool.
07cbd56d-ae89-41e6-845c-e69b5f7d6fdb Enjoy.
4dd96549-6452-42fa-a6f5-e051e5328aff Gather the ingredients.
4dd96549-6452-42fa-a6f5-e051e5328aff Preheat oven to 350 F.
4dd96549-6452-42fa-a6f5-e051e5328aff In a bowl, combine the dry ingredients: flour, oats, cinnamon, baking soda, and salt.
4dd96549-6452-42fa-a6f5-e051e5328aff In another large bowl, whisk or beat the mashed banana, butter, sugar, egg, and vanilla until smooth.
4dd96549-6452-42fa-a6f5-e051e5328aff Slowly fold the dry mixture into liquid mixture. Add the shredded zucchini, walnuts, and chocolate chips and mix until a sticky dough forms.
4dd96549-6452-42fa-a6f5-e051e5328aff Flour your hands and roll dough into 1-inch balls. Place the balls on a lined baking sheet.
4dd96549-6452-42fa-a6f5-e051e5328aff Bake cookies at 350 F 12 to 15 minutes. The edges should turn golden brown while the centers stay slightly soft.
4dd96549-6452-42fa-a6f5-e051e5328aff Let the cookies cool for about 10 minutes on the baking sheet and the transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
8ab0fe29-8298-4dd1-a4f4-256baa6da3cc Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F and cover a baking sheet with non-stick baking paper or a silicone mat.
8ab0fe29-8298-4dd1-a4f4-256baa6da3cc Add the butter and sugar to a medium mixing bowl. Cream together until light and fluffy using a whisk, or, to speed things up, with an electric hand or stand mixer. Add the beaten egg to this mixture a little at a time. Add the vanilla and beat again.
8ab0fe29-8298-4dd1-a4f4-256baa6da3cc In a small mixing bowl, combine the oats, flour, baking powder, and salt. Using a large tablespoon or a spatula, lightly fold the dry ingredients into the creamed butter until both are combined.
8ab0fe29-8298-4dd1-a4f4-256baa6da3cc Scoop even spoonfuls of the mixture onto the prepared baking sheet at least one inch apart. The size of the spoon will determine the finished size; teaspoons make dainty biscuits, tablespoons make large, thin biscuits.
8ab0fe29-8298-4dd1-a4f4-256baa6da3cc Bake in the center of the preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Keep an eye on them as they turn golden quickly, and from there can burn. Remove the tray from the oven and let the cookies sit for a minute before lifting them carefully onto a cooling rack. Repeat until all of the cookie dough is baked.
8ab0fe29-8298-4dd1-a4f4-256baa6da3cc Let the cookies cool completely since they will crisp up as they cool. Avoid touching them during this time as they break easily. Once cooled, lay them between layers of waxed or parchment paper and store them in a tin.
57feac50-7ce6-4cc4-aa35-0f17733ddd91 Gather the ingredients.
57feac50-7ce6-4cc4-aa35-0f17733ddd91 Cover a cookie sheet with waxed paper.
57feac50-7ce6-4cc4-aa35-0f17733ddd91 In a bowl set over hot, not boiling, water heat butterscotch morsels and peanut butter. Stir until melted and smooth.
57feac50-7ce6-4cc4-aa35-0f17733ddd91 Alternately, the butterscotch morsels and peanut butter can be melted together in a microwave-safe bowl in the microwave. Heat in 30 second intervals, stirring each time until melted and smooth.
57feac50-7ce6-4cc4-aa35-0f17733ddd91 Stir in corn flakes cereal until well coated. Drop from a spoon onto a prepared cookie sheet.
57feac50-7ce6-4cc4-aa35-0f17733ddd91 Chill in refrigerator until firm.
57feac50-7ce6-4cc4-aa35-0f17733ddd91 When the cookies are ready, carefully peel away from the waxed paper.
57feac50-7ce6-4cc4-aa35-0f17733ddd91 Store in the refrigerator in an airtight container between layers of waxed paper.
57feac50-7ce6-4cc4-aa35-0f17733ddd91 Enjoy cornflake cookies with a cold glass of milk!
f50adba5-b209-42f8-835e-f274f4f91e6f Gather the ingredients.
f50adba5-b209-42f8-835e-f274f4f91e6f Heat the oven to 375 F/190 C/Gas 5. Lightly grease baking sheets or line them with parchment paper or silicone baking mats.
f50adba5-b209-42f8-835e-f274f4f91e6f In a bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, and salt; stir to blend the dry ingredients thoroughly.
f50adba5-b209-42f8-835e-f274f4f91e6f In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer on medium-high speed, beat the granulated and brown sugars with the butter until light and fluffy.
f50adba5-b209-42f8-835e-f274f4f91e6f Add the eggs, beating well after each addition.
f50adba5-b209-42f8-835e-f274f4f91e6f Beat in the vanilla extract.
f50adba5-b209-42f8-835e-f274f4f91e6f Add the dry ingredients into the butter and sugar mixture and beat on medium speed just until blended.
f50adba5-b209-42f8-835e-f274f4f91e6f Add the chocolate chips and chopped walnuts or pecans, if using. Fold until well incorporated.
f50adba5-b209-42f8-835e-f274f4f91e6f Drop the cookie dough onto the prepared baking sheets by tablespoonfuls, leaving about 2 inches between cookies.
f50adba5-b209-42f8-835e-f274f4f91e6f Bake the cookies in the preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until they are set and lightly browned.
f50adba5-b209-42f8-835e-f274f4f91e6f Remove the chocolate chip cookies to a rack to cool.
f50adba5-b209-42f8-835e-f274f4f91e6f Serve and enjoy!
032ae000-b359-46a2-a0ab-154c97b19dc8 Cream the butter with the powdered sugar until well blended and smooth. Beat in the vanilla, then add the flour and salt.
032ae000-b359-46a2-a0ab-154c97b19dc8 Mix just until combined, but don't mix too much. You don't want too much gluten to form; the cookies should be tender. Add the nuts, if using.
032ae000-b359-46a2-a0ab-154c97b19dc8 Cover the dough and chill it for several hours in the refrigerator. We like to make this dough the day before we bake them.
032ae000-b359-46a2-a0ab-154c97b19dc8 When you're ready to bake, let the dough stand at room temperature for about 30 minutes. The dough will be really hard from being chilled. Preheat the oven to 400 F.
032ae000-b359-46a2-a0ab-154c97b19dc8 Form the dough into 1-inch balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet. The dough will not spread at all during baking, so you can place them pretty close together. We can usually get all of the cookies onto just two cookie sheets.
032ae000-b359-46a2-a0ab-154c97b19dc8 Bake the cookies for 8 to 12 minutes. The cookies should not brown on the top or just be very pale gold on the tops, but be lightly golden on the bottom.
032ae000-b359-46a2-a0ab-154c97b19dc8 Immediately take the cookies, one at a time, off the hot cookie sheet and drop into a shallow bowl full of powdered sugar, roll, and place on a rack to cool. When the cookies are cool, roll them again in powdered sugar to coat.
032ae000-b359-46a2-a0ab-154c97b19dc8 Store in an airtight container at room temperature up to 1 week, if they last that long!
13fff5e4-1df7-4d0d-a24b-562f2e88963c Brown the butter: put the butter in a saucepan and place the saucepan over medium heat. Cook until the butter begins to simmer. Continue cooking, stirring, just until butter begins to turn golden brown, about 4 to 5 minutes. Pour the melted butter off into a measuring cup or bowl, leaving the darkest sediment behind. Let the butter cool to room temperature.
13fff5e4-1df7-4d0d-a24b-562f2e88963c In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the browned butter and the granulated and brown sugars until light and fluffy. Add egg and egg yolk, milk, and vanilla. Beat on low speed until well blended.
13fff5e4-1df7-4d0d-a24b-562f2e88963c In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, and salt; whisk or stir to blend thoroughly.
13fff5e4-1df7-4d0d-a24b-562f2e88963c Gradually add the dry ingredients to the egg and butter mixture, mixing on low speed until soft dough forms. Scrape the bowl a few times. Fold in the chocolate chips. Cover the bowl and refrigerate for about an hour or overnight, or until the dough is chilled.
13fff5e4-1df7-4d0d-a24b-562f2e88963c Heat the oven to 375 F.
13fff5e4-1df7-4d0d-a24b-562f2e88963c Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or a silicone mat or spray the pan with nonstick cooking spray.
13fff5e4-1df7-4d0d-a24b-562f2e88963c Using a cookie scoop or tablespoon, drop mounds of dough onto the prepared baking sheets, allowing about 2 to 3 inches in between the cookies.
13fff5e4-1df7-4d0d-a24b-562f2e88963c Bake for 6 to 10 minutes, or until the cookies are browned around the edges.
13fff5e4-1df7-4d0d-a24b-562f2e88963c Cool completely and transfer to an airtight container for storage.
f84f7ad7-3a2a-485b-a19f-a85083a23fe7 Line a baking sheet with a silicone mat or buttered parchment paper. Heat the oven to 350 F.
f84f7ad7-3a2a-485b-a19f-a85083a23fe7 In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
f84f7ad7-3a2a-485b-a19f-a85083a23fe7 In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat butter, brown sugar, and granulated sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs and vanilla until well blended. Slowly beat in the milk and pumpkin, then add dry ingredients, beating just until blended.
f84f7ad7-3a2a-485b-a19f-a85083a23fe7 With a tablespoon or cookie scoop, drop cookie dough onto the prepared baking sheets. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned and tops are firm. Cool for about 5 minutes on the baking sheet, then loosen the bottoms with a spatula and let them cool completely.
f84f7ad7-3a2a-485b-a19f-a85083a23fe7 Combine the filling ingredients in a bowl with an electric mixer. Beat well until the filling is smooth. Frost the bottom of a cookie, then press the bottom of another cookie on the filling to make a sandwich. Repeat with remaining cookies.
e34b67b2-29a1-4991-a504-4365942349ad In a large mixing bowl, using an electric mixer, beat eggs, sugar, chocolate, oil, baking powder, and vanilla until blended. Beat in as much of the flour with the mixer as possible, then stir in the remaining flour.
e34b67b2-29a1-4991-a504-4365942349ad Cover and chill the cookie dough for 2 hours.
e34b67b2-29a1-4991-a504-4365942349ad Shape the cookie dough into 1-inch balls. Roll the dough balls in sifted confectioners' sugar, coating well.
e34b67b2-29a1-4991-a504-4365942349ad Place balls of cookie dough about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets and bake in a 375 F oven for 8 to 10 minutes, until crackled in appearance.
e34b67b2-29a1-4991-a504-4365942349ad Transfer cookies to a wire rack to cool. Sprinkle with more confectioners' sugar if desired.
115fd43f-3c60-4026-a563-c128873a39e1 Gather the ingredients.
115fd43f-3c60-4026-a563-c128873a39e1 Preheat the oven to 400 F/200 C/Gas 6. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or a silicone mat, or grease the pan lightly.
115fd43f-3c60-4026-a563-c128873a39e1 Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and nutmeg into a bowl; whisk to blend the dry mixture thoroughly and set aside.
115fd43f-3c60-4026-a563-c128873a39e1 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream together the butter and sugar. Beat in the egg, sweet potato, vanilla, and orange rind.
115fd43f-3c60-4026-a563-c128873a39e1 With the mixer on low speed, gradually beat in the dry ingredients.
115fd43f-3c60-4026-a563-c128873a39e1 Fold the chopped pecans into the batter.
115fd43f-3c60-4026-a563-c128873a39e1 Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto the prepared baking sheets, leaving about 2 inches between them. Bake the cookies for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned and firm.
115fd43f-3c60-4026-a563-c128873a39e1 Cool on racks and store in an airtight container.
115fd43f-3c60-4026-a563-c128873a39e1 If desired, glaze with a mixture of 1 cup confectioners' sugar and 2 tablespoons orange juice (or enough to make a thin glaze consistency) while cookies are still warm.
115fd43f-3c60-4026-a563-c128873a39e1 Enjoy!
72425c9c-d600-4d32-b170-523c8ec0e39a Gather the ingredients.
72425c9c-d600-4d32-b170-523c8ec0e39a Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line baking sheets with parchment paper or grease them lightly.
72425c9c-d600-4d32-b170-523c8ec0e39a Sift together the flour, cocoa, baking powder, and salt. Set aside.
72425c9c-d600-4d32-b170-523c8ec0e39a Combine the butter, brown sugar, and granulated sugar in a large mixing bowl. With an electric mixer, beat the butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
72425c9c-d600-4d32-b170-523c8ec0e39a Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Beat in vanilla.
72425c9c-d600-4d32-b170-523c8ec0e39a With the mixer on low speed, beat in flour mixture a little at a time until well blended and smooth.
72425c9c-d600-4d32-b170-523c8ec0e39a Fold in the finely chopped walnuts.
72425c9c-d600-4d32-b170-523c8ec0e39a Drop the chocolate cookie dough onto greased baking sheets by rounded tablespoons, leaving about 2 inches between cookies.
72425c9c-d600-4d32-b170-523c8ec0e39a Bake the cookies for 12 to 15 minutes, or until set. If desired, sprinkle with some granulated sugar while they're hot or dust with powdered sugar when cool.
72425c9c-d600-4d32-b170-523c8ec0e39a Let the cookies cool on the pans on a rack for about 5 minutes; transfer chocolate cookies to the rack to cool completely.
b6029aad-fede-4aff-94c3-2dfd0b389d40 Combine flour, soda, and salt; set aside.
b6029aad-fede-4aff-94c3-2dfd0b389d40 In another bowl, cream butter until light and lemon-colored; gradually add sugar, beating well after each addition. Slowly add beaten eggs to creamed mixture. Alternately add dry ingredients and juice to the creamed mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
b6029aad-fede-4aff-94c3-2dfd0b389d40 Fold in the coconut.
b6029aad-fede-4aff-94c3-2dfd0b389d40 Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
c26c9394-73c8-465d-8c0c-3bd328e9a055 Heat oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4).
c26c9394-73c8-465d-8c0c-3bd328e9a055 Grease a baking sheet or line with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat.
c26c9394-73c8-465d-8c0c-3bd328e9a055 Combine the flour, sugars, baking soda, salt, baking powder, and cinnamon in a bowl.
c26c9394-73c8-465d-8c0c-3bd328e9a055 In a mixing bowl, beat butter, egg, and orange juice together.
c26c9394-73c8-465d-8c0c-3bd328e9a055 With the mixer on low speed, slowly beat in the flour mixture until well blended. Stir in granola, quick cooking oats, and dried cranberries.
c26c9394-73c8-465d-8c0c-3bd328e9a055 Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto the prepared baking sheet, leaving about 1 1/2 to 2 inches between the cookies.
c26c9394-73c8-465d-8c0c-3bd328e9a055 Moisten a finger with a little water and lightly smooth out the tops of the cookie dough.
c26c9394-73c8-465d-8c0c-3bd328e9a055 Bake the cookies for about 15 to 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
c26c9394-73c8-465d-8c0c-3bd328e9a055 Let the cookies cool in pan for 5 minutes, then remove to a rack and let cool completely.
c26c9394-73c8-465d-8c0c-3bd328e9a055 Store in a tightly covered container for up to 1 week.
0721e0cf-d2ee-4993-9c97-659284b13cf7 In a large microwave-safe bowl, combine the sugar, milk, cocoa, salt, and butter and mix well. Microwave on high power for 2 and 1/2 minutes. Remove from the microwave to stir. Wash off the spoon and return the bowl to the microwave.
0721e0cf-d2ee-4993-9c97-659284b13cf7 Microwave for 2 and 1/2 minutes longer, or until the mixture boils thoroughly for 1 minute. Then remove the bowl from the microwave and stir in the peanut butter and vanilla until smooth. Add oatmeal and mix well. Do not use regular or instant oatmeal; quick-cooking oatmeal is essential to the success of this recipe.
0721e0cf-d2ee-4993-9c97-659284b13cf7 Let the mixture stand for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally to let the oatmeal absorb some of the liquid.
0721e0cf-d2ee-4993-9c97-659284b13cf7 Drop the mixture by spoonfuls onto waxed paper or parchment lined baking sheets or Silpat sheets. Let the cookies cool until you can touch the mixture; then reshape the cookies to make them more a ball shape. Let cool completely; store tightly covered at room temperature.
0721e0cf-d2ee-4993-9c97-659284b13cf7 You can also pour this mixture into a 9" square pan that has been greased with unsalted butter, let cool, then cut into squares.
ebe4d885-ab6a-4f85-8559-3507f5e1475c Gather the ingredients.
ebe4d885-ab6a-4f85-8559-3507f5e1475c Preheat oven to 375 F.
ebe4d885-ab6a-4f85-8559-3507f5e1475c In a large bowl, beat granulated sugar and brown sugar with butter and peanut butter until fluffy.
ebe4d885-ab6a-4f85-8559-3507f5e1475c Beat in eggs and vanilla, then add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Mix well. Cover dough and chill for at least 30 minutes, preferably 4 to 6 hours.
ebe4d885-ab6a-4f85-8559-3507f5e1475c Shape a scant 1/4 cup of dough around each unwrapped candy bar. Be sure that the candy bar is completely covered with dough, or it will melt out onto the cookie sheet during baking.
ebe4d885-ab6a-4f85-8559-3507f5e1475c Place the balls of dough 4 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet, about 9 cookies per sheet. ​​​
ebe4d885-ab6a-4f85-8559-3507f5e1475c Bake the large cookies at 375 F for 13 to 15 minutes or until cookies are light golden brown with some slightly darker brown spots.
ebe4d885-ab6a-4f85-8559-3507f5e1475c Cool 10 minutes, then remove from cookie sheets using a large spatula and cool on wire racks.
ebe4d885-ab6a-4f85-8559-3507f5e1475c Place milk chocolate chips in a small microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on high for 1 minute; remove and stir. Microwave for 30 seconds longer on high; remove and stir until smooth. Drizzle over cookies.
6f0801cb-5d32-4b58-ba73-449332643a42 Gather the ingredients.
6f0801cb-5d32-4b58-ba73-449332643a42 In ​a large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, and sugar and beat well.
6f0801cb-5d32-4b58-ba73-449332643a42 Add eggs and beat well, then add vanilla extract.
6f0801cb-5d32-4b58-ba73-449332643a42 Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt and mix well. Stir in cashews and white chocolate chips.
6f0801cb-5d32-4b58-ba73-449332643a42 Cover dough and chill for 1 to 4 hours.
6f0801cb-5d32-4b58-ba73-449332643a42 When ready to bake, preheat oven to 325 F.
6f0801cb-5d32-4b58-ba73-449332643a42 Drop dough by heaping teaspoons onto un-greased cookie sheets.
6f0801cb-5d32-4b58-ba73-449332643a42 Bake for 9 to 14 minutes or until the cookies are light golden brown around edges.
6f0801cb-5d32-4b58-ba73-449332643a42 Let cool on cookie sheets for 3 minutes, then remove to wire rack to cool completely.
6f0801cb-5d32-4b58-ba73-449332643a42 Serve and enjoy!
e8b430b2-35c1-4c64-8234-6771d5e62fd6 Preheat the oven to 375 F.
e8b430b2-35c1-4c64-8234-6771d5e62fd6 Lightly grease a large baking sheet or line it with parchment paper.
e8b430b2-35c1-4c64-8234-6771d5e62fd6 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat ​the butter until smooth and creamy; add the granulated and brown sugars and continue to beat for about 2 to 3 minutes, or until light in color and fluffy. Add the egg and vanilla and continue to beat until well blended. ​​​
e8b430b2-35c1-4c64-8234-6771d5e62fd6 In a separate bowl, combine the flour, salt, and baking soda; blend well with a spoon or whisk. Add the flour mixture to the butter and sugar mixture. Stir until thoroughly blended.
e8b430b2-35c1-4c64-8234-6771d5e62fd6 With a spoon or spatula, fold in the chocolate chips and pecans, if using.
e8b430b2-35c1-4c64-8234-6771d5e62fd6 If desired, chill the dough in the refrigerator for a few hours or overnight.
e8b430b2-35c1-4c64-8234-6771d5e62fd6 Drop the batter onto the prepared baking sheet from a teaspoon or small cookie scoop leaving about 2 inches between cookies.
e8b430b2-35c1-4c64-8234-6771d5e62fd6 Bake the cookies in the preheated oven for about 10 minutes, or until set and just lightly browned on the bottoms.
a25ff943-a266-4f76-81ae-67eb2ca81d11 Sift together flour, baking powder, and salt. Set aside.
a25ff943-a266-4f76-81ae-67eb2ca81d11 Cream butter and sugar together with an electric mixer. Beat in egg and vanilla.
a25ff943-a266-4f76-81ae-67eb2ca81d11 On low speed, beat in flour mixture, mixing until all the flour is incorporated. Do not overmix, or the cookies will turn out tough.
a25ff943-a266-4f76-81ae-67eb2ca81d11 Refrigerate dough for at least 30 minutes, preferably 1 to 2 hours.
a25ff943-a266-4f76-81ae-67eb2ca81d11 Preheat oven to 350 F. Line cookie sheets with parchment paper or a silicone mat.
a25ff943-a266-4f76-81ae-67eb2ca81d11 Drop dough using a rounded tablespoon onto prepared cookie sheets. Flatten slightly with your fingers. Top with sprinkles, if desired.
a25ff943-a266-4f76-81ae-67eb2ca81d11 Bake 8 to 12 minutes, or until cookies are golden brown on the bottom.
d75c90f4-3a1b-476f-bf57-2b594fd7800e Gather the ingredients.
d75c90f4-3a1b-476f-bf57-2b594fd7800e Preheat the oven to 300 F (150 C).
d75c90f4-3a1b-476f-bf57-2b594fd7800e Place the butter, brown sugar, and granulated sugar in the work bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment. Beat on medium speed for about 30 seconds, until the mixture, is fluffy.
d75c90f4-3a1b-476f-bf57-2b594fd7800e Beat in the egg and vanilla for 30 seconds longer, until well combined.
d75c90f4-3a1b-476f-bf57-2b594fd7800e In a mixing bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
d75c90f4-3a1b-476f-bf57-2b594fd7800e Add to the mixer, while beating on slow speed. Beat for about 15 seconds, stir in the chocolate chips and espresso powder and mix for 15 seconds longer.
d75c90f4-3a1b-476f-bf57-2b594fd7800e Prepare a cookie sheet with about 2 tablespoons of shortening (or use a non-stick spray). Using a 1-ounce scoop, or using a 2 tablespoon measure, drop the cookie dough onto the cookie sheet in dollops about 3 inches apart.
d75c90f4-3a1b-476f-bf57-2b594fd7800e Gently press down on the dough with the back of a spoon to spread out into 2-inch circles; there should be room on the sheet for six or eight cookies at a time.
d75c90f4-3a1b-476f-bf57-2b594fd7800e Transfer to the oven in batches and bake for about 20 minutes or until the cookies are nicely browned around the edges. Bake for a little longer for crisper cookies.
cb56e99f-78e2-4e1f-bca2-138e0c5ca7df Gather the ingredients. Cover a baking sheet with waxed paper or parchment paper.
cb56e99f-78e2-4e1f-bca2-138e0c5ca7df In a large saucepan over medium heat, place the sugar, milk, butter, and salt. Stir frequently and bring to a boil. Boil for 90 seconds.
cb56e99f-78e2-4e1f-bca2-138e0c5ca7df Remove from heat and stir in the peanut butter and vanilla extract until peanut butter melts and the mixture is smooth.
cb56e99f-78e2-4e1f-bca2-138e0c5ca7df Stir in the quick-cooking oats and blend well.
cb56e99f-78e2-4e1f-bca2-138e0c5ca7df Drop the mixture by spoonfuls onto the prepared baking sheet.
cb56e99f-78e2-4e1f-bca2-138e0c5ca7df Place the baking sheet in the refrigerator and allow to cool and chill until firm. When ready to serve, gently peel away the cookies from the waxed paper or parchment paper.
cb56e99f-78e2-4e1f-bca2-138e0c5ca7df Enjoy! Store the cookies in an airtight container in the refrigerator between pieces of parchment paper or waxed paper for up to one week.
15741525-3ae6-4357-ad8d-804b8c989f01 Gather the ingredients.
15741525-3ae6-4357-ad8d-804b8c989f01 Preheat the oven to 350 F (180 C). Line two large, rimmed cookie sheets with parchment paper.
15741525-3ae6-4357-ad8d-804b8c989f01 In a medium bowl, mix together the peanut butter, sugar, and egg until well combined. Many peanut butter brands contain sugar and salt as well. If yours contains sugar and you prefer a less sweet cookie, try making a batch with 3/4 or 2/3 cup sugar instead.
15741525-3ae6-4357-ad8d-804b8c989f01 With clean, oiled hands, roll pieces of dough into walnut sized balls. Place the dough balls 1 inch apart on the prepared cookie sheets, and flatten each with the heel of your hand. Or, for less mess and cookies with a slightly more free-form appearance, simply drop the dough by the teaspoonful onto the prepared cookie sheets.
15741525-3ae6-4357-ad8d-804b8c989f01 Bake at 350 F (180 C) for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned around edges. Transfer carefully to a wire rack to cool.
cb2375bd-c85c-41e0-b9ee-17aab126633c Preheat oven to 300 F (150 C/Gas 2). Line baking sheets with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat. Or spray the baking sheets lightly with baking spray.
cb2375bd-c85c-41e0-b9ee-17aab126633c In a bowl combine the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Blend well with a whisk and set aside.
cb2375bd-c85c-41e0-b9ee-17aab126633c In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
cb2375bd-c85c-41e0-b9ee-17aab126633c Add the eggnog, vanilla and egg yolks; beat at medium speed until smooth.
cb2375bd-c85c-41e0-b9ee-17aab126633c Add the flour mixture and beat on low speed just until dry ingredients are moistened.
cb2375bd-c85c-41e0-b9ee-17aab126633c Using a teaspoon or small cookie scoop, drop the dough onto the prepared baking sheets, leaving about 2 inches between the cookies.
cb2375bd-c85c-41e0-b9ee-17aab126633c If desired, sprinkle each mound of cookie dough with more nutmeg.
cb2375bd-c85c-41e0-b9ee-17aab126633c Bake for about 25 minutes, or until the bottoms are lightly browned.
cb2375bd-c85c-41e0-b9ee-17aab126633c Remove the cookies to a rack with a spatula.
b797421b-b711-4e19-b013-cf4eda0a4e8d Gather the ingredients.
b797421b-b711-4e19-b013-cf4eda0a4e8d Preheat oven to 375 F. Grease baking sheet(s).
b797421b-b711-4e19-b013-cf4eda0a4e8d In a saucepan, combine figs and water and place over medium heat. Cook for about 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until mixture is a thick paste. Set aside to cool.
b797421b-b711-4e19-b013-cf4eda0a4e8d In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream shortening, butter, and sugars until light and fluffy. Add the egg and vanilla; beat until smooth and well blended.
b797421b-b711-4e19-b013-cf4eda0a4e8d In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder, and salt; whisk to blend thoroughly.
b797421b-b711-4e19-b013-cf4eda0a4e8d Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture and stir to combine. Stir in the fig mixture until well mixed.
b797421b-b711-4e19-b013-cf4eda0a4e8d Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheets. Bake for 11 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
b797421b-b711-4e19-b013-cf4eda0a4e8d Cool completely before storing in a tightly covered container.
b797421b-b711-4e19-b013-cf4eda0a4e8d Serve and enjoy!
ad55f68c-8d1e-4d43-851d-f2a3b580e6e9 Heat the oven to 325 F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
ad55f68c-8d1e-4d43-851d-f2a3b580e6e9 Cream together the butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Beat in the granulated sugar, salt, and vanilla.
ad55f68c-8d1e-4d43-851d-f2a3b580e6e9 Add egg and milk; beat well.
ad55f68c-8d1e-4d43-851d-f2a3b580e6e9 Stir in the flour and toasted coconut.
ad55f68c-8d1e-4d43-851d-f2a3b580e6e9 Using a teaspoon or small cookie scoop, drop the cookie batter onto the prepared baking sheet then press a pecan half or cherry half into the top of each one.
ad55f68c-8d1e-4d43-851d-f2a3b580e6e9 Bake for 18 to 20 minutes, or until you can see that the bottoms have browned.
ad55f68c-8d1e-4d43-851d-f2a3b580e6e9 Remove the cookies to a rack to cool completely.
2009c10f-9b9a-4713-a141-820ed4438f30 Chill mixing bowl and beaters for 15 minutes.
2009c10f-9b9a-4713-a141-820ed4438f30 Preheat oven to 250 F.
2009c10f-9b9a-4713-a141-820ed4438f30 Line with or parchment paper.
2009c10f-9b9a-4713-a141-820ed4438f30 Beat egg whites and cream of tartar on high speed until soft peaks form. Add sugar a tablespoon at a time until all sugar is incorporated and melted into the meringue. The meringue should be shiny and form stiff peaks.
2009c10f-9b9a-4713-a141-820ed4438f30 Fold in mint or peppermint extract, miniature chocolate chips, and optional food coloring.
2009c10f-9b9a-4713-a141-820ed4438f30 Drop by scant teaspoonfuls (or use a pastry bag) onto prepared cookie sheets, placing cookies about 1 inch apart. (You want these bite-sized to pop the whole cookie into your mouth. Larger ones are fine but make a crumbly mess when you bite into them.)
2009c10f-9b9a-4713-a141-820ed4438f30 Bake about 1 hour until stiff and dry. Turn off oven, but leave meringue cookies in the oven until cool to further dry out another 2 hours.
0815f228-fc9e-46a3-beea-47c907c1d35f Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 375 F.
0815f228-fc9e-46a3-beea-47c907c1d35f Sift flour with baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, and nutmeg.
0815f228-fc9e-46a3-beea-47c907c1d35f In a large mixing bowl, cream shortening and brown sugar; beat in egg until well-blended. Stir in half of flour and spice mixture, then stir in walnuts, apple, and raisins. Blend in milk, then remaining flour mixture.
0815f228-fc9e-46a3-beea-47c907c1d35f Drop by rounded tablespoons of dough, about 2 inches apart, onto greased baking sheets. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until set and lightly browned on the bottoms.
0815f228-fc9e-46a3-beea-47c907c1d35f While cookies are still hot, spread thinly with Vanilla Glaze, below.
0815f228-fc9e-46a3-beea-47c907c1d35f Serve and enjoy!
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Gather the ingredients and preheat the oven to 350 F/177° Celsius/Gas 4.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Beat the shortening, gradually adding sugar and combine until light and fluffy.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Add the egg, carrots, and vanilla to the creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt; stir into carrot mixture and mix well.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Stir in chopped nuts, if using.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Bake for about 20 minutes.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Transfer cookies to racks to cool.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Meanwhile, make the icing.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Combine juice and zest with the butter.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Stir in the confectioners' sugar until desired spreading consistency is reached.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Add more juice or sugar as needed.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Once cookies are cool, spread icing on top.
50725b39-9066-44a4-8da6-794f3d5295e5 Serve and enjoy!
20f9222f-249d-4acd-93fc-e30e2fd0c498 Heat the oven to 375 F (190 C/Gas 5. Line baking sheets with parchment paper, silicone baking mats, or grease them lightly.
20f9222f-249d-4acd-93fc-e30e2fd0c498 Cream butter with brown sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg, sour cream, and vanilla. Stir in the flour, baking soda, and salt until well blended. Fold in any additions, if using.
20f9222f-249d-4acd-93fc-e30e2fd0c498 Drop by tablespoon or small cookie scoop onto the prepared baking sheets, leaving about 2 inches between the cookies.
20f9222f-249d-4acd-93fc-e30e2fd0c498 Bake in the preheated oven for about 10 minutes, or until lightly browned. Remove the cookies to racks to cool completely.
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa Gather the ingredients.
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa To brown the butter, heat in a large saucepan over medium heat until golden brown, about 5 to 7 minutes (do not burn).
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa Remove the brown butter from the heat and place in a large heatproof bowl.
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa Stir in the brown sugar until well blended.
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa Whisk in the eggs, one at a time, until incorporated.
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa In a large bowl, combine the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa Gradually add the flour mixture to the butter mixture and mix well to combine.
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa Divide and shape the dough into two logs. Wrap each in waxed paper and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa When ready to bake, remove the waxed paper and brush the logs with the beaten egg white. Roll the logs in the demerara sugar or sanding sugar. Gently press the sugar into the log to make sure it sticks.
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa Slice each log into 3/8-inch rounds.
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa Transfer the slices to parchment-lined baking sheets. Place 2 inches apart to allow room for spreading. Bake at 350 degrees F just until set, 8-10 minutes.
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa Cool for 1 minute on the baking sheet before removing to wire racks.
d02351dd-ab1c-4d42-9102-b1218403b9aa Enjoy!
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Put the flour, sugar, and salt in a large mixing bowl and mix with an electric mixer on low speed until blended.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Cut the butter into small pieces and add to the mixer a little at a time. Increase the speed to medium and continue beating until the mixture clumps.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Add the egg yolks and vanilla and continue beating on medium-low speed, or until the mixture forms a soft dough.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Turn the cookie dough out onto a lightly floured surface and separate into two portions.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Shape into balls and flatten to make two disks.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for about 30 minutes.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Take a disk out of the refrigerator and place it between two sheets of waxed paper or parchment paper.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Roll out to about 1/8-inch thickness.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e If the dough is still too cold and cracks when rolled, let it stand at room temperature for a few extra minutes.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Cut the dough out into rounds, squares, or shapes, and arrange on the prepared baking sheets.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Repeat with the remaining dough disk.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Place the baking sheet in the refrigerator to chill.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Heat the oven to 375 F.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Place the pan of chilled cookies in the oven and bake for about 9 to 12 minutes, or just until the edges are light brown.
f2e3de6a-d756-473c-9fbf-7ec9bf2b555e Cool the cookies on a rack and decorate or fill as desired.
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 Preheat oven to 350 F / 176 C
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 Line baking sheets with parchment paper, Silpat mats or lightly grease with vegetable shortening.
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 Put all dry cookie ingredients in a food processor and pulse about 3 times to thoroughly blend. If you aren't using a food processor place the ingredients in a large mixing bowl and whisk until thoroughly combined.
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 Add pieces of butter and pulse about 10 times. If using an electric mixing beat on high for about 1 minute.
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 Add egg, 1 tablespoon of milk, lemon extract and peel and pulse about 5 times. The mixture should form a sticky, stiff dough. If the dough is too dry, gradually drizzle in more milk. You don't want the dough too sticky or it will be harder to roll out.
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 Wrap the dough in waxed paper and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight before rolling and cutting out cookies.
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 Lightly flour a large sheet of waxed paper with sweet rice flour and roll the dough to about 1/8-inch thickness. Try to roll the dough evenly so cookies will bake evenly.
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 Use your favorite cookie cutters and dip in rice flour for easier cutting.
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 If the dough softens too much while cutting the cookies, place the dough on the waxed paper on a baking sheet and freeze it for several minutes and then continue.
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 Bake in a preheated oven for about 12 minutes or just until the edges of the cookies turn golden brown.
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 While cookies are baking prepare sugar cookie icing by whisking all icing ingredients until smooth. The goal is to add just enough milk for a spreadable consistency. Add milk gradually. If the icing gets too thin, add more powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon at a time. To decorate with different colors, divide the icing between bowls and add a few drops of food coloring, one at a time until you get the color you want. Stir until smooth.
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 Cool cookies completely before decorating with prepared icing.
2f3b2d64-d805-4865-9984-8f1044f97d09 Store in an air-tight container or wrap tightly and freeze for a make-ahead holiday convenience.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e Gather ingredients and allow all to come to room temperature before beginning.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e Preheat oven to 375 F.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e Using the paddle attachment of a stand mixer, cream together butter, sugar, and salt on low speed.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e Add the egg, milk, and vanilla and mix until blended.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e In a separate bowl, sift together the flour and baking powder.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e Add the dry ingredients to wet ingredients and mix only until they're combined.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e Turn the dough onto a work surface. Using the heel of your hand, gently flatten the dough into a thick round, taking care not to overwork it.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e Wrap it in plastic and chill in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e Unwrap the chilled dough, transfer it to a lightly floured (or powdered-sugared) workbench or butcher block, and use a rolling pin to roll the dough out to about 1/8-inch thick.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e Cut out the cookies and place them on an ungreased baking sheet. Remember to cut them as close together as you can so you don't waste any dough.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e Using a pastry brush, wash the tops of the cookies with milk and sprinkle on some sugar, unless you'll be icing the cookies.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until the edges and bottoms of the cookies are barely beginning to turn golden brown.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e When the cookies are cool enough to handle but still warm, remove them from the pan and cool them on a wire rack. Let them cool completely before icing.
aa8359bd-b52c-4b9a-a34c-867078da944e If you're icing your cookies, ice them now and enjoy!
4aeb54cf-c786-477d-baff-525e5700d430 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the butter until creamy. Beat in sugar gradually. Add the beaten eggs, milk, and vanilla extract; stir to blend.
4aeb54cf-c786-477d-baff-525e5700d430 In another bowl, combine the all-purpose flour, baking powder, and salt; stir to blend thoroughly.
4aeb54cf-c786-477d-baff-525e5700d430 Gradually stir the flour mixture into the first mixture. Mix until well blended.
4aeb54cf-c786-477d-baff-525e5700d430 Cover the bowl and refrigerate the sugar cookie dough for 2 to 3 hours, or until well chilled.
4aeb54cf-c786-477d-baff-525e5700d430 Heat the oven to 375 F.
4aeb54cf-c786-477d-baff-525e5700d430 Line baking sheet(s) with parchment paper or grease them lightly.
4aeb54cf-c786-477d-baff-525e5700d430 Scoop up the cookie dough with a rounded teaspoon or small cookie scoop and shape it into 3/4-inch balls.
4aeb54cf-c786-477d-baff-525e5700d430 Place the cookie balls about 2 inches apart on the prepared baking sheet.
4aeb54cf-c786-477d-baff-525e5700d430 Flatten the cookie dough balls with the bottom of a glass that's been lightly greased with butter and dipped in granulated sugar. Dip the glass in sugar each time you press a cookie.
4aeb54cf-c786-477d-baff-525e5700d430 Bake the cookies in the preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until the edges are lightly browned.
4aeb54cf-c786-477d-baff-525e5700d430 Remove the sugar cookies to racks immediately to cool.
7146ab81-4d4e-4d6e-92bb-58405b921ca5 Gather the ingredients.
7146ab81-4d4e-4d6e-92bb-58405b921ca5 Preheat oven to 350 F.
7146ab81-4d4e-4d6e-92bb-58405b921ca5 Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or grease lightly.
7146ab81-4d4e-4d6e-92bb-58405b921ca5 Stir together flour, ground almonds, baking powder, and salt; set aside.
7146ab81-4d4e-4d6e-92bb-58405b921ca5 In a mixing bowl cream butter and sugar at medium speed of electric hand-held mixer. Beat in egg white and almond extract.
7146ab81-4d4e-4d6e-92bb-58405b921ca5 Stir flour and ground almond mixture into the creamed mixture. Cover with plastic wrap; chill for about 2 hours.
7146ab81-4d4e-4d6e-92bb-58405b921ca5 Shape dough into small balls, about 3/4 inch. Place balls on the prepared baking sheet 2 inches apart; flatten slightly with the bottom of a glass. Press an almond into the center of each cookie.
7146ab81-4d4e-4d6e-92bb-58405b921ca5 Bake in preheated oven for about 12 minutes, or until set but not browned.
7146ab81-4d4e-4d6e-92bb-58405b921ca5 Enjoy!
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Gather the ingredients.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the shortening and brown sugar until smooth; beat in molasses and egg until well blended.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 In another bowl, combine the flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, and salt; stir to blend the dry ingredients.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Add to the dry ingredients to the first mixture and stir until thoroughly blended.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Cover the bowl and refrigerate the cookie dough for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until thoroughly chilled.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Preheat oven to 375 F.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Grease cookie sheets or line them with parchment paper or silicone baking mats.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Add about 1/2 cup of granulated sugar to a small bowl. Have a bowl of water nearby, along with a flat-bottomed cup or glass.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Form dough into 1-inch balls.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Dip the top of the balls into the sugar, then place, sugar side up, on the baking sheet. Leave about 2 to 3 inches between balls.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Dip the flat-bottomed cup or glass lightly in the bowl of water. Gently press the top of each cookie with the wet bottom of the glass or cup to moisten lightly. There's no need to flatten the balls; the cookies will spread while baking.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Bake for 10 to 11 minutes, until cookies, are set.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Let cool for about 1 minute on the cookie sheet.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Remove the cookies to racks to cool completely.
83277bf2-9f48-4fd4-b6fa-06e0899445d7 Serve and enjoy!
c100807e-ae7b-43a2-a4f5-19bd171911fb In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, and salt. Set aside.
