c100807e-ae7b-43a2-a4f5-19bd171911fb In another bowl, use electric beaters or a stand mixer to cream together the sugar and butter.
c100807e-ae7b-43a2-a4f5-19bd171911fb Add the egg, orange juice, and vanilla, beating on medium speed until evenly mixed.
c100807e-ae7b-43a2-a4f5-19bd171911fb Add the flour mixture to the wet ingredients in 2 or 3 additions, beating between additions until the flour is well incorporated and the dough begins to pull into a ball. If the dough is very sticky, add more flour, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing between each addition.
afe1d541-886c-445a-a418-bf2124eeceee Preheat the oven to 400 F.
afe1d541-886c-445a-a418-bf2124eeceee Sift the flour, baking soda and salt together in a medium-sized bowl.
afe1d541-886c-445a-a418-bf2124eeceee In a separate large bowl, beat together the 2/3 cup sugar, vegan margarine, and lemon zest until smooth and fluffy. Add the tofu and lemon juice and whip until well mixed, then add the flour, baking soda, and salt.
afe1d541-886c-445a-a418-bf2124eeceee Add the flour mixture to the margarine mixture and stir until well combined.
afe1d541-886c-445a-a418-bf2124eeceee Form dough into one-inch balls and roll into the 1/4 cup sugar until well coated. Flatten slightly and bake for 8-10 minutes until lightly golden brown.
afe1d541-886c-445a-a418-bf2124eeceee Serve and enjoy.
719b904a-0c55-43ad-ad53-d32d209e9614 Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 375 F.
719b904a-0c55-43ad-ad53-d32d209e9614 Cream butter and sugar together until light; add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
719b904a-0c55-43ad-ad53-d32d209e9614 Dissolve soda in milk; add to the creamed mixture with the flour, salt and chopped walnuts or pecans. Blend well.
719b904a-0c55-43ad-ad53-d32d209e9614 Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto a lightly greased baking sheet then sprinkle granulated sugar over cookies and put a walnut or pecan half on each one.
719b904a-0c55-43ad-ad53-d32d209e9614 Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
719b904a-0c55-43ad-ad53-d32d209e9614 Serve and enjoy!
c5bcdcc8-4806-44dd-b4f7-417a0a38bbc6 Gather the ingredients.
c5bcdcc8-4806-44dd-b4f7-417a0a38bbc6 In a large bowl, beat the eggs slightly.
c5bcdcc8-4806-44dd-b4f7-417a0a38bbc6 Add the sugar and salt.
c5bcdcc8-4806-44dd-b4f7-417a0a38bbc6 Add the flour and milk alternately to the eggs, blending until smooth. Then, stir in vanilla.
c5bcdcc8-4806-44dd-b4f7-417a0a38bbc6 The batter should be about as thick as pancake batter. If it is not, add more flour, a tablespoon at a time. If it is too thick, add a teaspoon of milk at a time. The consistency of the batter is critical to the success of the recipe.
c5bcdcc8-4806-44dd-b4f7-417a0a38bbc6 Heat 3 inches of oil in a deep fryer to 365 F. Place a rosette iron in the hot oil for 60 seconds. There is no way to take the temperature of the iron; just know that it has to be hot.
c5bcdcc8-4806-44dd-b4f7-417a0a38bbc6 Dip the hot iron into the batter, making sure not to let the batter run over the top of the iron. If you do, the rosette will be impossible to remove. This takes some practice. It is best if you make a few rosettes a little more shallow than they should be just so you get the feel of the technique.
c5bcdcc8-4806-44dd-b4f7-417a0a38bbc6 Immerse the coated iron in the hot oil and fry for 25 to 30 seconds until light brown.
c5bcdcc8-4806-44dd-b4f7-417a0a38bbc6 Slip the rosettes off the hot iron using the tip of a knife, and place onto a paper towel.
c5bcdcc8-4806-44dd-b4f7-417a0a38bbc6 On a large plate, combine the sugar and cinnamon and mix well.
c5bcdcc8-4806-44dd-b4f7-417a0a38bbc6 Dip the rosettes in this mixture while they are still warm. You can also sprinkle the cookies with powdered sugar. Do not skip this step. The cookies are not really sweetened until they are coated in some kind of sugar.
c5bcdcc8-4806-44dd-b4f7-417a0a38bbc6 Serve and enjoy.
5bcc9c26-42c6-4ff7-8dba-e3f59fc455d7 Gather the ingredients.
5bcc9c26-42c6-4ff7-8dba-e3f59fc455d7 Using a mixer, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
5bcc9c26-42c6-4ff7-8dba-e3f59fc455d7 Add the egg and vanilla, mixing well.
5bcc9c26-42c6-4ff7-8dba-e3f59fc455d7 In another bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, and salt. Gradually stir the flour mixture into butter and sugar until dough forms. Don't worry if the dough seems a little crumbly at first; it will come together.
5bcc9c26-42c6-4ff7-8dba-e3f59fc455d7 Wrap dough in plastic and chill for two hours in the refrigerator.
5bcc9c26-42c6-4ff7-8dba-e3f59fc455d7 Heat the oven to 350 F. On a lightly floured surface, roll out dough to a 1/4-inch or 1/8-inch thickness.
5bcc9c26-42c6-4ff7-8dba-e3f59fc455d7 Use holiday cookie cutters dipped in flour to make cutouts. Gather scraps and re-roll until all the dough is used.
5bcc9c26-42c6-4ff7-8dba-e3f59fc455d7 Place cookies 1 inch apart on a parchment-lined cookie sheet. Bake for 9 to 10 minutes or until the edges are lightly browned. Wait 1 minute and then transfer cookies to a wire rack to cool completely.
5bcc9c26-42c6-4ff7-8dba-e3f59fc455d7 Serve and enjoy!
4587c782-6f70-4410-8c2f-1a6c62398214 Early in the day or the day before: In a large bowl cream the shortening and the sugar. Add the eggs, extract and milk. In a medium bowl mix the dry ingredients with a wire whisk. Add the dry ingredients to the large bowl. Mix with mixer until well combined. With hands, shape dough into a ball. Wrap with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
4587c782-6f70-4410-8c2f-1a6c62398214 Preheat oven to 400 F. Lightly grease cookie sheets. Roll** half or 1/3 dough at a time, keep the rest refrigerated. For crisp cookies, roll dough, paper thin. For softer cookies, roll 1/8 " to 1/4" thick.
4587c782-6f70-4410-8c2f-1a6c62398214 With floured cookie cutter, cut into shapes. Re-roll trimmings and cut. Place cookies 1/2 inch apart on cookie sheets. Decorate*** Bake 8 minutes or until very light brown. With pancake turner, remove cookies to racks; cool. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.
4b5c7909-85f7-4f13-a626-4ae82d57ff17 Preheat oven to 375 F.
4b5c7909-85f7-4f13-a626-4ae82d57ff17 Cream together the granulated sugar, powdered sugar, butter, and cooking oil. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
4b5c7909-85f7-4f13-a626-4ae82d57ff17 Add dry ingredients, (the next four ingredients) and mix to incorporate.
4b5c7909-85f7-4f13-a626-4ae82d57ff17 Roll dough into small balls about the size of a quarter with a heavy-bottomed crystal vase with a decorative bottom or other cookie press, dip in sugar to coat well.
4b5c7909-85f7-4f13-a626-4ae82d57ff17 Smash each ball of dough, so they are spread out and flat. Leaving an imprint and sugar. Bake in the oven at 375 F for 10 minutes, until the edges just start to turn slightly brown. Do not bake too long.
4b5c7909-85f7-4f13-a626-4ae82d57ff17 Cool sugar cookies on the baking sheet briefly then transfer to a wire rack to cool the rest of the way.
4b5c7909-85f7-4f13-a626-4ae82d57ff17 Serve and enjoy!
f4ede948-ba03-489d-b26b-c0c751433bf6 Gather the ingredients.
f4ede948-ba03-489d-b26b-c0c751433bf6 Combine the powdered sugar, milk, and corn syrup in a bowl.
f4ede948-ba03-489d-b26b-c0c751433bf6 Whisk all ingredients together until smooth. You want the icing to be thin enough to outline the cookies and spread easily, but thick enough so that the icing won't run off the sugar cookies. It should be thicker than Elmer's glue and thinner than paste. It takes some practice to achieve the ideal consistency, but these measurements should yield the right one.
f4ede948-ba03-489d-b26b-c0c751433bf6 Decorate the cookies and enjoy!
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Gather the ingredients.
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Melt 3/4 cup/170 grams of the butter in a pan and cook it until it starts to brown and takes on a good aroma. Do not let it burn.
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Pour the butter into a bowl to cool and refrigerate until firm.
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Cut the remaining 1 cup of cold butter into pieces and mix with the sugar, salt, and vanilla until light and fluffy.
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Mix in the flour to form a stiff dough.
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Form the dough into two rolls, 1 to 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Roll these in granulated sugar. If you have large crystal sugar it makes a very nice decoration.
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Wrap in plastic foil and refrigerate overnight.
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Remove the dough from the refrigerator and preheat the oven to 350 F for a half an hour.
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Cut the roll of dough with a sharp knife into 1/4-inch slices.
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Place the cookie dough on a baking sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes, until cookies are set and slightly browned.
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Remove cookies from the oven and let cool completely. If they are still warm when you touch them, they could disintegrate (they are very tender).
cb3fb8cd-f062-4eab-bd92-815dfba4e176 Enjoy!
8b935b86-4030-4921-bcc6-87e60a124c91 Gather the ingredients.
8b935b86-4030-4921-bcc6-87e60a124c91 In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt until they are evenly mixed. Set this dry mixture aside.
8b935b86-4030-4921-bcc6-87e60a124c91 Transfer the melted butter into a smaller bowl and add the cocoa powder. Stir together until they are combined and no lumps remain. In a measuring cup or bowl, mix the vanilla extract with the eggs, then whisk them into the cocoa-butter mixture.
8b935b86-4030-4921-bcc6-87e60a124c91 Add this wet mixture to the dry flour mixture and mix thoroughly by hand with a rubber spatula. It might seem as if you need more liquid, but do not add any. Just keep folding and pressing until the mixture comes together. It will eventually reach the consistency of stiff brownie batter.
8b935b86-4030-4921-bcc6-87e60a124c91 Fold in the chocolate chips. Refrigerate the dough for 30 minutes to firm it up.
8b935b86-4030-4921-bcc6-87e60a124c91 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line two baking sheets with Silpat baking liners or parchment paper. (Alternatively, you can lightly grease them.)
8b935b86-4030-4921-bcc6-87e60a124c91 Pour confectioners' sugar into a small bowl. Scoop the dough by teaspoons, roll into balls, and drop the balls into the powdered sugar, rolling them around to cover them completely. Place the sugared dough balls on prepared baking sheets 1 1/2 inches apart.
8b935b86-4030-4921-bcc6-87e60a124c91 Bake the cookies for 12 to 15 minutes. The cookies will spread, puff up a bit, and form cracks. The longer you cook them, the more crispy they will become.
8b935b86-4030-4921-bcc6-87e60a124c91 Let the cookies cool for 10 minutes on the cookie sheets before using a spatula to remove to racks and cool completely. Store in a covered container.
8b935b86-4030-4921-bcc6-87e60a124c91 Enjoy!
bbd786d2-3133-4d1c-bf8e-a85ed7a8233f Gather the ingredients.
bbd786d2-3133-4d1c-bf8e-a85ed7a8233f Preheat oven to 375 F.
bbd786d2-3133-4d1c-bf8e-a85ed7a8233f Place sugar cookie dough on a piece of parchment paper. Place a sheet of waxed paper or plastic wrap over the sugar cookie dough (this is to keep the dough from sticking to the rolling pin and to make it easier to transfer to a baking sheet). Roll dough out to a circle about 12 inches wide and 1/4-inch thick. Trim the edges if you need to.
bbd786d2-3133-4d1c-bf8e-a85ed7a8233f Remove the waxed paper or plastic wrap and, keeping the dough on the parchment paper, transfer it to a pizza pan or baking sheet.
bbd786d2-3133-4d1c-bf8e-a85ed7a8233f Bake 12 to 14 minutes, or until the sugar cookie dough is golden brown.
bbd786d2-3133-4d1c-bf8e-a85ed7a8233f Let it cool completely, about 1 hour.
bbd786d2-3133-4d1c-bf8e-a85ed7a8233f With an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese and granulated sugar until smooth.
bbd786d2-3133-4d1c-bf8e-a85ed7a8233f Spread it on the cooled sugar cookie dough, leaving a 1/4-inch border all the way around.
bbd786d2-3133-4d1c-bf8e-a85ed7a8233f Top with the strawberry slices, fresh raspberries and banana slices in a decorative pattern.
bbd786d2-3133-4d1c-bf8e-a85ed7a8233f Dust with powdered sugar.
bbd786d2-3133-4d1c-bf8e-a85ed7a8233f Serve immediately.
0e4b04dc-a05e-42a1-a335-c7d3189c6548 Gather the ingredients.
0e4b04dc-a05e-42a1-a335-c7d3189c6548 Place rack in center of oven and heat to 400 degrees. In a large bowl, cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla. In a separate bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, and salt. Add to butter-sugar in three additions, mixing after each addition.
0e4b04dc-a05e-42a1-a335-c7d3189c6548 If pressing into a cookie pan mold, do not chill the dough. Coat cookie pan mold with cooking spray and press dough half way up the cavities of the pan. If using the Blossom Pops Cookie Pan, place 2.5 ounces in each cavity, and fill the cavities three times for a total of 12 cookies. (My advice is to attach the lollipop sticks to the back of the cookie with royal icing AFTER they are baked. When they are baked into the cookies, the end of the sticks tends to burn.) Bake 10-12 minutes or until lightly browned.
0e4b04dc-a05e-42a1-a335-c7d3189c6548 If rolling and cutting out cookies with this recipe, chill the dough at least 1 hour. Roll between lightly floured sheets of parchment ​paper, cut out shapes leaving at least 1 1/2 inches between each cookie, and bake as above. Cool cookies and decorate.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Gather the ingredients.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Add the softened butter, sugar, orange peel, and vanilla extract to the bowl of a stand mixer. You can also use a regular medium-sized bowl and a hand mixer. Blend until the ingredients are creamed together.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Add the egg and beat until light and fluffy.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Add the milk to the mixture and blend again. Scrape down the sides of the bowl as needed.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Sift together the dry ingredients and gradually add them to the creamed mixture. After the dough is combined, divide it in half, wrap in plastic wrap and chill for at least one hour.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Preheat the oven to 375 F.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Place the dough on a lightly floured surface and roll out to about 1/8-inch thick.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Cut out the dough using the shamrock cookie cutter. If you are making the coins, we recommend using a small round cookie cutter. Add the cookies to a greased or parchment-lined cookie sheet.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Bake for about 6 to 8 minutes or until set. Keep a careful eye on them while baking so they do not get over-baked. You don't want them to brown.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Roll out dough scraps into another sheet and repeat cutting out the shapes.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Allow the cookies to cool slightly on the cookie sheets and then transfer them to a cooling rack to finish cooling.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b While the cookies are cooling, prepare the royal icing. Beat together the powdered sugar, meringue powder, and milk until completely combined. Separate the icing into three bowls.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b In one bowl, add 2 tablespoons of powdered sugar. This will be the icing for edging the cookies. Place the icing in a piping bag with a small hole attachment.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b In the second bowl add the green food coloring and mix until completely combined. Place the icing in a piping bag with a larger hole opening attachment.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b In the third bowl add yellow food coloring. Add the icing to a third piping bag with a smaller opening.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Edge all of the cookies with the white icing. Flood each cookie with the green icing, using a toothpick to help spread the icing to the edges. Flood the coins with the yellow icing.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b Allow the cookies to completely dry -- it should take 1 to 2 hours. Use the edging icing to add designs to the tops of the cookies and to attach edible pearls and sprinkles to the cookies.
898a809e-f033-4599-8088-a8d867ca3f9b You can also thicken the rest of the green and yellow food coloring with more powdered sugar and use that icing to decorate the cookies as well. Allow them to dry and then serve!
b6ce8389-8367-43dd-981d-35f966b905dc Heat the oven to 400 F.
b6ce8389-8367-43dd-981d-35f966b905dc Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or a silicone mat, or grease the pan.
b6ce8389-8367-43dd-981d-35f966b905dc In a large bowl, combine the all-purpose flour, baking soda, and salt. Whisk or stir to blend the dry ingredients thoroughly.
b6ce8389-8367-43dd-981d-35f966b905dc In a mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar, egg, and vanilla with an electric mixer. Beat for 2 minutes.
b6ce8389-8367-43dd-981d-35f966b905dc Add the sour cream and half of the sifted dry ingredients; beat the mixture for about 1 minute.
b6ce8389-8367-43dd-981d-35f966b905dc Stir in remaining dry ingredients with a wooden spoon or the paddle attachment of the stand mixer on low speed.
b6ce8389-8367-43dd-981d-35f966b905dc Divide dough in half and roll each portion out on a lightly floured surface to about 1/4-inch thick. Cut out rounds, squares, or shapes with floured cookie cutters.
b6ce8389-8367-43dd-981d-35f966b905dc Place cookies on the prepared baking sheet; bake in the preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
ad8e4424-bf6c-467c-9710-8f2482310f04 Gather the ingredients.
ad8e4424-bf6c-467c-9710-8f2482310f04 Heat the oven to 325 F. Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper.
ad8e4424-bf6c-467c-9710-8f2482310f04 Stir the flour, salt, and finely chopped pecans together in a bowl; set aside.
ad8e4424-bf6c-467c-9710-8f2482310f04 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the butter and brown sugar together until light. Beat in vanilla.
ad8e4424-bf6c-467c-9710-8f2482310f04 Stir in the flour mixture, kneading the dough gently with your hands to bring it together, if necessary.
ad8e4424-bf6c-467c-9710-8f2482310f04 Press or gently roll out on a lightly floured surface; cut into circles or squares about 1/4-inch thick. If desired, sprinkle the cookies with vanilla sugar or coarse sugar.
ad8e4424-bf6c-467c-9710-8f2482310f04 Bake in the preheated oven for about 20 minutes. Time will vary with thickness, so check them after 12 to 15 minutes if they're a little thinner. They should be just beginning to brown around the edges.
ad8e4424-bf6c-467c-9710-8f2482310f04 Transfer the cookies to a rack to cool completely.
ad8e4424-bf6c-467c-9710-8f2482310f04 Enjoy the cookies plain or drizzle them with melted chocolate.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b Gather the ingredients.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b Stir together the sour cream and baking soda to mix thoroughly.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream together the sugars with butter and shortening.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b Beat in the eggs and molasses.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b Add spices, 5 1/4 cups of the flour, and the sour cream mixture, stirring until thoroughly mixed. If necessary, add extra flour.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b Cover the bowl and chill the cookie dough for about 1 hour.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line baking sheets with parchment paper, silicone mats, or leave them ungreased.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b Remove the dough from the refrigerator. Knead a portion of the dough a bit to bring it to a good rolling temperature that won't crack as you shape it.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b Roll the dough out on a floured surface and cut about 1/4-inch thick with a cookie cutter, thinner if you'd like crisper cookies. Use round cutters or use shapes.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b Arrange the cookies on the prepared baking sheets.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b Sprinkle the cookies with some granulated sugar or cinnamon sugar.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b Bake for about 8 to 10 minutes.
e4b46fab-f5ed-45d3-aea0-610f6258da7b Serve and enjoy!
08d8e648-e467-4311-b1d5-966a7ccd1d37 Preheat oven to 425 F.
08d8e648-e467-4311-b1d5-966a7ccd1d37 Stir together first flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt in a large bowl.
08d8e648-e467-4311-b1d5-966a7ccd1d37 Cut in butter with a pastry blender until crumbly. Stir in pecans.
08d8e648-e467-4311-b1d5-966a7ccd1d37 Whisk together egg, 1 cup cream, and vanilla; add to dry ingredients, stirring with a fork just until mixture forms a shaggy dough.
08d8e648-e467-4311-b1d5-966a7ccd1d37 Scoop dough onto parchment paper-lined baking sheets using a 1/3-cup measuring cup.
08d8e648-e467-4311-b1d5-966a7ccd1d37 Brush tops with 2 tablespoons cream.
08d8e648-e467-4311-b1d5-966a7ccd1d37 Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
08d8e648-e467-4311-b1d5-966a7ccd1d37 Bake at 425 F. for 18 minutes or until browned. Serve warm.
c4415f9a-4e30-4ff4-ad83-6a19f64f00e0 Gather the ingredients.
c4415f9a-4e30-4ff4-ad83-6a19f64f00e0 In a medium-sized mixing bowl, combine flour, baking soda, ground ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves. Set aside.
c4415f9a-4e30-4ff4-ad83-6a19f64f00e0 In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and brown sugar until fluffy, or about 4 minutes, with a hand mixer or standing mixer with a paddle attachment. Add molasses and beat well for about 2 minutes. Add in egg and beat until well combined.
c4415f9a-4e30-4ff4-ad83-6a19f64f00e0 One spoonful at a time, add the dry mixture into the creamed butter, beating until the mixture just holds together in a ball. Divide the dough in three and wrap each section in plastic wrap. Chill in the refrigerator for one hour.
c4415f9a-4e30-4ff4-ad83-6a19f64f00e0 Preheat oven to 350 F.
c4415f9a-4e30-4ff4-ad83-6a19f64f00e0 Line two large baking sheets with parchment paper and set aside.
c4415f9a-4e30-4ff4-ad83-6a19f64f00e0 Once the dough is chilled, lightly flour a countertop or work surface. Working with one piece of dough at a time, roll it out until about 1/4 inch in thickness.
c4415f9a-4e30-4ff4-ad83-6a19f64f00e0 Using a cookie cutter dipped in flour, cut out individual people-shaped cookies and place on prepared sheets. Once you've cut out all of the cookies, place sheets in the freezer for 15 minutes.
c4415f9a-4e30-4ff4-ad83-6a19f64f00e0 Working in batches, bake cookies for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned. After removing the pans from the oven, allow cookies to remain on pans for about 2 minutes before placing on a cooling rack to finish cooling.
c4415f9a-4e30-4ff4-ad83-6a19f64f00e0 Enjoy!
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 Gather the ingredients.
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 In a large bowl or stand mixer, beat the egg whites until soft peaks form.
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 Add the confectioners' sugar 1/2 cup at a time, beating for 1 minute between each addition. Continue beating for 5 minutes after the last addition. The mixture should be very stiff, like the icing used to hold a gingerbread house together.
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 Remove 1/2 cup of this meringue mixture and set aside for icing.
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 Fold the raw almond meal and cinnamon into the larger portion of meringue. Add the Kirschwasser, if you are using it, and incorporate.
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 Chill the dough for about 1 hour.
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 Using ample confectioners' sugar on your baking board or clean countertop, pat the dough into a square and roll out to 1/2-inch thick (or 1 centimeter).
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 Cut out stars with a cookie cutter that has been dusted with confectioners' sugar. Dust the cookie cutter between each cut.
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 Place stars on a nonstick cookie sheet or a cookie sheet lined with parchment paper.
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 Brush or spread the reserved meringue icing on each star, working it out to all the points.
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 Let the stars dry overnight (about 24 hours, if you can). An oven is a good place if you don't forget they are there and heat for something else.
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 The next day, heat the oven to 325 F. Bake each tray for 10 to 15 minutes. This is to dry out the cookies a little more and bake the egg whites. Try to remove the cookies before the icing turns brown, although a little brown tint can look nice.
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 Remove the cookies from the baking sheet and let them cool completely on a wire rack before storing in a covered container in a dry place at room temperature.
56f9b8c0-7731-4bf6-b77e-f4cca3b4e725 Enjoy with tea or coffee, or place them in pretty, beribboned bags to be given away as a little gift.
6d31dd94-7225-4b14-8792-791c17f572e8 Cream shortening with sugar.
6d31dd94-7225-4b14-8792-791c17f572e8 Beat in egg, molasses, and boiling water.
6d31dd94-7225-4b14-8792-791c17f572e8 Stir in 1 cup flour, soda, and salt.
6d31dd94-7225-4b14-8792-791c17f572e8 Add spices and remaining 4 cups of flour, or as needed to make a stiff dough.
6d31dd94-7225-4b14-8792-791c17f572e8 Mix well, shape into a ball or loaf and wrap in waxed paper.
6d31dd94-7225-4b14-8792-791c17f572e8 Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
6d31dd94-7225-4b14-8792-791c17f572e8 Next day, roll out on floured surface and cut with cookie cutters.
6d31dd94-7225-4b14-8792-791c17f572e8 Place on greased and floured baking sheets.
6d31dd94-7225-4b14-8792-791c17f572e8 Bake at 375 F for 10 to 12 minutes.
8a7f2f24-20c5-4e30-af8b-d13220a338f7 Heat the oven to 350 F.
8a7f2f24-20c5-4e30-af8b-d13220a338f7 Line baking sheet(s) with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat.
8a7f2f24-20c5-4e30-af8b-d13220a338f7 Beat the butter and cream cheese in a mixing bowl until light. Add the sugar and beat at medium speed until well blended. Beat in the vanilla.
8a7f2f24-20c5-4e30-af8b-d13220a338f7 Add flour and soda; mix well.
8a7f2f24-20c5-4e30-af8b-d13220a338f7 Fold in the chopped pecans; mix well; chill dough for 30 minutes.
8a7f2f24-20c5-4e30-af8b-d13220a338f7 Shape the chilled dough into 1-inch balls and place on the prepared baking sheets. Make an indentation in the center of each ball with a thumb or finger. Fill each indentation with about 1 teaspoon of the preserves.
8a7f2f24-20c5-4e30-af8b-d13220a338f7 Bake for 8 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned. Remove to cooling racks to cool completely.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Gather the ingredients.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Preheat oven to 400 F.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Cream butter; gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed of an electric hand-held mixer.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Add eggs, blending well.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Dissolve soda in vinegar.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with vinegar mixture, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Stir in slivered almonds and almond extract.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Gently press a whole almond or almond half into center of each cookie.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Bake in preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Cool almond cookies on wire racks.
531067f2-d273-4668-afa7-2730785a3b00 Serve and enjoy!
54184d3b-e123-4b3f-af1a-da5cce1e7a34 Gather the ingredients.
54184d3b-e123-4b3f-af1a-da5cce1e7a34 Line baking sheets with wax paper.
54184d3b-e123-4b3f-af1a-da5cce1e7a34 Spread a thick layer of peanut butter on a cracker. Gently press another cracker onto the peanut butter layer to make a sandwich cookie. Repeat with the remaining crackers.
54184d3b-e123-4b3f-af1a-da5cce1e7a34 Melt the almond bark or candy melts in a microwave oven or in the top of a double boiler over simmering water as directed on the package.
54184d3b-e123-4b3f-af1a-da5cce1e7a34 Dip each sandwich cookie in the melted chocolate or almond bark. With a fork, lift the cookie out and shake gently to let the excess drip off.
54184d3b-e123-4b3f-af1a-da5cce1e7a34 Place the cookies on the wax paper-lined pan.
54184d3b-e123-4b3f-af1a-da5cce1e7a34 Before the chocolate sets, sprinkle the treats with colorful decorating sugar or candy sprinkles. Refrigerate until firm.
54184d3b-e123-4b3f-af1a-da5cce1e7a34 Serve and enjoy!
743a09c6-968f-4fc7-acfb-2e164256339c Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 375 F.
743a09c6-968f-4fc7-acfb-2e164256339c In a large bowl, beat the eggs and sugar until light and foamy, about 5 minutes.
743a09c6-968f-4fc7-acfb-2e164256339c Melt the lard or butter and let cool slightly. When cooled to room temperature, add it slowly to the egg-sugar mixture with the vanilla, mixing constantly.
743a09c6-968f-4fc7-acfb-2e164256339c Whisk together flour and baking powder; slowly add it to the egg mixture to create a firm dough.
743a09c6-968f-4fc7-acfb-2e164256339c Roll out the dough to 1/8-inch thick on parchment-lined baking pans and cut with a round cutter.
743a09c6-968f-4fc7-acfb-2e164256339c Cut out a hole in the center of half of the cookies and remove scraps.
743a09c6-968f-4fc7-acfb-2e164256339c Bake about 8 minutes. Remove from oven and cool completely.
743a09c6-968f-4fc7-acfb-2e164256339c Re-roll scraps and repeat.
743a09c6-968f-4fc7-acfb-2e164256339c Sprinkle the cookies with holes with confectioner's sugar. Spread cookies without holes with a jam of choice. Press together jam-filled cookie with holed-cookies to form a sandwich.
743a09c6-968f-4fc7-acfb-2e164256339c Serve and enjoy!
16588b62-395a-450c-a50f-7867d0415adc Place the condensed milk, butter, pinch of salt, and 2 egg yolks (reserve egg whites) in a small saucepan. Heat over medium-low heat, stirring, until mixture thickens and turns a light caramel color, about 15 minutes. Be very careful to stir constantly towards the end of the cooking time, as the mixture will stick to the pot and burn easily. Stir in vanilla and set aside to cool.
16588b62-395a-450c-a50f-7867d0415adc In a small bowl, mix the flour, baking powder and salt together. Preheat the oven to 325 degrees. Grease a large baking sheet with butter.
16588b62-395a-450c-a50f-7867d0415adc Place all 4 egg whites (reserve remaining 2 egg yolks) in the bowl of a standing mixer fitted with the whisk attachment. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Add sugar gradually while still beating, until stiff peaks form. Add egg yolks and beat to mix.
16588b62-395a-450c-a50f-7867d0415adc Carefully fold the dry ingredients into the egg whites, until just mixed. Place batter in a pastry bag fitted with a wide round tip. Pipe 2-inch diameter circles of batter, spaced about an inch apart, on the baking sheet. (or use a spoon to spread batter into a 2-inch circle).
16588b62-395a-450c-a50f-7867d0415adc Bake cookies for 6-8 minutes, until puffed and light golden brown. Remove from oven and trim edges from cookies with a 2-inch cookie cutter if desired. Transfer cookies to a cooling rack while they are still warm, or they will stick to the pan.
16588b62-395a-450c-a50f-7867d0415adc Spread the bottom of one cookie with 1-2 teaspoons of the filling. Top with another cookie. Repeat with remaining cookies.
16588b62-395a-450c-a50f-7867d0415adc In a small saucepan, bring 2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup water to a boil. Boil for 1-2 minutes, or until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat and let cool for several minutes. Use a fork to dip the cookies in the sugar glaze, then place them on a cooling rack to dry. Do not wrap cookies in paper until they are dry to the touch.
16588b62-395a-450c-a50f-7867d0415adc Store cookies in an airtight container, or wrap them in tissue paper to give as gifts.
d9666762-9c12-4248-8799-ab3d3433d4a3 Cookie dough: Beat all ingredients, except the flour, with an electric mixer for about 3 minutes, until well mixed. Add the flour, mixing in one cup at a time, until combined. Using a 2-ounce scoop, or 2 rounded tablespoons, drop the dough on to an un-greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350 F, for 10-12 minutes. Cool completely on wire rack.
d9666762-9c12-4248-8799-ab3d3433d4a3 Filling: Beat all the ingredients with an electric mixer on low until combined and then on high for about 2-3 minutes until light and fluffy.
d9666762-9c12-4248-8799-ab3d3433d4a3 Once the cookie halves have cooled, frost half of them and top with the other half to create the sandwiches. Wrap individual the whoopie pies in plastic wrap to keep.
5eacac1e-fd17-43fe-8118-a1841dc7c021 Preheat oven to 350 F.
5eacac1e-fd17-43fe-8118-a1841dc7c021 Place the cornstarch, flour, baking powder, and salt in a bowl and mix briefly.
5eacac1e-fd17-43fe-8118-a1841dc7c021 Cut the butter into small pieces and add to the flour mixture, blending with your fingers until the mixture is smooth.
5eacac1e-fd17-43fe-8118-a1841dc7c021 Add the powdered sugar, vanilla, and Pisco, and mix with your hands until the dough is homogeneous and smooth (add another tablespoon or two of Pisco if the dough is too crumbly to form a ball). Let the dough rest in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.
5eacac1e-fd17-43fe-8118-a1841dc7c021 Roll out dough to 3/8" thickness, and cut into 2-inch circles.
5eacac1e-fd17-43fe-8118-a1841dc7c021 Place cookies on baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
5eacac1e-fd17-43fe-8118-a1841dc7c021 Bake cookies for 10 to 15 minutes, until they are barely golden brown. Let cookies cool 5 minutes, then transfer to rack to cool completely.
5eacac1e-fd17-43fe-8118-a1841dc7c021 To fill the cookies, spread one cookie with dulce de leche and top with a second cookie. Roll the edges in the coconut.
5eacac1e-fd17-43fe-8118-a1841dc7c021 Store in an airtight container.
18e6159f-dea7-4a8f-b342-00dafba43693 Gather the ingredients.
18e6159f-dea7-4a8f-b342-00dafba43693 Heat the oven to 350 F.
18e6159f-dea7-4a8f-b342-00dafba43693 Line a large baking sheet with foil or parchment paper. Break the whole graham crackers along the scored line so you have 48 pieces. Place 24 on the prepared baking sheet.
18e6159f-dea7-4a8f-b342-00dafba43693 Put 1 square of chocolate on each cracker.
18e6159f-dea7-4a8f-b342-00dafba43693 Place a standard-sized marshmallow on each piece of chocolate.
18e6159f-dea7-4a8f-b342-00dafba43693 Put the pan in the heated oven for about 4 to 6 minutes, or just long enough to melt the marshmallow and soften the chocolate.
18e6159f-dea7-4a8f-b342-00dafba43693 Remove the pan from the oven and place the other half of graham cracker on top pushing down slightly so it adheres. Serve while still warm and gooey.
18e6159f-dea7-4a8f-b342-00dafba43693 Enjoy!
0e22ff4e-2376-4300-bee0-dbf23e353676 In a medium bowl, beat butter with one cup powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
0e22ff4e-2376-4300-bee0-dbf23e353676 Gradually add remaining powdered sugar alternately with the cream until frosting is fluffy and desired consistency.
0e22ff4e-2376-4300-bee0-dbf23e353676 Beat in the vanilla and salt.
0e22ff4e-2376-4300-bee0-dbf23e353676 If you're using peanut butter, add it now. Or divide the frosting in half and make half peanut butter and half vanilla.
0e22ff4e-2376-4300-bee0-dbf23e353676 Spread a generous portion of the frosting on one graham cracker, top with another, and squeeze gently.
0e22ff4e-2376-4300-bee0-dbf23e353676 Eat immediately or cover and let stand a few hours.
c13c4b62-bbfa-46f5-bda7-d9dada8bd889 With electric mixer at high speed, cream butter, sugar, and vanilla until light. Stir in beaten egg; blend well.
c13c4b62-bbfa-46f5-bda7-d9dada8bd889 Sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt; stir into creamed mixture. Fold in the chopped pecans. Shape into a roll about 2 inches in diameter; wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
c13c4b62-bbfa-46f5-bda7-d9dada8bd889 Heat the oven to 350 F.
c13c4b62-bbfa-46f5-bda7-d9dada8bd889 Cut roll into thin slices about 1/8-inch thick and place on ungreased baking sheet.
c13c4b62-bbfa-46f5-bda7-d9dada8bd889 Bake in the preheated oven for about 8 to 10 minutes.
06982b3c-ebf2-40a6-a161-36419278d374 Gather the ingredients.
06982b3c-ebf2-40a6-a161-36419278d374 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the shortening and butter together until creamy Add the granulated and brown sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
06982b3c-ebf2-40a6-a161-36419278d374 Add peanut butter and eggs to the creamed mixture; blend well.
06982b3c-ebf2-40a6-a161-36419278d374 Sift together the flour and baking soda; stir into creamed mixture.
06982b3c-ebf2-40a6-a161-36419278d374 Shape the cookie dough into 2 rolls about 2 inches in diameter. Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
06982b3c-ebf2-40a6-a161-36419278d374 Heat the oven to 350 F. Line baking sheets with parchment paper or leave them ungreased.
06982b3c-ebf2-40a6-a161-36419278d374 Slice the chilled rolls of dough into rounds about 1/4-inch thick; arrange the cookies on the prepared baking sheets.
06982b3c-ebf2-40a6-a161-36419278d374 Bake the cookies in the preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes and then remove them to a rack to cool completely.
06982b3c-ebf2-40a6-a161-36419278d374 Store the cooled cookies in an airtight container.
06982b3c-ebf2-40a6-a161-36419278d374 Enjoy these peanut butter cookies with milk for a quick snack or dessert. They're perfect for lunch boxes, too!
b922876e-1a4b-47ad-a81f-d9b36b5bc205 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, combine the shortening, butter, and sugar. Beat until light and fluffy.
b922876e-1a4b-47ad-a81f-d9b36b5bc205 Beat in vanilla and egg, beating until well blended.
b922876e-1a4b-47ad-a81f-d9b36b5bc205 Sift flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
b922876e-1a4b-47ad-a81f-d9b36b5bc205 Stir in dates and walnuts. Shape dough into two 2-inch rolls; wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
b922876e-1a4b-47ad-a81f-d9b36b5bc205 Slice chilled cookie dough into 1/8 inch slices; bake on greased baking sheets at 375 F for 8 to 10 minutes.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, and salt. Set aside.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add the lightly beaten egg and vanilla; beat thoroughly.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 Add the flour mixture to the creamed mixture and beat until well blended.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 Divide the dough into three parts (about 10 ounces each if you're weighing the dough) and put them in separate bowls.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 To one portion, beat in the chopped cherries. If more color is desired, beat in a small amount of food coloring.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 To the second portion, add 1/4 cup of chopped pecans.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 To the third portion, beat in the melted chocolate and another 1/4 cup of chopped pecans, if desired.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 Line a small loaf pan (8 1/2-by-4 1/2) with waxed paper or parchment; pack the chocolate dough evenly into the bottom of the loaf pan. Over the chocolate pecan dough, pack the plain pecan dough and then top it with the cherry dough. Or layer as desired.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 Cover the pan with waxed paper or plastic wrap and place it in the refrigerator for about 3 hours, or until thoroughly chilled.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 Heat the oven to 375 F.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 Grease baking sheets or line with parchment paper or silicone baking mats.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 Turn the chilled dough out of the pan and remove the paper.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 Slice the loaf of dough thinly and place the rectangular cookies on the prepared baking sheet about 1 inch apart.
d03ed3f8-8740-4f7e-b3a7-a1afe49a75e6 Bake in the preheated oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until the edges begin to brown.
0432aadd-0cc3-4a79-8c7b-07df5bbc589d Gather the ingredients.
0432aadd-0cc3-4a79-8c7b-07df5bbc589d In a bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, and salt. Whisk to blend thoroughly and set aside.
0432aadd-0cc3-4a79-8c7b-07df5bbc589d In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream 1 cup of the granulated sugar with the butter until light and fluffy. Beat in the egg, lemon juice, and lemon zest.
0432aadd-0cc3-4a79-8c7b-07df5bbc589d Gradually blend in the flour mixture into the creamed mixture.
0432aadd-0cc3-4a79-8c7b-07df5bbc589d Shape the dough into two rolls about 2 inches wide and 7 inches long. Wrap the rolls in waxed paper or plastic wrap and refrigerate the dough until firm, about 1 to 2 hours.
0432aadd-0cc3-4a79-8c7b-07df5bbc589d Preheat the oven to 375 F.
0432aadd-0cc3-4a79-8c7b-07df5bbc589d Line cookie sheets with parchment paper or spray with nonstick cooking spray.
0432aadd-0cc3-4a79-8c7b-07df5bbc589d Unwrap the cookie dough and cut into uniform slices about 1/4-inch thick.
0432aadd-0cc3-4a79-8c7b-07df5bbc589d Sprinkle slices lightly with the remaining sugar and place on the prepared baking sheets.
0432aadd-0cc3-4a79-8c7b-07df5bbc589d Bake in the preheated oven until lightly browned around the edges, about 12 minutes.
0432aadd-0cc3-4a79-8c7b-07df5bbc589d Cool the cookies on a rack and store in an airtight container.
5c4bba8d-cbff-40cd-95ef-baa66580d1b8 Melt butter in a large saucepan over low heat. Stir in the brown sugar and molasses until the sugar is dissolved and the mixture is well combined. Remove from heat.
5c4bba8d-cbff-40cd-95ef-baa66580d1b8 Let the mixture cool 5 minutes, then transfer to a large mixing bowl. Beat in the egg.
5c4bba8d-cbff-40cd-95ef-baa66580d1b8 In a separate large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and pumpkin pie spice.
5c4bba8d-cbff-40cd-95ef-baa66580d1b8 Mix the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients with a wooden spoon or sturdy spatula (not an electric mixer) until you can't see any flour anymore. The dry ingredients should be well incorporated but do not overmix or the gingerbread cookies will be tough.
5c4bba8d-cbff-40cd-95ef-baa66580d1b8 Divide the gingerbread cookie dough in half. Form each half into a disk. Wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate at least 1 hour or up to four days.
5c4bba8d-cbff-40cd-95ef-baa66580d1b8 When ready to bake, remove one disk of gingerbread cookie dough at a time from the refrigerator and let it come to room temperature.
5c4bba8d-cbff-40cd-95ef-baa66580d1b8 Heat the oven to 350 F. Line cookie sheets with Silpat mats or parchment paper.
5c4bba8d-cbff-40cd-95ef-baa66580d1b8 Place a little flour on the Silpat mats or parchment paper (alternatively, flour a board generously). Unwrap the dough, and place the plastic wrap on top of the dough as a buffer to keep the rolling pin from sticking to the dough.
5c4bba8d-cbff-40cd-95ef-baa66580d1b8 Roll the gingerbread cookie dough to a thickness of 1/4 to 1/2 inch. Cut into desired shapes. Arrange the gingerbread cookies on the baking sheets, so that they are 1 inch apart. Repeat with remaining disk of dough.
5c4bba8d-cbff-40cd-95ef-baa66580d1b8 Bake the gingerbread cookies 7 to 4 minutes or until just firm to the touch. The cooking time will depend on how thick you rolled the cookies.
5c4bba8d-cbff-40cd-95ef-baa66580d1b8 Remove the cookies from the oven, wait 2 minutes, and, using a flat spatula, transfer them to a wire rack to cool completely.
5c4bba8d-cbff-40cd-95ef-baa66580d1b8 Decorate with royal icing, colored sugars, sprinkles, or candy canes. Store for up to one week in a covered container with an optional slice of white bread to retain the moisture in the cookies.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Gather the ingredients.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Preheat to 350 F.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Mix together the flour, baking powder, and salt with a wire whisk.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Using an electric mixer or stand mixer with a paddle attachment, cream the sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Add eggs in one at a time.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Mix in the anise extract and ground seeds.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Gradually add in flour mixture until well combined.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Add and hand-stir almonds.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Divide dough in half. Shape into logs or any desired shape and place on sheet.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes and cool completely, about 25 minutes.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Slice logs diagonally. Discard parchment and place log slices cut-side down on the baking sheet. Bake for 12 minutes. Turn and bake for another 8 minutes or until just beginning to color.
cab81c92-9e7b-4ab9-bfea-38f3c992d175 Serve and enjoy with coffee or tea.
dd84cb30-1daf-49e7-a664-08320e5b959a Heat oven to 350F. Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper.
dd84cb30-1daf-49e7-a664-08320e5b959a In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, and salt, and set aside. In another large bowl or stand mixer fitted with the whisk attachment, beat the eggs until well blended. Increase the speed to high and beat in the sugar 2 tablespoons at a time until mixture is thick and foamy, about 4 to 5 minutes.
dd84cb30-1daf-49e7-a664-08320e5b959a Add oil and extract(s) to the eggs and beat briefly to blend. Replace whisk with the paddle attachment and, on lowest speed, beat in flour mixture and almonds just until mixture holds together. It will be soft, but shouldn't be too sticky. If necessary, add a few more tablespoons of flour.
dd84cb30-1daf-49e7-a664-08320e5b959a Divide dough in half. Dampen hands lightly and form each half into a 3-inch-by-12-inch log on the prepared baking sheet, spacing 4 inches apart. Bake about 45 minutes or until golden brown and firm to the touch. Remove from oven and let cool at least 10 minutes.
dd84cb30-1daf-49e7-a664-08320e5b959a Carefully place logs on a cutting board and cut diagonally with a serrated knife or a ham slicer into 1/2- to 3/4-inch slices.
dd84cb30-1daf-49e7-a664-08320e5b959a Place pieces cut side down on ungreased baking sheets. Bake 5 minutes. Turn pieces over and bake 5 minutes longer or until completely dry. Cool completely on wire racks. Store in an airtight container for up to 3 months or freeze.
ddd4bc15-d000-4502-9a7b-1c5895bc3878 Pre-heat oven to 350 F.
ddd4bc15-d000-4502-9a7b-1c5895bc3878 In a medium bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and chocolate chips.
ddd4bc15-d000-4502-9a7b-1c5895bc3878 Add eggs and vanilla, stirring until blended.
ddd4bc15-d000-4502-9a7b-1c5895bc3878 Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead 8 to 10 times.
ddd4bc15-d000-4502-9a7b-1c5895bc3878 Form dough into a log about 2-inches wide and 16-inches thick.
ddd4bc15-d000-4502-9a7b-1c5895bc3878 Place log onto​ a baking sheet coated with non-stick spray.
ddd4bc15-d000-4502-9a7b-1c5895bc3878 Bake 30 minutes; remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes.
ddd4bc15-d000-4502-9a7b-1c5895bc3878 Place log on cutting board and with a serrated knife, cut log diagonally into 1/2 inch slices, using a sawing motion.
ddd4bc15-d000-4502-9a7b-1c5895bc3878 Place slices cut side up, on ​a baking sheet.
ddd4bc15-d000-4502-9a7b-1c5895bc3878 Reduce heat to 325 F and bake for 10 minutes.
ddd4bc15-d000-4502-9a7b-1c5895bc3878 Turn slices over and bake an additional 10 to 12 minutes until golden. Centers will be slightly soft but will harden as they cool. Remove to wire rack to cool.
47acae59-e058-4dfa-a9b2-f2522e59266f Preheat oven to 325 F
47acae59-e058-4dfa-a9b2-f2522e59266f Butter an 8x8 inch baking dish
47acae59-e058-4dfa-a9b2-f2522e59266f Combine all dry ingredients except sugar in a medium mixing bowl and use a large whisk to mix thoroughly.
47acae59-e058-4dfa-a9b2-f2522e59266f In another mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar until blended.
47acae59-e058-4dfa-a9b2-f2522e59266f Add dry ingredients to eggs and sugar and mix until blended.
47acae59-e058-4dfa-a9b2-f2522e59266f Fold in toasted almonds and stir to combine.
47acae59-e058-4dfa-a9b2-f2522e59266f Pour into prepared baking dish and bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until just starting to turn golden brown. Cool for 5 minutes.
47acae59-e058-4dfa-a9b2-f2522e59266f Use a sharp knife to divide the biscotti into 4 equal pieces. Cut each piece into 6 even slices.
47acae59-e058-4dfa-a9b2-f2522e59266f Place biscotti slices on a baking sheet and bake an additional 15 minutes, or until crisp.
47acae59-e058-4dfa-a9b2-f2522e59266f Store in an airtight container.
bc9631cd-0b9f-4e86-b5dc-8dc89f84353b Gather the ingredients.
bc9631cd-0b9f-4e86-b5dc-8dc89f84353b In a large bowl, cut butter into the flour as for pie dough until it resembles small peas. Stir in sour cream, mixing well.
bc9631cd-0b9f-4e86-b5dc-8dc89f84353b Preheat oven to 350 F. Divide dough in half, wrap in plastic and refrigerate for 3 hours.
bc9631cd-0b9f-4e86-b5dc-8dc89f84353b Take one piece of dough out at a time. Roll on a lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
bc9631cd-0b9f-4e86-b5dc-8dc89f84353b Cut with a large round cookie cutter or coffee cup. Fill center with 2 teaspoons filling. Bring up all four sides and pinch to close. Repeat with remaining dough and filling.
bc9631cd-0b9f-4e86-b5dc-8dc89f84353b Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until the bottom of the cookie is just beginning to brown.
bc9631cd-0b9f-4e86-b5dc-8dc89f84353b Remove from pan with a metal spatula and cool on wire racks.
bc9631cd-0b9f-4e86-b5dc-8dc89f84353b Store in an airtight container. Dust with confectioners' sugar when ready to serve—not before because it will make the cookie soggy.
bc9631cd-0b9f-4e86-b5dc-8dc89f84353b Enjoy!
115e06ee-28a3-47cf-9f6a-c76bc90163ed First, place the softened butter or margarine in a large mixing bowl and whip with an electric mixer on the lowest setting until creamy.
115e06ee-28a3-47cf-9f6a-c76bc90163ed Add the flour. Wearing rubber gloves, work the flour into the butter with your fingers until combined. Add the powdered sugar, vanilla, baking powder, and semolina and continue working them in with your fingers until the dough has a smooth consistency. The warmth from your hands will help melt the butter and soften the mixture as you work.
115e06ee-28a3-47cf-9f6a-c76bc90163ed In the meantime, start the syrup. Add 4 cups of boiling water to a saucepan. Add the granulated sugar and the half lemon. Bring to a boil then gently simmer uncovered for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from the heat and let it cool down just a bit.
115e06ee-28a3-47cf-9f6a-c76bc90163ed Next, add the eggs to the dough mixture and knead them into the dough until smooth.
115e06ee-28a3-47cf-9f6a-c76bc90163ed With your hands, pinch off a piece of dough and roll it into a ball about the size of an apricot. Place it on an ungreased metal oven tray. Continue making even-sized balls and lining them up side by side, leaving some space in between.
115e06ee-28a3-47cf-9f6a-c76bc90163ed Gently press down on the top of each ball to flatten it slightly. Press an almond or a hazelnut into the center of each.
115e06ee-28a3-47cf-9f6a-c76bc90163ed Bake in a 160C or 320F oven for 20 to 25 minutes until the tops of your cookies are golden brown.
115e06ee-28a3-47cf-9f6a-c76bc90163ed Remove your tray from the oven and, while it is still hot, pour the warm syrup evenly over the top.
115e06ee-28a3-47cf-9f6a-c76bc90163ed Let the tray cool down to room temperature. As they cool, the cookies will absorb the syrup and get soft.
115e06ee-28a3-47cf-9f6a-c76bc90163ed When the şekerpare are cool, they are ready to serve. Serve two or three on a decorative plate and garnish them with a spoonful of Turkish clotted cream, called "kaymak" if you wish.
f6316f43-c265-4488-a9c9-df984bd8a8ff Cream the butter and granulated sugar in a stand mixer on high until it is light, fluffy and turning a pale color.
f6316f43-c265-4488-a9c9-df984bd8a8ff Add the vanilla extract and orange zest to the butter mixture. Turn the mixer to low speed and add the eggs, one at a time, scraping down the sides of the bowl with a spatula as needed. Do not rush this process or the mixture may curdle. Though this can be corrected with the addition of a little flour, it is best to avoid if you can.
f6316f43-c265-4488-a9c9-df984bd8a8ff Beat the mixture on medium-high for about 3 to 4 minutes, until the mixture has lightened in color and is very fluffy.
f6316f43-c265-4488-a9c9-df984bd8a8ff In a separate bowl, mix together the flour and baking powder. Very gently fold the flour and baking powder into the egg mixture using a spoon, not the stand mixer. Once the batter is smooth, cover it and transfer it to the refrigerator for 2 hours.
f6316f43-c265-4488-a9c9-df984bd8a8ff Preheat the oven to 375 F.
f6316f43-c265-4488-a9c9-df984bd8a8ff Generously grease 2 standard madeleine pans, do not skimp on this process as enough greasing now will prevent the cakes from sticking. Spoon the cold batter into the molds.
f6316f43-c265-4488-a9c9-df984bd8a8ff Bake them in the preheated oven for 10 to 13 minutes, until they are puffed and turn golden brown.
f6316f43-c265-4488-a9c9-df984bd8a8ff Invert the pans onto wire racks and give them a hard tap to remove the cookies from the molds. Leave them to cool but not cold. Serve them warm dusted with confectioners’ sugar for the best flavor.
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Gather the ingredients.
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Preheat the oven to 325 F. Line several baking sheets with parchment paper.
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Add the confectioner's sugar and almond meal to a food processor fixed with a metal blade. Run until a fine powder forms. Sift four times, discarding any tiny lumps or almond meal “pebbles” between sifting. Set aside.
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Using a stand mixer fixed with the whisk attachment, whip the room temperature egg whites on medium speed until foamy. Add the granulated sugar one tablespoon at a time. Once the mixture thickens and all of the sugar is added, stop the mixer.
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Add cream of tartar, scrape down the sides of the bowl, then turn the mixer back on, increasing the speed to high.
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Whip the mixture for about 5 to 6 minutes, or until a peak at the end of the whisk attachment holds its form. (You can test this by turning off the mixer and checking to see if the mixture at the tip of the whisk attachment doesn’t drip).
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Remove the bowl from the stand mixer and set it on a counter or table. Add a third of the almond meal-confectioner's sugar mixture and fold gently to combine. Add another third of the almond meal-confectioner's sugar mixture, then fold again.
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Once incorporated, add the final third as well as the gel food coloring. Fold one final time. The batter that forms after three rounds of folding should be firm with a glossy shine. Test the batter by lifting the spatula; if the batter drips very slowly from the spatula like lava, it’s ready. If not, continue to fold the batter for another 30 seconds. Be careful not to overmix.
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Affix a pastry bag with a #12 plain round tip. Fill the bag 3/4-full with batter. Pipe into 1.5-inch rounds on the lined baking sheets at least an inch apart. You want to pipe so that the bag is perpendicular to the baking sheet, not at an angle. After piping a circle of batter, flick your wrist quickly to the side so that a point doesn’t form at the top of the macaron. (If a tip does form, no worries, you can smooth it out with a small spatula later).
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Firmly tap the baking sheet on your work surface to get rid of any air bubbles potentially stuck in the batter. Let the prepared baking sheets sit at room temperature until a dry shell forms on the macarons. Test by touching the batter with your fingertip. If your fingertip doesn’t stick to the batter, the macarons are ready for the oven. The “resting” phase can take 20 minutes to 40 minutes, depending on the humidity in the room.
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Bake the macarons, one baking sheet at a time, in the lower third of the oven for 12 to 14 minutes, rotating the baking sheet halfway through. When done, the tops will be firm to the touch and the center won't jiggle like jelly.
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Remove the macarons from the oven and let cool for at least 10 minutes. Gently peel the macarons off the parchment paper and transfer to a wire rack. (If you try to do this while the macarons are still hot, they'll come apart). Repeat with the remaining macarons and allow them to cool completely before filling.
d1d87537-13ea-4f1e-9dfc-40ad96875e63 Arrange the macarons by two’s, top side down, making sure to match sizes best you can. Depending on the size of the macaron, squeeze a nickel to quarter size amount of filling onto the bottom of the macaron. Lay the second macaron on top, and very gently press together so that the filling expands but doesn’t come out the sides.
4b4139be-8a36-40ee-baaf-536c1f70c23e Gather the ingredients.
4b4139be-8a36-40ee-baaf-536c1f70c23e Write fortunes on pieces of paper that are 3 1/2 inches long and 1/2 inch wide.
4b4139be-8a36-40ee-baaf-536c1f70c23e Preheat oven to 300 F. Grease 2 9-X-13 inch baking sheets.
4b4139be-8a36-40ee-baaf-536c1f70c23e In a medium bowl, lightly beat the egg white, vanilla extract, almond extract, and vegetable oil until frothy, but not stiff.
4b4139be-8a36-40ee-baaf-536c1f70c23e Sift the flour, cornstarch, salt, and sugar in a separate bowl. Stir the water into the flour mixture.
4b4139be-8a36-40ee-baaf-536c1f70c23e Add the flour to the egg white mixture and stir until you have a smooth batter. The batter should not be runny but should drop easily off a wooden spoon.
4b4139be-8a36-40ee-baaf-536c1f70c23e Place level tablespoons of batter onto the cookie sheet, spacing them at least 3 inches apart. Gently tilt the baking sheet back and forth and from side to side so that each tablespoon of batter forms into a circle 4 inches in diameter.
4b4139be-8a36-40ee-baaf-536c1f70c23e Bake until the outer 1/2-inch of each cookie turns golden brown, and they are easy to remove from the baking sheet with a spatula (14 to 15 minutes).
4b4139be-8a36-40ee-baaf-536c1f70c23e Working quickly, remove the cookie with a spatula and flip it over in your hand.
4b4139be-8a36-40ee-baaf-536c1f70c23e Place a fortune in the middle of a cookie.
4b4139be-8a36-40ee-baaf-536c1f70c23e To form the fortune cookie shape, fold the cookie in half, then gently pull the edges downward over the rim of a glass, wooden spoon or the edge of a muffin tin. Place the finished cookie in the cup of the muffin tin so that it keeps its shape. Continue with the rest of the cookies.
4b4139be-8a36-40ee-baaf-536c1f70c23e Serve and enjoy!
e414795d-72a5-4a2c-a416-592802050a93 To make the dough: In a large bowl, cut butter into flour as for pie dough. Add eggs and lemon juice and mix just until dough comes together. Don't overwork.
e414795d-72a5-4a2c-a416-592802050a93 Cut dough into eighths, wrap in plastic, and refrigerate the dough overnight.
e414795d-72a5-4a2c-a416-592802050a93 To make the filling: In a small saucepan, bring water and sugar to a boil. Add zest and let simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat and cool. Combine cooled syrup with ground nuts until thoroughly mixed.
e414795d-72a5-4a2c-a416-592802050a93 To shape and bake: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Line sheet pans with parchment paper. If you've made walnut-size balls of dough, working with a few at a time and leaving the rest refrigerated, roll thinly and place 1 teaspoon filling at one end and roll up, curving slightly. If you've cut the dough into eighths, work with one at a time, leaving the rest refrigerated, and roll into a thin circle. Cut into wedges as for a pie. Place 1 teaspoon filling at the widest end of each wedge and roll to the point.
e414795d-72a5-4a2c-a416-592802050a93 Place the crescents seam-side down on the prepared pans. Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly golden. At this point, they can be rolled while still warm in confectioners' sugar or cooled completely on a wire rack and then dusted with confectioners' sugar. The choice is yours. The former method produces a slight glaze as the sugar melts on the hot cookies. In either case, cool completely before storing tightly covered. These cookies keep well.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Using a whisk and a large bowl, beat the eggs until light yellow, thickened and foamy.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Add the confectioners' sugar a spoonful at a time and beat for 10 minutes.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Dissolve the ammonium carbonate in the Kirschwasser. Add any clear liquid flavorings of your choice at this time.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Mix the liquids into the confectioners' sugar mixture and beat another 10 minutes.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Mix the flour in a spoonful at a time. The dough should be about as soft as sugar cookie dough before it is refrigerated. If it is too stiff, mix in a little more liquid.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Knead lightly into a smooth ball, wrap in plastic foil, and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Lightly dust a wooden board or work surface with sugar or cornstarch and, using about 1/4 of the dough, roll it to just under 1/2-inch thick. Keep the rest of the dough covered so it does not dry out. Use a springerle rolling pin or various cookie molds to imprint cookies. Place the mold over the area you want to be imprinted, and bear down hard on the dough.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Cut out the imprinted shapes using a knife, a small roller cutter, a biscuit cutter, or a cutter designed for your cookie mold.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Lay the cookies on a baking sheet or wooden board that has been lightly dusted with sugar or cornstarch. Let dry right side up for 24 to 48 hours.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Before baking, wet the bottom of the cookies by laying them on a clean, moist kitchen towel.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Sprinkle anise on a parchment-lined baking pan and set the cookies on top.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Bake at 300 F/150 C for 10 minutes, then lower the temperature to 280 F/140 C and bake for another 10 minutes, until the underside starts to gain color. Try not to let the tops brown.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Remove and cool. When cool, you can paint them with food coloring. In earlier times, they even used gold leaf to decorate some of these cookies.
ca26ea2f-f9e5-4b47-bf67-48ba6a6a43d9 Store the cookies in a covered container with a slice of apple to keep them moist, and enjoy.
5ecbe961-9587-4982-b561-1b91c705e71b Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 350 F.
5ecbe961-9587-4982-b561-1b91c705e71b In a large bowl or stand mixer, beat together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
5ecbe961-9587-4982-b561-1b91c705e71b Add eggs and vanilla and mix until completely incorporated.
5ecbe961-9587-4982-b561-1b91c705e71b Add the flour and mix into a smooth dough. It shouldn't need to be refrigerated before rolling unless your kitchen is very hot.
5ecbe961-9587-4982-b561-1b91c705e71b Roll dough between pieces of parchment paper to 1/8-inch thick or 3/16-inch thickness, if sandwiching cookies together.
5ecbe961-9587-4982-b561-1b91c705e71b Remove top piece of parchment paper and cut dough into various shapes. Since the dough doesn't expand much when baking, a mere 1/2-inch space between cookies will be fine. If at any time the dough is getting too soft, refrigerate it for a few minutes and then continue.
5ecbe961-9587-4982-b561-1b91c705e71b If making sandwiched cookies, cut an even number of plain cookies and an even number of cookies of the same shape that have had a small "window" cut out with a thimble or piping tip so the jam or filling will peek through.
5ecbe961-9587-4982-b561-1b91c705e71b Remove the scraps and, grabbing the parchment paper by opposite corners, place it on a sheet pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Do not let the cookies brown, they should remain light but still be baked through.
5ecbe961-9587-4982-b561-1b91c705e71b Cool completely. Repeat with remainder of dough. Excess dough can be wrapped and refrigerated.
5ecbe961-9587-4982-b561-1b91c705e71b If sandwiching cookies together, sprinkle confectioner's sugar over cookies with a "window." Spread jam or filling on "window-less" cookies. Place confectioners' sugar cookie on top of the jammed cookie.
5ecbe961-9587-4982-b561-1b91c705e71b Serve and enjoy!
2330789d-4673-48ff-b6b5-b84e9a2bd6bb Heat oven to 350 degrees. In a large bowl or stand mixer, cream 8 ounces room-temperature butter and 1/2 cup sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in 1 large room-temperature egg yolk and 1 teaspoon vanilla, mixing well. Add 1/4 cup ground almonds and 1 2/3 cups all-purpose flour, thoroughly incorporating.
2330789d-4673-48ff-b6b5-b84e9a2bd6bb Using walnut-size pieces of dough, shape into a crescent and place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake 20 minutes or until slightly brown on the edges.
2330789d-4673-48ff-b6b5-b84e9a2bd6bb While still hot, roll in confectioners' sugar. Re-roll in confectioners' sugar when cool and store tightly covered.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Place flour in a large bowl.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Add sesame oil and mix together with your hands. Rub the flour between your hands and fingers to combine.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd In another bowl, whisk honey, sake, and water together.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Add to flour mixture and knead gently with your hands to form a dough.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Wrap dough in plastic wrap and set aside for 30 minutes.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd After 30 minutes, on a floured surface, roll out dough to half an inch thick.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Cut dough into one-inch strips to make diamond or rectangle shapes. Or cut into a flower shape.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Put a small hole in the center of each cookie.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd To make syrup, put rice malt syrup, honey, and ginger in a saucepan over medium heat.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Bring to a simmer and then remove immediately from heat.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Pour into a rectangular dish or glass baking pan.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Bring a sturdy, flat-bottomed fryer or saucepan with oil, making sure the oil doesn't go higher than half the height of the pot.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Heat over medium heat until oil temperature is 212 F.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd In small batches, drop pastries in oil and fry, gently turning them until they puff and float (about 4 to 5 minutes).
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Now raise the heat of the oil to about 300 F and continue to fry until the Yakgwa turns a golden brown.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Remove Yakgwa from oil and place into the dish with ginger syrup.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd When all of them have been placed in the syrup, turn each one over once so they are coated.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Soak in the syrup for a few hours, and then remove with a slotted spoon onto another dish topped with parchment.
4050ee28-b778-4b54-9f44-7944711fc1bd Sprinkle with pine nuts and sesame seeds.
a21a61d1-b948-46c9-b028-0b782d022184 Gather the ingredients.
a21a61d1-b948-46c9-b028-0b782d022184 In a large saucepan, heat milk with Turkish delight until candy starts to melt and reduce in size. Remove from the heat.
a21a61d1-b948-46c9-b028-0b782d022184 To the saucepan, add 1/2 of the cocoa, 1/2 of the biscuits, 1/2 of the walnuts, and half of the rum. Mix thoroughly and set aside.
a21a61d1-b948-46c9-b028-0b782d022184 In a separate bowl, mix the softened butter with 5 tablespoons confectioners' sugar and 2 egg yolks.
a21a61d1-b948-46c9-b028-0b782d022184 Add this to the ingredients in the saucepan and mix thoroughly.
a21a61d1-b948-46c9-b028-0b782d022184 Add in the rest of the rum, cocoa, biscuits, walnuts, and the coarsely chopped sour cherries.
a21a61d1-b948-46c9-b028-0b782d022184 Whip the egg whites until they form stiff peaks.
a21a61d1-b948-46c9-b028-0b782d022184 Blend into the mixture.
a21a61d1-b948-46c9-b028-0b782d022184 Sprinkle remaining 1 tablespoon confectioners' sugar and shredded coconut on a large piece of plastic wrap. Put the dough in the middle and roll it up in the plastic wrap, forming it into the shape of a salami.
a21a61d1-b948-46c9-b028-0b782d022184 Wrap tightly and refrigerate 6 to 7 hours.
a21a61d1-b948-46c9-b028-0b782d022184 Remove plastic wrap and cut into 1/2-inch slices when ready to serve.
1765358b-a229-43be-9bdb-0ae4ba804ff7 Preheat an oven to 400 F and line a baking sheet with parchment paper and very lightly grease with a little butter.
1765358b-a229-43be-9bdb-0ae4ba804ff7 Combine the almonds, sugar, egg whites, and vanilla extract in a food processor and pulse the mixture until it has taken on the texture of a very coarse paste. Turn the food processor on high speed and blend the paste for 2 minutes, until it is very smooth and thick.
1765358b-a229-43be-9bdb-0ae4ba804ff7 Spoon the batter into a pastry bag fitted with a wide tip and pipe the batter into uniform, 1-inch mounds on the parchment-lined baking sheet. You can draw a template onto the parchment paper if you want the biscuits to be precise, however, home-made biscuits do not want to look like they are made from a machine.
1765358b-a229-43be-9bdb-0ae4ba804ff7 Allow the batter to rest, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
1765358b-a229-43be-9bdb-0ae4ba804ff7 Bake the macaroons for 12 minutes. Remove the hot macaroons to a wire rack and cool to room temperature and dust with the confectioners’ sugar before serving.
1765358b-a229-43be-9bdb-0ae4ba804ff7 The biscuits are best eaten as soon as possible if you have to store them place into an airtight box.
c6f6ed98-30d8-44b6-b6b8-71a9671da344 Gather the ingredients.
c6f6ed98-30d8-44b6-b6b8-71a9671da344 Dissolve baking soda in the brandy.
c6f6ed98-30d8-44b6-b6b8-71a9671da344 Whisk together the flour and baking powder.
c6f6ed98-30d8-44b6-b6b8-71a9671da344 Combine the oil, grape molasses, and sugar in a saucepan. Stir well and boil for several minutes until completely blended.
c6f6ed98-30d8-44b6-b6b8-71a9671da344 Transfer to a mixing bowl, and stir in brandy mixture, orange juice, cinnamon, and cloves.
c6f6ed98-30d8-44b6-b6b8-71a9671da344 Add the flour mixture slowly, mixing to create the cookie dough.
c6f6ed98-30d8-44b6-b6b8-71a9671da344 Preheat oven to 350 F / 175C.
c6f6ed98-30d8-44b6-b6b8-71a9671da344 Using pieces of dough, pat into thick cookies, about 1/2-inch high, into round or oval shapes.
c6f6ed98-30d8-44b6-b6b8-71a9671da344 Place on cookie sheets and bake for about 20 minutes. Cooking time will vary slightly depending on the size of the cookies.
c6f6ed98-30d8-44b6-b6b8-71a9671da344 Serve and enjoy!
909d1960-6566-4764-933a-2f07de31f064 By hand or with a mixer, beat the eggs, sugar, and oil until thick. Beat in the vanilla (or zest) and salt, and stir in the cornflour until smooth. Mix in enough flour to form a somewhat stiff but pliable dough.
909d1960-6566-4764-933a-2f07de31f064 Line two large baking trays with parchment paper. Feed the dough through a large fluted tip attached to a manual meat grinder, pastry bag or cookie press. Use scissors to cut the dough into 2-inch strips (I like to gently twist the dough) and arrange the sticks fairly close together on the lined trays.
909d1960-6566-4764-933a-2f07de31f064 Preheat your oven to 350 F (180 C). Bake the cookies, one pan at a time, for about 15 minutes, or until lightly colored. Carefully transfer the parchment paper with cookies to a rack to cool.
4ad6d0f2-c8cb-4d13-b13e-377a7b46d5fd Heat oven to 325 degrees. In a medium bowl, cream 8 ounces softened butter and add 5 tablespoons sugar, 2 teaspoons vanilla and 1 tablespoon water.
4ad6d0f2-c8cb-4d13-b13e-377a7b46d5fd In a separate medium bowl, whisk together 2 cups all-purpose flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt, and add to creamed mixture, combining thoroughly. Add 2 cups finely chopped pecans until completely incorporated.
4ad6d0f2-c8cb-4d13-b13e-377a7b46d5fd Scoop onto ungreased baking sheets and tamp down with a glass dipped inall-purpose flour. OR, form walnut-size pieces of dough into crescent shapes. Bake 20 minutes.
4ad6d0f2-c8cb-4d13-b13e-377a7b46d5fd While still warm, roll in confectioners' sugar. When cookies are thoroughly cool, roll in confectioners' sugar again and store in an airtight container. These will keep several weeks.
2a1e7b9f-3ec3-4beb-8729-efbea7db7419 Preheat your oven to 400 F (200 C) with a rack in the middle position.
2a1e7b9f-3ec3-4beb-8729-efbea7db7419 Cut the lard or shortening into the flour using a pastry cutter or fork, or pulse them together with a food processor a few times until just blended. Transfer mixture to a large mixing bowl.
2a1e7b9f-3ec3-4beb-8729-efbea7db7419 Stir in the beaten eggs, one third at a time, stirring with a wooden spoon after each addition until well blended.
2a1e7b9f-3ec3-4beb-8729-efbea7db7419 Add the liqueur, sugar, olive oil and lemon zest, and mix until combined.
2a1e7b9f-3ec3-4beb-8729-efbea7db7419 Set a large pot of water to boil over high heat.
2a1e7b9f-3ec3-4beb-8729-efbea7db7419 Meanwhile, using your fingers, pinch off lumps of the dough and shape each lump into a stick about 3 inches long. Cut a small slit into the middle of each end, then pinch and mold each side with your fingers to form a rough bone shape.
2a1e7b9f-3ec3-4beb-8729-efbea7db7419 When the water is boiling, boil the bone cookies, a few at a time, just until they float—remove them from the water immediately as soon as they start to float, using a slotted spoon or fine-mesh skimmer, draining away excess water by gently shaking the spoon or skimmer over the pot.
2a1e7b9f-3ec3-4beb-8729-efbea7db7419 Arrange the cookies on a parchment paper-lined baking sheet and bake until well browned about 20 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool completely on a wire cooling rack.
2a1e7b9f-3ec3-4beb-8729-efbea7db7419 When cookies are completely cooled, sprinkle them liberally and evenly with powdered sugar. The best way to do this is to use a fine-mesh sieve, held high above the cookies, and firmly tap the side of the sieve with the fingers of the other hand.
2a1e7b9f-3ec3-4beb-8729-efbea7db7419 Serve and enjoy!
9df0f392-81ee-4251-b5d6-bc08fb4c727d In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, spices, and baking soda until thoroughly mixed. Add honey, eggs, rum, and zest and form a smooth dough. Wrap in plastic and let rest at least 30 minutes.
9df0f392-81ee-4251-b5d6-bc08fb4c727d Heat oven to 325 F. Roll dough 1/8- to 1/4-inch thick between two pieces of parchment paper. Remove top parchment paper and cut out various shapes, leaving 2 inches between cookies. Remove scraps. Lift parchment paper by opposite corners and place on a sheet pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden at the edges. Cool completely on the pan before removing to a wire rack. Repeat with remaining dough and dough scraps.
9df0f392-81ee-4251-b5d6-bc08fb4c727d When cookies are completely cool, decorate with icing, if desired. Let icing harden before storing in an airtight container with parchment paper between the layers.
37d298cd-8af5-4620-afbb-fc8c75e309e7 Cream the butter with the powdered sugar until well blended and smooth. Beat in the vanilla, then add the flour and salt.
37d298cd-8af5-4620-afbb-fc8c75e309e7 Mix just until combined, but don't mix too much. You don't want too much gluten to form; the cookies should be tender. Add the nuts, if using.
37d298cd-8af5-4620-afbb-fc8c75e309e7 Cover the dough and chill it for several hours in the refrigerator. We like to make this dough the day before we bake them.
37d298cd-8af5-4620-afbb-fc8c75e309e7 When you're ready to bake, let the dough stand at room temperature for about 30 minutes. The dough will be really hard from being chilled. Preheat the oven to 400 F.
37d298cd-8af5-4620-afbb-fc8c75e309e7 Form the dough into 1-inch balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet. The dough will not spread at all during baking, so you can place them pretty close together. We can usually get all of the cookies onto just two cookie sheets.
37d298cd-8af5-4620-afbb-fc8c75e309e7 Bake the cookies for 8 to 12 minutes. The cookies should not brown on the top or just be very pale gold on the tops, but be lightly golden on the bottom.
37d298cd-8af5-4620-afbb-fc8c75e309e7 Immediately take the cookies, one at a time, off the hot cookie sheet and drop into a shallow bowl full of powdered sugar, roll, and place on a rack to cool. When the cookies are cool, roll them again in powdered sugar to coat.
37d298cd-8af5-4620-afbb-fc8c75e309e7 Store in an airtight container at room temperature up to 1 week, if they last that long!
f281be14-f4f7-450b-b528-bd2c756a011d Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 375 F.
f281be14-f4f7-450b-b528-bd2c756a011d In a large bowl, beat the eggs and sugar until light and foamy, about 5 minutes.
f281be14-f4f7-450b-b528-bd2c756a011d Melt the lard or butter and let cool slightly. When cooled to room temperature, add it slowly to the egg-sugar mixture with the vanilla, mixing constantly.
f281be14-f4f7-450b-b528-bd2c756a011d Whisk together flour and baking powder; slowly add it to the egg mixture to create a firm dough.
f281be14-f4f7-450b-b528-bd2c756a011d Roll out the dough to 1/8-inch thick on parchment-lined baking pans and cut with a round cutter.
f281be14-f4f7-450b-b528-bd2c756a011d Cut out a hole in the center of half of the cookies and remove scraps.
f281be14-f4f7-450b-b528-bd2c756a011d Bake about 8 minutes. Remove from oven and cool completely.
f281be14-f4f7-450b-b528-bd2c756a011d Re-roll scraps and repeat.
f281be14-f4f7-450b-b528-bd2c756a011d Sprinkle the cookies with holes with confectioner's sugar. Spread cookies without holes with a jam of choice. Press together jam-filled cookie with holed-cookies to form a sandwich.
f281be14-f4f7-450b-b528-bd2c756a011d Serve and enjoy!
7ea90add-ffd6-42e2-9ea0-fc575bc1987d In a large bowl, mix together flour and yeast. Work in Crisco and butter. Add eggs and sour cream, mixing with your hands until well incorporated. Shape into a ball, wrap with plastic, and chill at least 1 hour or overnight.
7ea90add-ffd6-42e2-9ea0-fc575bc1987d Heat oven to 350 degrees. Line baking sheets with parchment paper or bake on ungreased pans.
7ea90add-ffd6-42e2-9ea0-fc575bc1987d Sprinkle granulated sugar thickly on a flat surface. Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickeness. Cut into 3-inch circles. Place 1 tablespoon of filling in center and either fold two ends to the center and pinch, or fold in half, crimping the edge, to form a half moon shape. Transfer kolachky to prepared pan and repeat until all the dough is finished.
7ea90add-ffd6-42e2-9ea0-fc575bc1987d Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until edges start to brown. Cool and dust with confectioners' sugar. Store tightly covered.
9363ccc0-fcd8-4106-8873-c508656c70ce Gather the ingredients.
9363ccc0-fcd8-4106-8873-c508656c70ce Preheat an oven to 350 F / 180 C.
9363ccc0-fcd8-4106-8873-c508656c70ce Sift together the flour, salt, and cinnamon and set aside. In another bowl, with an electric mixer, beat the butter and sugar until creamy. Beat in the egg yolks and vanilla.
9363ccc0-fcd8-4106-8873-c508656c70ce Gradually mix in the flour mixture to form a thick, stiff dough.
