(Note: An electric mixer with a paddle attachment will help pull together the dough, which may initially be crumbly. Or, use your hands to warm the ingredients and work the dough, squeezing and kneading, to help combine the ingredients into a manageable dough.) If using the ground nuts, mix them in as well.
9363ccc0-fcd8-4106-8873-c508656c70ce Shape the dough into small balls about 1" (3 cm) in diameter. Place the balls on ungreased baking sheets (you can line the pans with parchment paper if you like) and flatten them by pressing with a fork in a criss-cross pattern. Brush the tops lightly with egg white (not too much).
9363ccc0-fcd8-4106-8873-c508656c70ce Bake the cookies 8 to 9 minutes, or until barely colored for a chewy cookie; bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden for a crispy cookie.
9363ccc0-fcd8-4106-8873-c508656c70ce Allow the cookies to cool on the baking sheet for a minute before transferring them to a rack to cool completely.
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a Gather the ingredients and preheat oven to 325 F/162.5 C.
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a In a large bowl, sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a In a medium bowl, use an electric mixer to beat together the butter and shortening, and sugar.
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a Add the egg and almond extract and beat until well blended.
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a Add to the flour mixture and mix well. Note: The dough will be crumbly at this point.
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a Use your fingers to form the mixture into a dough, and then form the dough into 2 rolls or logs that are 10 to 12 inches long.
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a Wrap and refrigerate for 2 hours (this will make it easier to shape the dough into circles).
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a Take a log and lightly score the dough at 3/4-inch intervals so that you have 15 pieces and cut the dough.
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a Roll each piece into a ball and place on a lightly-greased cookie tray, approximately 1 1/2-inches apart.
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a Add an almond in the center of each cookie and press down lightly. Repeat with the remaining dough.
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a Brush each cookie lightly with a beaten egg.
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a Bake for 15 minutes to 18 minutes, until golden brown.
f6befb24-b959-4c87-944c-53a73fafed3a Cool and enjoy or store in a sealed container.
b58b410d-38cd-42cb-946b-ff315d85168a Gather the ingredients.
b58b410d-38cd-42cb-946b-ff315d85168a Mix the butter with the sugar, salt, and the egg.
b58b410d-38cd-42cb-946b-ff315d85168a Add the flour and baking powder and knead until mixed. Cover and allow the cookie dough to rest for 1 hour in the fridge.
b58b410d-38cd-42cb-946b-ff315d85168a Warm the syrup in a small saucepan and stir in the sugar, butter, and cinnamon. Set aside and allow to cool to lukewarm.
b58b410d-38cd-42cb-946b-ff315d85168a Preheat the oven to 340 F/170 C. Line cookie sheets with parchment paper.
b58b410d-38cd-42cb-946b-ff315d85168a Flour a clean work surface and roll the chilled dough out to a thickness of 1/16-inch/2 mm.
b58b410d-38cd-42cb-946b-ff315d85168a Score the dough in a grid-pattern (optional). Using a cookie cutter with a diameter of about 3-inches/8 cm, cut cookie rounds from the dough and place on the cookie sheet.
b58b410d-38cd-42cb-946b-ff315d85168a Bake for 20 minutes or until golden.
b58b410d-38cd-42cb-946b-ff315d85168a Spread a layer of syrup on the flat side of half of the cookies and cover with the remaining cookies.
b58b410d-38cd-42cb-946b-ff315d85168a Serve warm and enjoy!
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Gather the ingredients.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Place the flour, yeast, granulated sugar, and salt in the large bowl of a stand mixer. Add the milk, butter, and egg to the bowl, and use a spatula to mix the wet and dry ingredients together.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Use the dough hook attachment to knead the mixture until it forms a soft, supple, non-sticky dough. If you don't have a stand mixer, simply knead the dough on a floured surface or a silicone mat.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Once the dough has reached the right consistency, shape it into a ball and place it back into the bowl.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Cover the bowl with plastic wrap or a damp tea towel and put it in a warm, draft-free place until the dough has almost doubled in volume. Because this is an enriched dough, it will take a little longer to rise than ordinary bread dough.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Sprinkle about a third of the brown sugar over a clean tray or baking sheet, and pour the rest of the sugar into a large plate.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Using your fist, punch the dough down and knead it smooth again.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Divide the dough into 16 equal portions and toss into the sugar on the baking sheet or tray, making sure that each portion is evenly coated. Set the sugared dough pieces to one side.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Now take a piece of sugared dough and roll it back and forth on a clean (unfloured) work surface to create a long, thin tube shape measuring about 12-inches (30 cm) long.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Dredge the tube through the sugar on the plate, making sure it is thoroughly covered, fold it in half and then roll it back and forth until it forms a tube measuring about the same length as before.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Toss the tube in the sugar on the baking sheet or tray and set aside. Repeat with the remaining pieces of dough. The dough pieces should 'sweat' in the sugar; this means that a small part of the sugar will begin to appear damp.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Grease a clean baking sheet (or cover it with greaseproof or parchment paper). Twist the tubes into long, small, pretzel shapes, tucking the ends underneath the dough. Place the pretzels on the baking sheet.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec To make magere mannen, press the pretzels slightly inwards to create a longer, narrower shape, and then flatten with the palms of your hands.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Cover the baking sheet with plastic wrap and allow to rise in a warm, draft-free place until the pretzels have doubled in size.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 390 F/200 C.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Bake the krakelingen for about 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown, but keep an eye on them. They can easily burn once the sugar begins to caramelize.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Remove the pretzels from the oven and allow them to rest on the baking sheet for a few minutes before cooling on a wire cooling rack.
052f753f-2f09-42d3-bcd5-bd66fbd1abec Serve and enjoy!
a2122519-5870-4b3a-9b39-425d5ebc9c99 Gather the ingredients.
a2122519-5870-4b3a-9b39-425d5ebc9c99 Chop the 6 peeled, cored and quartered apples into small chunks and place them in a saucepan. Add 3/4 cup unsweetened apple cider or apple juice (can be reconstituted from frozen), 2 to 4 tablespoons the sweetener of choice (agave syrup, honey or sugar), 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon ground cloves.
a2122519-5870-4b3a-9b39-425d5ebc9c99 Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover, and simmer, stirring often, for 1 hour. The apples should be very mushy.
a2122519-5870-4b3a-9b39-425d5ebc9c99 Remove cover and simmer for another 1 to 2 hours, stirring frequently so the fruit doesn't burn. The mixture will get thick and turn dark brown, from the caramelized sugar.
a2122519-5870-4b3a-9b39-425d5ebc9c99 When you stop cooking is up to personal preference. Again, the picture shows apple butter which was cooked until it was shiny, dry and thick like jam. You can always quit while it is still soft and a bit runny.
be86f318-818b-4952-86aa-dd9e1004321e Gather the ingredients.
be86f318-818b-4952-86aa-dd9e1004321e Place the speculaas cookies in a plastic zip-top bag. Remove the air and seal the bag. Lightly crush the cookies into coarse granules using a rolling pin, this ensures that no large chunks are left behind when you later food-process the cookies into crumbs.
be86f318-818b-4952-86aa-dd9e1004321e Transfer the cookie pieces into a food processor fitted with an S-blade or into a blender. Pulse until the cookies have been ground into a fine powder.
be86f318-818b-4952-86aa-dd9e1004321e Slowly stream in the vegetable oil with the food processor running. Then slowly add water. Continue to blend until a smooth paste forms.
be86f318-818b-4952-86aa-dd9e1004321e Add the powdered sugar, one spoonful at a time, processing until incorporated. Scrape down the sides of the food processor or blender periodically to make sure the powdered sugar is well combined.
be86f318-818b-4952-86aa-dd9e1004321e Transfer the cookie butter to an airtight container or into a mason jar with a tight-fitting lid. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.
be86f318-818b-4952-86aa-dd9e1004321e Enjoy the cookie butter spread on toast, on top of pancakes or waffles, with a scoop of ice cream, or with sliced apples. Of course, it also tastes great enjoyed straight from the jar on a spoon! The cookie butter will keep in an airtight container the refrigerator for up to one week.
a9fccbdc-a758-4b4c-b5bd-dddc1535aadc Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F.
a9fccbdc-a758-4b4c-b5bd-dddc1535aadc In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
a9fccbdc-a758-4b4c-b5bd-dddc1535aadc Beat in the egg yolks and vanilla until well mixed.
a9fccbdc-a758-4b4c-b5bd-dddc1535aadc Add the flour, baking powder, and salt and beat at low speed until thoroughly mixed. If the dough is too soft, wrap in plastic and chill 1 hour.
a9fccbdc-a758-4b4c-b5bd-dddc1535aadc Use a small scoop to portion out cookies onto parchment-lined baking sheets.
a9fccbdc-a758-4b4c-b5bd-dddc1535aadc Use the end of a wooden spoon or a finger dipped in flour to make a depression in the center of each cookie.
a9fccbdc-a758-4b4c-b5bd-dddc1535aadc Fill with about 1/2 teaspoon strawberry jam.
a9fccbdc-a758-4b4c-b5bd-dddc1535aadc Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned around the edges.
a9fccbdc-a758-4b4c-b5bd-dddc1535aadc Remove to a wire rack to cool completely.
a9fccbdc-a758-4b4c-b5bd-dddc1535aadc Serve and enjoy!
4848e698-760e-448b-a877-f40a5e1771e3 Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 300 F/150 C.
4848e698-760e-448b-a877-f40a5e1771e3 Combine the flour, sugar, salt, and cinnamon and stir to mix.
4848e698-760e-448b-a877-f40a5e1771e3 Cut the butter into small cubes. Rub the flour mix and the butter together between your thumb and forefingers until it resembles wet sand.
4848e698-760e-448b-a877-f40a5e1771e3 Press the dough onto a greased cookie sheet, roughly forming a rectangle. Brush surface with the beaten egg and decorate with almond slivers and sugar crystals or caramel shards.
4848e698-760e-448b-a877-f40a5e1771e3 Bake for 35 minutes or until browned.
4848e698-760e-448b-a877-f40a5e1771e3 Using a sharp knife, immediately cut into the desired shapes. Leave to cool and crisp up, before transferring to a wire cooling rack to cool completely.
4848e698-760e-448b-a877-f40a5e1771e3 Serve and enjoy!
d3478319-d409-4195-9102-705efff4ab24 Gather the ingredients.
d3478319-d409-4195-9102-705efff4ab24 In a large bowl, beat the eggs with sugar until light and lemon-colored.
d3478319-d409-4195-9102-705efff4ab24 Add the spices, baking soda-water mixture, and honey. Mix well.
d3478319-d409-4195-9102-705efff4ab24 Add flour gradually and mix until a stiff dough forms. Shape into a ball, wrap in plastic, and let it rest for 30 minutes.
d3478319-d409-4195-9102-705efff4ab24 Preheat oven to 400 F. On parchment paper cut to fit your baking pans, roll the dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
d3478319-d409-4195-9102-705efff4ab24 Cut into your desired shape. Lift the parchment paper by opposite corners and place on the baking pans. See these steps for rolling and cutting gingerbread.
d3478319-d409-4195-9102-705efff4ab24 Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly brown around the edges. Let cool completely before storing in an airtight container. It's best to ice or glazes these cookies right before serving.
d3478319-d409-4195-9102-705efff4ab24 Gather the ingredients for the glaze, if making.
d3478319-d409-4195-9102-705efff4ab24 Combine all the ingredients in a microwaveable bowl and nuke for 20 seconds at a time until almost completely melted. Stir until smooth.
d3478319-d409-4195-9102-705efff4ab24 Use immediately to decorate cookies.
d3478319-d409-4195-9102-705efff4ab24 Serve and enjoy!
5a99a19f-09ae-4b32-b848-ba7a92bfa4df Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 325 F.
5a99a19f-09ae-4b32-b848-ba7a92bfa4df In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
5a99a19f-09ae-4b32-b848-ba7a92bfa4df Add the egg yolks and mix well.
5a99a19f-09ae-4b32-b848-ba7a92bfa4df Add the all-purpose flour and chopped walnuts and mix until well incorporated.
5a99a19f-09ae-4b32-b848-ba7a92bfa4df Divide the dough in half. Wrap half in plastic and put in the freezer while you make the base.
5a99a19f-09ae-4b32-b848-ba7a92bfa4df With slightly dampened hands, pat the remaining half of dough into a 15.5 x 10.5-inch jellyroll pan until even. Re-dampen hands as necessary if dough starts to stick to your fingers.
5a99a19f-09ae-4b32-b848-ba7a92bfa4df Spread almond paste over surface to within 1/4 inch of edges.
5a99a19f-09ae-4b32-b848-ba7a92bfa4df Top with strawberry filling and spread in the same way.
5a99a19f-09ae-4b32-b848-ba7a92bfa4df Remove dough from freezer and grate evenly over the entire surface of filling. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.
5a99a19f-09ae-4b32-b848-ba7a92bfa4df Cool 10 minutes on a wire rack.
5a99a19f-09ae-4b32-b848-ba7a92bfa4df While still in the pan and warm, cut into nine horizontal rows and six vertical rows to make 54 bars. Cool completely in the pan.
5a99a19f-09ae-4b32-b848-ba7a92bfa4df Dust with confectioner's sugar and transfer bars to paper cups and a pretty serving tray. Store any leftovers tightly covered container.
d82ce5d9-b834-4542-bf48-0559ee819caf Gather the ingredients.
d82ce5d9-b834-4542-bf48-0559ee819caf In a stand mixer with a paddle attachment (or by hand), knead the butter, sugar, salt and 2 of the eggs until it forms a supple dough (about 3 minutes).
d82ce5d9-b834-4542-bf48-0559ee819caf Set the dough aside and allow to rest for 15 minutes.
d82ce5d9-b834-4542-bf48-0559ee819caf Line the cookie sheet with the parchment paper. Preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C.
d82ce5d9-b834-4542-bf48-0559ee819caf Roll small portions of cookie dough between your hands to form equally sized little balls.
d82ce5d9-b834-4542-bf48-0559ee819caf Place on the cookie sheet and use the palm of your hand to flatten the balls.
d82ce5d9-b834-4542-bf48-0559ee819caf Beat the remaining egg with a whisk and brush the cookies with beaten egg. Press the peanuts into the cookies.
d82ce5d9-b834-4542-bf48-0559ee819caf Bake for about 20 minutes, or until golden brown. Remove the cookies from the oven and allow to cool on a wire cooling rack.
d82ce5d9-b834-4542-bf48-0559ee819caf Serve and enjoy!
ce6100b9-3117-4c86-8cf3-2f7840640825 Preheat the oven to 350 F/177 C.
ce6100b9-3117-4c86-8cf3-2f7840640825 Place the butter, 3/4 cup of the powdered sugar, and vanilla in a large mixing bowl. Stir vigorously, or beat with an electric mixer at medium-high speed until completely combined.
ce6100b9-3117-4c86-8cf3-2f7840640825 In a separate bowl, combine flour and 1/4 teaspoon of the salt.
ce6100b9-3117-4c86-8cf3-2f7840640825 Add the flour to the butter about 1/2 cup at a time, beating well after each addition, until well incorporated.
ce6100b9-3117-4c86-8cf3-2f7840640825 Carefully fold in the nuts.
ce6100b9-3117-4c86-8cf3-2f7840640825 Take a small amount of dough, and roll it into a 1- to 2-inch ball. Place it on a on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
ce6100b9-3117-4c86-8cf3-2f7840640825 Repeat with more dough, leaving about 2 inches of space between balls. Bake for about 15 minutes.
ce6100b9-3117-4c86-8cf3-2f7840640825 Stir together the rest of the powdered sugar and salt.
ce6100b9-3117-4c86-8cf3-2f7840640825 After taking cookies out of the oven, roll them one by one in this mixture.
ce6100b9-3117-4c86-8cf3-2f7840640825 Place on rack to cool. If desired, roll cookies in sugar again once they have cooled completely.
ce6100b9-3117-4c86-8cf3-2f7840640825 Serve and enjoy!
dfd6280f-84c7-4e69-85fe-99ac43fbb1f9 Gather the ingredients.
dfd6280f-84c7-4e69-85fe-99ac43fbb1f9 Heat oven to 350 F/177 C.
dfd6280f-84c7-4e69-85fe-99ac43fbb1f9 Grease a 13-by-9-by-2-inch cookie sheet.
dfd6280f-84c7-4e69-85fe-99ac43fbb1f9 In a bowl, thoroughly mix coconut flakes, flour, egg yolks, brown sugar, butter and extract until a sticky dough that is moldable forms.
dfd6280f-84c7-4e69-85fe-99ac43fbb1f9 Divide the dough into 24 uniform balls.
dfd6280f-84c7-4e69-85fe-99ac43fbb1f9 Place the balls on the greased cookie sheet and bake for about 25 minutes. They should be golden brown.
dfd6280f-84c7-4e69-85fe-99ac43fbb1f9 Remove from the oven and let cool completely before eating.
dfd6280f-84c7-4e69-85fe-99ac43fbb1f9 If desired, drizzle with melted chocolate and chopped nuts.
48c8a296-3dcd-4c5b-a2b1-244cb5e9ddfb In a large bowl, cream butter, vanilla sugar and confectioners' sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, sour cream and dissolved baker's ammonia and mix again. Note: If using baking powder, combine it with the flour in the next step.
48c8a296-3dcd-4c5b-a2b1-244cb5e9ddfb Add flour and mix thoroughly. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate until manageable, about 2 hours.
48c8a296-3dcd-4c5b-a2b1-244cb5e9ddfb Heat oven to 350 F. Dust a work surface or parchment-lined pan with equal parts confectioners' sugar and granulated sugar. Roll out dough between 1/8- to 1/4-inch thickness and cut into cookie shapes of choice. Remove scraps and repeat with remaining dough. Brush cookies with beaten egg white and sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
48c8a296-3dcd-4c5b-a2b1-244cb5e9ddfb Bake 10-15 minutes or until just beginning to brown around the edges. You want these cookies to be blonde in color. Cool on pan for a few minutes then transfer to a wire rack. When completely cool, store tightly covered.
333c316d-0455-4351-be9f-5ede36284186 Preheat the oven to 200 F (95 C).
333c316d-0455-4351-be9f-5ede36284186 Wash and dry your bowl and beater to make sure all traces of fat or oil are gone. Egg whites do not whip up if there are any oils at all.
333c316d-0455-4351-be9f-5ede36284186 Separate the egg whites from the yolks. This is easiest when the eggs are a few days old and cold. Then allow the egg whites to come to room temperature for a half an hour so they whip up higher.
333c316d-0455-4351-be9f-5ede36284186 Start whipping the egg whites on medium speed until they are foamy, then increase to highest speed. When they are white and starting to be stiff, begin adding the sugar one tablespoon at a time. You may have to scrape the sides of the bowl as you go.
333c316d-0455-4351-be9f-5ede36284186 Add the salt and continue beating for several minutes until glossy and stiff. They will be about the consistency of thick frosting.
333c316d-0455-4351-be9f-5ede36284186 Stir in the extracts, if using. Use about one teaspoon of clear vanilla extract or a quarter teaspoon of almond, orange, lemon, coconut or mint extracts.
333c316d-0455-4351-be9f-5ede36284186 Fill the meringue into a pastry bag if you have one. Choose a big tip, like a star tip, for decorative lines.
333c316d-0455-4351-be9f-5ede36284186 Line two cookie sheets with parchment paper. Squeeze meringues onto cookie sheet well spaced. Use about one tablespoon per cookie. If you don't have a pastry bag or don't feel like using one, you may also make drop cookies using two spoons and smooth the tops a bit.
333c316d-0455-4351-be9f-5ede36284186 Place both cookie sheets in the oven and set the timer for one hour. Keep the oven door slightly ajar by propping it open with a wooden spoon. Switch the bottom cookie sheet with the top after about one half hour.
333c316d-0455-4351-be9f-5ede36284186 Lower the oven temperature as far as you can (my oven goes down to 175 F or 80 C) and let the cookies bake or dry out another two hours. Yes, it will take that long. Turn off oven and let cookies cool in the oven.
333c316d-0455-4351-be9f-5ede36284186 If the cookies are becoming too brown, turn off oven, close door and let them slowly cool down for several hours or overnight.
333c316d-0455-4351-be9f-5ede36284186 Bake these cookies on dry days only. Once cool, keep in an airtight container for several weeks.
1ea42367-8d76-4582-aaee-ed4d1dcc2407 Gather the ingredients.
1ea42367-8d76-4582-aaee-ed4d1dcc2407 Using a mixer on medium-high speed, cream the butter, brown sugar, eggs, and flavor extracts until the mixture is fluffy.
1ea42367-8d76-4582-aaee-ed4d1dcc2407 Reduce the mixer speed and stir in the dry ingredients until the dough is completely mixed together.
1ea42367-8d76-4582-aaee-ed4d1dcc2407 Preheat a French-Belgian waffle iron over medium heat. Place a 1-inch ball of dough into each section of the preheated iron and bake over the medium-heat burner for approximately 45 seconds on each side.
1ea42367-8d76-4582-aaee-ed4d1dcc2407 The Gaulettes are done when they turn golden brown. Allow them to cool completely on a wire rack.
1ea42367-8d76-4582-aaee-ed4d1dcc2407 Serve and enjoy!
3948a6ea-35f2-466e-ad82-d8c9a3e1cf20 Gather the ingredients.
3948a6ea-35f2-466e-ad82-d8c9a3e1cf20 In a saucepan, heat the honey with 2 3/4 tablespoons/40 g of the water and the sugar until the mixture reaches 194 F (90 C) on a candy thermometer.
3948a6ea-35f2-466e-ad82-d8c9a3e1cf20 Remove the saucepan from the heat and mix in the rye flour and salt using a hand mixer with a dough hook attachment (or pour the mixture into the bowl of a stand mixer with a dough hook attachment and knead the dough that way).
3948a6ea-35f2-466e-ad82-d8c9a3e1cf20 Knead the dough thoroughly. Grease some plastic wrap with sunflower oil and cover the dough with the plastic wrap. Allow the dough to rest for one day at room temperature.
3948a6ea-35f2-466e-ad82-d8c9a3e1cf20 The next day, preheat the oven to 340 F/170 C. Add the ground anise, the remaining 1 1/3 tablespoons/20 g of water, and baking powder to the dough and knead well.
3948a6ea-35f2-466e-ad82-d8c9a3e1cf20 Rub a little of the sunflower oil into your hands and roll little balls, roughly the size of a marble.
3948a6ea-35f2-466e-ad82-d8c9a3e1cf20 Place the balls into a round spring form cake tin. The cake tin may be densely packed, it doesn't matter if the pepernoten touch each other.
3948a6ea-35f2-466e-ad82-d8c9a3e1cf20 Bake the pepernoten for 20 minutes in the preheated oven until golden brown. When you lightly press down on the cookies, they should bounce back a little.
3948a6ea-35f2-466e-ad82-d8c9a3e1cf20 Take the tin from the oven, invert over a dish and separate the pepernoten. Allow to cool and keep in an airtight container.
3aa70ba6-3526-4285-94dc-c30b06ce0eae In a large bowl, beat the egg yolks, confectioners' sugar, and vanilla sugar, until frothy. Beat in the softened butter, brandy, if using, and lemon juice, until smooth and thoroughly combined.
3aa70ba6-3526-4285-94dc-c30b06ce0eae In a medium bowl, whip the egg whites until stiff but not dry. Stir 1/4 of the whites into the yolk mixture to lighten it, then carefully fold in the remaining whites, trying not to deflate them.
3aa70ba6-3526-4285-94dc-c30b06ce0eae In a medium bowl, whisk together the flour and baking powder. Sift it over the batter in three additions, carefully folding it in after each addition, being careful not to deflate the volume. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
3aa70ba6-3526-4285-94dc-c30b06ce0eae Heat oven to 350 F. Using your hands, take about 1 teaspoon batter and roll into a ball. Place balls 1 inch apart on a parchment-lined baking sheet. Bake 6 to 8 minutes until only very light golden in color. Do not overbake. Allow ​to cool completely.
3aa70ba6-3526-4285-94dc-c30b06ce0eae With a sharp paring knife, cut a circle on the bottom of each cookie, being careful not to poke through the other side, and scoop out the insides, saving the crumbs in a separate bowl to make the filling.
08a5a8f3-f16d-4556-a9d3-13b5ad073cac Using a stand or hand mixer, cream together the eggs and sugar until lightened in color. Beat in the butter, sesame paste and vanilla.
08a5a8f3-f16d-4556-a9d3-13b5ad073cac In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Mix the dry ingredients into the wet and then stir in the chocolate chips. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for about 8 hours or overnight.
08a5a8f3-f16d-4556-a9d3-13b5ad073cac Pre-heat the oven to 325 degrees.
08a5a8f3-f16d-4556-a9d3-13b5ad073cac Use a cookie scoop to form balls of dough and place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Keep the dough balls at least 3" apart because the cookies will spread. I used a 2 oz. scoop and got about 14 large cookies.)
08a5a8f3-f16d-4556-a9d3-13b5ad073cac Bake for 15 - 16 minutes until the edges are lightly browned. Sprinkle with sea salt and then allow the cookies to cool thoroughly before removing them from the baking sheet. The cookies will be very soft when they first come out and will break if you try to move them. Once cool, they will be firm enough to move but remain chewy in the center for a long time.
069100fd-b36c-4d03-8712-fbe1087113ee Gather the ingredients.
069100fd-b36c-4d03-8712-fbe1087113ee Add the egg and butter to a large bowl and cream together using a hand or stand mixer.
069100fd-b36c-4d03-8712-fbe1087113ee Beat in the sugar, orange zest, and orange juice.
069100fd-b36c-4d03-8712-fbe1087113ee In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt.
069100fd-b36c-4d03-8712-fbe1087113ee Fold the dry ingredients into the wet, turn out onto a floured surface to form a dough ball, wrap in plastic and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
069100fd-b36c-4d03-8712-fbe1087113ee While the dough is chilling, make the filling by adding the dates to a bowl with the hot water and let soak for 30 minutes.
069100fd-b36c-4d03-8712-fbe1087113ee Add the soaked dates and about 1/4 cup of the water to a food processor with the honey and salt. Puree until completely smooth.
069100fd-b36c-4d03-8712-fbe1087113ee Pre-heat the oven to 375 F.
069100fd-b36c-4d03-8712-fbe1087113ee Roll the dough out to between 1/8- to 1/4-inch thick (I like thicker cookies). Use a 3 1/2-inch round cutter to cut circles out of the dough.
069100fd-b36c-4d03-8712-fbe1087113ee Place about a teaspoon of honey date filling in the center of each dough round and fold into the classic triangular shape (see an easy tutorial here).
069100fd-b36c-4d03-8712-fbe1087113ee Place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
069100fd-b36c-4d03-8712-fbe1087113ee Cool and enjoy!
3f791c6a-5d2b-4e92-bcec-105160439135 Gather the ingredients.
3f791c6a-5d2b-4e92-bcec-105160439135 Combine the flour, eggs, alcohol, butter, sugar, both citrus zests, and salt to make a workable dough. Knead it well and let it sit for at least 1 hour, covered.
3f791c6a-5d2b-4e92-bcec-105160439135 Pluck off pieces and roll them out using your fingers to form snakes about as thin as your pinkie and cut them into 1/4 inch-long pieces.
3f791c6a-5d2b-4e92-bcec-105160439135 Fry the pieces a few at a time in the hot oil until brown and drain them on absorbent paper. Should the oil start to froth after a bit and the froth overflows the pot, change the oil.
3f791c6a-5d2b-4e92-bcec-105160439135 Take a second, preferably round-bottomed, pot and put the honey, sugar, and water in it.
3f791c6a-5d2b-4e92-bcec-105160439135 Boil the mixture until the foam dies down and it begins to turn yellow. At this point reduce the heat as much as possible.
3f791c6a-5d2b-4e92-bcec-105160439135 Add the struffoli and the diced candied fruit.
3f791c6a-5d2b-4e92-bcec-105160439135 Stir to distribute everything evenly through the honey and turn the mixture out onto a plate.
3f791c6a-5d2b-4e92-bcec-105160439135 Shape the mixture into a wreath with a hole in the middle, dipping your hands frequently into cold water lest you burn yourself.
3f791c6a-5d2b-4e92-bcec-105160439135 Sprinkle the candied fruit strips and the diavolini over the ring and arrange the cherry halves evenly.
3f791c6a-5d2b-4e92-bcec-105160439135 Serve and enjoy!
f54a8725-bffe-43e6-9d14-630352513fa0 In a large bowl, cut butter into flour as for pie dough until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Cut ice cream into small chunks and add to flour mixture. Cut in with a pastry blender until ice cream absorbs flour and dough binds together.
f54a8725-bffe-43e6-9d14-630352513fa0 Knead dough in bowl 5 to 8 strokes or until smooth. Divide dough into 2 equal-size pieces. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for several hours.
f54a8725-bffe-43e6-9d14-630352513fa0 When ready to bake, heat oven to 400 degrees. Roll out one piece of dough on a lightly floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut with floured 2 1/2-inch round plain or fluted cookie cutter.
f54a8725-bffe-43e6-9d14-630352513fa0 Place cookies on ungreased baking sheets, spacing about 1 inch apart. Spoon level teaspoonful of filling onto center of each cookie. Repeat with remaining dough and filling.
f54a8725-bffe-43e6-9d14-630352513fa0 Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until cookies are golden. Remove from baking sheets and place on wire racks to cool completely. Store in an airtight container. When ready to serve, dust with confectioners' sugar.
8e34f08c-1510-47cc-852e-e32082e63f79 Add the pitted dates to a bowl and fill with the cup of hot water. Allow them to soak for at least 30 minutes. When ready, add the dates and about 1/4 cup of the water to a food processor along with the honey and salt. Puree until completely smooth.
8e34f08c-1510-47cc-852e-e32082e63f79 To make the cookies, sift together the flour, sugar, and salt in a large bowl.
8e34f08c-1510-47cc-852e-e32082e63f79 Cut in the butter using a pastry cutter or fork. You can also do this in a stand mixer.
8e34f08c-1510-47cc-852e-e32082e63f79 Add the vanilla and buttermilk and stir until combined. Note that the batter will probably be too thick for a mixer and you will need to do this by hand.
8e34f08c-1510-47cc-852e-e32082e63f79 Turn the dough out onto a floured board and form into a disk. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
8e34f08c-1510-47cc-852e-e32082e63f79 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Roll out the cookie dough, on a well-floured surface, to about 1/4" thick.
8e34f08c-1510-47cc-852e-e32082e63f79 Use a cookie cutter (mine was about 3") to cut out rounds and place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
8e34f08c-1510-47cc-852e-e32082e63f79 Bake for 12 to 14 minutes and allow to cool for at least 15 minutes before moving. The cookies will be very soft when you take them out of the oven but will harden after cooling.
8e34f08c-1510-47cc-852e-e32082e63f79 Place a tablespoon of honey date filling in the center of one cookie and top with a second cookie to spread the filling. A 3" cutter will yield about 16 cookies which will be 8 sandwiched cookies.
7232789b-01f3-48ca-8544-31167cfbbfe1 Gather the ingredients.
7232789b-01f3-48ca-8544-31167cfbbfe1 In a large bowl, mix together the flour, raw cane sugar, butter, milk, spice, baking soda, and zest with your hands or a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment. The dough is ready when you can shape it into a ball without it sticking to your hands.
7232789b-01f3-48ca-8544-31167cfbbfe1 Cover the dough ball with plastic wrap and set aside at room temperature for an hour so the spices can work their magic.
7232789b-01f3-48ca-8544-31167cfbbfe1 Meanwhile, heat the oven to 347 F / 175 C. Grease one or more cookie sheet pans or line them with parchment paper.
7232789b-01f3-48ca-8544-31167cfbbfe1 Lightly flour your work surface and roll 1/4-inch thick.
7232789b-01f3-48ca-8544-31167cfbbfe1 Using a cookie cutter or speculaasplank, cut the dough and place the shapes on the prepared sheet pan(s).
7232789b-01f3-48ca-8544-31167cfbbfe1 Brush the cookies with egg white and sprinkle brown sugar and flaked almonds on top.
7232789b-01f3-48ca-8544-31167cfbbfe1 Bake 10 to 25 minutes, depending on the size and thickness of the cookies, or until the almonds are caramelizing and the cookies are turning a slightly darker shade of brown.
7232789b-01f3-48ca-8544-31167cfbbfe1 Remove from the oven and allow to cool a few minutes on the pan(s) and then transfer to a rack to cool completely.
7232789b-01f3-48ca-8544-31167cfbbfe1 Serve and enjoy!
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf Gather the ingredients.
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf Put the sesame seeds in a strainer and wash well under cold, running water. Shake to remove excess liquid, and set aside to drain for 1 hour (they will still be damp).
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf Dissolve the baking soda in the lemon juice.
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf Sift together the flour and baking powder.
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf In a mixing bowl, combine olive oil, lemon juice (with baking soda), grated peel, brandy, cinnamon, cloves, and hot water. Beat on medium-high to combine.
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf Add sugar and beat until well blended, and not separating (about 5 to 8 minutes).
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf Slowly beat in 8 cups of flour mixture.
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf When the flour is mixed in, turn the dough out onto a floured surface (or knead in the bowl) and knead by hand for 10 to 15 minutes, adding more flour if needed, until the dough doesn't stick to your hands. The dough will be soft.
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf Preheat the oven to 425 F (220 C).
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf Take a piece of dough the size of an unshelled walnut and squeeze it in your fist to form a dense ball. Roll out into a rope shape, about 3 inches long.
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf Dip in sesame seeds and pat to flatten and push seeds into the surface of the cookie.
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf The cookies can be left as is or formed into rings (pinch ends together).
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf Bake on the rack under the middle of the oven on non-stick or very lightly oiled cookie sheets at 425 F (220 C) for 15 to 20 minutes, until dark golden.
caf69ba0-0704-453c-8bea-8a0b51fcc5cf Cool completely before serving.
1f83ec2d-0589-4961-a503-99bb1524900e Gather the ingredients.
1f83ec2d-0589-4961-a503-99bb1524900e Heat the oven to 350 F.
1f83ec2d-0589-4961-a503-99bb1524900e Using a stand or hand mixer, cream together the eggs and sugar until lightened in color. Beat in the butter and almond extract.
1f83ec2d-0589-4961-a503-99bb1524900e In a separate bowl, sift together the salt, baking powder, and all-purpose flour (or, if making the Passover version, the potato starch and cake meal).
1f83ec2d-0589-4961-a503-99bb1524900e Fold the dry ingredients into the wet, stir in the sliced almonds, and turn out onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. The dough will be very sticky and you'll need additional flour (or cake meal) to shape it into a loaf, approximately 3 inches high.
1f83ec2d-0589-4961-a503-99bb1524900e Bake for 45 minutes.
1f83ec2d-0589-4961-a503-99bb1524900e With a serrated knife, slice while the loaf is still warm.
3f5f0ca9-fbf9-4088-9193-f1178e3e3a64 Gather the ingredients.
3f5f0ca9-fbf9-4088-9193-f1178e3e3a64 Melt the butter and mix it with the sugar, cinnamon, salt, and water.
3f5f0ca9-fbf9-4088-9193-f1178e3e3a64 Stir in the flour and carefully blend in the chopped almonds.
3f5f0ca9-fbf9-4088-9193-f1178e3e3a64 Let the dough rest for several hours in the fridge.
3f5f0ca9-fbf9-4088-9193-f1178e3e3a64 Preheat oven to 350 F/180 C.
3f5f0ca9-fbf9-4088-9193-f1178e3e3a64 Form little balls with a spoon or ice cream scoop and put on parchment paper. Cover with plastic wrap and flatten a bit.
3f5f0ca9-fbf9-4088-9193-f1178e3e3a64 Take the plastic wrap off and bake cookies for 8 minutes in the preheated oven.
3f5f0ca9-fbf9-4088-9193-f1178e3e3a64 Allow to cool on a wire serving rack and keep in an airtight container.
3f5f0ca9-fbf9-4088-9193-f1178e3e3a64 Serve with coffee or use as a dessert garnish. Enjoy!
4a75c674-e01b-4394-bf58-cdcf2b2afb3f Gather the ingredients.
4a75c674-e01b-4394-bf58-cdcf2b2afb3f In a large bowl, beat cream cheese with butter until light and fluffy.
4a75c674-e01b-4394-bf58-cdcf2b2afb3f Add the flour, 1 cup at a time, and mix well.
4a75c674-e01b-4394-bf58-cdcf2b2afb3f Wrap dough in plastic and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
4a75c674-e01b-4394-bf58-cdcf2b2afb3f Heat oven to 350 F.
4a75c674-e01b-4394-bf58-cdcf2b2afb3f Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick on a silicone mat or a surface that has been dusted with equal parts confectioners' and granulated sugars (not flour), because the granulated sugar will act as ball bearings and help keep the dough from sticking.
4a75c674-e01b-4394-bf58-cdcf2b2afb3f Cut into 2-inch squares. Place 1/2 to 1 teaspoon filling on center of each square. Brush a tiny bit of beaten egg white on one corner and press the opposite corner on it, pressing the dough together lightly to seal.
4a75c674-e01b-4394-bf58-cdcf2b2afb3f Using a spatula, transfer the filled cookies to a parchment-lined sheet pan and bake for 15 minutes (longer if baking from frozen) or until corners start to brown.
4a75c674-e01b-4394-bf58-cdcf2b2afb3f Using a spatula, remove cookies from the baking sheet and transfer to a wire rack to cool completely before dusting with confectioners’ sugar. Serve and enjoy!
67a00fde-8ca6-4ff2-aa0e-713bbb61c3bd In a large mixing bowl, mix together all the ingredients (except the egg white) and knead well. You may use a mixer with a dough hook attachment here. You should be able to shape the dough into a ball without it sticking to your hands. Cover the dough with plastic wrap and set aside for an hour. so that the spices can work their magic.
67a00fde-8ca6-4ff2-aa0e-713bbb61c3bd Preheat the oven to 347 F / 175 C. Grease a cookie sheet or line with parchment paper.
67a00fde-8ca6-4ff2-aa0e-713bbb61c3bd Wet your hands and roll little marble-sized balls of dough (approx. 1/2 inch/12 mm). Place the dough balls on the cookie sheet. Using your thumb, gently press down on each ball to flatten slightly. Brush with egg white.
67a00fde-8ca6-4ff2-aa0e-713bbb61c3bd Bake for about 20 minutes, or until the cookies puff up and turn a slightly darker shade of brown. Allow to cool.
057127ca-2231-4c19-babe-709b3a6d5002 Preheat the oven to 300 F. Using a stand or hand mixer, beat the butter, granulated sugar, and powdered sugar in a mixing bowl for 5 minutes, or until fluffy. Add in the almond extract. Slowly add in the all-purpose flour. If you do not have a heavy-duty stand mixer and are using a hand-held, you may want to mix in half of the flour with the mixer, then the remaining with a spoon. This will lessen the risk of burning out the motor on a hand mixer.​​
057127ca-2231-4c19-babe-709b3a6d5002 Cover with plastic wrap and chill in the refrigerator for up to one hour.
057127ca-2231-4c19-babe-709b3a6d5002 Roll out the chilled cookie dough on a well-floured surface. Roll into a rope that is 1 1/2 to 2 inches thick.​
057127ca-2231-4c19-babe-709b3a6d5002 Cut diagonally into diamond shapes and place on ungreased cookie sheets. Place one almond in the center of each cookie.
057127ca-2231-4c19-babe-709b3a6d5002 Bake for 12 minutes. Remove and cool on cooling racks.
b81d2bc5-8ff5-41dc-a799-76c76a111df0 Gather your ingredients and preheat oven to 350 F. Grease a ten-cup Bundt pan with butter and set aside. Cream together the butter and sugar in a stand mixer using a paddle beater. If you don’t have a mixer, use a wooden spoon and beat together in a mixing bowl. Beat until the butter and sugar turn pale in color and smooth in texture.
b81d2bc5-8ff5-41dc-a799-76c76a111df0 With the mixer running (or continuously beating by hand), add the eggs one at a time and beat into the mixture until fully incorporated before adding the next. Add all but 1 teaspoon of the lemon zest, vanilla extract, and the food coloring. Mix again.
b81d2bc5-8ff5-41dc-a799-76c76a111df0 In another bowl, lightly whisk together the flour, baking powder, cocoa powder, and salt. Tip one-third of the flour mixture and one-third of the sour cream into the butter mixture and mix briefly. Repeat twice more.
b81d2bc5-8ff5-41dc-a799-76c76a111df0 Half fill the greased Bundt tin with the batter, carefully lay the raspberries on the surface in an even layer. Cover with the remaining mixture and cook in the center of the preheated oven for 1 hour. Check from time to time that the cake is not browning too quickly, if it is, lower the heat slightly. The cake is ready when a skewer inserted into the center comes out clean.
b81d2bc5-8ff5-41dc-a799-76c76a111df0 Remove the cake from the oven and leave to cool for 15 minutes. Turn the cake upside down onto a cooling rack and let the cake gently ease out of the pan, letting it fall and not forcing it. Remove the tin, turn the cake right-side up and let it cool.
b81d2bc5-8ff5-41dc-a799-76c76a111df0 Make the glaze: Whisk the cream cheese to create a light cream with either an electric or hand whisk. Add the powdered sugar and whisk again. Then whisk in the lemon juice and zest. Whisk in the milk a little at a time until you get a thick but pourable consistency. Slowly pour the glaze from the center of the cake and allow it to trickle down the sides and the center opening.
b81d2bc5-8ff5-41dc-a799-76c76a111df0 The cake is delicious the day it is made, but will keep for a two to three days in an airtight tin and also freezes well for up to a month if unglazed.
86024ab5-b52f-413c-8f5d-2954ca01265d Gather the ingredients. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan and set aside. Preheat oven to 350 F.
86024ab5-b52f-413c-8f5d-2954ca01265d In a large bowl, beat the eggs until thick. Gradually beat in the sugar.
86024ab5-b52f-413c-8f5d-2954ca01265d In another bowl, combine the melted butter with flour, cocoa, vanilla, sweetened flaked coconut, and pecans.
86024ab5-b52f-413c-8f5d-2954ca01265d Add the chocolate mixture to egg and sugar mixture. Stir well to combine.
86024ab5-b52f-413c-8f5d-2954ca01265d Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake for 30 minutes or until a skewer inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.
86024ab5-b52f-413c-8f5d-2954ca01265d Remove the cake from the oven. Immediately spread marshmallow fluff gently on the surface of the warm cake.
86024ab5-b52f-413c-8f5d-2954ca01265d Prepare the frosting. In a medium bowl, combine the melted butter, cocoa powder, vanilla extract, and milk. Stir in the powdered sugar.
86024ab5-b52f-413c-8f5d-2954ca01265d Spread the frosting gently over the warm marshmallow crème, swirling to give a marbled effect.
86024ab5-b52f-413c-8f5d-2954ca01265d Sprinkle the chopped pecans over the top.
86024ab5-b52f-413c-8f5d-2954ca01265d Cut into squares to serve.
9f2f013d-5588-4db3-8eb9-5eefaa3fa19f Pre-heat the oven to 325 degrees F and butter and flour an 8" square baking pan.
9f2f013d-5588-4db3-8eb9-5eefaa3fa19f Add the butter and chocolate to a heat-proof bowl and set it over a pot of simmering water. Stir until melted and allow to cool slightly.
9f2f013d-5588-4db3-8eb9-5eefaa3fa19f Whisk the granulated sugar into the butter and chocolate mixture, then whisk in the eggs and vanilla.
9f2f013d-5588-4db3-8eb9-5eefaa3fa19f Sift together the all-purpose flour, baking powder and salt and stir into the chocolate batter.
9f2f013d-5588-4db3-8eb9-5eefaa3fa19f Make the peanut butter swirl filling by stirring together the melted butter, confectioners sugar, peanut butter and salt until smooth.
9f2f013d-5588-4db3-8eb9-5eefaa3fa19f Pour the chocolate batter into the prepared pan and spread out evenly. Drop tablespoons of peanut butter filling on top of the batter and use a butter knife or a long skewer to gently swirl the peanut butter filling into the batter. Do not mix all the way so that the pretty swirl pattern remains on top.
9f2f013d-5588-4db3-8eb9-5eefaa3fa19f Bake for about 35 to 40 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean. Let cool and cut into 9 squares. Note that you can add a cup of chocolate chips or peanut butter chips to the batter before baking, if you like.
ecfa72ec-d1fd-4a9e-a50d-043ed0ad64a5 Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 375 F. Grease and flour two 8-inch round cake pans and set aside.
ecfa72ec-d1fd-4a9e-a50d-043ed0ad64a5 To make the cake, sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt into the bowl of an electric mixer.
ecfa72ec-d1fd-4a9e-a50d-043ed0ad64a5 Add the water, oil, white vinegar, and vanilla extract. Beat until well blended. Note: the mixture will be on the thin side.
ecfa72ec-d1fd-4a9e-a50d-043ed0ad64a5 Pour the batter into the prepared pans. Bake for about 30 minutes or until a tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
ecfa72ec-d1fd-4a9e-a50d-043ed0ad64a5 Remove the pans from oven and place on wire racks to cool for 10 minutes. Turn out of pan and cool completely before filling and frosting.
ecfa72ec-d1fd-4a9e-a50d-043ed0ad64a5 Prepare the creme filling. In a stand mixer, beat 1 1/2 cups of the powdered sugar, shortening, butter, and salt until smooth and fluffy.
ecfa72ec-d1fd-4a9e-a50d-043ed0ad64a5 In a separate bowl, combine the remaining 1/2 cup powdered sugar, meringue powder, water, and vanilla extract. Stir with a fork.
ecfa72ec-d1fd-4a9e-a50d-043ed0ad64a5 Add the meringue powder mixture to the mixture in the stand mixer. Beat 5 minutes or until light and fluffy.
ecfa72ec-d1fd-4a9e-a50d-043ed0ad64a5 Place one of the chocolate cake layers on a cake stand or serving platter. Top with the creme filling and spread all the way to the edges. Top with the other cake layer. Chill until ready to top with ganache.
ecfa72ec-d1fd-4a9e-a50d-043ed0ad64a5 Prepare the ganache. In a microwave-safe bowl, heat the chocolate chips, heavy cream, and corn syrup in 30-second intervals. Stir after each interval until the chocolate chips are completely melted and the ganache is smooth.
ecfa72ec-d1fd-4a9e-a50d-043ed0ad64a5 Pour the ganache over the cake, allowing it to coat the top and drip down the sides. There will be enough ganache to repeat this process up to three or four times. Allow each layer to cool and set slightly before pouring on the next layer. This will allow for a thick coating of ganache to cover the entire cake. Clean up any excess chocolate with a paper towel. Allow the cake to firm and set in the refrigerator before serving.
ecfa72ec-d1fd-4a9e-a50d-043ed0ad64a5 Slice, serve and enjoy!
f9359dd7-a947-4526-9dd2-c04580a3b853 Gather the ingredients.
f9359dd7-a947-4526-9dd2-c04580a3b853 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and set aside. In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda, and salt together; set aside.
f9359dd7-a947-4526-9dd2-c04580a3b853 In large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
f9359dd7-a947-4526-9dd2-c04580a3b853 Add the eggs, melted chocolate, and vanilla extract.
f9359dd7-a947-4526-9dd2-c04580a3b853 Add dry ingredients to the creamed butter mixture alternately with the beer, buttermilk, and reserved cherry juice.
f9359dd7-a947-4526-9dd2-c04580a3b853 Add the chopped maraschino cherries and nuts.
f9359dd7-a947-4526-9dd2-c04580a3b853 Pour the cake batter into the prepared pan. Bake for 35-40 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
f9359dd7-a947-4526-9dd2-c04580a3b853 Set the cake on a wire rack and allow to cool completely before frosting.
f9359dd7-a947-4526-9dd2-c04580a3b853 For the chocolate beer frosting: In a large bowl, combine the cocoa powder, butter, corn syrup, beer, vanilla extract, and salt.
f9359dd7-a947-4526-9dd2-c04580a3b853 Add the powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
f9359dd7-a947-4526-9dd2-c04580a3b853 Spread evenly over the cake.
f9359dd7-a947-4526-9dd2-c04580a3b853 Cut into to squares to serve and enjoy! Of course, this tastes great washed down with a mug of your favorite beer!
765b9e6b-601d-474c-b043-63de7f3b64d5 Gather your ingredients and preheat the oven to 360 F. Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper or a silicone baking mat.
765b9e6b-601d-474c-b043-63de7f3b64d5 Put the butter, sugar and the vanilla extract into the bowl of a stand mixer (you can use an electric hand mixer, or a wire whisk to mix by hand). Beat for at least five minutes until the mixture is pale in color and light and fluffy in texture. Add the egg and beat again, finally add the buttermilk and mix thoroughly.
765b9e6b-601d-474c-b043-63de7f3b64d5 Sift the cocoa powder, flour, baking powder, and soda together, then add to the mixer bowl and gently beat into the butter mix. Finally, add the red food gel. If the color is not strong enough, add a little more until you reach the desired color making sure to only add the tiniest drop at a time, the gel is potent.
765b9e6b-601d-474c-b043-63de7f3b64d5 Oil the parchment and use a palette knife to spread the cake mixture into a 10- to 12-inch circle. Cook the cake in the middle of the preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes until slightly firm to the touch in the center. Remove from the oven and leave to cool for 5 minutes, then transfer to a cooling rack until cool.
765b9e6b-601d-474c-b043-63de7f3b64d5 Choose your trifle serving dish, either 4 individual glasses, or one large dish. When the cake is cool use a sharp knife, to cut the cake into circles to fit the glasses or dish. Aim for at least two slices for each. Hold onto the leftover crumbs as these will be for decoration.
765b9e6b-601d-474c-b043-63de7f3b64d5 Place one slice in the dish and cover with a generous layer of mixed berries. Pour over a layer of thick custard, then another layer of cake followed by berries again. Finish with a layer of whipped cream and garnish with fruits and cake crumb.
765b9e6b-601d-474c-b043-63de7f3b64d5 To serve: if you are using frozen berries, put the trifle(s) into the refrigerator and leave the berries to thaw slowly in the glass. They will give off some juice which will soak into the cake, making it even yummier. Fresh fruit trifles can be served immediately or stored in the fridge covered with plastic wrap until needed.
44bdc25d-011a-417c-bdb5-fb3d9d0f08b6 Gather your ingredients.
44bdc25d-011a-417c-bdb5-fb3d9d0f08b6 Lightly grease a 9-inch springform pan. Line the bottom and sides with greaseproof paper and put to one side. Preheat the oven to 325 F.
44bdc25d-011a-417c-bdb5-fb3d9d0f08b6 In a large non-stick saucepan, melt the remaining butter on low heat. Add the chopped chocolate to the pan and stir until melted. Remove from the heat instantly and leave to cool for 10 minutes.
44bdc25d-011a-417c-bdb5-fb3d9d0f08b6 Beat the egg yolks, both sugars, and the amaretto in a stand mixer until frothed up and doubled in volume. If you do not have a stand mixer, an electric or hand whisk will work too.
44bdc25d-011a-417c-bdb5-fb3d9d0f08b6 Using a fine sieve, sift the cocoa powder over the beaten egg and sugar mixture, then mix on low speed. You do not want to beat the air out of the eggs or the cake will not rise when cooked.
44bdc25d-011a-417c-bdb5-fb3d9d0f08b6 Put the egg whites in a scrupulously clean bowl and using clean beaters, whisk until the whites start to stiffen and are slightly glossy.
44bdc25d-011a-417c-bdb5-fb3d9d0f08b6 The chocolate should now be cooled enough fold gently into the egg mixture using a metal tablespoon. Gently stir 1/3 of the beaten egg whites into the mixture, then gently fold the remaining 2/3, making sure it is evenly colored with no streaks of chocolate.
44bdc25d-011a-417c-bdb5-fb3d9d0f08b6 Carefully spoon the mixture into the prepared pan and tap on the work surface a couple of times to release any air bubbles.
44bdc25d-011a-417c-bdb5-fb3d9d0f08b6 Bake in the center of the preheated oven for 50 minutes until set, but not solid. The center should spring lightly to the touch. The surface of the cake may crack a little but don't worry, it's a feature of this style of cake.
44bdc25d-011a-417c-bdb5-fb3d9d0f08b6 Remove from the oven and place the pan on a cooling rack and leave to cool completely.
44bdc25d-011a-417c-bdb5-fb3d9d0f08b6 Drench the cake with a heavy dusting of cocoa powder, garnish with fresh raspberries, raspberry sauce, and cream if desired.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 Gather the ingredients.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 Spray a 7-inch round baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Cut a sheet of parchment paper to fit into the bottom of the pan and spray it lightly.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the butter and sugar together until it is light and fluffy.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in the vanilla.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 In a separate bowl, combine the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt; blend thoroughly with a spoon or whisk. Add the dry ingredients to the first mixture and beat on low speed just until blended.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 With a spoon or spatula, fold in the chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 Spread the batter in the prepared pan and cover with foil.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 Add 1 1/2 cups of water to the Instant Pot inner pot and put a baking sling in the pot. (If you don't have a silicone sling make one by putting a trivet in the pot, and putting in a long, folded sheet of foil; this will make it easier to lift the pan out when the brownies are ready.) Place the pan on the trivet or sling.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 Secure the Instant Pot lid and ensure the steam release valve is in the sealing position. Choose the pressure cook function (or manual on older models), high pressure, and set the time to 40 minutes. When the time is up, let the pressure release naturally for 10 minutes. Carefully turn the valve to venting to release the remaining steam. Lift the pan of brownies out, remove the foil, and set them on a rack to cool.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 When the brownies are cool, prepare the chocolate ganache glaze. Place the semisweet chocolate in a bowl and set it aside. Pour the heavy cream into a saucepan. Place the pan over medium heat and bring the cream to a boil. Pour the cream over the semisweet chocolate; stir until the chocolate has melted and the mixture is smooth.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 Slide a knife around the side of the pan to loosen the brownies. Carefully remove the brownies to a plate.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 Spread the chocolate glaze mixture over the brownies, little some drip down the sides, if desired.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 Sprinkle chopped nuts over the wet glaze. Cool completely.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 Slice the brownies and serve.
b3dd2c6d-1d63-4481-856d-c9ab4c0355e6 Enjoy!
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Gather the ingredients.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Place the brewed coffee in a medium-sized mixing bowl. Whisk in the chopped chocolate and the cocoa powder until they are melted and completely combined. Set the bowl aside to cool in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line a muffin tin with paper cups.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 In another bowl whisk together the sugar, flour, baking soda, and salt.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Add the melted butter, eggs, vinegar, and vanilla extract to the cooled chocolate mixture and whisk until smooth.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Gradually add in the flour mixture to the wet mixture and whisk until combined, but do not over mix.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Divide the batter evenly among the muffin cups. Bake the cupcakes for 15 to 20 minutes, or until firm and just set.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Cool the cupcakes in the tin for five minutes and then remove them and place them on a wire rack. Allow them to completely cool before filling and frosting.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Prepare the marshmallow cream filling. Beat together the marshmallow creme, butter, and powdered sugar together in a medium-sized bowl using a hand mixer until completely smooth.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Place the cream mixture into a pastry bag that is fitted with a large, round hole. Set it aside.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Use a small round cookie cutter, about 1-inch in diameter, or use the bottom of a decorating tip, to cut holes in the top of each cupcake, cutting about 1/2-inch deep. Set the pieces of the cupcake aside, then fill each cupcake with the marshmallow cream until it reaches the top of the cupcake. Wipe off any excess cream. Set them aside while you make the other frostings.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Make the ganache frosting. Place the chocolate chips in a medium-sized bowl. Heat the heavy cream on the stovetop until hot, but not quite boiling. Pour the heavy cream over the chocolate chips. Allow it to sit for a minute and then whisk the mixture until it is smooth and glossy. Allow it to sit for 2 minutes.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Dip the top of each cupcake into the ganache frosting. Twist and remove the cupcake from the frosting and place on a tray or plate. Set the cupcakes aside to allow the ganache to harden, probably about 30 minutes.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 While the ganache is hardening, prepare the white icing. Whisk together the milk and powdered sugar until thick and completely combined. It needs to be on the thicker side in order for the curly cues to stay intact. If the icing is too thin, whisk in more powdered sugar.
7590f535-ba8f-452b-99d7-99321528cbe7 Place the icing in a pastry bag fitted with a small round hole. Once the ganache has completely hardened pipe the curly cue design onto the top of each cupcake. Serve immediately or place them in an airtight container until you are ready to serve.
00b6f689-3422-49e0-a623-02dad0aafc31 Gather the ingredients.
00b6f689-3422-49e0-a623-02dad0aafc31 Add milk, flour, and baking powder in a 12-ounce microwave-safe mug. Whisk until smooth.
00b6f689-3422-49e0-a623-02dad0aafc31 Add the Nutella and stir until the batter has no lumps.
00b6f689-3422-49e0-a623-02dad0aafc31 Microwave on high for about 45 to 60 seconds.
00b6f689-3422-49e0-a623-02dad0aafc31 Continue microwaving slowly in 15-second intervals. Microwaves vary but what you’re looking for is to see the cake look set and dry, the edges will pull away from the side of the mug and the cake will feel springy and fluffy to the touch. It will probably take an additional 30 to 60 seconds in total.
00b6f689-3422-49e0-a623-02dad0aafc31 For best results, serve immediately.
4c6c21ba-437d-498b-b0a4-229bef7a1c99 Pre-heat oven to 325 F.
4c6c21ba-437d-498b-b0a4-229bef7a1c99 Grease and flour a bundt cake pan or 10-inch springform pan. Since this cake is a bit heavy, layered cake pans are not recommended.
4c6c21ba-437d-498b-b0a4-229bef7a1c99 Mix all of the dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
4c6c21ba-437d-498b-b0a4-229bef7a1c99 Add applesauce and mix well until batter is smooth. Pour contents into prepared baking pan.
4c6c21ba-437d-498b-b0a4-229bef7a1c99 Bake for 50 to 55 minutes, until done.
75721763-798f-4c82-bf77-5072db70f48b Preheat oven to 350 F.
75721763-798f-4c82-bf77-5072db70f48b Grease and flour two 9-inch baking pans.
75721763-798f-4c82-bf77-5072db70f48b Mix the sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
75721763-798f-4c82-bf77-5072db70f48b Add the eggs, milk, and vanilla. Whisk by hand or with a mixer for about 2 minutes on medium speed.
75721763-798f-4c82-bf77-5072db70f48b Add the boiling water and mix. The batter will be thin.
75721763-798f-4c82-bf77-5072db70f48b Pour the batter evenly into the pans.
75721763-798f-4c82-bf77-5072db70f48b Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until a toothpick, comes out clean from the center.
75721763-798f-4c82-bf77-5072db70f48b Let the cakes cool in the pans for about 10 minutes. You can then easily remove them from the pans and let completely cool on a wire rack.
75721763-798f-4c82-bf77-5072db70f48b To assemble the cake, use any frosting or filling you like.
2e67b7fe-40e0-4c28-a053-3a359daa086a Gather the ingredients.
2e67b7fe-40e0-4c28-a053-3a359daa086a Heat the oven to 350 F. Lightly oil two 8-inch round cake pans and dust with a sprinkle of cocoa powder. Set aside.
2e67b7fe-40e0-4c28-a053-3a359daa086a In a medium-sized mixing bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt. Set aside.
2e67b7fe-40e0-4c28-a053-3a359daa086a In a large mixing bowl using an electric hand mixer at a high-speed setting, cream the shortening with the sugar until fluffy—about 4 minutes.
2e67b7fe-40e0-4c28-a053-3a359daa086a Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add the rice milk, maple syrup, and vanilla, beating until combined.
2e67b7fe-40e0-4c28-a053-3a359daa086a Using a wooden spoon, stir the dry ingredients into the wet in several additions until just combined.
2e67b7fe-40e0-4c28-a053-3a359daa086a Pour the cake batter into the prepared cake pans and bake for 30 to 40 minutes, rotating halfway through, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of a cake comes out clean.
2e67b7fe-40e0-4c28-a053-3a359daa086a Allow cakes to cool completely on a wire cooling rack before frosting with a dairy-free frosting of your choice.
2e67b7fe-40e0-4c28-a053-3a359daa086a Serve and enjoy!
681c4515-1eb7-43f1-81b1-6f90cf444a5a Heat the oven to 350 F.
681c4515-1eb7-43f1-81b1-6f90cf444a5a Grease and flour an 8-inch square or 9-inch round baking pan.
681c4515-1eb7-43f1-81b1-6f90cf444a5a In a large bowl, combine 3/4 cup of granulated sugar, flour, baking powder, and salt together. Stir to blend thoroughly.
681c4515-1eb7-43f1-81b1-6f90cf444a5a In the top of a double boiler or in a stainless steel or glass bowl over simmering water, melt the unsweetened chocolate with butter.
681c4515-1eb7-43f1-81b1-6f90cf444a5a Add the chocolate mixture to the dry ingredients along with milk and vanilla; beat with an electric mixer until smooth.
681c4515-1eb7-43f1-81b1-6f90cf444a5a Spoon chocolate cake batter into the prepared pan, and spread it evenly.
86f4c088-b5e6-495c-9dfb-1932dec1a9f9 ​Preheat oven to 350 F. Lightly oil an 8-inch springform pan and line the bottom with parchment paper.
86f4c088-b5e6-495c-9dfb-1932dec1a9f9 In a double boiler or microwave, melt the chocolate. Alternatively, place the chocolate in a heatproof bowl and set it into a small saucepan of gently simmering water. (Make sure that the bottom of the bowl nests in the saucepan but doesn't touch the water.) Stir frequently until the chocolate is completely melted, remove the bowl from the saucepan, and set aside. (It's a good idea to dry any condensation from the outside of the bowl so the water doesn't drip into the chocolate and cause it to seize.)
86f4c088-b5e6-495c-9dfb-1932dec1a9f9 In a large bowl, combine the chocolate and sugar, mixing well with a wire whisk. Whisk in the oil, coffee (if using), vanilla, cinnamon, and salt.
86f4c088-b5e6-495c-9dfb-1932dec1a9f9 Add the eggs one at a time, whisking after each addition.
86f4c088-b5e6-495c-9dfb-1932dec1a9f9 Sprinkle the cocoa powder evenly over the top of the batter, then whisk until it is fully incorporated.
86f4c088-b5e6-495c-9dfb-1932dec1a9f9 Pour the batter into the prepared pan, smoothing the top with a spatula.
86f4c088-b5e6-495c-9dfb-1932dec1a9f9 Bake in the preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until the top of the cake is firm and has a thin, shiny crust and a tester inserted in the center comes out mostly clean.
86f4c088-b5e6-495c-9dfb-1932dec1a9f9 Place the cake, still in its pan, on a wire rack to cool.
86f4c088-b5e6-495c-9dfb-1932dec1a9f9 Run an offset spatula or knife around the perimeter of the cake to loosen it, then open the springform pan latch, and remove the ring from the pan bottom. Place a large plate on top of the cake, and holding both the plate and pan bottom, flip to invert the cake. Remove the pan bottom, peel off the parchment, and invert the cake back onto a cake plate or platter, so it is right side up.
86f4c088-b5e6-495c-9dfb-1932dec1a9f9 Serve solo or with fresh berries, sorbet, whipped cream, or ice cream.
91e848f4-5d01-413e-ac0a-2617abf9a35f Gather the ingredients.
91e848f4-5d01-413e-ac0a-2617abf9a35f Preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4.
91e848f4-5d01-413e-ac0a-2617abf9a35f Grease and flour an 8-inch square baking pan.
91e848f4-5d01-413e-ac0a-2617abf9a35f In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, and salt. Whisk or stir to blend thoroughly.
91e848f4-5d01-413e-ac0a-2617abf9a35f Make three wells in the flour mixture.
91e848f4-5d01-413e-ac0a-2617abf9a35f In one put the vanilla; in another the vinegar, and in the third the vegetable oil.
91e848f4-5d01-413e-ac0a-2617abf9a35f Pour the cold water over the mixture and stir until moistened.
91e848f4-5d01-413e-ac0a-2617abf9a35f Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until it springs back when touched lightly.
91e848f4-5d01-413e-ac0a-2617abf9a35f Frost with chocolate frosting or your favorite icing or glaze. Or sift powdered sugar over the cake.
91e848f4-5d01-413e-ac0a-2617abf9a35f Enjoy!
5242100d-ea6b-4d32-9440-e64c0191f95f Preheat the oven to 350 F. Lightly oil and flour 2 9-inch round spring-form cake pans and set aside. In a small mixing bowl or dish, combine the soy milk and cider vinegar until well-mixed. Set aside (mixture will thicken slightly).
5242100d-ea6b-4d32-9440-e64c0191f95f In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking soda, baking powder, and salt until well combined. Create a well in the center of the ingredients. Add the soy milk mixture, eggs (or egg replacer, if using), coffee, dairy-free sour cream, vegetable oil, and vanilla extract to the well. Using an electric hand mixer, beat the ingredients on a medium-speed setting for 1 to 2 minutes, or until smooth. (Note: the batter will be rather thin, but this is normal!)
5242100d-ea6b-4d32-9440-e64c0191f95f Pour the batter into the prepared pans and bake for 30 to 40 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cakes emerges clean. Allow cakes to cool in the pan for 20 to 30 minutes, then carefully remove the cakes from the pans and allow to cool completely on wire cooling racks before layering and frosting with Dairy-Free Chocolate Frosting.
02b0bc6b-7874-40f3-9bc9-893ec8c2ac5f Gather the ingredients.
02b0bc6b-7874-40f3-9bc9-893ec8c2ac5f Preheat the oven to 350 F.
02b0bc6b-7874-40f3-9bc9-893ec8c2ac5f Lightly butter a 9-inch springform pan and set aside.
02b0bc6b-7874-40f3-9bc9-893ec8c2ac5f In a medium saucepan, melt the chocolate and butter over the lowest heat, do not rush this process, melting the chocolate too quickly will cause it to"shock" into a hard lump. Mix in the cocoa powder and espresso powders until smooth and set aside for a few minutes to cool.
02b0bc6b-7874-40f3-9bc9-893ec8c2ac5f While the chocolate is cooling, whisk together the eggs, sugar, and flour until they are completely combined and foamy.
02b0bc6b-7874-40f3-9bc9-893ec8c2ac5f Fold the egg mixture into the chocolate until the color is uniform and pour the batter into the prepared pan. Place into the center of the preheated oven and bake for 45 minutes or until a toothpick pulls out moist crumbs when inserted near the center of the torte. If the pick is sticky, then cook for a little longer.
02b0bc6b-7874-40f3-9bc9-893ec8c2ac5f Allow the cake to cool in the pan on a rack for 15 minutes. Run a knife or inverted spatula along the edges of the gateau and loosen the sides of the pan. Cool for 5 minutes and remove the sides of the pan. Invert the cake onto a pretty cake platter and cool completely before serving decorated as you wish.
02b0bc6b-7874-40f3-9bc9-893ec8c2ac5f Serve and enjoy!
1d7b587b-8035-4fa8-beb6-ff3d08b7d77d Combine all ingredients except the truffles into a large microwave-safe mug. Whisk until the batter is completely smooth. If you’d like a darker red color, you can add more food coloring and mix again again. ​
1d7b587b-8035-4fa8-beb6-ff3d08b7d77d Press the chocolate truffle balls into the center of the cake batter. Make sure the balls are completely covered.
1d7b587b-8035-4fa8-beb6-ff3d08b7d77d Microwave the cake on medium high for about 50 to 60 seconds. Microwave strengths vary, but you're looking for it to rise and feel springy to touch. It should also pull away from the sides a bit.
cc6d6c01-e9b5-4f6c-8b41-e96a203659db Preheat oven to 350 F. Spray two 8" round cake pans OR one 13" x 9" cake pan with​ a nonstick baking spray containing flour and set aside.
cc6d6c01-e9b5-4f6c-8b41-e96a203659db Pour one portion of the cake mix into a large bowl. In a small bowl, combine the cocoa powder and hot water; mix well. This makes the chocolate "bloom" and increases the flavor.
cc6d6c01-e9b5-4f6c-8b41-e96a203659db Make a well in​ the center of the cake mix and add the vanilla, oil, eggs, and 1 cup milk. Beat the mixture for 1 minute with an electric mixer at low speed until blended. then stir in the cocoa mixture and the melted chocolate. Scrape the sides and bottom of the bowl and beat 2 minutes longer at medium speed until the batter is smooth.
cc6d6c01-e9b5-4f6c-8b41-e96a203659db Pour the batter into the prepared pans and bake the layer cakes for 20 to 30 minutes, or until the cake springs back when pressed lightly in center and begins to pull away from edges of ​the pan. Bake the 9" x 13" cake for 25 to 35 minutes until the cake tests done.
5987d3b0-bbf0-47dd-a242-01a8ce1549c4 Gather the ingredients.
5987d3b0-bbf0-47dd-a242-01a8ce1549c4 Preheat oven to 350 F. Spray a 13- by 9-inch pan with a nonstick baking spray containing flour and set aside.
5987d3b0-bbf0-47dd-a242-01a8ce1549c4 In a large saucepan, melt 3 squares of the chocolate and 2/3 cup butter in the hot water and bring to a boil.
5987d3b0-bbf0-47dd-a242-01a8ce1549c4 Remove from the heat and add the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, salt, and baking soda. Mix well with a wire whisk or eggbeater.
5987d3b0-bbf0-47dd-a242-01a8ce1549c4 Stir in the buttermilk, eggs, and 2 teaspoons vanilla; beat until smooth. Pour into the prepared 13- x 9-inch pan.
5987d3b0-bbf0-47dd-a242-01a8ce1549c4 Bake at 350 F for 25 to 30 minutes, until the top springs back when touched with a fingertip.
5987d3b0-bbf0-47dd-a242-01a8ce1549c4 In a heavy saucepan, melt 2 squares of the chocolate and 1/3 cup butter together.
5987d3b0-bbf0-47dd-a242-01a8ce1549c4 Add the powdered sugar, milk, 2 teaspoons vanilla, and a pinch of salt and beat well. You may need to add more milk or powdered sugar to reach the desired consistency: the frosting should be just barely pourable.
5987d3b0-bbf0-47dd-a242-01a8ce1549c4 When the cake comes out of the oven, let cool for 15 minutes, then beat the frosting again and pour onto the cake.
5987d3b0-bbf0-47dd-a242-01a8ce1549c4 Spread the frosting, and let the cake cool. Cut into squares to serve.
70b5a657-b5d8-426f-83a8-32f43aa3cb95 Gather the ingredients.
70b5a657-b5d8-426f-83a8-32f43aa3cb95 Heat the oven to 325 F. Butter a 10-inch tube cake pan and dust it with cocoa powder (or use flour).
70b5a657-b5d8-426f-83a8-32f43aa3cb95 In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed, beat the butter and shortening until creamy. Add the sugar and continue to beat for about 3 minutes, or until light and fluffy.
70b5a657-b5d8-426f-83a8-32f43aa3cb95 Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add the vanilla and beat until well blended.
70b5a657-b5d8-426f-83a8-32f43aa3cb95 In another bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, and cocoa; use a whisk or spoon to blend thoroughly.
70b5a657-b5d8-426f-83a8-32f43aa3cb95 Add about one-third of the flour mixture to the batter. With the mixer on low speed, add 1/2 cup of the milk and beat until blended. Repeat with another one-third of the flour mixture and the remaining milk and beat until blended. Add the remaining flour mixture and beat until blended. Do not overbeat.
70b5a657-b5d8-426f-83a8-32f43aa3cb95 Spoon the batter into the prepared tube cake pan and spread evenly.
70b5a657-b5d8-426f-83a8-32f43aa3cb95 Bake for about 70 to 80 minutes, or until a toothpick or skewer comes out clean when inserted into the cake. Don't open the oven until the cake has reached the minimum time of 70 minutes.
70b5a657-b5d8-426f-83a8-32f43aa3cb95 Cool in the pan for 10 minutes; carefully turn the cake out onto a rack to cool completely.
70b5a657-b5d8-426f-83a8-32f43aa3cb95 Serve with ice cream or whipped cream or dust with sifted powdered sugar.
96d9bf41-a969-4356-b361-b1f3b8c1de72 Gather the ingredients.
96d9bf41-a969-4356-b361-b1f3b8c1de72 Using a chocolate cake mix or a recipe for a homemade cake, prepare and bake the cake in a 9x13x2-inch baking pan for 25 to 30 minutes, or per package instructions.
96d9bf41-a969-4356-b361-b1f3b8c1de72 Prepare the pudding with milk following the package directions.
96d9bf41-a969-4356-b361-b1f3b8c1de72 Cool the baked cake on a rack.
96d9bf41-a969-4356-b361-b1f3b8c1de72 Cut the cake into cubes.
96d9bf41-a969-4356-b361-b1f3b8c1de72 Put half of the cake cubes into a 2-quart bowl.
96d9bf41-a969-4356-b361-b1f3b8c1de72 Drizzle half of the Kahlua over the cake cubes.,
96d9bf41-a969-4356-b361-b1f3b8c1de72 Spread half of the prepared pudding over the cake and Kahlua layer and then spread half of the whipped topping over the pudding.
96d9bf41-a969-4356-b361-b1f3b8c1de72 Repeat the layers and then break the Skor bar up and sprinkle the pieces over the top.
96d9bf41-a969-4356-b361-b1f3b8c1de72 Serve and enjoy!
04eebe1f-dd87-417f-a535-1ba843e239a4 Gather the ingredients.
04eebe1f-dd87-417f-a535-1ba843e239a4 Preheat oven to 350 F.
04eebe1f-dd87-417f-a535-1ba843e239a4 Grease and flour a 9-inch square baking pan or spray with a flour and oil baking spray.
04eebe1f-dd87-417f-a535-1ba843e239a4 Combine flour, granulated sugar, cocoa, baking soda, and salt in a mixing bowl. Add oil, buttermilk, and vanilla, along with beaten egg. Whisk or slowly beat until well blended.
04eebe1f-dd87-417f-a535-1ba843e239a4 Pour into prepared pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
04eebe1f-dd87-417f-a535-1ba843e239a4 Meanwhile, combine topping ingredients in a small bowl, stirring until well blended.
04eebe1f-dd87-417f-a535-1ba843e239a4 Spread topping over the warm cake and broil about 4 inches from heat for 3 minutes, or until topping is browned and bubbly.
04eebe1f-dd87-417f-a535-1ba843e239a4 Serve and enjoy!
891ce5da-9368-41ca-96c2-13c31a8a4c04 Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
891ce5da-9368-41ca-96c2-13c31a8a4c04 Combine the first set of ingredients with a wire whisk. Set aside.
891ce5da-9368-41ca-96c2-13c31a8a4c04 In a microwavable container melt chocolate with water. Microwave 1 minute and check chocolate. If not melted, continue microwaving for 10 seconds at a time. Set aside.
891ce5da-9368-41ca-96c2-13c31a8a4c04 In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar. Add the eggs one at a time. Add the vanilla and mix. Pour in the chocolate a little at a time and mix. Combine completely. Add the flour mixture alternately with the milk until all is used.
891ce5da-9368-41ca-96c2-13c31a8a4c04 Pour batter into prepared pans.
891ce5da-9368-41ca-96c2-13c31a8a4c04 Bake for 27 to 35 minutes until tested with a toothpick and cake has pulled away from the pans.
891ce5da-9368-41ca-96c2-13c31a8a4c04 Frost Chocolate Fudge Cake as desired.
bda30fc3-1293-43cd-a114-0b22737a5130 Preheat oven to 350 F.
bda30fc3-1293-43cd-a114-0b22737a5130 In a mixing bowl, use a whisk to stir together the chocolate cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, oil, eggs, and water. Mix in chocolate chips and pour the batter into a greased 12-cup bundt pan.
bda30fc3-1293-43cd-a114-0b22737a5130 Bake for 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
bda30fc3-1293-43cd-a114-0b22737a5130 Cool cake for 90 minutes on a wire rack before turning over onto a serving plate. Dust the cake with powdered sugar before serving.
1673a4e5-ce33-4a25-8140-64c6a17b7416 Gather the ingredients.
1673a4e5-ce33-4a25-8140-64c6a17b7416 Spray a 1-1/2 cup (12 ounce) microwave-safe mug or cup with a nonstick baking spray containing flour. Then add the chocolate cake mix, peanut butter, milk, and mini chocolate chips to the mug or cup and mix together well with a fork until the mixture is smooth.
1673a4e5-ce33-4a25-8140-64c6a17b7416 Microwave on high for 1 minute for an 800 to 1000-watt microwave oven; 1 minute and 15 seconds for 600-watt microwave ovens and below. The batter will puff up and the surface will look like a cake. ​
1673a4e5-ce33-4a25-8140-64c6a17b7416 Remove carefully from the microwave; the cup may be hot. Put the cup on the counter and let stand on a solid surface for 1 minute, then eat. The cake will deflate a bit as it stands. The cake may have a fudgy layer on the bottom; that's okay!
735afba9-a27a-492e-b457-0bdbd17554d2 Gather the ingredients.
735afba9-a27a-492e-b457-0bdbd17554d2 Preheat the oven to 350 F/177 C. Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch cake pans, knocking out any excess flour. (Alternatively, lightly grease the pans and line the bottoms with parchment paper, then oil the parchment.)
735afba9-a27a-492e-b457-0bdbd17554d2 In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, matcha, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
735afba9-a27a-492e-b457-0bdbd17554d2 In another large bowl, whisk together the sour cream, eggs, oil, and vanilla. Slowly add the wet ingredients to the dry, whisking until smooth. (Switch to a spoon or use electric beaters if you find the batter too thick to whisk easily.)
735afba9-a27a-492e-b457-0bdbd17554d2 Divide the batter evenly between the two cake pans, smoothing the tops with a spatula. Bake the cakes in the preheated oven until they are firm to the touch, begin to pull away from the sides of the pan, and a tester inserted in the center comes out clean, about 25 to 30 minutes.
735afba9-a27a-492e-b457-0bdbd17554d2 Allow the cakes to cool on a rack in their pans for 10 minutes. Run a sharp knife around the edge of each cake, then invert onto the cooling rack. Remove the pans and allow the cakes to cool completely before frosting.
735afba9-a27a-492e-b457-0bdbd17554d2 To make the frosting: beat the butter in a stand mixer or with handheld beaters until smooth and creamy. Beat in the confectioner's sugar at low speed, just until incorporated. Add the white chocolate, vanilla, and cream, and beat on medium speed for about 3 minutes more, or until the frosting is light and fluffy.
735afba9-a27a-492e-b457-0bdbd17554d2 When the cake has cooled completely, place one layer on a cake plate. Spread with about 3/4 cup of the frosting, then top with the second layer. Spread the top and sides of the cake with the remaining frosting.
735afba9-a27a-492e-b457-0bdbd17554d2 Enjoy!
6b8253b6-c947-4ef2-8560-548eca255946 Heat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4. Grease and flour a 9-by-13-by-2-inch baking pan, two 9-inch layer cake pans, or three 8-inch layer cake pans.
6b8253b6-c947-4ef2-8560-548eca255946 In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, granulated sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, soda, and salt; stir or whisk to blend thoroughly. Add eggs, milk, oil, and vanilla. Beat with electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
6b8253b6-c947-4ef2-8560-548eca255946 Using a spoon, stir in boiling water until blended.
6b8253b6-c947-4ef2-8560-548eca255946 Pour the thin batter into the prepared baking pan(s).
