6b8253b6-c947-4ef2-8560-548eca255946 Bake for about 35 minutes for a rectangular cake or 30 to 35 minutes for layers. A wooden pick inserted in center should come out clean.
6b8253b6-c947-4ef2-8560-548eca255946 Cool for 10 minutes in pan on rack and then remove from pan and cool completely.
6b8253b6-c947-4ef2-8560-548eca255946 Frost as desired.
6b8253b6-c947-4ef2-8560-548eca255946 Cake is shown with creamy butter frosting.
b84010f6-ca94-4f34-87ca-a02d70e9ea3c Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 9x13x2-inch baking pan or spray with baking spray.
b84010f6-ca94-4f34-87ca-a02d70e9ea3c Measure cake flour, baking powder, and salt into a bowl; set aside.
b84010f6-ca94-4f34-87ca-a02d70e9ea3c Beat butter with brown sugar and granulated sugar until creamy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Slowly beat in about 1/3 of the flour mixture with about 1/4 cup of milk. Repeat with another 1/3 of the flour mixture and the remaining 1/4 cup of milk. Beat in the remaining flour mixture, 1 teaspoon vanilla, and 1/4 teaspoon almond extract. Spread in the prepared cake pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
b84010f6-ca94-4f34-87ca-a02d70e9ea3c Cool in the pan on a rack for 10 minutes. Loosen the sides of the cake. cover the top of the cake with a piece of parchment paper or waxed paper. Place a rectangular rack or cake plate over the pan and carefully turn over so the cake is now sitting on the parchment paper and rack; remove the pan. Let cool completely then frost top and sides.
d1c4e68e-4529-4f3f-8354-872cb8f2be04 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Lightly oil a 9-inch round cake pan and set aside.
d1c4e68e-4529-4f3f-8354-872cb8f2be04 In a medium-sized mixing bowl, sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt. In another small mixing bowl, whisk together the water, almond milk, canola oil, and vanilla. Add the wet ingredients to the dry, mixing until just combined.
d1c4e68e-4529-4f3f-8354-872cb8f2be04 Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 25 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Allow to cool completely on a wire cooling rack before icing with vegan ganache, if desired.
69f3b26a-64c4-4284-8017-298e4393c3be Heat oven to 350 F. Grease and flour a 13x9x2-inch baking pan.
69f3b26a-64c4-4284-8017-298e4393c3be Sift dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients and stir with a large spoon until smooth and well combined.
69f3b26a-64c4-4284-8017-298e4393c3be Pour batter into the pan.
69f3b26a-64c4-4284-8017-298e4393c3be Bake at 350 F for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
69f3b26a-64c4-4284-8017-298e4393c3be Set the pan on a wire rack until the cake top feels completely cool to the touch.
69f3b26a-64c4-4284-8017-298e4393c3be Frost with your favorite frosting.
39cf43c3-63fa-4f74-a256-c071bf3f5d05 Gather the ingredients.
39cf43c3-63fa-4f74-a256-c071bf3f5d05 Grease the crock pot interior or spray with non-stick spray.
39cf43c3-63fa-4f74-a256-c071bf3f5d05 Mix all ingredients together in a bowl until well blended; transfer to the slow cooker.
39cf43c3-63fa-4f74-a256-c071bf3f5d05 Cover and cook on LOW for 6 to 8 hours. Do not lift the lid.
39cf43c3-63fa-4f74-a256-c071bf3f5d05 Serve warm with ice cream.
bc55f910-dbaa-42c9-8ce7-839cb4cfaad1 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
bc55f910-dbaa-42c9-8ce7-839cb4cfaad1 Cream margarine and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
bc55f910-dbaa-42c9-8ce7-839cb4cfaad1 Add eggs one at a time. Beat thoroughly after each addition.
bc55f910-dbaa-42c9-8ce7-839cb4cfaad1 Stir in the cooled melted chocolate.
bc55f910-dbaa-42c9-8ce7-839cb4cfaad1 Sift dry ingredients together and add to the batter alternately with the mashed bananas; stir in vanilla.
bc55f910-dbaa-42c9-8ce7-839cb4cfaad1 Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
bc55f910-dbaa-42c9-8ce7-839cb4cfaad1 Bake in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until cake tests done. A toothpick inserted into the center of the cake should come out clean.
bc55f910-dbaa-42c9-8ce7-839cb4cfaad1 Frost with a fluffy white frosting or chocolate sour cream frosting.
fe52654d-f81a-442a-8f7a-a84af41e8b37 Gather the ingredients.
fe52654d-f81a-442a-8f7a-a84af41e8b37 Preheat oven to 350 F. Grease and flour three 9-inch round baking pans.
fe52654d-f81a-442a-8f7a-a84af41e8b37 Mix cocoa with boiling water in small bowl; stir until smooth. Set aside to cool.
fe52654d-f81a-442a-8f7a-a84af41e8b37 Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla. Gradually add cocoa mixture. Combine well.
fe52654d-f81a-442a-8f7a-a84af41e8b37 With wire whisk, combine flour, baking soda, and salt. Alternately add flour mixture with milk and sour cream to butter mixture. Beat until blended. Pour batter into pans.
fe52654d-f81a-442a-8f7a-a84af41e8b37 Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool cake 10 minutes.
fe52654d-f81a-442a-8f7a-a84af41e8b37 Remove from pans to wire racks. Cool completely. Frost cake as desired.
fe52654d-f81a-442a-8f7a-a84af41e8b37 Serve and enjoy!
1e799aec-9c8e-4760-8030-61c2d9879f34 Gather the ingredients.
1e799aec-9c8e-4760-8030-61c2d9879f34 In a large saucepan, stir together the egg yolk and the granulated sugar until it turns light yellow and slightly foamy. In a separate small saucepan over low heat, bring the milk to a simmer.
1e799aec-9c8e-4760-8030-61c2d9879f34 Once the milk is just beginning to bubble (be careful not to let the milk boil or the milk may curdle), add half of the milk, whisking constantly, to the egg-sugar mixture. Add the remainder of the hot milk to the tempered eggs, continue stirring, and cook over low-medium heat for 1-2 minutes, until the mixture thickens and coats a spoon.
1e799aec-9c8e-4760-8030-61c2d9879f34 Place the chopped chocolate into a double boiler set over 2 inches of simmering water. Pour the milk-egg mixture over the chocolate, stirring constantly, until it is melted and the mixture is completely smooth. Chocolate can be melted in the microwave but this must be approached with caution as the chocolate can easily burn.
1e799aec-9c8e-4760-8030-61c2d9879f34 Add the butter and the vanilla extract to the hot chocolate milk mixture and continue cooking and stirring until the butter is completely melted about 3 minutes. Pour the batter into a very lightly greased 9-inch loaf pan or classic round tin and refrigerate the chocolate fondant for 6 to 8 hours, or overnight.`
1e799aec-9c8e-4760-8030-61c2d9879f34 To unmold the cake, place the bottom of the pan into a large pan of hot water for 30 seconds. Loosen the edges of the cake with a butter knife or an offset spatula, and invert it onto a chilled serving platter. Cut the cake into crosswise slices and serve it cold.
e6187657-2b66-4f83-967f-587f40180e84 Gather the ingredients.
e6187657-2b66-4f83-967f-587f40180e84 Sift together powdered sugar and cocoa.
e6187657-2b66-4f83-967f-587f40180e84 Melt butter. Add butter and vanilla to the sifted mixture. Stir.
e6187657-2b66-4f83-967f-587f40180e84 Add milk to get desired spreading consistency. If more milk is required, add by a tablespoon at a time.
e6187657-2b66-4f83-967f-587f40180e84 Use chocolate fudge frosting immediately or refrigerate for up to 2 days or up to 3 months in the freezer.
34ed6d87-f0e2-404e-a755-38bf0716ca6a Gather the ingredients.
34ed6d87-f0e2-404e-a755-38bf0716ca6a Preheat the oven to 350 F and lightly grease a 9-inch square or round cake pan.
34ed6d87-f0e2-404e-a755-38bf0716ca6a In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, cinnamon, and cayenne and stir. Add the cold water, vegetable oil, white vinegar, and vanilla and stir until just combined.
34ed6d87-f0e2-404e-a755-38bf0716ca6a Pour the batter into the cake pan and bake for about 30 minutes, or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
34ed6d87-f0e2-404e-a755-38bf0716ca6a Let the cake cool completely. Dust with powdered sugar and serve.
b5e5733a-1dd7-4240-ae79-fbb7657784cd Gather the ingredients.
b5e5733a-1dd7-4240-ae79-fbb7657784cd In a large mixing bowl, combine confectioners' sugar and cocoa; stir in the sweetened condensed milk and the vanilla, mixing thoroughly. The mixture will be quite stiff. Stir or knead in coconut and nuts, if using. A heavy-duty mixer with paddle attachment makes mixing much easier, or use the dough hook attachment on a hand-held mixer.
b5e5733a-1dd7-4240-ae79-fbb7657784cd Chill the chocolate mixture for about 15 to 20 minutes, then shape into 1-inch balls. If the mixture is sticky, butter your hands if necessary.
b5e5733a-1dd7-4240-ae79-fbb7657784cd Arrange the candy balls on a baking sheet lined with wax paper or parchment paper. Cover the candy and chill the cocoa balls for at least 2 hours, or until they are quite firm.
b5e5733a-1dd7-4240-ae79-fbb7657784cd Store the chocolate coconut candies in tightly covered containers separated with sheets of wax paper.
b5e5733a-1dd7-4240-ae79-fbb7657784cd Enjoy!
00748d1a-d1d1-4b6b-8a63-4bee987e9c21 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Lightly oil or grease (with dairy-free soy margarine) two 9-inch round cake pans. Set aside.
00748d1a-d1d1-4b6b-8a63-4bee987e9c21 In a medium-sized mixing bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Set aside.
00748d1a-d1d1-4b6b-8a63-4bee987e9c21 In a blender, process the tofu until creamy. Add the maple syrup and oil and process until smooth. Stir the tofu mixture and almond milk into the dry ingredients. Add the boiling water and continue to stir until the batter is just combined. (The batter should be fairly smooth but will still have some lumps in it.)
00748d1a-d1d1-4b6b-8a63-4bee987e9c21 Pour the batter into the prepared pans and bake for about 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cakes comes out clean. Allow the cakes to cool in the pans for about 15 to 20 minutes on a wire cooling rack before removing from the pans to finish cooling on the cooling rack. Once cakes are completely cool, frost with a dairy-free frosting of your choice.
375380b1-b515-4eb7-8222-f1f815aa5b73 Gather the ingredients.
375380b1-b515-4eb7-8222-f1f815aa5b73 In a large saucepan, combine ingredients and mix well to blend. Bring to a boil; cover and cook 3 minutes.
375380b1-b515-4eb7-8222-f1f815aa5b73 Uncover and cook to 238 F on a candy thermometer or until soft ball forms when dropped in cold water. Cool for 3 minutes.
375380b1-b515-4eb7-8222-f1f815aa5b73 Beat until thick and spreadable. It should begin to lose its glossiness.
375380b1-b515-4eb7-8222-f1f815aa5b73 Spread on layers and over sides of cake.
375380b1-b515-4eb7-8222-f1f815aa5b73 Enjoy!
31b8d5a7-faf8-46f9-9b62-f7c77cbe1136 Preheat the oven to 300 F. Using solid shortening, grease an 8" springform pan and dust with cocoa; set aside. You can wrap the pan in heavy-duty foil if you'd like; that will help shield the batter more from the heat of the oven.
31b8d5a7-faf8-46f9-9b62-f7c77cbe1136 In a microwave, melt chocolate and butter in a microwave-safe bowl on medium power, stirring once, until melted, about 1 to 2 minutes.
31b8d5a7-faf8-46f9-9b62-f7c77cbe1136 Add the brown sugar and granulated sugar, 1/2 cup cocoa, eggs, salt, and vanilla and mix well. Do not overbeat; this is a fudgy cake and it shouldn't rise much while baking.
31b8d5a7-faf8-46f9-9b62-f7c77cbe1136 Pour the cake batter into the prepared pan.
31b8d5a7-faf8-46f9-9b62-f7c77cbe1136 Bake at 300 F for 25 to 30 minutes or until the cake just barely springs back when touched lightly in the center. The cake will not be completely set.
31b8d5a7-faf8-46f9-9b62-f7c77cbe1136 Cool on a wire rack.
31b8d5a7-faf8-46f9-9b62-f7c77cbe1136 Run a sharp knife around the sides of the pan to release the cake.
31b8d5a7-faf8-46f9-9b62-f7c77cbe1136 Gently unlock the spring on the pan and remove the sides.
31b8d5a7-faf8-46f9-9b62-f7c77cbe1136 Cover the cake and chill thoroughly, for at least 4 to 6 hours, before serving.
31b8d5a7-faf8-46f9-9b62-f7c77cbe1136 Slice the cake into thin wedges and serve with whipped cream, vanilla or chocolate ice cream, or hot fudge sauce.
90efb9cd-74b4-4337-8229-88b7e613fffe Gather the ingredients. Preheat your oven to 350 F.
90efb9cd-74b4-4337-8229-88b7e613fffe Butter and flour two 9-inch cake pans. It can help to line the bottom with a circle of parchment paper cut to fit the pan.
90efb9cd-74b4-4337-8229-88b7e613fffe In a large mixing bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda and salt, until everything is blended.
90efb9cd-74b4-4337-8229-88b7e613fffe In a separate mixing bowl, combine the eggs, milk, oil and vanilla, and whisk to combine. Then whisk in the boiling water.
90efb9cd-74b4-4337-8229-88b7e613fffe Now add the wet ingredients to the dry and stir until combined.
90efb9cd-74b4-4337-8229-88b7e613fffe Then pour the batter into your prepared pans and transfer them to the oven.
90efb9cd-74b4-4337-8229-88b7e613fffe Bake for about 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, or with a crumb or two attached. You can start testing after 27 minutes because it's better to check too soon than to over bake.
90efb9cd-74b4-4337-8229-88b7e613fffe Cool the cakes for 10 minutes in the pans on a wire rack, then loosen the edges by running a knife along the sides, turn the cakes out onto the racks and cool for at least another hour.
90efb9cd-74b4-4337-8229-88b7e613fffe Once cool, frost with your favorite chocolate frosting recipe.
90efb9cd-74b4-4337-8229-88b7e613fffe Serve and enjoy.
54abf85b-9494-4b2f-a0a8-9865dc0b86db Gather the ingredients.
54abf85b-9494-4b2f-a0a8-9865dc0b86db Preheat the oven to 350 F. Spray or lightly grease an 8x8 baking pan.
54abf85b-9494-4b2f-a0a8-9865dc0b86db In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, salt, and baking soda.
54abf85b-9494-4b2f-a0a8-9865dc0b86db Add the water, olive oil, white or apple cider vinegar, and vanilla extract and mix until blended. Add the chocolate chips and stir just until incorporated.
54abf85b-9494-4b2f-a0a8-9865dc0b86db Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes. The cake should be cooked through.
54abf85b-9494-4b2f-a0a8-9865dc0b86db Let cool before slicing and serving.
c9696d8c-66d4-4bcf-b0fb-b8287c1a84ec Gather the ingredients.
c9696d8c-66d4-4bcf-b0fb-b8287c1a84ec Preheat the oven to 300 F.
c9696d8c-66d4-4bcf-b0fb-b8287c1a84ec Grease an 8-inch round cake pan and dust it generously with cocoa powder.
c9696d8c-66d4-4bcf-b0fb-b8287c1a84ec In a mixing bowl, whisk the eggs and sugar together for 2 minutes, or until light and foamy.
c9696d8c-66d4-4bcf-b0fb-b8287c1a84ec In a separate bowl, add the chocolate and butter. Place this over a saucepan of simmering water—creating a double boiler—until both ingredients are melted. Stir to combine.
c9696d8c-66d4-4bcf-b0fb-b8287c1a84ec Add the chocolate mixture to the egg mixture, along with the cocoa powder, salt, and vanilla. Whisk until everything is combined.
c9696d8c-66d4-4bcf-b0fb-b8287c1a84ec Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake in the oven for 30 minutes. Remove and let cool in the pan for 15 minutes.
c9696d8c-66d4-4bcf-b0fb-b8287c1a84ec Invert onto a wire rack and allow the cake to cool completely.
c9696d8c-66d4-4bcf-b0fb-b8287c1a84ec Refrigerate until ready to serve and enjoy!
0655f1cb-33d6-423a-9417-9589872a113d Preheat the oven to 180 C / 350 F / Gas 4
0655f1cb-33d6-423a-9417-9589872a113d In a large baking bowl cream the sugar with the margarine and butter until light and fluffy and very pale in color. You can use either an electric hand whisk, wooden spoon, or fork (obviously the electric whisk makes it easier).
0655f1cb-33d6-423a-9417-9589872a113d Add the beaten egg a little at a time and again beat well.
0655f1cb-33d6-423a-9417-9589872a113d Sieve the cocoa with the flour and baking powder. Fold gently into the butter and egg mixture. Finally, add the milk and boiling water, stir well.
0655f1cb-33d6-423a-9417-9589872a113d Grease 2 x 7"/18cm cake tins. Divide the mixture between the two tins, and gently spread to create a smooth surface.
0655f1cb-33d6-423a-9417-9589872a113d Bake in the preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes until risen. To check the cake is cooked insert a metal skewer into the center, it should come out clean with crumbs on it, not cake mixture.
0655f1cb-33d6-423a-9417-9589872a113d Remove the cakes from the tins and leave to cool on a wire rack. Once cooled decorate as desired.
85461a77-9866-4f55-8b39-29c4784b45d5 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Butter and flour an 8"x8"x2" or 9"x9"x2" cake pan.
85461a77-9866-4f55-8b39-29c4784b45d5 In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
85461a77-9866-4f55-8b39-29c4784b45d5 In another large bowl, use an electric hand mixer or a manual rotary beater to beat together the butter and sugar until light and creamy.
85461a77-9866-4f55-8b39-29c4784b45d5 Add the egg and vanilla extract and continue beating until the egg is fully incorporated and the batter is lemon colored. Add the yogurt, orange juice, and milk, and beat until well-mixed.
85461a77-9866-4f55-8b39-29c4784b45d5 Slowly add the flour mixture to the wet mixture while continuing to beat on medium speed, for one to two minutes, or until the batter is smooth.
85461a77-9866-4f55-8b39-29c4784b45d5 Pour the batter into the prepared pan, smoothing the top with a spatula if necessary.
85461a77-9866-4f55-8b39-29c4784b45d5 Bake in the preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until the cake is golden and a tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
85461a77-9866-4f55-8b39-29c4784b45d5 Transfer the cake pan to a rack to cool.
8e6777b5-38ff-4bdb-9e49-db425d9cbcf8 Gather the ingredients.
8e6777b5-38ff-4bdb-9e49-db425d9cbcf8 Preheat oven to 350 F.
8e6777b5-38ff-4bdb-9e49-db425d9cbcf8 Mix cake mix and pineapple together in a large bowl.
8e6777b5-38ff-4bdb-9e49-db425d9cbcf8 Pour into lightly greased 13x9 pan. Don't be surprised when it gets foamy.
8e6777b5-38ff-4bdb-9e49-db425d9cbcf8 Bake in the preheated oven for about 20 minutes or until golden and springs back when touched in middle.
ece6fc73-e6fb-412d-9a5c-4922c5c3a04f Gather the ingredients.
ece6fc73-e6fb-412d-9a5c-4922c5c3a04f Preheat the oven to 325 F.
ece6fc73-e6fb-412d-9a5c-4922c5c3a04f In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the egg whites until frothy. Add the cream of tartar and salt and continue beating until the egg whites stand in soft, glossy peaks. Gradually beat in 1 cup of the granulated sugar. Fold in the vanilla.
ece6fc73-e6fb-412d-9a5c-4922c5c3a04f Sift the measured flour 3 more times and mix with the remaining 1/2 cup of sugar. With a large spatula, fold the flour mixture gently into the batter until well incorporated.
ece6fc73-e6fb-412d-9a5c-4922c5c3a04f Spoon the angel food cake batter into an ungreased 10-inch tube cake pan. Bake in the center of the preheated oven for 55 to 65 minutes. When done, the cake will be golden brown and will spring back when pressed lightly with a finger.
ece6fc73-e6fb-412d-9a5c-4922c5c3a04f Remove from the oven and invert the pan (turn upside down, cake and all) until it is entirely cooled. The pan should have extensions on top which will keep the cake from resting directly on the countertop. If not, invert the center tube onto a large soda bottle or support the edges of the pan with a few cans or jars.
ece6fc73-e6fb-412d-9a5c-4922c5c3a04f To remove the completely cooled cake from the pan, carefully slide a spatula or knife around the sides. Remove the sides and then slide loosen it from the bottom and the middle tube with a spatula or knife. Enjoy!
01c01a42-d375-4663-9d90-d317fe14089d Gather your ingredients and preheat oven to 350 F. Grease a ten-cup Bundt pan with butter and set aside. Cream together the butter and sugar in a stand mixer using a paddle beater. If you don’t have a mixer, use a wooden spoon and beat together in a mixing bowl. Beat until the butter and sugar turn pale in color and smooth in texture.
01c01a42-d375-4663-9d90-d317fe14089d With the mixer running (or continuously beating by hand), add the eggs one at a time and beat into the mixture until fully incorporated before adding the next. Add all but 1 teaspoon of the lemon zest, vanilla extract, and the food coloring. Mix again.
01c01a42-d375-4663-9d90-d317fe14089d In another bowl, lightly whisk together the flour, baking powder, cocoa powder, and salt. Tip one-third of the flour mixture and one-third of the sour cream into the butter mixture and mix briefly. Repeat twice more.
01c01a42-d375-4663-9d90-d317fe14089d Half fill the greased Bundt tin with the batter, carefully lay the raspberries on the surface in an even layer. Cover with the remaining mixture and cook in the center of the preheated oven for 1 hour. Check from time to time that the cake is not browning too quickly, if it is, lower the heat slightly. The cake is ready when a skewer inserted into the center comes out clean.
01c01a42-d375-4663-9d90-d317fe14089d Remove the cake from the oven and leave to cool for 15 minutes. Turn the cake upside down onto a cooling rack and let the cake gently ease out of the pan, letting it fall and not forcing it. Remove the tin, turn the cake right-side up and let it cool.
01c01a42-d375-4663-9d90-d317fe14089d Make the glaze: Whisk the cream cheese to create a light cream with either an electric or hand whisk. Add the powdered sugar and whisk again. Then whisk in the lemon juice and zest. Whisk in the milk a little at a time until you get a thick but pourable consistency. Slowly pour the glaze from the center of the cake and allow it to trickle down the sides and the center opening.
01c01a42-d375-4663-9d90-d317fe14089d The cake is delicious the day it is made, but will keep for a two to three days in an airtight tin and also freezes well for up to a month if unglazed.
b13aa8fc-1508-46c8-b7c1-1cd294d27cd6 Gather the ingredients.
b13aa8fc-1508-46c8-b7c1-1cd294d27cd6 Preheat the oven to 350 F (175 C). Grease a large ring mold.
b13aa8fc-1508-46c8-b7c1-1cd294d27cd6 Beat the butter and sugar until light and creamy (about 5 minutes).
b13aa8fc-1508-46c8-b7c1-1cd294d27cd6 Turn the beater to the lowest setting and add the eggs, one by one.
b13aa8fc-1508-46c8-b7c1-1cd294d27cd6 Zest the lemons and squeeze out the juice. Set the lemon juice aside to use later. Add the lemon zest, quark, and milk to the butter mixture. Don't be alarmed if the mixture looks slightly curdled at this stage.
b13aa8fc-1508-46c8-b7c1-1cd294d27cd6 Sift the baking powder and flour into the batter and gently fold through the mixture.
b13aa8fc-1508-46c8-b7c1-1cd294d27cd6 Pour the batter into the ring mold. Arrange most of the blueberries on top of the batter (they will sink while cooking). Keep some blueberries aside to decorate the top of the cake later.
b13aa8fc-1508-46c8-b7c1-1cd294d27cd6 Bake the cake until a skewer inserted into the cake comes out clean, about 50 to 55 minutes.
b13aa8fc-1508-46c8-b7c1-1cd294d27cd6 Allow to cool in the mold on a wire rack for 1/2 hour and then invert on the rack (still in the mold) and allow to cool for 1 1/5 hours.
b13aa8fc-1508-46c8-b7c1-1cd294d27cd6 To make the lemon glaze, mix the powdered sugar and half the lemon juice in a bowl and whisk until completely lump-free. It should be opaque and pourable. Add a little extra lemon juice, if the consistency is too thick.
b13aa8fc-1508-46c8-b7c1-1cd294d27cd6 When the quark cake is stone cold, remove it from the mold and set the rack with the cake over a piece of wax paper or paper kitchen towels, for easy clean-up. Drizzle the cake with the lemon glaze, decorate with blueberries and finish with a dusting of powdered sugar.
b13aa8fc-1508-46c8-b7c1-1cd294d27cd6 Place the cake on a cake stand and serve in generous slices.
66f5f7ec-9857-41b5-8e36-41dcef9b2bb1 Heat the oven to 325 F.
66f5f7ec-9857-41b5-8e36-41dcef9b2bb1 Generously grease and flour a tube cake pan.
66f5f7ec-9857-41b5-8e36-41dcef9b2bb1 Process the vanilla wafers in the food processor until the crumbs are fine or put them in a plastic food storage bag and use a rolling pin to crush them. Chop the pecans finely by hand or throw them into the food processor with the crumbs and pulse a few more times.
66f5f7ec-9857-41b5-8e36-41dcef9b2bb1 In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream ​the butter and sugar until light and fluffy, about 4 to 5 minutes. Add the eggs, one at a time, and blend well after each addition.
66f5f7ec-9857-41b5-8e36-41dcef9b2bb1 Add half of the finely crushed vanilla wafers and blend well. Add the nuts, coconut, milk, and remaining vanilla wafer crumbs. Beat until blended.
66f5f7ec-9857-41b5-8e36-41dcef9b2bb1 Spoon the batter into a greased and floured tube cake pan.
66f5f7ec-9857-41b5-8e36-41dcef9b2bb1 Bake the cake in the preheated oven for 1 hour.
66f5f7ec-9857-41b5-8e36-41dcef9b2bb1 Leave the cake in pan on a rack for 10 minutes to cool slightly; invert onto a cake plate.
a7d44985-2d5c-4416-8329-60803bc5d839 Grease your bundt pan with cooking spray. Pour the 1/2 cup of melted butter into the bottom of the pan and sprinkle the 1/2 cup of brown sugar evenly over the butter.
a7d44985-2d5c-4416-8329-60803bc5d839 Prepare the pineapple by cutting the peeled fruit into rings and coring each ring. Cut each ring in half. Lay the curved edge of each half ring into the indentations of the bundt pan. Place the maraschino cherries in between each piece of pineapple. You may need more or fewer maraschino cherries and pineapple rings depending on the shape of your bundt pan.
a7d44985-2d5c-4416-8329-60803bc5d839 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Place the oven rack on the lower middle part of the oven. Cream together the 1/2 cup of butter and 1 1/2 cups of sugar in the bowl of a stand mixer with the whisk attachment until creamy, about 10 minutes on medium-high speed.
a7d44985-2d5c-4416-8329-60803bc5d839 Beat in the 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla until fluffy.
a7d44985-2d5c-4416-8329-60803bc5d839 Sift together the dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
a7d44985-2d5c-4416-8329-60803bc5d839 Add the dry ingredients alternately with the 1 1/4 cup of milk to the creamed mixture in your stand mixer. Beat after each addition and scrape down the sides of the bowl as needed.
a7d44985-2d5c-4416-8329-60803bc5d839 Pour the cake batter over the prepared bundt pan.
a7d44985-2d5c-4416-8329-60803bc5d839 Place the pan in the preheated oven and bake for about 40 minutes, or until edges are bubbly and a toothpick comes out of the cake cleanly.
a7d44985-2d5c-4416-8329-60803bc5d839 Remove the cake from the oven and allow it to cool for 15 minutes in the cake pan. Then flip the cake onto your chosen serving platter and serve while it is still warm.
d22c99e1-b58b-4ebf-89e6-1a82dffdf705 Gather the ingredients.
d22c99e1-b58b-4ebf-89e6-1a82dffdf705 Preheat the oven to 350°F. Butter a 9-inch square or round cake tin.
d22c99e1-b58b-4ebf-89e6-1a82dffdf705 In a medium bowl, mix together the flour, cocoa powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
d22c99e1-b58b-4ebf-89e6-1a82dffdf705 In a large bowl cream together the butter and sugars with an electric mixer. Beat in the eggs one at a time. Mix in the vanilla, then beat in the mashed banana.
d22c99e1-b58b-4ebf-89e6-1a82dffdf705 Turn the flour mixture into the banana mixture in two batches and stir until just blended. Mix in the chocolate chips until evenly distributed.
d22c99e1-b58b-4ebf-89e6-1a82dffdf705 Scrape the batter into the pan, smooth the top and bake for about 30 to 35 minutes, until a wooden skewer either comes out clean or with a little bit of melted chocolate from the chips. The top of the cake should feel springy but firm.
d22c99e1-b58b-4ebf-89e6-1a82dffdf705 Cool in the pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes, then turn the cake out of the pan and finish cooling, upright, on the wire rack.
162b23c0-ec5e-4711-b732-9e84b0f980b6 Preheat the oven to 325 F. Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt cake pan.
162b23c0-ec5e-4711-b732-9e84b0f980b6 In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, and spices; set aside.
162b23c0-ec5e-4711-b732-9e84b0f980b6 In mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream the butter and sugars until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in pumpkin and vanilla.
162b23c0-ec5e-4711-b732-9e84b0f980b6 Slowly beat the dry ingredients into the batter. Continue beating on medium speed until the batter is smooth and well blended. Spoon the cake batter into the prepared Bundt pan and bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until a wooden toothpick or cake tester comes out clean when inserted in the center.
162b23c0-ec5e-4711-b732-9e84b0f980b6 Cool for 15 minutes in the pan on a rack; invert onto a serving plate to cool completely. Glaze with the Maple Pecan Glaze or dust with powdered sugar before serving.
a2dd6e94-d253-4570-8182-441e3f631e92 Gather the cake ingredients.
a2dd6e94-d253-4570-8182-441e3f631e92 Pre heat the oven to 325 F (165 C/Gas 3). Generously grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan. Make sure you get all the nooks and crannies of the Bundt cake pan.
a2dd6e94-d253-4570-8182-441e3f631e92 In a large bowl or the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment, combine the flour, 2 cups of sugar, salt, baking powder and soda, the buttermilk, 1 cup of butter, 2 teaspoons of vanilla, and the eggs; beat on low speed until moistened. Increase the mixer speed to medium and beat for about 3 minutes longer.
a2dd6e94-d253-4570-8182-441e3f631e92 Spoon the batter into the prepared cake pan and spread evenly.
a2dd6e94-d253-4570-8182-441e3f631e92 Bake the cake in the preheated oven for 55 to 65 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
a2dd6e94-d253-4570-8182-441e3f631e92 Meanwhile, gather the glaze ingredients.
a2dd6e94-d253-4570-8182-441e3f631e92 In a small saucepan over low heat, combine the 3/4 cup of sugar, 1/3 cup of butter, 3 tablespoons of water, and 2 teaspoons of vanilla; cook, stirring, just until butter melts. Do not bring the mixture to a boil.
a2dd6e94-d253-4570-8182-441e3f631e92 Remove the cake to a rack and (while it is still in the pan) pierce it all over with a fork or skewer.
a2dd6e94-d253-4570-8182-441e3f631e92 Pour the hot butter glaze over the warm cake.
a2dd6e94-d253-4570-8182-441e3f631e92 Let the cake stand 5 to 10 minutes, or until glaze is absorbed.
a2dd6e94-d253-4570-8182-441e3f631e92 Then carefully turn it out onto a cake plate and sprinkle with some confectioners' sugar, if you'd like.
1710a2ee-aa85-4d4f-b024-4d4b3c492f55 Heat oven to 325 F. Butter and flour a 12-cup Bundt cake pan, or spray with a baking spray. Drain syrup from peaches; measure 1/3 cup of the syrup and reserve. Chop peaches finely and set aside.
1710a2ee-aa85-4d4f-b024-4d4b3c492f55 Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add the eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Beat in vanilla.
1710a2ee-aa85-4d4f-b024-4d4b3c492f55 In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, and soda. Blend dry mixture into the creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk; fold in reserved 1/3 cup of peach syrup and the chopped peaches. Spoon into prepared baking pan. Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until a toothpick or cake tester comes out clean when inserted in center.
1710a2ee-aa85-4d4f-b024-4d4b3c492f55 Cool in pan on a rack for 15 minutes. Invert the cake onto the rack to cool completely. Put the baking pan over the cooled cake (matching the grooves and pattern) and flip with the rack then put a serving plate over the cake and invert again.
9e496d14-1688-44f3-9f70-41845f8c5522 Gather the ingredients.
9e496d14-1688-44f3-9f70-41845f8c5522 Preheat oven to 350 F.
9e496d14-1688-44f3-9f70-41845f8c5522 Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt cake pan or a tube cake pan.
9e496d14-1688-44f3-9f70-41845f8c5522 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the butter and sugars together until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla and sweet potato until well blended.
9e496d14-1688-44f3-9f70-41845f8c5522 In another bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, soda, salt, and spices; use a whisk or spoon to blend the dry ingredients. Stir the flour mixture into the batter, alternating with the buttermilk, until blended. Do not overmix. Fold in chopped pecans. Spoon the batter into prepared Bundt cake pan or tube cake pan.
9e496d14-1688-44f3-9f70-41845f8c5522 Bake the cake in the preheated oven for 55 to 65 minutes, or until a wooden skewer or toothpick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.
9e496d14-1688-44f3-9f70-41845f8c5522 Cool in the pan on a rack for 10 minutes. Carefully invert the cake onto the rack to cool completely.
9e496d14-1688-44f3-9f70-41845f8c5522 Transfer the cake to a serving plate, brush all over with melted butter then dust with powdered sugar.
9e496d14-1688-44f3-9f70-41845f8c5522 If desired, drizzle with the orange glaze, below, or another thin glaze or icing.
9e496d14-1688-44f3-9f70-41845f8c5522 Serve and enjoy!
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b Gather the ingredients.
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b Preheat oven to 325 F; grease and flour a bundt pan.
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b Mix the softened butter and sugar until fluffy.
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b Then mix in the eggs, doing so thoroughly.
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b Add the dry ingredients, alternating with the 1 cup of buttermilk and combine with care. Put the lemon zest and lemon juice in last. Mix well.
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b Pour into the Bundt pan and pop in the oven, baking for approximately 45 to 50 minutes in a GAS oven, perhaps a bit longer using electric.
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b While the cake is baking, combine the glaze ingredients together in a medium-sized bowl using a hand mixer. (You can use a whisk, but the hand mixer will be easiest.)
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b Perform the "toothpick" test by inserting a toothpick into the thickest part of the bundt cake. If it's done, it'll come back with no wet batter. This helps to make certain it is done. Just make sure you don't overcook it.
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b Allow the bundt cake to cool on a rack.
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b Run a knife around ​the cake in pan for easier removal.
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b Flip the cake over, carefully, to be right-side-up. Then, with a long-tined fork, poke holes in it once it is on the serving plate.
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b Once the holes are poked, spread the lemon glaze all over the cake. The glaze will sink into the holes providing more lemony flavor throughout.
5daea058-ae3d-4dc8-a6bf-480985fd427b Enjoy!
c6bf06fd-0a91-44b3-a150-9a80aef6c020 Heat oven to 350 F. Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt cake pan.
c6bf06fd-0a91-44b3-a150-9a80aef6c020 Combine cake ingredients in a large mixing bowl and beat on low speed of electric mixer until blended. Scrape the sides and bottom of the bowl and then beat on high speed for 2 minutes. Spoon into the prepared pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes, or until the cake springs back when lightly touched with a finger.
c6bf06fd-0a91-44b3-a150-9a80aef6c020 Cool completely before frosting.
9893b428-5d67-4f91-b373-36aa9f957ebb Gather the ingredients.
9893b428-5d67-4f91-b373-36aa9f957ebb Generously grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan. Preheat oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas Mark 4.
9893b428-5d67-4f91-b373-36aa9f957ebb Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, and cocoa; set aside.
9893b428-5d67-4f91-b373-36aa9f957ebb In a large mixing bowl with a handheld electric mixer at high speed, beat eggs until light in color and fluffy. Gradually beat in granulated sugar until light and fluffy; beat in oil.
9893b428-5d67-4f91-b373-36aa9f957ebb With mixer at low speed, beat in the sifted dry ingredients in 3 additions, alternating with the buttermilk.
9893b428-5d67-4f91-b373-36aa9f957ebb Drain shredded zucchini; fold into the flour mixture along with vanilla and pecans. Spoon into prepared Bundt pan and bake for 55 to 60 minutes, or until a wooden pick or cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
9893b428-5d67-4f91-b373-36aa9f957ebb Cool in pan on a rack for 10 minutes, then remove from pan to cool completely.
9893b428-5d67-4f91-b373-36aa9f957ebb Sift confectioners' sugar over cake before serving.
9893b428-5d67-4f91-b373-36aa9f957ebb Serve and enjoy!
52261e0b-d064-4b5c-ba2b-73cf0413a57d Heat oven to 300 F.
52261e0b-d064-4b5c-ba2b-73cf0413a57d Generously grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt cake pan or spray with baking spray with flour.
52261e0b-d064-4b5c-ba2b-73cf0413a57d Combine the flour, baking soda, and salt in a bowl; set aside.
52261e0b-d064-4b5c-ba2b-73cf0413a57d In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat 1 cup butter and ricotta cheese with 1 cup granulated sugar and 1 1/2 cups brown sugar until light. Beat in egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in the vanilla.
52261e0b-d064-4b5c-ba2b-73cf0413a57d Stir in the flour mixture.
52261e0b-d064-4b5c-ba2b-73cf0413a57d Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Fold the beaten whites into the batter until well incorporated. Spoon into the prepared pan and bake for about 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes, or until the cake springs back when lightly touched with a finger.
52261e0b-d064-4b5c-ba2b-73cf0413a57d Cool in the pan on a rack for 10 minutes. Carefully invert the cake onto a rack to cool completely. Use a spatula to loosen the sides of the cake, if necessary.
52261e0b-d064-4b5c-ba2b-73cf0413a57d Glaze with the browned butter glaze (below) or dust the cake with confectioners' sugar.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Preheat the oven to 325 F.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Grease and flour a tube or Bundt cake pan.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Cream the butter. Add in the sugar and continue to cream mixture.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Add the eggs one at a time.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Measure out the flour and mix in the salt.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Slowly add the flour to the butter mixture.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Once combined add in the juice and zest.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Carefully pour the cake batter into the prepared pan.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Allow the cake to cool for 15 minutes in the pan.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Remove the cake from the pan and continue to allow it on a wire baking rack.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Once the cake is completely cool and placed on a serving platter, make the lemon glaze.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Zest the lemon into a medium sized bowl.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Juice the lemon into a measuring cup.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 If necessary, add additional liquid like more lemon juice, lemon liqueur, water, lemonade or lemon soda to make 1/4 cup of liquid.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Add the liquid to the bowl with the zest.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Stir in the sifted powdered sugar. If the glaze is too stiff, add more liquid. If it is too wet, add more powdered sugar. Decoratively drizzle the glaze over the cake.
fde0ec60-9bd3-49fb-adf3-f8ac8322f4a2 Serve this lemon pound cake by itself or with a little whipped cream.
8666e8f2-5fc2-45d1-9c90-08aa919ff800 Gather the ingredients.
8666e8f2-5fc2-45d1-9c90-08aa919ff800 Preheat the oven to 325 F. Generously butter and flour a 10-inch Bundt cake pan.
8666e8f2-5fc2-45d1-9c90-08aa919ff800 Into a bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt. Set aside.
8666e8f2-5fc2-45d1-9c90-08aa919ff800 In a mixing bowl using an electric mixer, cream 1 cup butter with the granulated sugar; beat at high speed until mixture is very light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
8666e8f2-5fc2-45d1-9c90-08aa919ff800 Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition and scraping down the side of the bowl frequently.
8666e8f2-5fc2-45d1-9c90-08aa919ff800 Blend in the lemon zest.
8666e8f2-5fc2-45d1-9c90-08aa919ff800 Add a portion of the sifted flour mix to the creamed mixture, alternating it with portions of the sour cream and ending with the dry ingredients. Scrape the sides of the bowl frequently.
8666e8f2-5fc2-45d1-9c90-08aa919ff800 Pour the batter into the prepared cake pan.
8666e8f2-5fc2-45d1-9c90-08aa919ff800 Bake in the preheated oven for 55 to 65 minutes, or until a cake tester or wooden pick inserted near the center of the cake comes out clean. Remove from oven and cool in the pan for 10 minutes.
8666e8f2-5fc2-45d1-9c90-08aa919ff800 Meanwhile, combine lemon glaze ingredients in a bowl, blending until smooth.
8666e8f2-5fc2-45d1-9c90-08aa919ff800 Carefully turn the lemon cake out onto a platter; drizzle evenly with the glaze.
8c9efd13-bf7c-41a5-8359-890b801ef91f Preheat oven to 325 F. Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt cake pan or tube cake pan.
8c9efd13-bf7c-41a5-8359-890b801ef91f In a large mixing bowl with electric mixer, cream butter, and cream cheese with 2 2/3 cups of the sugar until light and fluffy.
8c9efd13-bf7c-41a5-8359-890b801ef91f Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in almond extract.
8c9efd13-bf7c-41a5-8359-890b801ef91f Sift together the flour, baking powder, and salt. Combine the milk with 1/4 cup of the amaretto liqueur.
8c9efd13-bf7c-41a5-8359-890b801ef91f Add dry mixture to the creamed mixture in three additions, alternating with the milk mixture and ending with dry ingredients. Mix the batter until smooth and well blended.
8c9efd13-bf7c-41a5-8359-890b801ef91f Pour batter into the prepared pan. Bake for 1 hour, or until a toothpick or cake tester comes out clean when inserted in center.
8c9efd13-bf7c-41a5-8359-890b801ef91f Meanwhile, combine the remaining 3/4 cup of amaretto with 1/3 cup sugar in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
8c9efd13-bf7c-41a5-8359-890b801ef91f Remove from heat and let cool. Remove to a rack and cool in the pan for 15 minutes.
ec1826f8-31d1-424e-9a86-c09f8cafe17e Heat the oven to 325 F.
ec1826f8-31d1-424e-9a86-c09f8cafe17e Generously grease and flour a 10-inch one-piece tube cake pan or Bundt cake pan.
ec1826f8-31d1-424e-9a86-c09f8cafe17e In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the butter and shortening until creamy.
ec1826f8-31d1-424e-9a86-c09f8cafe17e With the electric mixer on medium speed, gradually beat in the granulated sugar. Continue beating for about 5 minutes, or until light and fluffy.
ec1826f8-31d1-424e-9a86-c09f8cafe17e Beat in the 8 ounces of cream cheese until well blended.
ec1826f8-31d1-424e-9a86-c09f8cafe17e Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
ec1826f8-31d1-424e-9a86-c09f8cafe17e Add the flour and 1 teaspoon of vanilla; beat just until well blended.
ec1826f8-31d1-424e-9a86-c09f8cafe17e Spoon the batter into the prepared 10-inch tube pan or ​Bundt cake pan.
ec1826f8-31d1-424e-9a86-c09f8cafe17e Bake in the preheated 325 F oven for about 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 25 minutes, or until a wooden pick comes out clean when inserted in the center.
ec1826f8-31d1-424e-9a86-c09f8cafe17e Let it cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then invert the cake onto a rack to cool completely.
ec1826f8-31d1-424e-9a86-c09f8cafe17e To glaze the cake, place wax paper or parchment under the rack.
a07505ae-af3b-4d2b-a362-eb2e670ba53f Preheat the oven to 300 F. Grease and flour a 10 to 12-cup tube or Bundt cake pan.
a07505ae-af3b-4d2b-a362-eb2e670ba53f Combine the butter, shortening, and sugar in the bowl of a large stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment. Cream everything together on medium speed for 3-5 minutes, until light and fluffy.
a07505ae-af3b-4d2b-a362-eb2e670ba53f Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add the lemon extract to the cake batter and beat well.
a07505ae-af3b-4d2b-a362-eb2e670ba53f Turn the mixer to low and add a third of the flour, then once the flour is almost incorporated, add half of the 7-UP soda. Add half of the remaining flour, then the rest of the soda, and finish up by adding the last of the flour. Let the mixer run until almost all of the flour streaks have disappeared. Finish mixing the cake batter by hand, until it is homogenous and no dry patches remain.
a07505ae-af3b-4d2b-a362-eb2e670ba53f Scrape the batter into the prepared pan. Bake the 7-UP Cake for 75-90 minutes, or until cake tests done. If the top starts to look too dark before the center is cooked, cover it with loosely tented foil. Cool the cake in the pan for 30 minutes on a wire rack. Turn out the cake on to the rack, and cool completely before serving.
a07505ae-af3b-4d2b-a362-eb2e670ba53f Once cool, sprinkle a light dusting of powdered sugar over the entire cake.
a07505ae-af3b-4d2b-a362-eb2e670ba53f Alternately, you can skip the powdered sugar and make a lemon glaze for the cake. This is extra-delicious if you substitute 2 tablespoons of 7UP for the lemon juice. Bundt cakes keep very well, and this one is no exception. Store This 7-UP Pound Cake, well-wrapped, at room temperature for a week, in the refrigerator for two weeks, or for several months in the freezer.
e5e9fc17-7f80-4989-9b85-60de19166c2e Heat the oven to 325 F.
e5e9fc17-7f80-4989-9b85-60de19166c2e Generously butter a 12-cup Bundt cake pan, covering all the nooks and crannies. Dust with flour.
e5e9fc17-7f80-4989-9b85-60de19166c2e Combine the vegetable oil with sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
e5e9fc17-7f80-4989-9b85-60de19166c2e Combine the flour, salt, and baking soda together, and add to the first mixture.
e5e9fc17-7f80-4989-9b85-60de19166c2e Stir in the vanilla extract.
e5e9fc17-7f80-4989-9b85-60de19166c2e Fold in apples and nuts.
e5e9fc17-7f80-4989-9b85-60de19166c2e Spoon the batter into the prepared cake pan, and spread it evenly.
e5e9fc17-7f80-4989-9b85-60de19166c2e Bake in the preheated oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 hour and 20 minutes. A toothpick inserted into the cake should come out clean.
e5e9fc17-7f80-4989-9b85-60de19166c2e Cool the cake on a rack for 10 minutes in the pan; invert the cake onto a rack, and place it on a large sheet of foil or parchment paper.
e5e9fc17-7f80-4989-9b85-60de19166c2e When the cake has cooled completely, drizzle with your favorite icing or glaze, such as our caramel icing.
b683d6f4-5c4b-476e-8ef9-d1dd8aedbc62 Preheat oven to 350 F.
b683d6f4-5c4b-476e-8ef9-d1dd8aedbc62 In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar together.
b683d6f4-5c4b-476e-8ef9-d1dd8aedbc62 Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
b683d6f4-5c4b-476e-8ef9-d1dd8aedbc62 In a medium bowl, combine flours, baking powder, and salt.
b683d6f4-5c4b-476e-8ef9-d1dd8aedbc62 Working in 2 to 3 batches, combine flour mixture with butter mixture. Once all of the flour mixtures has been incorporated, mix in extracts.
b683d6f4-5c4b-476e-8ef9-d1dd8aedbc62 Coat Bundt pan with non-stick baking spray. Spoon batter into the bundt pan and spread out evenly.
b683d6f4-5c4b-476e-8ef9-d1dd8aedbc62 Bake in the oven at 350 F for 40 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
b683d6f4-5c4b-476e-8ef9-d1dd8aedbc62 Remove from oven and cool in the pan on a cooling rack for 15 minutes.
b683d6f4-5c4b-476e-8ef9-d1dd8aedbc62 After 15 minutes, invert cake onto cooling rack and cool completely. When ready to serve, dust with powdered sugar.
a7f4cd9f-665a-4871-b049-4bda79aeda1e Preheat oven to 350 F.
a7f4cd9f-665a-4871-b049-4bda79aeda1e Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan.
a7f4cd9f-665a-4871-b049-4bda79aeda1e Combine cake ingredients and mix for 2 minutes. Place batter in cake pan.
a7f4cd9f-665a-4871-b049-4bda79aeda1e Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour. Remove from oven and cool cake in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
a7f4cd9f-665a-4871-b049-4bda79aeda1e For the glaze: combine glaze ingredients over low to medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar and butter are melted.
a7f4cd9f-665a-4871-b049-4bda79aeda1e Carefully dump cake onto serving place. Poke holes in the top of cake. Evenly pour glaze over warm cake. Use spoon or pastry brush to completely cover the cake with the glaze that has dripped onto the plate. Don't cover cake while still warm.
a7f4cd9f-665a-4871-b049-4bda79aeda1e Serve with whipped cream.
bae218fb-e52b-469c-949e-777dd25048c3 Gather the ingredients.
bae218fb-e52b-469c-949e-777dd25048c3 Preheat the oven to 325 F.
bae218fb-e52b-469c-949e-777dd25048c3 Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt cake pan.
bae218fb-e52b-469c-949e-777dd25048c3 Combine the cake and pudding mixes with the eggs, 1/2 cup water, oil (or melted butter) and 1/2 cup limoncello. Mix the ingredients with an electric mixer for at least 2 minutes. Carefully pour into the prepared pan.
bae218fb-e52b-469c-949e-777dd25048c3 Bake the cake for 1 hour. Cool in pan on a wire rack for 20 minutes. Remove the cake from the pan to complete cooling on a wire rack.
bae218fb-e52b-469c-949e-777dd25048c3 Once the cake is completely cool, move it to a serving plate. Use a meat fork, or a kabob skewer to poke holes all over the cake.
bae218fb-e52b-469c-949e-777dd25048c3 In a small saucepan, melt the butter with the remaining water and sugar. Bring the butter mixture to a boil and boil it for 5 minutes. Remove your pot from the heat and stir in the remaining limoncello.
bae218fb-e52b-469c-949e-777dd25048c3 Carefully pour the glaze over the top of the cake. If necessary, use a pastry brush to brush on any of the glaze overflow. Immediately sprinkle almonds on top of the cake.
bae218fb-e52b-469c-949e-777dd25048c3 Store the Limoncello Bundt Cake in an airtight container.
bae218fb-e52b-469c-949e-777dd25048c3 Serve and enjoy!
35a7e0e7-6d24-4281-8adb-979a389b0df9 Gather the ingredients.
35a7e0e7-6d24-4281-8adb-979a389b0df9 Heat oven to 325 F. Generously grease and flour a 10- to 12-cup bundt cake pan. Get all the nooks and crannies.
35a7e0e7-6d24-4281-8adb-979a389b0df9 In a bowl, combine the flour, oats, baking powder, soda, salt, and spices; set aside.
35a7e0e7-6d24-4281-8adb-979a389b0df9 In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream the butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
35a7e0e7-6d24-4281-8adb-979a389b0df9 Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add the vanilla and blend well.
35a7e0e7-6d24-4281-8adb-979a389b0df9 Slowly beat in the dry ingredients, alternating with the buttermilk and ending with the dry ingredients.
35a7e0e7-6d24-4281-8adb-979a389b0df9 Stir in shredded zucchini and nuts.
35a7e0e7-6d24-4281-8adb-979a389b0df9 Spoon the batter into the prepared Bundt cake pan.
35a7e0e7-6d24-4281-8adb-979a389b0df9 Bake the cake for 65 to 75 minutes, or until golden brown and a cake tester or toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
35a7e0e7-6d24-4281-8adb-979a389b0df9 Cool on a rack for 10 minutes; invert onto a serving plate to cool completely.
35a7e0e7-6d24-4281-8adb-979a389b0df9 Drizzle a glaze over the cake (see below) or dust with powdered sugar.
8602fb2b-bab4-49dd-81d5-db16961ab9a5 Preheat oven to 350 F. Spray a 12" bundt pan (nonstick too) with a nonstick baking spray containing flour and set aside.
8602fb2b-bab4-49dd-81d5-db16961ab9a5 In a small bowl, beat egg white until foamy. Gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar until stiff peaks form. Fold in coconut, 1 tbsp. flour, 1 tsp. vanilla, and chocolate chips. Set aside.
8602fb2b-bab4-49dd-81d5-db16961ab9a5 In a large bowl, place 2 cups flour, 1 1/4 cups sugar, brown sugar, cocoa, salt, baking soda, 2 tsp. vanilla, 3 eggs, 1 egg yolk, milk, butter, and sour cream. With the same beaters, mix this batter on low until combined, then beat on medium-high for 3 minutes.
8602fb2b-bab4-49dd-81d5-db16961ab9a5 Spoon one-third of the cake batter into the prepared pan. Drop half of the coconut filling by teaspoons in the center of the batter, keeping the filling away from the edges of the pan. Cover filling with one-third of the remaining cake batter and top with the rest of the coconut filling. Carefully cover the coconut filling with the rest of the batter and spread evenly to cover.
8602fb2b-bab4-49dd-81d5-db16961ab9a5 Bake the cake at 350 F for 55 to 65 minutes until the cake is set, edges start pulling away from the pan, and a toothpick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean. Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then loosen edges and invert cake onto a serving plate. Cool completely.
be1075ab-0da0-4838-83f4-28d46516f3ba Gather the ingredients.
be1075ab-0da0-4838-83f4-28d46516f3ba Preheat oven to 350 F.
be1075ab-0da0-4838-83f4-28d46516f3ba Grease and flour 12-cup bundt cake pan.
be1075ab-0da0-4838-83f4-28d46516f3ba Place all ingredients, except chocolate glaze, in a large bowl. Mix on low for 1 minute. Mix for another 3 minutes on medium until completely combines.
be1075ab-0da0-4838-83f4-28d46516f3ba Pour batter into prepared pan and bake for 50-60 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove cake from pan and cool completely.
be1075ab-0da0-4838-83f4-28d46516f3ba Top cake with Chocolate Glaze.
be1075ab-0da0-4838-83f4-28d46516f3ba Serve and enjoy!
882bcb8a-26ed-45ff-a621-a98471462bb3 Gather the ingredients.
882bcb8a-26ed-45ff-a621-a98471462bb3 Place the rack in the middle of the oven and preheat to 350 F. Grease and flour a Bundt pan or kugelhopf pan or a babka pan.
882bcb8a-26ed-45ff-a621-a98471462bb3 Beat butter and sugar together until creamy.
882bcb8a-26ed-45ff-a621-a98471462bb3 Sift together flour and baking powder. Alternately, add eggs and flour to the batter until all are combined. Stir in vanilla.
882bcb8a-26ed-45ff-a621-a98471462bb3 Place 1/3 of cake batter into a separate mixing bowl and stir in cocoa powder and juice of 1/2 orange.
882bcb8a-26ed-45ff-a621-a98471462bb3 In the original bowl containing the majority of the batter, stir in all of the orange zest and the juice of the remaining 1/2 orange.
882bcb8a-26ed-45ff-a621-a98471462bb3 Spread 1/3 of orange batter evenly in the bottom of the prepared Bundt pan.
882bcb8a-26ed-45ff-a621-a98471462bb3 Gently dribble half of the chocolate batter on top with a spoon or frosting bag. Repeat layers, ending with orange batter on top.
882bcb8a-26ed-45ff-a621-a98471462bb3 Bake on the center rack of the oven for 1 hour. Remove from the oven and let cool on a wire rack for 20 minutes.
882bcb8a-26ed-45ff-a621-a98471462bb3 Then invert onto the wire rack to cool completely.
882bcb8a-26ed-45ff-a621-a98471462bb3 Serve and enjoy!
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 Gather the ingredients.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 Preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 Generously grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or nonstick Bundt cake pan.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 In a medium bowl, combine 1 1/4 cups brown sugar, 3/4 cup flour, the cold butter pieces, and cinnamon. Mix with a fork until crumbly, and butter is blended in well. Stir in chopped pecans.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 In a bowl, combine 3 2/4 cups flour, baking powder, baking soda.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla extract and vanilla yogurt.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 With the mixer on low speed, beat in the dry ingredients just until blended.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 Spoon about 3 cups of the batter into the prepared pan. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of the streusel mixture and the apples, then 1/2 cup of the streusel mixture.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 Spoon remaining batter over streusel apple layer.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 Top with remaining streusel. Press streusel down into batter lightly.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 Bake cake in the preheated oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until a wooden pick or cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 Cool for 5 minutes in the pan.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 Hold a baking sheet over the top of the cake and carefully invert it. Remove tube pan or bundt pan; cool completely. Move to a serving plate and ice with vanilla glaze, if desired.
30aaec71-21b1-4a6c-ab74-ecddb402ce38 Serve and enjoy!
975db3a8-c506-4888-bc5c-659e342ec2e3 Gather the ingredients.
975db3a8-c506-4888-bc5c-659e342ec2e3 Heat the oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4). Grease and flour a 10-inch tube cake pan or Bundt cake pan or spray it with baking spray with flour.
975db3a8-c506-4888-bc5c-659e342ec2e3 Into a medium bowl sift together the flour, salt, baking powder, and baking soda; set aside.
975db3a8-c506-4888-bc5c-659e342ec2e3 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed, beat the sugar and vegetable oil until well blended. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add the vanilla and beat to blend.
975db3a8-c506-4888-bc5c-659e342ec2e3 With the mixer on low speed, gradually beat in the sifted flour mixture until well blended. Add the grated carrots, chopped pecans or walnuts, coconut, maraschino cherries, and the mashed bananas. Stir to mix the ingredients thoroughly; spoon the batter into the prepared tube cake pan.
975db3a8-c506-4888-bc5c-659e342ec2e3 Bake the cake for 1 hour, or until it tests done (a wooden pick inserted in center should come out clean).
975db3a8-c506-4888-bc5c-659e342ec2e3 Cool the cake in the pan on a rack for 10 minutes, then carefully remove it from the pan and cool completely on the rack.
975db3a8-c506-4888-bc5c-659e342ec2e3 While the cake is cooling, prepare the frosting.
975db3a8-c506-4888-bc5c-659e342ec2e3 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the butter, cream cheese, and confectioners' sugar until smooth and creamy. Add milk, a few teaspoons at a time, until the frosting is a good spreading consistency. With a spoon, fold in the chopped pecans or walnuts and then spread the frosting over the cooled cake.
98392283-3afb-4b96-b9ca-9bf4f373b057 Pre-heat the oven to 350 F and butter and flour a bundt or tube style pan.
98392283-3afb-4b96-b9ca-9bf4f373b057 Using a hand or stand mixer, beat together the eggs and sugar until lightened in color.
98392283-3afb-4b96-b9ca-9bf4f373b057 Beat in the butter, vanilla, and yogurt. Stir in the food coloring, if using.
98392283-3afb-4b96-b9ca-9bf4f373b057 Add the pistachios to a food processor and pulse until ground
98392283-3afb-4b96-b9ca-9bf4f373b057 In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, ground pistachios, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
98392283-3afb-4b96-b9ca-9bf4f373b057 Beat the dry ingredients into the wet and pour the batter into the prepared pan.
98392283-3afb-4b96-b9ca-9bf4f373b057 Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
98392283-3afb-4b96-b9ca-9bf4f373b057 Make the glaze by whisking together the powdered sugar, milk, cardamom, and salt until smooth.
98392283-3afb-4b96-b9ca-9bf4f373b057 Drizzle over the cooled cake and sprinkle on some additional chopped pistachios, if desired.
c226acb3-d889-4d15-ac14-e1b4d4f6cbe8 Preheat oven to 350 F.
c226acb3-d889-4d15-ac14-e1b4d4f6cbe8 Whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in mixing bowl for 30 seconds; reserve. Cream the butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs one at a time, mixing thoroughly before adding the next. Beat in sour cream and vanilla. Add the flour mixture, stirring until combined. Stir in walnuts.
c226acb3-d889-4d15-ac14-e1b4d4f6cbe8 Butter a 10-inch bundt pan, and dust with flour. Pour half the batter into the pan and spread evenly. Mix the swirl ingredients in a small bowl. Sprinkle around the center of the batter, and cover with the rest of the batter.
c226acb3-d889-4d15-ac14-e1b4d4f6cbe8 Bake for 50 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
c226acb3-d889-4d15-ac14-e1b4d4f6cbe8 For the glaze: Add the powdered sugar to a mixing bowl, stir in enough milk to create a thick glaze. Stir in the cinnamon to taste. Drizzle over the top of the cake. Once the icing is set, slice and serve with hot coffee.
85fb8de0-3377-4d28-916e-2ff7c4e429cc Heat the oven to 350 F.
85fb8de0-3377-4d28-916e-2ff7c4e429cc Generously grease and flour a 10- to 12-cup Bundt pan.
85fb8de0-3377-4d28-916e-2ff7c4e429cc Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium-low heat; add cocoa, stirring until smooth. Whisk in the water and remove from heat. To the warm cocoa mixture, add the sugar, sour cream, 1 tablespoon vanilla, and eggs; whisk until smooth. In another bowl combine the flour, soda, and salt. Add all at once to the first mixture, whisking until well blended.
85fb8de0-3377-4d28-916e-2ff7c4e429cc Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until it feels firm to the touch and has slightly pulled away from the sides of the pan. Cool in pan on a rack for 20 minutes. Carefully loosen the cake with a knife and invert onto a large plate.
55309221-086a-452c-a56b-a4a659832756 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Spray a 12-inch Bundt pan with a nonstick baking spray containing flour (even nonstick pans) and set aside.
55309221-086a-452c-a56b-a4a659832756 In a large bowl combine the flour, brown sugar, sugar, 1 cup peanut butter, butter, baking powder, baking soda, milk, vanilla, and eggs, and beat on low speed until combined; then beat three minutes at medium speed until the batter expands slightly, is lighter, and smooth. By hand, stir in 1/2 cup of the chocolate chips. Spoon the batter into the prepared pan.
55309221-086a-452c-a56b-a4a659832756 Bake the cake at 350 F for 55 to 65 minutes until set, brown, and a toothpick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean (except some chocolate might stick to the toothpick). Cool the cake in the pan for 10 minutes, then loosen the edges and turn the cake onto a serving plate or cake plate. Cool the cake completely, then frost.
55309221-086a-452c-a56b-a4a659832756 For frosting, in a small saucepan, melt 1-1/2 cups chocolate chips with 1/3 cup of the peanut butter. You can also melt these two ingredients in a small bowl in the microwave oven for 2 minutes at 50% power, stirring until smooth. Spoon the frosting over the cake and let stand until the frosting sets. Slice the cake into wedges to serve.
3406b23a-3b5f-4fb0-a622-f7ddab0ca72b Heat oven to 350 F. Coat 10-cup Bundt pan with cooking spray and set aside. Drain the mandarin oranges, reserving juice.
3406b23a-3b5f-4fb0-a622-f7ddab0ca72b In a large bowl, combine cake mix, reserved juice from can of mandarin oranges, eggs, oil, and grated orange zest. Beat for 2 minutes. Pour 1/3 of batter in prepared pan and layer half of the drained mandarin oranges on top. Pour another 1/3 of the cake batter into the pan and layer with remaining mandarin oranges. Pour last third of cake batter into the pan.
3406b23a-3b5f-4fb0-a622-f7ddab0ca72b Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in the pan for 20 minutes. Remove from pan onto wire rack and cool completely.
3406b23a-3b5f-4fb0-a622-f7ddab0ca72b When completely cool, dust with confectioners' sugar or brush on the glaze.
3406b23a-3b5f-4fb0-a622-f7ddab0ca72b To make the glaze, combine reserved juice from the orange and confectioner's sugar in a small bowl until well blended. Gently brush glaze all over cake with a pastry brush.
ce1b77cb-2721-44fa-b6fd-db1095023e13 Preheat oven to 350 F.
ce1b77cb-2721-44fa-b6fd-db1095023e13 Cream together butter, shortening, 1/2 cup brown sugar, and the granulated sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, and baking soda. Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with the 1 cup milk. Fold in chopped apple.
ce1b77cb-2721-44fa-b6fd-db1095023e13 Pour batter into a generously buttered and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch bundt baking pan. Combine 1/2 cup chopped pecans with 1/2 cup brown sugar; sprinkle over top of the cake.
ce1b77cb-2721-44fa-b6fd-db1095023e13 Bake at 350 F for about 30 to 40 minutes, or until done. The cake will bounce back when lightly touched in center.
8e3dd054-37e7-4a2f-9222-82a4f04763fb Heat oven to 350 F.
8e3dd054-37e7-4a2f-9222-82a4f04763fb Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt cake pan or 10-inch tube cake pan.
8e3dd054-37e7-4a2f-9222-82a4f04763fb In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the butter and sugar until light (about 3 to 4 minutes).
8e3dd054-37e7-4a2f-9222-82a4f04763fb Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla.
8e3dd054-37e7-4a2f-9222-82a4f04763fb In another bowl, combine the flour, salt, baking powder, and soda; whisk to blend thoroughly.
8e3dd054-37e7-4a2f-9222-82a4f04763fb With the mixer on low, add the dry ingredients, about 1 cup at a time, to the creamed mixture, alternating with the sour cream and orange juice and ending with the flour. Mix until well blended.
8e3dd054-37e7-4a2f-9222-82a4f04763fb Spoon the batter into the prepared baking pan.
8e3dd054-37e7-4a2f-9222-82a4f04763fb Bake in the preheated oven for 45 to 50 minutes, or until a cake tester or wooden pick comes out clean when inserted in center of the cake.
8e3dd054-37e7-4a2f-9222-82a4f04763fb Cool the cake for 10 minutes in the pan on a rack. Turn it out onto a cake plate and let it cool completely before slicing.
ad106353-c844-40ed-af39-66f482cd750b Heat oven to 350 F. In a medium bowl, gently toss blueberries and zest, if using, with flour and set aside.
ad106353-c844-40ed-af39-66f482cd750b In a large bowl, combine cake mix and sour cream. Add eggs one at a time, beating at low speed after each addition. Continue to beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Fold in blueberries and zest.
ad106353-c844-40ed-af39-66f482cd750b Coat a 10-inch Bundt pan with cooking spray. Transfer batter to pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick tests clean. Cool in pan on a wire rack for 15 minutes before inverting. Cool completely. Dust with confectioners' sugar or pour on lemon glaze. Serve with blueberry sauce, if desired.
1b0d6fc0-ef5f-47dd-af74-1a0ca802aaee Grease and flour a bundt cake pan or tube cake pan. Heat oven to 325 F.
1b0d6fc0-ef5f-47dd-af74-1a0ca802aaee Cream sugars and butter until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla.
1b0d6fc0-ef5f-47dd-af74-1a0ca802aaee Sift together the cake flour and salt into a separate bowl.
1b0d6fc0-ef5f-47dd-af74-1a0ca802aaee In a third, smaller bowl, combine the sour cream and baking soda.
1b0d6fc0-ef5f-47dd-af74-1a0ca802aaee Blend dry ingredients into the creamed mixture a little at a time, alternating additions with the sour cream and baking soda mixture, ending with the flour mixture.
1b0d6fc0-ef5f-47dd-af74-1a0ca802aaee Spoon the batter into the prepared baking pan. Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until a cake tester or wooden pick comes out clean when inserted in the center of the cake.
1b0d6fc0-ef5f-47dd-af74-1a0ca802aaee Cool in pan or rack for 10 minutes.
1b0d6fc0-ef5f-47dd-af74-1a0ca802aaee Invert onto a serving plate and cool completely.
1b0d6fc0-ef5f-47dd-af74-1a0ca802aaee Drizzle with a glaze or dust with powdered sugar.
1b33768e-5aa2-4e47-8ef3-2eb3f834c7fd Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F.
1b33768e-5aa2-4e47-8ef3-2eb3f834c7fd Lightly grease and flour a 12-cup bundt pan with dairy-free soy margarine or oil and all-purpose flour. Set aside.
1b33768e-5aa2-4e47-8ef3-2eb3f834c7fd In a small bowl or cup, whisk together the soy milk and lemon juice (or cider vinegar, if using). Allow mixture to rest for at least 5 minutes or until thick. Set aside.
1b33768e-5aa2-4e47-8ef3-2eb3f834c7fd In a separate small mixing bowl, combine the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, and salt until well mixed. Set aside.
1b33768e-5aa2-4e47-8ef3-2eb3f834c7fd In a large mixing bowl, use an electric mixer to beat together the sugar, maple syrup, canola oil, and vanilla extract until smooth.
1b33768e-5aa2-4e47-8ef3-2eb3f834c7fd Add the pumpkin puree and beat again until smooth.
1b33768e-5aa2-4e47-8ef3-2eb3f834c7fd Add the flour mixture and the soy milk mixture in several additions until all ingredients have been added, alternating between the flour mixture and the soy milk mixture and ending with the flour mixture. Mix until just combined.
1b33768e-5aa2-4e47-8ef3-2eb3f834c7fd Carefully pour the batter into the prepared bundt pan.
1b33768e-5aa2-4e47-8ef3-2eb3f834c7fd Place the pan in the preheated oven on the middle rack and bake for 60 to 70 minutes, or until the surface of the cake springs back slightly when touched or a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake emerges clean.
1b33768e-5aa2-4e47-8ef3-2eb3f834c7fd Allow the cake to cool for 30 minutes in the pan on a wire cooling rack, then gently remove the cake from the pan, invert on a wire cooling rack, and allow the cake to cool completely.
1b33768e-5aa2-4e47-8ef3-2eb3f834c7fd Once cake the is cooled, ice with vegan ganache.
1b33768e-5aa2-4e47-8ef3-2eb3f834c7fd Serve and enjoy!
270ac05c-2f88-427f-b9b8-22f48c31a3ab Grease and flour a 9-inch square baking pan. Heat the oven to 400 F.
270ac05c-2f88-427f-b9b8-22f48c31a3ab Combine the flour, salt, baking powder, and 1/3 cup of sugar; add 1 to 2 teaspoons of orange zest. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
270ac05c-2f88-427f-b9b8-22f48c31a3ab In another bowl whisk together the milk, orange juice, egg, and vanilla; add all at once then stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
270ac05c-2f88-427f-b9b8-22f48c31a3ab Spread the batter in the prepared baking pan.
577e86aa-f1bb-412e-9735-f5674dd6288e Gather the ingredients.
577e86aa-f1bb-412e-9735-f5674dd6288e Place the rack in the middle of the oven and preheat to 350 F. Grease and flour a Bundt pan or kugelhopf pan or a babka pan.
577e86aa-f1bb-412e-9735-f5674dd6288e Beat butter and sugar together until creamy.
577e86aa-f1bb-412e-9735-f5674dd6288e Sift together flour and baking powder. Alternately, add eggs and flour to the batter until all are combined. Stir in vanilla.
577e86aa-f1bb-412e-9735-f5674dd6288e Place 1/3 of cake batter into a separate mixing bowl and stir in cocoa powder and juice of 1/2 orange.
577e86aa-f1bb-412e-9735-f5674dd6288e In the original bowl containing the majority of the batter, stir in all of the orange zest and the juice of the remaining 1/2 orange.
577e86aa-f1bb-412e-9735-f5674dd6288e Spread 1/3 of orange batter evenly in the bottom of the prepared Bundt pan.
577e86aa-f1bb-412e-9735-f5674dd6288e Gently dribble half of the chocolate batter on top with a spoon or frosting bag. Repeat layers, ending with orange batter on top.
577e86aa-f1bb-412e-9735-f5674dd6288e Bake on the center rack of the oven for 1 hour. Remove from the oven and let cool on a wire rack for 20 minutes.
577e86aa-f1bb-412e-9735-f5674dd6288e Then invert onto the wire rack to cool completely.
577e86aa-f1bb-412e-9735-f5674dd6288e Serve and enjoy!
ea022c83-6f39-4a18-8e43-1518045a71c5 Gather the ingredients.
ea022c83-6f39-4a18-8e43-1518045a71c5 Preheat the oven to 375 F.
ea022c83-6f39-4a18-8e43-1518045a71c5 Into a medium bowl, sift together 2 cups of flour, the granulated sugar, baking powder, and salt. Cut in 1/3 cup of butter with a pastry blender to make a fine crumbly mixture. Add the beaten egg and milk; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
ea022c83-6f39-4a18-8e43-1518045a71c5 Spoon batter into a generously buttered 9-inch square pan. Spoon both kinds of preserves over the batter and then swirl it through the batter with a knife.
ea022c83-6f39-4a18-8e43-1518045a71c5 Mix topping ingredients with fork or fingers until crumbly and sprinkle evenly over batter.
ea022c83-6f39-4a18-8e43-1518045a71c5 Bake in the preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.
ea022c83-6f39-4a18-8e43-1518045a71c5 Cut into squares and serve while still warm.
ea022c83-6f39-4a18-8e43-1518045a71c5 Enjoy!
415dc708-76c2-4835-ade7-5097a977756e Gather the ingredients.
415dc708-76c2-4835-ade7-5097a977756e Preheat the oven to 350 F. Grease one loaf pan with cooking spray.
415dc708-76c2-4835-ade7-5097a977756e Start by making the streusel topping. Simply melt the butter and whisk it together with the sugar, brown sugar, flour, and pumpkin pie spice. Set the streusel mixture aside while you make the coffee cake
415dc708-76c2-4835-ade7-5097a977756e In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, sugar, brown sugar, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder, and salt.
415dc708-76c2-4835-ade7-5097a977756e After you have melted the butter and let it cool, measure the milk in a measuring cup and add the butter. Whisk in the two eggs, pumpkin puree, and vanilla extract until completely combined.
415dc708-76c2-4835-ade7-5097a977756e Combine the wet mixture with the dry mixture in the large bowl, until completely combined. Be careful not to overbeat the mixture. Just mix until combined and all of the ingredients are moistened.
415dc708-76c2-4835-ade7-5097a977756e Pour the coffee cake mixture into the greased loaf pan.
415dc708-76c2-4835-ade7-5097a977756e Spread the top to make it even. Top with an even coating of the streusel topping. Place in the middle rack of the oven and bake for about 35 to 40 minutes. Check for doneness by sticking a toothpick in the center of the loaf. If it comes out clean, the loaf is done!
415dc708-76c2-4835-ade7-5097a977756e Serve and enjoy!
85e672d8-c88f-49c3-948e-7604cda31e09 Place sugar and butter in a large bowl or stand mixer. Scald the milk and pour it into the bowl with sugar and butter. Stir until butter is completely melted. Let cool to 110 F.
85e672d8-c88f-49c3-948e-7604cda31e09 Add yeast and mix well.
85e672d8-c88f-49c3-948e-7604cda31e09 Add egg-salt mixture and half the flour, stirring constantly.
85e672d8-c88f-49c3-948e-7604cda31e09 Add the vanilla and raisins, if using, and mix well.
85e672d8-c88f-49c3-948e-7604cda31e09 Add the remaining flour and mix well. The dough will be sticky.
85e672d8-c88f-49c3-948e-7604cda31e09 Turn out into a greased bowl and cover with greased plastic wrap. Let rise until doubled.
85e672d8-c88f-49c3-948e-7604cda31e09 Grease two (9-by-5-inch) loaf pans and make the crumb topping in a medium bowl by combining flour and sugar, and cutting in the butter with your fingers. Set aside.
85e672d8-c88f-49c3-948e-7604cda31e09 Using slightly dampened hands, punch down dough and divide it in half.
85e672d8-c88f-49c3-948e-7604cda31e09 Place in prepared pans. Sprinkle half the crumb topping on each cake. Place on a baking sheet to catch any crumbs that fall off while baking, cover with greased plastic wrap, and let rise until dough mounds slightly over the top.
85e672d8-c88f-49c3-948e-7604cda31e09 Heat oven to 300 F and bake for 50 minutes or until the instant-read thermometer registers 190 F.
85e672d8-c88f-49c3-948e-7604cda31e09 Remove from oven and cool in pan for 5 minutes.
85e672d8-c88f-49c3-948e-7604cda31e09 Then turn out and cool coffee cakes completely on their side on a wire rack.
a8357e4a-e4c3-4b09-85ac-acee77333710 Gather the ingredients.
a8357e4a-e4c3-4b09-85ac-acee77333710 Heat the oven to 350 F.
a8357e4a-e4c3-4b09-85ac-acee77333710 Generously butter and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
a8357e4a-e4c3-4b09-85ac-acee77333710 In a large mixing bowl, cream butter, 1 1/2 cups of sugar, and sour cream until light and fluffy.
a8357e4a-e4c3-4b09-85ac-acee77333710 Add the eggs and vanilla to the creamed mixture and beat well.
a8357e4a-e4c3-4b09-85ac-acee77333710 Combine the flour, baking powder, soda, and salt in a separate bowl and whisk or stir to blend thoroughly. Add the dry mixture to the mixing bowl and beat until blended.
a8357e4a-e4c3-4b09-85ac-acee77333710 Make topping/filling mixture by combining chopped nuts, 2 teaspoons of sugar, and cinnamon.
a8357e4a-e4c3-4b09-85ac-acee77333710 In the bottom of the prepared tube pan put about one-third of topping mixture. Alternate layers of batter and topping, ending with batter.
a8357e4a-e4c3-4b09-85ac-acee77333710 Bake the coffee cake in the preheated oven for 45 minutes, or until a toothpick or wooden skewer inserted into the center comes out clean.
fc90c0e5-6999-4699-b4ba-b19f28c8f398 Preheat an oven to 325 F. Butter an 8-by-8 baking pan and set it aside.
fc90c0e5-6999-4699-b4ba-b19f28c8f398 In a large bowl or the bowl of a standing mixer, cream the butter and brown sugar, scraping down the sides of the bowl as needed, until light and fluffy looking, about 2 minutes.
fc90c0e5-6999-4699-b4ba-b19f28c8f398 Add the eggs, one at a time, beating for 30 seconds after each addition. This step builds the structure of the cake, so don't skip it and don't rush it.
fc90c0e5-6999-4699-b4ba-b19f28c8f398 Stir in the vanilla and then the squash.
fc90c0e5-6999-4699-b4ba-b19f28c8f398 In a small bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and spices. Add to the squash mixture and stir just until completely combined. To keep the cake tender, be careful not to overmix at this point, it will develop the gluten in the flour and toughen the cake. It will be a thick batter.
fc90c0e5-6999-4699-b4ba-b19f28c8f398 Pour the batter into the buttered pan. Bake until the cake is golden and a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes.
fc90c0e5-6999-4699-b4ba-b19f28c8f398 Let the cake cool at least 10 minutes before cutting. Serve warm or at room temperature.
e491511e-3e8b-4daa-af39-d85b03b3db65 Gather the ingredients.
e491511e-3e8b-4daa-af39-d85b03b3db65 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Lightly grease an 8" x 8" cake pan with dairy-free soy margarine and set aside.
e491511e-3e8b-4daa-af39-d85b03b3db65 In a large mixing bowl, sift together the flours, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt and set aside. In another small mixing bowl, whisk together the almond milk, canola oil, apple cider vinegar and vanilla until well mixed. Add the wet ingredients and the Egg Replacer mixture to the dry, mixing until just combined (do not overmix!). Fold in 1 cup of the blueberries and pour the batter into the prepared pan. Arrange the remaining 1 cup blueberries on top of the batter.
e491511e-3e8b-4daa-af39-d85b03b3db65 Make the topping. In a small mixing bowl, mix together the brown sugar, cake flour, ​and cinnamon. Using a pastry cutter or fork, cut in the pieces of soy margarine until the mixture resembles a crumbly topping. Sprinkle the mixture evenly over the cake. Bake on a middle rack in the oven for 35-40 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake emerges clean and the top is golden brown. Allow the cake too cool on a wire cooling rack. Serve warm or at room temperature.
b9b316c8-1808-4a99-9e61-184ca5b4856b Heat oven to 400 F. Butter an 8-inch square baking pan.
b9b316c8-1808-4a99-9e61-184ca5b4856b To make the cake: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, sugar, salt, and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
b9b316c8-1808-4a99-9e61-184ca5b4856b In a separate bowl, mix egg, milk and melted butter until well combined. Pour into dry ingredients, add the pears and mix well. Pour into prepared pan.
b9b316c8-1808-4a99-9e61-184ca5b4856b To make the streusel: In a small bowl, mix sugar and flour and cut in butter with your fingers until crumbs form. Sprinkle over top of batter in pan.
b9b316c8-1808-4a99-9e61-184ca5b4856b Bake 30 to 35 minutes until golden and dry on top. Cool in pan and cut into 8 squares. This cake keeps for up to 4 days, covered at room temperature.
f5fdb77f-ce3f-4c16-87c3-332097e4ff30 Preheat the oven to 275 F. Grease a 22cm square tin and line with greaseproof paper.
f5fdb77f-ce3f-4c16-87c3-332097e4ff30 In a small saucepan, slowly melt the butter, golden syrup and black treacle. Do not boil, the mixture, it just needs to be warm. Once melted give the mixture a good stir.
