f5fdb77f-ce3f-4c16-87c3-332097e4ff30 Sieve the flour, sugar, ginger, and bicarbonate of soda into a large baking bowl. Slowly pour the melted butter mixture into the dry ingredients and stir thoroughly. The batter will be very stiff and unyielding, but don't worry.
f5fdb77f-ce3f-4c16-87c3-332097e4ff30 Mix the egg and milk together in a jug.
f5fdb77f-ce3f-4c16-87c3-332097e4ff30 Very slowly pour the milk and egg into the thick batter while constantly stirring. The batter will gradually slacken and thin out. Keep stirring until smooth and shiny.
f5fdb77f-ce3f-4c16-87c3-332097e4ff30 Pour the thick batter into your prepared tin.
f5fdb77f-ce3f-4c16-87c3-332097e4ff30 Pop the cake into the center of the preheated oven and cook for about 1 hour. The cake will rise and start to turn golden brown. The cake is cooked when you a skewer inserted into the cake comes out clean.
f5fdb77f-ce3f-4c16-87c3-332097e4ff30 Once cooked, take the cake from the oven and leave it to cool in the tin placed on a cooling rack. Now for the difficult bit.
f5fdb77f-ce3f-4c16-87c3-332097e4ff30 Once the cake is cooled, remove from the tin, wrap tightly in foil and put away for 3 - 4 days to help the cake mature and become sticky and so even more delicious. If you are impatient, of course, you can eat it but if you wait, it is well worth it.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F. Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with non-stick cooking spray or softened butter. Line the bottom with parchment paper.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 In a medium-sized bowl, combine the oil and sugar and whisk vigorously to combine.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 Add the eggs, then the yolks, one at a time, whisking after each addition.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 Whisk in the vanilla and the sour cream and whisk a final time to combine.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 In a medium mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and salt and whisk to combine.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 Add the dry ingredients to the wet in three installments, gently folding with a flexible spatula after each.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 Transfer the batter to the prepared pan and decoratively place the pineapple chunks on top.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 Place the cake in the preheated oven for about 55 minutes, rotating the cake at 30 minutes. The cake can be pulled from the oven when a tester inserted in the center comes out with only a moist crumb or two.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 Let the cake cool for 20 minutes or so, then invert the cake onto a cooling rack. Let cool to room temperature before frosting.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 To make the frosting, place the butter in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment and beat on low to medium-low until smooth, about 2 minutes.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 Begin slowly adding the sugar, about a cup at a time, alternating with the heavy cream, and keeping the mixer at the same low-ish speed.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 Continue slowly mixing in this fashion (adding sugar and cream, scraping with a flexible spatula periodically, and taking time to let the mixer run between additions), until most of the sugar and cream has been incorporated.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 Add the vinegar and salt and mix again.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 Add the remaining sugar and cream and slowly add the pineapple syrup, a couple of tablespoons at a time, mixing on medium-low (at the highest) for at least 5 to 10 minutes, if not longer. The frosting will be quite light, creamy, and fluffy when it is done.
a3cfe7c8-3a94-4b68-9939-94ecc07c8003 Generously frost the cake before serving.
cbf4e1de-73dd-4124-ab45-026382c91589 Gather the ingredients.
cbf4e1de-73dd-4124-ab45-026382c91589 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Spray an 8-inch square or round cake pan with a nonstick baking spray containing flour.
cbf4e1de-73dd-4124-ab45-026382c91589 In a medium bowl, combine the cake mix, water, oil, and egg. Mix until combined, then beat for 1 minute at medium speed.
cbf4e1de-73dd-4124-ab45-026382c91589 Pour the cake batter into the prepared pan.
cbf4e1de-73dd-4124-ab45-026382c91589 Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean. The cake should also be pulling away from the sides of the pan.
cbf4e1de-73dd-4124-ab45-026382c91589 Let the cake cool completely on a wire rack, then frost or dust with powdered sugar.
e50b3372-b556-46df-9051-0e7e683ded9a Cream butter with 1 cup of the sugar until light and fluffy.
e50b3372-b556-46df-9051-0e7e683ded9a Beat in egg yolks.
e50b3372-b556-46df-9051-0e7e683ded9a Sift together the dry ingredients; add to the first mixture alternately with sour cream, beating until smooth.
e50b3372-b556-46df-9051-0e7e683ded9a Stir in orange zest and chopped pecans.
e50b3372-b556-46df-9051-0e7e683ded9a Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
e50b3372-b556-46df-9051-0e7e683ded9a Pour batter into a buttered 9-inch tube pan and bake at 350 F for 45 to 50 minutes.
e50b3372-b556-46df-9051-0e7e683ded9a Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar with orange juice and Grand Marnier; pour over hot cake.
e50b3372-b556-46df-9051-0e7e683ded9a Decorate top with pecan halves. Cool on rack before removing from pan.
552ae7c1-68c1-4000-984e-af41746896b9 Butter two 9-inch layer cake pans; line the bottoms waxed paper then butter the paper.
552ae7c1-68c1-4000-984e-af41746896b9 Measure the flour and sift it with the baking powder into a bowl.
552ae7c1-68c1-4000-984e-af41746896b9 In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter until light, then gradually add the sugar, beating until creamy.
552ae7c1-68c1-4000-984e-af41746896b9 Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
552ae7c1-68c1-4000-984e-af41746896b9 Stir in the flour mixture, a little at a time, alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir well after each addition, but do not beat. Stir in the vanilla extract.
552ae7c1-68c1-4000-984e-af41746896b9 Turn the batter into prepared cake pans.
552ae7c1-68c1-4000-984e-af41746896b9 Bake in a preheated 325 F oven until the cakes spring back when lightly touched near the center with a finger, about 35 minutes.
552ae7c1-68c1-4000-984e-af41746896b9 Cool layers 10 minutes in the pans, then turn out onto cake racks to cool completely.
061e19e7-21c7-48d5-a8fd-624335e9026e Preheat oven to 350 F.
061e19e7-21c7-48d5-a8fd-624335e9026e Sift together the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, baking soda, and spices.
061e19e7-21c7-48d5-a8fd-624335e9026e Stir in melted butter, molasses, egg, and buttermilk or sour milk.
061e19e7-21c7-48d5-a8fd-624335e9026e Beat in hot water.
061e19e7-21c7-48d5-a8fd-624335e9026e Pour batter into a generously greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
061e19e7-21c7-48d5-a8fd-624335e9026e Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, until cake springs back when lightly touched with finger.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Gather the ingredients.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Heat the oven to 350 F. Grease and flour a 10-by-15-inch sheet cake pan or jelly roll pan.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Shred the zucchini in a food processor with a shredding disk or by hand using a box grater. Measure 2 cups of shredded zucchini into a bowl and set aside.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d In a medium bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, and nutmeg. Mix well with a whisk or spoon and set aside.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer beat the brown sugar and granulated sugar with the 1 stick of softened butter and sour cream until smooth.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in the vanilla.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Gradually beat in the flour mixture until well blended.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Stir in the shredded zucchini.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Spread the batter in the prepared baking pan.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Bake in the preheated oven for 20 to 24 minutes, or until the cake is golden brown and bounces back when lightly touched with a finger.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Remove the pan to a rack and cool completely before frosting.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Meanwhile, make the frosting. In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese with the 6 tablespoons of butter until smooth and fluffy. Beat in the vanilla.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Gradually beat in 3 1/2 cups of the confectioners' sugar; blend well.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Add milk, as needed, until the frosting reaches a good spreading consistency.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d Spread the frosting over the cooled cake.
00c16878-3399-4ef2-ace6-145405c8980d If desired, sprinkle with chopped nuts and/or shredded coconut.
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 Gather the ingredients.
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 Preheat oven to 350 F.
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 Shred baby carrots (this takes some time, but is well worth it).
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 In​ a large bowl, combine oil, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla, and eggs and beat well.
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 Stir in half of the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt and mix well.
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 Add carrots and beat well.
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 Then beat in remaining flour.
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 Stir in 1/2 cup walnuts and mix well.
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 Pour into a 9-by-13-inch pan and spread evenly.
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 Bake at 350 F for 45 to 55 minutes until dark golden brown and cake springs back when lightly touched in center.
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 Cool ​the carrot cake on a wire rack.
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 Fold walnuts or coconut into cream cheese frosting.
f7a1389e-99b1-4ee3-b73a-f7b006f9e8e7 Spread over cooled carrot cake.
8a0d8654-cd8e-4cd8-9440-c2985d40dbc4 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 300 F.
8a0d8654-cd8e-4cd8-9440-c2985d40dbc4 In a medium bowl, mix together the graham cracker crumbs, chopped pecans, sugar, and pumpkin pie spice. Stir in the melted butter.
8a0d8654-cd8e-4cd8-9440-c2985d40dbc4 Press the mixture evenly into the bottom and 1 1/2 inches up the side of a 10-inch springform pan. Wrap the springform pan with foil to prevent any leaks. Bake in the oven for 10 minutes. Let cool.
8a0d8654-cd8e-4cd8-9440-c2985d40dbc4 Mix the cottage cheese and eggs in a blender on high speed until smooth. Set aside.
8a0d8654-cd8e-4cd8-9440-c2985d40dbc4 In a large bowl, beat together the cream cheese, granulated sugar, flour, orange zest, pumpkin pie spice, salt, and cottage cheese mixture until smooth.
8a0d8654-cd8e-4cd8-9440-c2985d40dbc4 Fold in the pumpkin puree.
8a0d8654-cd8e-4cd8-9440-c2985d40dbc4 Pour into the baked graham cracker crust. Bake at 300 F for 1 1/2 hours. Turn the oven off. With the oven door ajar, let the cheesecake cool in the oven for 1 hour. Remove from oven.
8a0d8654-cd8e-4cd8-9440-c2985d40dbc4 Once cooled, heat the oven to 350 F. Mix the sour cream and orange marmalade in a small bowl.
8a0d8654-cd8e-4cd8-9440-c2985d40dbc4 Spread over the cheesecake. Bake for 10 minutes. Cool slightly and refrigerate.
8a0d8654-cd8e-4cd8-9440-c2985d40dbc4 To serve, remove the rim of the springform pan. Thinly slice the orange into rings. Remove the pulp. Decorate the cheesecake with the rind cut into semicircles.
444d8ec5-92cc-4578-9343-2024baf343bc Gather the ingredients. Grease a 9-inch springform pan with cooking spray or softened butter. Line the bottom and sides with parchment paper.
444d8ec5-92cc-4578-9343-2024baf343bc To make the crust, place 36 Oreos in a food processor fitted with the metal blade and process until fine crumbs form.
444d8ec5-92cc-4578-9343-2024baf343bc Add the melted butter and process until combined, scraping the bowl periodically with a rubber spatula.
444d8ec5-92cc-4578-9343-2024baf343bc Transfer the crumbs to the prepared pan and firmly press the crumbs into the bottom and 3/4 of the way up the sides of the pan. Place the crust in the freezer while you prepare the filling.
444d8ec5-92cc-4578-9343-2024baf343bc Place the heavy cream and vanilla in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the whisk attachment and whisk on medium-high until stiff peaks form. Transfer to a large bowl.
444d8ec5-92cc-4578-9343-2024baf343bc Place the cream cheese, sugar and salt in the bowl of the stand mixer, now fitted with the paddle attachment (no need to clean it) and beat on medium until smooth, scraping the bowl with a rubber spatula as needed.
444d8ec5-92cc-4578-9343-2024baf343bc Fold the whipped cream into the cream cheese in several installments with a rubber spatula, being mindful not to deflate the air you just whipped into the cream.
444d8ec5-92cc-4578-9343-2024baf343bc Process the remaining Oreos until coarse crumbs form. Gently fold the coarse crumbs into the cheesecake batter.
444d8ec5-92cc-4578-9343-2024baf343bc Transfer the filling to the prepared crust, smoothing the top with an offset spatula or butter knife. Add filling just to the top of the crust. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 5 hours, preferably overnight.
444d8ec5-92cc-4578-9343-2024baf343bc When ready to serve, remove the sides of the pan and then slide a long knife between the parchment paper and the metal bottom to loosen and remove the sides. Peel off the parchment. Sprinkle crushed Oreos over the top of the cake to decorate.
444d8ec5-92cc-4578-9343-2024baf343bc Place the cake on a serving plate, slice into wedges with a serrated knife, and serve. Run the knife under hot water each time you make a cut to ensure clean slices.
2fc7df40-38d6-4c9b-80ab-34e0258da7ff Gather the ingredients.
2fc7df40-38d6-4c9b-80ab-34e0258da7ff Toast 2 cups of sweetened shredded coconut. (1 1/2 cups will be used for the crust and the remaining 1/2 cup is reserved for garnish.)
2fc7df40-38d6-4c9b-80ab-34e0258da7ff Make the crust. Wrap outside of a 9-inch springform pan with 2 3/4-inch sides with foil. This helps keep any leaks from the springform pan from spilling onto your oven floor.
2fc7df40-38d6-4c9b-80ab-34e0258da7ff In a medium bowl, combine the graham cracker crumbs, 1 1/2 cups of the toasted coconut, and sugar.
2fc7df40-38d6-4c9b-80ab-34e0258da7ff Add the butter and mix to blend.
2fc7df40-38d6-4c9b-80ab-34e0258da7ff Press the mixture onto the bottom and up the sides of the prepared pan. Chill while preparing the filling.
2fc7df40-38d6-4c9b-80ab-34e0258da7ff Preheat oven to 325 F. Beat cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl until blended.
2fc7df40-38d6-4c9b-80ab-34e0258da7ff Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Beat in the egg yolk.
2fc7df40-38d6-4c9b-80ab-34e0258da7ff Add the cream of coconut, heavy whipping cream, and shredded coconut. Beat just until blended.
2fc7df40-38d6-4c9b-80ab-34e0258da7ff Pour filling into chilled crust. Bake cheesecake until puffed and golden, about 1 hour 25 minutes.
2fc7df40-38d6-4c9b-80ab-34e0258da7ff Transfer to a wire rack and cool completely. Refrigerate until well chilled.
2fc7df40-38d6-4c9b-80ab-34e0258da7ff When ready to serve, garnish the rim of the cheesecake with remaining 1/2 cup of toasted coconut.
aae6e667-5868-4853-8d1d-8b49b1edd106 Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 350 F.
aae6e667-5868-4853-8d1d-8b49b1edd106 In a large bowl combine crushed vanilla wafer cookies, melted butter, and sugar. In this recipe, vanilla wafer cookies are crushed and used in the crust, while whole vanilla wafer cookies are also used as a garnish on top of the finished cheesecake. When you purchase an 11-ounce box of vanilla wafer cookies, first remove 12 cookies for the garnish. Then, pulse the remaining cookies in the box in the food processor. They will measure out to the 2 cups of cookie crumbs necessary for the crust.
aae6e667-5868-4853-8d1d-8b49b1edd106 Pat the crust mixture into the bottom and halfway up the sides of a 10-inch springform pan. To prevent leaks, line the outside of the pan with aluminum foil or place the springform pan on a rimmed baking sheet.
aae6e667-5868-4853-8d1d-8b49b1edd106 In a large bowl, beat the cream cheese, sugar, sour cream, eggs, mashed bananas, and lemon juice until smooth.
aae6e667-5868-4853-8d1d-8b49b1edd106 Pour the mixture into the prepared pan and bake for 1 hour, or until the cheesecake is light brown on top.
aae6e667-5868-4853-8d1d-8b49b1edd106 Cool completely at room temperature. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for at least 12 hours before serving.
aae6e667-5868-4853-8d1d-8b49b1edd106 When ready to serve, prepare the topping. In a medium bowl, whisk together the milk, pudding mix, and powdered sugar. Beat for 2 minutes. Gently stir in the whipped topping.
aae6e667-5868-4853-8d1d-8b49b1edd106 Spread the topping over the top of the cheesecake.
aae6e667-5868-4853-8d1d-8b49b1edd106 Remove the side of the springform pan and place on serving platter. Garnish with vanilla wafer cookies and fresh banana slices.
aae6e667-5868-4853-8d1d-8b49b1edd106 Enjoy!
dbb4e3ea-bdfa-47d1-b4c0-f127723d1d41 Gather the ingredients.
dbb4e3ea-bdfa-47d1-b4c0-f127723d1d41 Preheat oven to 400 F. Lightly grease and flour a 9-inch round baking pan. (Non-stick baking spray can also be used.)
dbb4e3ea-bdfa-47d1-b4c0-f127723d1d41 Combine the ricotta cheese, powdered sugar, and eggs in a large mixing bowl and blend well.
dbb4e3ea-bdfa-47d1-b4c0-f127723d1d41 Add the lemon juice, lemon zest, vanilla extract, orange zest, almond extract, and rum extract. Beat by hand until smooth and creamy.
dbb4e3ea-bdfa-47d1-b4c0-f127723d1d41 Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake until golden brown and set, about 40 minutes.
dbb4e3ea-bdfa-47d1-b4c0-f127723d1d41 Place on a wire rack and cool completely. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
dbb4e3ea-bdfa-47d1-b4c0-f127723d1d41 Before serving, dust with additional powdered sugar, if desired.
dbb4e3ea-bdfa-47d1-b4c0-f127723d1d41 The cheesecake can also be garnished with your favorite nuts or fruit if desired. For an Italian cannoli-like flavor, try chopped pistachios and additional orange zest.
dbb4e3ea-bdfa-47d1-b4c0-f127723d1d41 Enjoy as a sweet treat after your favorite Italian meal!
db947972-6f72-4989-90f0-cca27eb6a9b0 Gather the ingredients. Preheat oven to 350 F.
db947972-6f72-4989-90f0-cca27eb6a9b0 In a large bowl combine the crushed graham crackers, melted butter, and granulated sugar.
db947972-6f72-4989-90f0-cca27eb6a9b0 Pat the crust mixture into the bottom and halfway up the sides of a 10-inch springform pan. To prevent leaks, line the outside of the pan with aluminum foil or place the springform pan on a rimmed baking sheet.
db947972-6f72-4989-90f0-cca27eb6a9b0 Make the filling. In a large bowl, beat the cream cheese, sugar, sour cream, eggs, mashed bananas, and lemon juice until smooth.
db947972-6f72-4989-90f0-cca27eb6a9b0 Pour the mixture into the prepared pan and bake for 1 hour, or until the cheesecake is light brown on top.
db947972-6f72-4989-90f0-cca27eb6a9b0 Cool completely at room temperature. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for at least 12 hours before serving.
db947972-6f72-4989-90f0-cca27eb6a9b0 Garnish individual servings with whipped cream, fresh banana slices, and a dusting of ground cinnamon.
db947972-6f72-4989-90f0-cca27eb6a9b0 Serve and enjoy!
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 375 F.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 For the crust, combine the chocolate wafer crumbs with the sugar in a medium bowl. Mix in the melted butter until the crumbs are moistened.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 Press the mixture evenly into the bottom of a 9-inch springform pan. Wrap your springform pan in heavy-duty in foil to prevent any leaks spilling out onto your oven floor. A rimmed baking sheet can also be placed beneath the cheesecake as it bakes to catch any drips. Place in the refrigerator to chill and set while preparing the filling.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 For the filling, in a large bowl beat the cream cheese, mascarpone, flour, and salt until smooth and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 Add the sugar and beat again until smooth.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 Add the coffee liqueur, vanilla extract, and instant espresso powder. Beat to combine.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 Add the eggs, one at a time, beating just until blended.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 Pour the filling into the chilled crust. Bake until set but the center still jiggles slightly, 50 to 65 minutes.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 Cool completely on a wire rack. Once cooled, cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 When ready to serve, unclasp and remove the side of the springform pan. Using a small sifter, dust the top of the cheesecake with cocoa powder to coat the top of the cheesecake.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 For the whipped cream, combine the heavy cream, coffee liqueur, and powdered sugar in a large bowl and whip at high speed until stiff peaks form. Transfer the spiked whipped cream to a piping bag fitted with your choice of tip.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 Slice the ladyfingers in half and press them into the sides of the cake, curved-end up. You can use a small amount of whipped cream from the pastry bag to help them stick.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 Pipe the spiked whipped cream along the top edge of the cheesecake.
45a4ef2b-fd27-4c16-b9a5-90fe24f49973 Cut and serve immediately. Refrigerate any leftovers.
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 Gather the ingredients.
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 Make the crust. Combine the graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup of the sugar, and melted butter.
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 Press the mixture evenly on the bottom and halfway up the side of a lightly buttered 9-inch springform pan. Chill while preparing the next steps.
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 Make the cheesecake filling. Beat the cream cheese in a large bowl until smooth; blend in 1 1/4 cups of the remaining sugar, and the flour. Beat with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 Add the eggs and egg yolk, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in the vanilla and cream.
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 Pour into the prepared crust and smooth the top. Bake in a 450 F oven for 10 minutes. Lower temperature to 250 F and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes longer.
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 Remove cake from the oven and cool completely on a wire rack.
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 Make the topping. Drain the juice from the can of pineapple slices into a small bowl. Set aside pineapple slices.
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 In a small saucepan, combine the reserved syrup from the can of pineapples with the orange juice or water. Sprinkle gelatin over the juices to soften, about 5 minutes. Heat over very low heat, stirring often, until gelatin clears and dissolves. Chill until syrupy but not set.
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 Cut 4 of the reserved pineapple slices in half and arrange around the edge on top of cake. Place one whole pineapple ring in the center. (Reserve remaining pineapple slices for another use.)
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 Spoon the chilled pineapple topping over to cover the center of the cake. Place maraschino cherries in the center of each pineapple ring.
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 Chill for at least three hours or until topping is set. Remove the side of the springform pan before slicing and serving.
36e1bb5b-1ef6-481f-a4b9-1d7b6359d7e0 Enjoy!
9a5c08b8-72a6-4bc5-bd6f-b4998daa3b16 Gather your ingredients.
9a5c08b8-72a6-4bc5-bd6f-b4998daa3b16 Place the graham crackers and sugar in a food processor and process until completely crumbled. Drizzle in the melted butter.
9a5c08b8-72a6-4bc5-bd6f-b4998daa3b16 Press the graham cracker crust into 6 greased mini cheesecake molds. If you are using a muffin tin, make sure to use liners. Bake for 5 to 10 minutes at 350 F or until lightly browned.
9a5c08b8-72a6-4bc5-bd6f-b4998daa3b16 Beat the softened cream cheese with the sugar and vanilla extract until combined and fluffy.
9a5c08b8-72a6-4bc5-bd6f-b4998daa3b16 Fold the whipped cream topping into the cream cheese mixture.
9a5c08b8-72a6-4bc5-bd6f-b4998daa3b16 Fill the prepared molds with the cream cheese filling. Fill the molds a little bit at a time. Then press down on the top of the filling with a spoon or spatula so they completely fill the mold and there are no gaps or pockets of air.
9a5c08b8-72a6-4bc5-bd6f-b4998daa3b16 Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours, or until completely chilled and firm.
9a5c08b8-72a6-4bc5-bd6f-b4998daa3b16 Remove the cheesecakes from the molds, top with fresh berries and serve! They can also be kept chilled for up to 2 days before serving!
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f Gather the ingredients and preheat your oven to 350 F.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f Grease a 9-inch springform pan with cooking spray or softened butter.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f To make the crust, place the wafer cookies, 3 tablespoons of the granulated sugar, and 1/2 teaspoon of the salt in a food processor fitted with the metal blade and process until fine crumbs form. Add the melted butter and process until combined, scraping the bowl periodically with a rubber spatula, if necessary.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f Add the melted butter and process until combined, scraping the bowl periodically with a rubber spatula, if necessary.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f Transfer the crumbs to the prepared pan and firmly press the crumbs into the bottom and 3/4 of the way up the sides of the pan. Place the crust in the freezer for 30 minutes.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f Meanwhile, place the chocolate and 1/2 cup of the heavy cream in a small microwave safe bowl and microwave on high in 30 second bursts, until the chocolate has melted and the mixture is smooth. Set aside to cool to room temperature.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f Bake the crust for 8 to 10 minutes, rotating at the halfway point until dry and fragrant.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f To prepare the cheesecake filling, in the bowl of a stand mixer, fitted with the paddle attachment, mix the cream cheese, light brown sugar, vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon of the salt and mix on medium-low speed until smooth, scraping down the bowl with a rubber spatula, as needed.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f Reduce the speed to low and add the eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition until incorporated, and scraping down the bowl as needed.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f Stir the flour into the cooled chocolate mixture.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f Add the chocolate mixture to the stand mixer bowl and mix on low until just combined.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f Transfer the filling to the prepared pan and place it on a cookie sheet in the oven. Bake for about 55 to 60 minutes, until the edges are set, but the middle jiggles just a bit.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f For the toppings, place the cherries, 1 /3 cup of the granulated sugar, remaining 1/4 teaspoon of the salt, cornstarch, and 1/4 cup of the Kirsch in a medium saucepan on the stovetop over medium-high heat and cook until the sugar melts and the cherries burst and release their juice, stirring frequently, about 30 minutes. Cool to room temperature.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f Place the remaining 1 1/2 cups of the heavy cream, confectioners’ sugar, a few tablespoons of the cherry juice from the compote and the 3 tablespoons of the remaining Kirsch, in the now clean bowl of the stand mixer, fitted with the whisk attachment, and whisk until medium peaks form.
22e7c90f-f344-4082-bfec-ce134d3a698f To serve, spread the Kirsh whipped cream over the cooled cheesecake. Serve immediately or chill, tightly covered, in the refrigerator until ready to serve. Serve slices of cheesecake with a generous spoonful or two of the cherry compote.
08c4f4cf-88f9-448e-91b9-ce559397df79 Gather the ingredients.
08c4f4cf-88f9-448e-91b9-ce559397df79 In a medium bowl, combine the chocolate cookie wafer crumbs with the melted butter.
08c4f4cf-88f9-448e-91b9-ce559397df79 Press the moist crumbs into the bottom and one inch up the sides of a 9-inch springform pan. Set in the refrigerator to firm up.
08c4f4cf-88f9-448e-91b9-ce559397df79 In a large bowl, beat the cream cheese, Nutella, sugar, cocoa powder, and vanilla extract until smooth and well combined.
08c4f4cf-88f9-448e-91b9-ce559397df79 Gently fold in the non-dairy whipped topping.
08c4f4cf-88f9-448e-91b9-ce559397df79 Pour the filling into the prepared crust and smooth the top. Refrigerate for about 4-6 hours or until firm.
08c4f4cf-88f9-448e-91b9-ce559397df79 In a large bowl, whip the heavy cream with confectioners’ sugar and hazelnut liqueur to make whipped cream.
08c4f4cf-88f9-448e-91b9-ce559397df79 Remove the cheesecake from the springform pan and place on a cake plate. Pipe hazelnut whipped cream around the rim of the cheesecake.
08c4f4cf-88f9-448e-91b9-ce559397df79 Garnish with toasted hazelnuts.
08c4f4cf-88f9-448e-91b9-ce559397df79 Cut into wedges to serve. Store remaining cheesecake in the refrigerator.
3b02a9e9-c1e8-4f88-9981-9f17cb09ac76 Gather the ingredients.
3b02a9e9-c1e8-4f88-9981-9f17cb09ac76 For the crust, mix together the graham cracker crumbs, chopped pecans, brown sugar, and melted butter in a bowl until crumbs are moistened.
3b02a9e9-c1e8-4f88-9981-9f17cb09ac76 Press mixture over bottom of a lightly buttered 9-inch springform pan. Refrigerate to chill. Heat oven to 375 F.
3b02a9e9-c1e8-4f88-9981-9f17cb09ac76 For the filling, put cream cheese, eggs, sour cream, granulated sugar, vanilla, and salt in large mixer bowl. Beat until well blended.
3b02a9e9-c1e8-4f88-9981-9f17cb09ac76 Pour the filling over chilled crust. Bake until the edges are set and the center is still slightly loose, about 60 minutes or until the cake has puffed and trembles just slightly when shaken. Do not overbake. The cheesecake will settle and firm as it cools.
3b02a9e9-c1e8-4f88-9981-9f17cb09ac76 Remove cheesecake from oven. Cool on wire rack until completely cool. Cover lightly with plastic wrap. Refrigerate to chill, several hours to overnight.
3b02a9e9-c1e8-4f88-9981-9f17cb09ac76 For the topping, put 1 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup butter, and cream into medium saucepan. Heat to boil over high heat, stirring occasionally until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat. Cool slightly but not completely.
3b02a9e9-c1e8-4f88-9981-9f17cb09ac76 Pour the topping over the top of the chilled cake while still warm enough to pour.
3b02a9e9-c1e8-4f88-9981-9f17cb09ac76 Sprinkle the chopped nuts and mini chocolate chips over the topping.
3b02a9e9-c1e8-4f88-9981-9f17cb09ac76 Arrange the pecan halves along the rim of the cake in a circle.
3b02a9e9-c1e8-4f88-9981-9f17cb09ac76 Refrigerate until ready to serve. Enjoy!
72721c98-e099-4e02-b5f9-1b9fbfc14139 Preheat the oven to 325 F.
72721c98-e099-4e02-b5f9-1b9fbfc14139 Lightly butter the inside of a 9-inch springform cake pan. Line the bottom and sides of the pan with parchment paper.
72721c98-e099-4e02-b5f9-1b9fbfc14139 Mix the cracker crumbs with the melted butter. Press the crumb mixture into the base of the tin and press firmly to create an even base for your cheesecake. Set aside.
72721c98-e099-4e02-b5f9-1b9fbfc14139 Using a stand or hand electric mixer, beat together the cream cheese with the sugar. Add the flour and beat again. Reduce the speed of the mixer and add the beaten eggs; it is essential that you do not mix too quickly at this stage or there will be too much air in the cheesecake and it will crack while cooking.
72721c98-e099-4e02-b5f9-1b9fbfc14139 Using a wooden spoon, stir in the eggnog and spices, then gently pour the filling into the graham cracker shell. Tap the pan lightly on the worktop to release any air bubbles.
72721c98-e099-4e02-b5f9-1b9fbfc14139 Place a large baking pan into the center of the preheated oven and pour in approximately 1 1/2 inches of hot water (this is called a bain marie). Carefully set the filled cake pan into the water, close the oven door and bake for 50 minutes or until the cheesecake is firm, but ever-so-slightly wobbly in the center.
72721c98-e099-4e02-b5f9-1b9fbfc14139 Remove the cheesecake from the oven and leave to cool on a rack for 20 minutes, then refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours, but if you can, chilling the cheesecake overnight is even better.
72721c98-e099-4e02-b5f9-1b9fbfc14139 Before serving, remove from the refrigerator 30 minutes prior to allow the cheesecake to come to room temperature. When ready to slice, grate over a light dusting of fresh nutmeg for that lovely Christmas aroma to accompany your dessert to the table.
f020de6c-fc4e-48fd-88ed-65df8e1f7793 Heat the oven to 350 F.
f020de6c-fc4e-48fd-88ed-65df8e1f7793 Thoroughly mix the cracker crumbs with the melted butter and sugar. Press the mixture into the bottom of a 9-inch springform pan. Press with the palm of your hand to firm up the base, then bake for 10 minutes in the preheated oven. Once cooked, leave the base to cool completely.
f020de6c-fc4e-48fd-88ed-65df8e1f7793 Place all the sauce ingredients into a small saucepan, bring to a gentle boil, then lower the heat and cook for 5 minutes.
f020de6c-fc4e-48fd-88ed-65df8e1f7793 Press the raspberries with the back of a fork to break up the fruit. Push the sauce through a fine sieve to create a smooth, thick sauce. Put to one side.
f020de6c-fc4e-48fd-88ed-65df8e1f7793 In a large bowl, beat together the cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, zest, and eggs to create a thick, smooth batter.
f020de6c-fc4e-48fd-88ed-65df8e1f7793 Pour half of the cream over the biscuit crumb. Drizzle over the raspberry sauce then very carefully, ladle over the remaining cream trying to avoid disturbing the raspberry sauce too much.
f020de6c-fc4e-48fd-88ed-65df8e1f7793 Place the cake in the center of the hot oven and bake for 50 minutes. The cake will turn a delicious golden brown.
f020de6c-fc4e-48fd-88ed-65df8e1f7793 Once cooked, take the cheesecake from the oven and leave it to cool completely. Wrap the cheesecake in paper or place into an airtight box and refrigerate for 2 hours (or overnight if possible). Do not try to cut the cake before then, as the base will crumble and the topping will fall apart.
f020de6c-fc4e-48fd-88ed-65df8e1f7793 When ready to serve, drench with the powdered sugar, a few strands of lemon zest for decoration, and a little extra raspberry sauce on the side, if you have any left.
f020de6c-fc4e-48fd-88ed-65df8e1f7793 Enjoy!
5051ff69-c112-4259-942e-8a95daa3fceb Lightly grease the inside of a 9-inch springform cake pan. Line the bottom and sides of the pan with parchment paper. Mix the cracker crumbs with the melted butter. Press the crumb mixture into the base of the tin and press firmly to create an even crust for your cheesecake. Pop the tin into the refrigerator.
5051ff69-c112-4259-942e-8a95daa3fceb Melt the white chocolate in a heatproof bowl, set over a pan of simmering water. Make sure the base of the dish does not touch the water or the chocolate may scorch. Stir when melted using a wooden spoon. Set aside to cool slightly.
5051ff69-c112-4259-942e-8a95daa3fceb Make the filling: whisk the cream cheese and heavy cream together using either a stand or hand mixer to create a smooth thickened mixture. You should see soft peaks in the cream when you lift the beaters. Gently stir in the vanilla extract.
5051ff69-c112-4259-942e-8a95daa3fceb With the beaters running on medium speed, slowly pour in the cooled white chocolate. You may get little pieces of chocolate going hard, but don't worry, they'll add a nice texture to the cheesecake.
5051ff69-c112-4259-942e-8a95daa3fceb Place the raspberries into a blender and mix well. Pass the sauce through a fine sieve to remove the seeds.
5051ff69-c112-4259-942e-8a95daa3fceb Spoon approximately half of the filling into the base and spread evenly. Drizzle two-thirds of the raspberry sauce over the surface and use a skewer or a toothpick to swirl the sauce through the batter to create a marbled effect.
5051ff69-c112-4259-942e-8a95daa3fceb Spoon over the remaining chocolate, smooth with a palette knife and clean up any bits of the mixture on the lining paper—this will make it easier to remove later.
5051ff69-c112-4259-942e-8a95daa3fceb Cover the cheesecake with plastic wrap and pop into the refrigerator for 4 hours, overnight is even better if you have the time.
5051ff69-c112-4259-942e-8a95daa3fceb To serve: remove the plastic wrap, then snap open the tin and remove the baking paper. Leave the cheesecake on the base; if you want to remove it, gently run a long knife under the graham cracker crust and slide the cake onto a plate.
5051ff69-c112-4259-942e-8a95daa3fceb Decorate with fresh raspberries and the remaining sauce as you wish.
fac4dd52-060e-4325-878e-75956685109d Slather outsides of bread with butter.
fac4dd52-060e-4325-878e-75956685109d Spread cheesecake filling liberally over unbuttered side of the bread and place coarsely chopped Oreos, generously, on top of filling.
fac4dd52-060e-4325-878e-75956685109d Drizzle raspberry syrup or Nutella over Oreos and cheese mixture, then top with the other slice of bread.
fac4dd52-060e-4325-878e-75956685109d Place in griddle and cook until cheese is gooey and bread is crispy.
572d1909-05bd-4753-bd2c-e65dcfce19ca Gather the ingredients.
572d1909-05bd-4753-bd2c-e65dcfce19ca Pre-heat the oven to 350 F.
572d1909-05bd-4753-bd2c-e65dcfce19ca Add the graham crackers to a food processor and pulse until you have crumbs. Add in the sugar and melted butter.
572d1909-05bd-4753-bd2c-e65dcfce19ca Press the graham cracker mixture into the bottom of an 8" x 8" square baking pan. Note that a glass pan works very well for this recipe.
572d1909-05bd-4753-bd2c-e65dcfce19ca Bake for 10 minutes and allow to cool slightly, while leaving the oven on.
572d1909-05bd-4753-bd2c-e65dcfce19ca For the lime filling: Add the egg yolks to a mixing bowl and, using a stand or hand mixer, beat for a few minutes until fluffy.
572d1909-05bd-4753-bd2c-e65dcfce19ca Mix in the sweetened condensed milk, lime juice, salt, and lime zest.
572d1909-05bd-4753-bd2c-e65dcfce19ca Pour the mixture into the graham cracker crust and return to the oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until set.
572d1909-05bd-4753-bd2c-e65dcfce19ca Cool to room temperature and then refrigerate for 4 hours.
572d1909-05bd-4753-bd2c-e65dcfce19ca Slice into bars and serve with a wedge of lime on top, if desired.
bb37e491-9cf6-4639-abdd-d7c42ca6c386 Start by greasing and lining the sides and base of a 20cm / 8" diameter springform cake tin with greaseproof paper.
f1c207d0-970d-4a2a-8221-a4d78a9684a8 Gather the ingredients.
f1c207d0-970d-4a2a-8221-a4d78a9684a8 Mix the graham cracker crumbs with the chocolate chips and melted butter in a small bowl. Take a small pinch of the mixture and press in the palm of your hand, the mixture should bind and if it is too greasy add a little more crumb. If it's too dry, add a bit more butter.
f1c207d0-970d-4a2a-8221-a4d78a9684a8 Place 12 foil cups into a 12-hole muffin tin. Divide the crumb between the 12 and press firmly into the base of the cup using the back of a spoon.
f1c207d0-970d-4a2a-8221-a4d78a9684a8 Heat the oven to 350 F.
f1c207d0-970d-4a2a-8221-a4d78a9684a8 Whip the cream cheese and sugar using a hand or electric mixer until it is light and fluffy. Sift the cocoa into the mixture and beat well. Then add the vanilla and food color and beat again.
f1c207d0-970d-4a2a-8221-a4d78a9684a8 Beat the eggs into the mixture one at a time. Do not rush this process. Each egg needs to be thoroughly mixed in before adding another, or you risk the mixture curdling.
f1c207d0-970d-4a2a-8221-a4d78a9684a8 Divide the cheese batter evenly between the twelve cups. Once filled, tap the muffin tin firmly on the counter to level the mixture.
f1c207d0-970d-4a2a-8221-a4d78a9684a8 Pop the tin into the center of the preheated oven and bake for 25 minutes; if the cheesecakes start to crack, lower the temperature slightly. The cheesecakes are cooked once the center is firm.
f1c207d0-970d-4a2a-8221-a4d78a9684a8 Remove the tin from the oven and allow to cool.
f1c207d0-970d-4a2a-8221-a4d78a9684a8 The cakes can now either be decorated and sprinkled with grated chocolate or, if you are feeling adventurous, try a few chocolate curls. Otherwise, wrap carefully and pop the cakes into the freezer and decorate once defrosted, see notes below.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 Gather the ingredients.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 Preheat oven to 350 F. Prepare a springform pan by lining it with tin foil or parchment paper. You can also use a standard cake pan or several ramekins. Grease either with butter or coconut oil.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 In a large bowl, stir room-temperature or microwave-warmed butter into cracker crumbs (or pulse in the processor to combine).
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 Press into the bottom of the prepared pan to make a bottom crust. Set in refrigerator.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 Place fresh mango slices in a food processor or blender. Add 2 tablespoons water and the coconut flavoring (if using). Blend well to make a thick puree. If using fresh mango, you may want to add 2 teaspoons sugar to sweeten it. Set aside.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 Place the cream cheese in a large mixing bowl. If it's cold, cover with a plate and microwave for 1 to 2 minutes until soft. Add sugar and beat at low speed until smooth.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 Begin adding eggs, one at a time, beating at low speed. This can also be done by hand with a whisk to avoid over-beating.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 Add half the mango puree into the cream cheese mixture and sprinkle with flour. Mix on low speed or by hand just until incorporated. The small amount of flour in this recipe was added to avoid cracks in the baked cheesecake.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 Pour batter into the prepared pan(s) and smooth out the top.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 Now the fun part: drizzle the remaining puree onto the surface of the cake in 3 horizontal lines or dots all over the surface.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 With a cake tester, skewer, or thin-bladed knife, swirl the batter and puree together using wide circular movements.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 Bake for 1 hour, or 10 minutes longer if the cake appears undercooked. Keep in mind that the top of cheesecake will always be a little jiggly, but it will firm up later.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 Allow the cheesecake to cool in the pan before removing. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
c1a73829-33ae-48ca-ac88-1ad1a9a282b0 Slice, serve, and enjoy.
875c14e0-a930-4a54-a55b-3aeb86aa2913 Gather the ingredients.
875c14e0-a930-4a54-a55b-3aeb86aa2913 In a medium bowl, beat the cream cheese until smooth and fluffy. Make sure you take the time to do this properly since the cream cheese has to blend thoroughly with the sweetened condensed milk to set up properly.
875c14e0-a930-4a54-a55b-3aeb86aa2913 Gradually add the sweetened condensed milk, beating constantly, adding the fresh lemon juice halfway through. Add the remaining sweetened condensed milk and beat until the mixture is smooth.
875c14e0-a930-4a54-a55b-3aeb86aa2913 Pour into a graham cracker or cookie crust and chill at least 1 hour before serving.
bdaeb7df-6b43-4aa9-add9-13ac47f164f1 Gather the ingredients.
bdaeb7df-6b43-4aa9-add9-13ac47f164f1 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
bdaeb7df-6b43-4aa9-add9-13ac47f164f1 Make the cheesecake filling by combining the cream cheese with the sugar, egg, lemon juice, sour cream (or Greek yogurt), flour and salt until fully mixed.
bdaeb7df-6b43-4aa9-add9-13ac47f164f1 Spread a layer of phyllo dough over each pan and brush with the melted butter. Add 8 more sheets to each pan, with melted butter brushed over each sheet. Allow the dough sheets to overhang the pan.
bdaeb7df-6b43-4aa9-add9-13ac47f164f1 Pour the cheesecake filling equally into each pan and sprinkle on the chopped pistachios. Fold the edges of the phyllo dough over the cheesecake. Don't worry about making it perfect. It will crumple up naturally. Brush on a little more melted butter and place on a baking sheet. Bake in the oven for 20 minutes, then cover the browned phyllo crust loosely with aluminum foil and continue baking for an additional 20 minutes.
bdaeb7df-6b43-4aa9-add9-13ac47f164f1 Make the syrup by adding the sugar, water, honey and lemon juice to a pot and simmering gently until the sugar dissolves. When the cheesecakes are done, remove from the oven and let cool just until you can remove them from the spring-form. Pour the honey syrup over each one and let sit for a few minutes to let it soak in.
bdaeb7df-6b43-4aa9-add9-13ac47f164f1 Serve and enjoy!
63a0b3b5-eb17-4f9e-a7f0-e96cc5d5b15f Preheat the oven to 350 F. Grease a 9-inch springform pan well with dairy-free soy margarine. Set aside.
63a0b3b5-eb17-4f9e-a7f0-e96cc5d5b15f Make the crust. In a small mixing bowl, combine the graham cracker crumbs and white granulated sugar until well combined. Add the melted dairy-free soy margarine and mix until well combined. Press the mixture evenly into the bottom and up 2 inches of the sides of the prepared pan. Place in the oven for 5 minutes. Transfer to a cooling rack while preparing the filling.
63a0b3b5-eb17-4f9e-a7f0-e96cc5d5b15f Make the filling. Using a standing mixer or an electric hand mixer, beat the dairy-free cream cheese in a large mixing bowl until smooth. Add the sugar and continue to mix until smooth, about 2-3 minutes. Add the Egg Replacer, beating until well combined, followed by the dairy-free sour cream, peanut butter, and pure vanilla extract, beating well after each addition and scraping down the sides periodically to ensure even mixing. Fold in the dairy-free chocolate chips until evenly distributed. Pour the filling into the prepared crust and bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until the top of the cheesecake is lightly browned.
63a0b3b5-eb17-4f9e-a7f0-e96cc5d5b15f Spread several tablespoons of dairy-free sour cream over the surface of the cheesecake to fill in any cracks. Transfer to a wire cooling rack to cool completely for 1-2 hours, then transfer to the refrigerator for at least 2 hours to chill completely.
63a0b3b5-eb17-4f9e-a7f0-e96cc5d5b15f Prepare the vegan ganache, and while it is still warm, pour evenly over the top of the cheesecake. Return the cheesecake to the refrigerator for 2-3 hours more, or until the ganache has set. Serve cake cold.
ef895dc7-15d3-462f-9199-919526efd640 Wrap the bottom of a 9-inch springform pan with 3 or 4 layers of heavy-duty foil.
ef895dc7-15d3-462f-9199-919526efd640 Combine the crust ingredients; pat into the springform pan, patting gently partway up the sides of the pan. Place in the refrigerator or freezer while you prepare the filling.
ef895dc7-15d3-462f-9199-919526efd640 Heat oven to 450 F.
ef895dc7-15d3-462f-9199-919526efd640 Beat cream cheese until smooth and fluffy; beat in brown sugar until light and well blended. Slowly beat in the eggs, then the sour cream and vanilla. Beat just until well blended.
ef895dc7-15d3-462f-9199-919526efd640 Pour into the prepared crust. Place the foil-wrapped pan in a large, shallow roasting pan. Place in the oven and add about 1/2 inch of hot water.
ef895dc7-15d3-462f-9199-919526efd640 Reduce heat to 325 F and bake for 45 to 55 minutes, until the cheesecake is firm around edges but still slightly jiggly in the center.
ef895dc7-15d3-462f-9199-919526efd640 Turn the oven off and leave the cheesecake in the oven for 30 minutes longer. Place the cheesecake on a rack to cool to room temperature. Remove the pan sides.
ef895dc7-15d3-462f-9199-919526efd640 Prepare the sauce.
ef895dc7-15d3-462f-9199-919526efd640 Heat the 5 tablespoons of butter and pecan halves in a saucepan over medium heat.
ef895dc7-15d3-462f-9199-919526efd640 Cook, stirring until the butter is lightly browned and pecans are aromatic. Add the brown sugar to the butter and cook, stirring, until the sugar is dissolved.
ef895dc7-15d3-462f-9199-919526efd640 Stir in the cream until well blended and heat through. Serve with bread pudding, cheesecake, or pound cake.
ef895dc7-15d3-462f-9199-919526efd640 Refrigerate leftover cheesecake and sauce. Warm the sauce slightly and thin as necessary with a little cream.
71212c62-8b94-43e0-953d-9c7d43a1961c Heat the oven to 325 F / 165 C / Gas Mark 3.
71212c62-8b94-43e0-953d-9c7d43a1961c Combine the graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup of melted butter, and 2 teaspoons of sugar; press into the bottom of a 10-inch springform pan.
71212c62-8b94-43e0-953d-9c7d43a1961c Combine cream cheese and cottage cheese in a large mixing bowl; beat until smooth. Gradually add 1 1/2 cups of granulated sugar, beating well. Add eggs and beat until well blended. Add 6 tablespoons of cornstarch, flour, lemon juice, and vanilla; stir well. Add 1/2 cup of melted butter and the sour cream, beating until smooth.
71212c62-8b94-43e0-953d-9c7d43a1961c Pour filling into a 10-inch springform pan with graham cracker crust (below). (Place a shallow baking pan on the bottom rack of the oven with about an inch of hot water.) Bake cheesecake in the center of oven at 325 F / 165 C / Gas Mark 3 for about 70 minutes, or until firm around edges. Turn off oven and let cheesecake cool in the oven for 2 hours.
71212c62-8b94-43e0-953d-9c7d43a1961c Remove from oven and cool completely.
71212c62-8b94-43e0-953d-9c7d43a1961c Remove from pan; refrigerate. When completely chilled, top with blueberry glaze (below).
2c965e97-2cf8-41e5-b709-d01fb83464da Preheat oven to 375 F. Lightly oil a 10” spring-form pan or, alternatively, six 4” spring-form pans. Set aside.
50a66094-61e2-466d-869f-6555790c6faa Gather the ingredients.
50a66094-61e2-466d-869f-6555790c6faa Preheat the oven to 375 F/190 C/Gas 5.
50a66094-61e2-466d-869f-6555790c6faa For the crust, combine the graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup of brown sugar, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, and 8 tablespoons of melted butter in a large bowl. Mix thoroughly until all crumbs are blended into the butter.
50a66094-61e2-466d-869f-6555790c6faa Spread the crumbs in a 9- to 10-inch pie plate, and tamp down firmly over the bottom and the sides.
50a66094-61e2-466d-869f-6555790c6faa Bake for 12 minutes. Remove to a rack to cool.
50a66094-61e2-466d-869f-6555790c6faa Reduce the oven temperature to 325 F/165 C/Gas 3.
50a66094-61e2-466d-869f-6555790c6faa In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese with the 3/4 cup of brown sugar until smooth and creamy. Add the eggs and vanilla and beat until well blended. Pour 1 1/2 cups of the cream cheese mixture into the cooled crust.
50a66094-61e2-466d-869f-6555790c6faa Into the remaining cream cheese mixture, beat the pumpkin, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon, and the nutmeg. Spread over the first layer.
50a66094-61e2-466d-869f-6555790c6faa Bake the pie for 40 to 50 minutes, until set and just slightly jiggly in the center.
50a66094-61e2-466d-869f-6555790c6faa Cool on a rack. Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled (about 3 to 4 hours) before slicing.
50a66094-61e2-466d-869f-6555790c6faa Serve topped with whipped cream and drizzle with caramel or butterscotch sauce, if desired.
fa9310de-c943-451c-a8cf-a1b86026d2d0 Gather the ingredients.
fa9310de-c943-451c-a8cf-a1b86026d2d0 Preheat oven to 375 F. Spray a 9x13-inch cake pan with non-stick cooking spray.
fa9310de-c943-451c-a8cf-a1b86026d2d0 In a bowl, combine butter, egg yolks, coffee, sugar, and flour with your hands until the mixture is crumbly.
fa9310de-c943-451c-a8cf-a1b86026d2d0 Press the mixture into the bottom of the cake pan. This forms the base for the cake.
fa9310de-c943-451c-a8cf-a1b86026d2d0 In a separate bowl, combine eggs, white cheese, sugar, vanilla sugar, and flour.
fa9310de-c943-451c-a8cf-a1b86026d2d0 Pour this mixture on top of the cake base.
fa9310de-c943-451c-a8cf-a1b86026d2d0 Bake for 30 minutes or until the cheese does not wiggle. Remove cake and cool for 30 minutes.
fa9310de-c943-451c-a8cf-a1b86026d2d0 Turn oven temperature down to 200 F.
fa9310de-c943-451c-a8cf-a1b86026d2d0 In a small bowl, mix sour cream with vanilla sugar and sugar. Spread evenly over the cooled cake.
fa9310de-c943-451c-a8cf-a1b86026d2d0 Bake again for 20 minutes.
fa9310de-c943-451c-a8cf-a1b86026d2d0 Refrigerate until fully cooled and firm and then serve!
91e406cf-4762-4ab5-9633-beaa692a5d81 Have mixing bowl and beaters chilled for best results.
91e406cf-4762-4ab5-9633-beaa692a5d81 Beat whipped cream until soft peaks form; add maple syrup and beat until firm.
95558e95-3c3c-49db-908b-8b1323406a58 In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until thick and light lemon yellow color. Add 1/2 cup of sugar and the flour, beating until blended. Pour the egg mixture into a measuring cup.
95558e95-3c3c-49db-908b-8b1323406a58 In the same bowl, beat the cream cheese with a small amount of the evaporated milk until smooth. Add remaining milk, the lemon juice, and the grated lemon peel; beat until smooth and well blended. Pour egg mixture into the cream cheese mixture; beat just until blended.
95558e95-3c3c-49db-908b-8b1323406a58 Pour mixture into the graham cracker crust. Bake at 325 F for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool completely on a wire rack.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Gather the ingredients.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas Mark 4.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Combine the graham cracker crumbs, sugar, and melted butter in a small bowl, stirring well.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Firmly press mixture in bottom and 1 inch up sides of a buttered 9-inch springform pan.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Bake crust at 350 F/180 C/Gas Mark 4 for 8 minutes; cool in pan on a wire rack.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Beat cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Gradually add 1 1/4 cups sugar, adding egg yolks one at a time, beating after each addition.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Stir in sour cream, lime rind, and Key lime juice.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Beat egg whites at high speed until stiff peaks form. Fold into cream cheese mixture.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Pour batter into prepared crust.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Bake at 350 F/180 C/Gas Mark 4 for 1 hour and 5 minutes; turn the oven off.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Partially open oven door; let cheesecake cool in oven 15 minutes. Remove from oven, and immediately run a knife around edge of pan to release sides.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Cool completely in pan on a wire rack; cover and chill 8 hours.
276d1843-4885-46f8-8acd-32e02126aade Serve and enjoy!
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec Gather the ingredients.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec Preheat oven to 350 F. Grease a 9-inch springform pan and line the bottom with waxed paper.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec In a medium bowl, add the graham cracker crumbs and melted butter. Toss with a fork until evenly moistened.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec Press the mixture over the bottom and 1-inch up the sides of the prepared pan. Refrigerate until ready to use.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec In a large bowl, use an electric mixer to beat the cream cheese and sugar until smooth, scraping down the sides of the bowl when necessary.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec Beat in the sour cream until blended.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in the vanilla.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec Pour half of the batter into the prepared pan.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec In a small saucepan over low heat, combine the jam and lemon juice, stirring often, until melted and smooth.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec Drizzle 1/4 of the jam mixture in stripes over the batter.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec Spoon the remaining cheesecake batter over the jam, then drizzle with the remaining jam.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec Swirl gently with a thin knife to marbleize the batter slightly.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec Bake the cheesecake for 1 hour to 1 hour 10 minutes, until firm around the edges but still slightly wobbly in the center.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec While still in the pan, set the cheesecake on a wire rack to cool completely. Wrap the cake pan in plastic and chill for at least 4 hours. Remove the cake from the refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec Remove the pan sides and place the cake on a serving platter.
6e3e5c52-b645-418a-b947-989e73f31bec Garnish with fresh raspberries, serve, and enjoy!
5bb208e3-b648-4fae-bb46-297f44a34859 Gather the ingredients.
5bb208e3-b648-4fae-bb46-297f44a34859 Melt chocolate chips over low heat in saucepan or microwave, stirring frequently until smooth and melted. Set aside to cool.
5bb208e3-b648-4fae-bb46-297f44a34859 In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, and butter until smooth.
5bb208e3-b648-4fae-bb46-297f44a34859 On low speed, blend in the melted chocolate.
5bb208e3-b648-4fae-bb46-297f44a34859 Fold in whipped topping until blended.
5bb208e3-b648-4fae-bb46-297f44a34859 Spoon blended mixture into prepared graham cracker crust.
5bb208e3-b648-4fae-bb46-297f44a34859 Cover and chill until firm, about 2 to 4 hours.
5bb208e3-b648-4fae-bb46-297f44a34859 Garnish with whipped topping and shaved chocolate, if desired.
5bb208e3-b648-4fae-bb46-297f44a34859 Slice, serve, and enjoy!
bb4e1909-0aeb-49cd-b14b-afe81ba7bf64 Combine graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons of sugar, 3 tablespoons of melted butter, and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, if using; press into bottom and about 2 inches up the sides of a 9-inch springform pan. Bake at 325 F for 5 minutes.
bb4e1909-0aeb-49cd-b14b-afe81ba7bf64 Beat cream cheese and 1 cup of sugar until smooth. Beat in egg yolks to blend. Blend in sour cream, vanilla, and lemon.
bb4e1909-0aeb-49cd-b14b-afe81ba7bf64 Beat whites until stiff not dry. Fold into the cream cheese mixture. Pour into prepared graham cracker crust-lined springform pan.
bb4e1909-0aeb-49cd-b14b-afe81ba7bf64 Bake at 300 F for 1 hour. Turn the oven off but leave the cheesecake in the oven for 1 hour with door closed. Open oven door, and keep the cake in 30 minutes longer.
bb4e1909-0aeb-49cd-b14b-afe81ba7bf64 Remove and chill overnight.
63fcdfcc-0fac-448d-870e-fa88591dd45c Gather the ingredients.
63fcdfcc-0fac-448d-870e-fa88591dd45c In a medium bowl, mix the graham cracker crumbs with the granulated sugar and melted butter.
63fcdfcc-0fac-448d-870e-fa88591dd45c Reserve 2 tablespoons of the crumbs in a small bowl and set aside. Press the remaining crumbs into the bottom of an 8- to 9-inch springform pan. Put the crust in the refrigerator to chill while you make the filling.
63fcdfcc-0fac-448d-870e-fa88591dd45c In a large bowl with an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese with the confectioners' sugar until fluffy.
63fcdfcc-0fac-448d-870e-fa88591dd45c Add the crushed pineapple and blend well.
63fcdfcc-0fac-448d-870e-fa88591dd45c Fold the whipped topping into the pineapple mixture.
63fcdfcc-0fac-448d-870e-fa88591dd45c Spread the filling over the chilled crust and sprinkle with the reserved graham cracker crumbs.
63fcdfcc-0fac-448d-870e-fa88591dd45c Cover with plastic wrap and chill thoroughly before serving.
63fcdfcc-0fac-448d-870e-fa88591dd45c Slice, serve, and enjoy!
0c788122-295e-44de-a2dc-2178babea2ae Preheat oven to 325 F (165 C/Gas Mark 3).
0c788122-295e-44de-a2dc-2178babea2ae Combine crust ingredients and press into bottom of a 9-inch springform pan.
0c788122-295e-44de-a2dc-2178babea2ae In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually add condensed milk; beat until smooth. Add flour, eggs, and vanilla; beat until well blended. Pour into prepared crust. Wrap the bottom of the springform pan in heavy-duty foil; place the pan in a shallow baking pan, such as a jelly roll pan.
0c788122-295e-44de-a2dc-2178babea2ae Put the pans in the oven and add about 2 cups of hot water to the shallow baking pan, or a depth of about 1/2 inch.
0c788122-295e-44de-a2dc-2178babea2ae Bake for 1 hour, or until lightly browned. The cheesecake will be just slightly jiggly in the center. Cool.
0c788122-295e-44de-a2dc-2178babea2ae Chill and garnish with dollops of whipped cream and fresh sliced strawberries.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d Gather the ingredients.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d In a food processor, process the graham crackers and chopped pecans with the sugar until you have fine crumbs. Mix with the melted butter until well blended.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d Reserve a few tablespoons of the graham cracker crust crumbs for the topping, if desired.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d Put about 1 1/2 to 2 tablespoons of graham cracker mixture in each canning jar (no need to grease the jars). Tamp down with a pestle or any tool that will fit in the canning jar to tamp the crumbs. The food pusher from the food processor should fit nicely.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d Heat the oven to 350 F.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d In a large mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese and brown sugar. Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in the sour cream and vanilla or vanilla bean paste.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d Add about 3 tablespoons of the cream cheese mixture to each graham cracker lined canning jar. Or, add about 1 tablespoon and top with a few chocolate chips or pecans or a dab of chocolate or caramel sauce, then finish with about 1 1/2 to 2 tablespoons of the cream cheese mixture.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d Top each cheesecake with chopped pecans and chocolate chips, along with a sprinkling of the reserved graham cracker crumbs.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d Put the jars in one or two baking dishes and add about 1 1/2 inches of hot water to the bottom of the baking dishes.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d Bake for about 30 to 35 minutes, or until the filling is set. A small knife inserted in the center should come out clean.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d If you are checking the temperature, insert an instant-read thermometer in a cheesecake. The filling should register about 165 F ( about 72 C) when it's done.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d Cover the cheesecakes with jar lids and store in the refrigerator or freezer. If you freeze them, transfer to the refrigerator to thaw at least 2 hours before you plan to serve them.
960cadfb-e020-4fba-8a5c-02343d62739d Enjoy!
4e0fd38b-e711-4aa3-8f45-d39f6c3651ba Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
4e0fd38b-e711-4aa3-8f45-d39f6c3651ba Combine the graham cracker crumbs with the melted butter and granulated sugar. Pat the mixture into the bottom and up the sides of a 9-inch pie plate. See the variation to use a springform pan.
4e0fd38b-e711-4aa3-8f45-d39f6c3651ba Bake in the preheated oven for 10 minutes. Remove to a cooling rack.
4e0fd38b-e711-4aa3-8f45-d39f6c3651ba In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese until light and fluffy. Beat in the sweet potato puree, brown sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Beat in the eggs until smooth and well-blended.
4e0fd38b-e711-4aa3-8f45-d39f6c3651ba Spoon sweet potato cheesecake filling into the graham cracker crust.
4e0fd38b-e711-4aa3-8f45-d39f6c3651ba Bake in the preheated 350 degree F oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until the pie filling is set.
4e0fd38b-e711-4aa3-8f45-d39f6c3651ba Cool the pie on a cooling rack. Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 Gather the ingredients.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 Preheat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas Mark 4.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 Combine 1/4 cup of confectioners' sugar with the graham cracker crumbs and melted butter; blend thoroughly.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 Pack the crumbs firmly into the bottom of an 8 or 9-inch springform pan.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 Wrap the pan bottom and sides with heavy-duty foil to prevent leaks.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat 1 cup of granulated sugar with the cream cheese, 1 teaspoon of vanilla, and 4 large eggs.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 Pour into the graham cracker crust.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 Bake in the preheated oven for 50 minutes.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 Remove cheesecake from the oven and increase the oven temperature to 425 F.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 In a small bowl, combine the sour cream with 1/4 cup of confectioners' sugar and 2 teaspoons of vanilla.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 Spread the mixture over the cheesecake and return it to the hot oven. Continue baking for 8 minutes.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 Remove to a rack to cool completely.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 Top with cherry pie filling and chill thoroughly or chill the cheesecake without the topping and serve with topping drizzled over each slice.
a431ea84-77de-4a80-a99f-4962e2132965 Serve and enjoy1
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Gather the ingredients.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan, or coat with cooking spray.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Sprinkle 1/2 cup of the pecans evenly over bottom of pan.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Mix cranberries and 1/4 cup of the sugar in a small bowl; let stand while preparing batter.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Sift flour, remaining 1 cup sugar, baking powder, and salt into a large bowl.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Cut in shortening with a pastry blender or fork until mixture resembles a coarse meal.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Stir in the remaining pecans and lemon zest.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c In a small bowl, whisk together eggs and milk.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Add all at once to flour mixture; stir just until moist.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Stir in sugared cranberries.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Spoon onto prepared pan; spread top until even.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Bake at 350 degrees F. for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool in pan on a rack 10 minutes. Loosen around edge and center with knife; turn out onto rack. Cool completely.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Wrap loaf tightly. Store overnight at room temperature to allow flavors to meld and make slicing easier.
e1c723a0-82e8-42f2-8f0b-51a7c2536c7c Serve and enjoy!
0fd65f38-88e8-401a-afe9-fbe21ed882d6 Gather the ingredients.
0fd65f38-88e8-401a-afe9-fbe21ed882d6 Preheat the oven to 325 F/165 C/Gas Mark 3. Mix the pears with 1/2 cup of the sugar and let stand.
0fd65f38-88e8-401a-afe9-fbe21ed882d6 Put butter in a 2-quart baking dish and place in the oven until melted.
0fd65f38-88e8-401a-afe9-fbe21ed882d6 Combine the remaining sugar, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt in a mixing bowl. Mix well.
0fd65f38-88e8-401a-afe9-fbe21ed882d6 Whisk together the milk and egg in a separate small mixing bowl.
0fd65f38-88e8-401a-afe9-fbe21ed882d6 Slowly combine the milk and egg mixture with the dry ingredients to make a batter.
0fd65f38-88e8-401a-afe9-fbe21ed882d6 Pour the batter over the melted butter. Do not stir.
0fd65f38-88e8-401a-afe9-fbe21ed882d6 Spoon the sliced pears over the batter. Do not stir.
0fd65f38-88e8-401a-afe9-fbe21ed882d6 Bake in the preheated oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until nicely browned and the pears are tender. If the topping appears to be over-browning, cover the dish with foil and continue baking until the pears are tender.
0fd65f38-88e8-401a-afe9-fbe21ed882d6 Remove the cobbler from the oven and set it on a rack to cool slightly.
0fd65f38-88e8-401a-afe9-fbe21ed882d6 Enjoy the cobbler hot or cold with a scoop of ice cream or whipped cream.
b2269920-ce9c-455a-b0b9-06278084e572 Cut the panettone into one-inch square cubes, and place them in a large bowl.
b2269920-ce9c-455a-b0b9-06278084e572 Prepare the rum syrup: Place the sugar, water, cinnamon stick, pinch of salt and lime juice in a small saucepan and bring to boil. Simmer gently for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and let cool. Stir in the rum and the vanilla.
b2269920-ce9c-455a-b0b9-06278084e572 Spoon the syrup over the cubed pieces of panettone, and stir to make sure all the cake soaks up some syrup. Set aside.
b2269920-ce9c-455a-b0b9-06278084e572 Make the rum custard: Place the egg yolks in a heat-proof mixing bowl. Add the sugar, cornstarch, and a pinch of salt and whisk vigorously until mixture becomes pale yellow.
b2269920-ce9c-455a-b0b9-06278084e572 Add 1 cup of cream and 2 cups of milk to a large saucepan, and heat until it just starts to come to a boil. Gradually pour the milk mixture into the egg/sugar mixture, whisking constantly.
b2269920-ce9c-455a-b0b9-06278084e572 Return entire mixture (milk, eggs, sugar) to the saucepan and cook over medium-low heat, stirring, until mixture thickens and turns glossy about 5 minutes.
b2269920-ce9c-455a-b0b9-06278084e572 Remove from heat and stir in the butter and vanilla. Let cool for 5-10 minutes, then stir in the rum. Cover with saran wrap and chill mixture in the refrigerator for about 15 minutes, or until ready to assemble trifle.
b2269920-ce9c-455a-b0b9-06278084e572 Place the whipping cream in a large bowl and stir in the sugar. Whip cream until slightly stiff. Whisk 1/2 of the whipped cream into the custard. Set aside the rest for the top of the trifle.
b2269920-ce9c-455a-b0b9-06278084e572 In a glass bowl or trifle dish, place a layer of the cubed panettone, using about 1/3 of the cubes. Add 1/3 cup of the diced pineapple and 1/3 cup of the orange segments. Cover fruit with 1/3 of the custard mixture. Repeat layers two more times, ending with a layer of custard.
b2269920-ce9c-455a-b0b9-06278084e572 Spread the remaining whipped cream over the top of the trifle. Decorate the trifle with assorted fruit, such as more pineapple and orange, bananas, kiwi, grated coconut, pomegranate seeds, strawberries, blueberries or raspberries. Chill until ready to serve.
389fabfa-4601-4d26-99f8-7cd98b988f51 Gather the cake ingredients.
389fabfa-4601-4d26-99f8-7cd98b988f51 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Lightly coat a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
389fabfa-4601-4d26-99f8-7cd98b988f51 In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, salt, and 3/4 cup of sugar.
389fabfa-4601-4d26-99f8-7cd98b988f51 Add the room-temperature butter, milk, and eggs. Beat with a hand mixer at medium speed for 4 minutes or until all of the ingredients combine.
389fabfa-4601-4d26-99f8-7cd98b988f51 Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Position the plum halves on top, cut side up, pushing them down slightly into the batter.
389fabfa-4601-4d26-99f8-7cd98b988f51 Gather the topping ingredients.
389fabfa-4601-4d26-99f8-7cd98b988f51 Cut the remaining 1/4 cup of sugar and the cloves into 3 tablespoons of cold butter until crumbs form.
389fabfa-4601-4d26-99f8-7cd98b988f51 Sprinkle it over the plums.
389fabfa-4601-4d26-99f8-7cd98b988f51 Bake the cake on the center oven rack for about 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in several places comes out clean.
389fabfa-4601-4d26-99f8-7cd98b988f51 Let the cake cool in the pan to absorb the juice from the plums, resulting in an especially moist cake with intense plum flavor throughout.
389fabfa-4601-4d26-99f8-7cd98b988f51 Sprinkle the top with confectioner's sugar, if desired, and cut the cake into 12 squares.
2c5ed67f-34e8-4228-8ab2-9c062a277dea Gather the ingredients.
2c5ed67f-34e8-4228-8ab2-9c062a277dea Start by making the streusel topping. In a small bowl, combine the flour, butter, and brown sugar.
2c5ed67f-34e8-4228-8ab2-9c062a277dea With a fork, mix and mash until you have a crumbly texture.
2c5ed67f-34e8-4228-8ab2-9c062a277dea Combine the flour, sugar and baking powder in a 12-ounce mug.
2c5ed67f-34e8-4228-8ab2-9c062a277dea Add the apple sauce and mix well. Add the milk and diced apples but only mix lightly.
2c5ed67f-34e8-4228-8ab2-9c062a277dea Cook on medium-high in microwave for about 1 minute. Microwaves vary, but you’re looking for the cake to look done, and the edges to pull away slightly from the cup.
2c5ed67f-34e8-4228-8ab2-9c062a277dea While still warm, add the streusel topping and drizzle with caramel sauce.
2c5ed67f-34e8-4228-8ab2-9c062a277dea Serve immediately and enjoy!
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Gather the ingredients.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Rinse the strawberries under cold water; drain well.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Hull and slice the berries and place them in a bowl.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Sprinkle with the 1/3 cup of sugar; cover and let stand at room temperature for about 1 hour.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 In another bowl, beat the whipping cream until foamy. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons of powdered sugar, as desired, and continue beating until the cream holds soft peaks. Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Preheat the oven to 425 F. Set the rack in the center of the oven.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or buttered foil.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 In a food processor or bowl combine the flour, baking powder, salt, and 3 tablespoons of sugar. Blend well.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Slice the butter into about 8 pieces and add to the mixture.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Pulse in the food processor or blend with a pastry cutter or fingertips until the mixture resembles coarse meal. It should still have a few pea-sized chunks of butter left in the mixture.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Transfer the mixture to a large bowl and make a well in the center. With a fork stir in the milk or half-and-half just until the dough is moist. Be very careful not to overwork. The dough doesn't have to hold together well at this point. Let the dough rest in the bowl for a minute.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface. Fold the dough over on itself (knead) 2 or 3 times, until it is holding together and is less sticky.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Gently pat the dough into a 6 by 12-inch rectangle about 3/4-inch thick and cut into 8 (3-inch) biscuits with a floured round cutter. Or make smaller (2 or 2 1/2-inch) biscuits if you would like a few more servings. For flaky, soft biscuits, work the dough as little as possible.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Arrange the biscuits on the prepared baking sheet. Brush the biscuits with some milk or cream and sprinkle tops with some sugar, if desired.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Bake the biscuits in the preheated oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until risen and golden brown.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Remove the hot biscuits to a platter and split each horizontally with a serrated knife.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Butter the cut sides of the hot biscuits and then top with about 1/3 cup of berry mixture and some of the chilled whipped cream. Replace the tops and top with a tablespoon or so of berries and more whipped cream. Garnish with more strawberry slices and mint leaves, if desired.
f1cc6a7d-6c2e-41c0-acb9-92b7dcda99b0 Serve and enjoy!
751cec65-e03c-43e6-8b46-3c5270d96256 Gather the ingredients.
751cec65-e03c-43e6-8b46-3c5270d96256 Peel the apples; core them and cut into thin slices. Toss the sliced apples in a bowl with lemon juice to keep them from browning.
751cec65-e03c-43e6-8b46-3c5270d96256 Add the granulated sugar, the brown sugar, melted butter, flour, and spices. Stir until mixture is well blended.
751cec65-e03c-43e6-8b46-3c5270d96256 Prepare the pie pastry; fit into a pie plate and set aside.
751cec65-e03c-43e6-8b46-3c5270d96256 Heat the oven to 375 F.
751cec65-e03c-43e6-8b46-3c5270d96256 In a large bowl, combine the topping ingredients; blend with a pastry blender, two forks, or your fingers. Alternatively, pulse the ingredients a few times in a food processor.
751cec65-e03c-43e6-8b46-3c5270d96256 Pour the apple mixture into the prepared pie shell. Sprinkle the topping mixture evenly over top of apples.
751cec65-e03c-43e6-8b46-3c5270d96256 Bake the pie in the preheated oven for about 45 to 60 minutes, until apples are tender and topping is browned.
751cec65-e03c-43e6-8b46-3c5270d96256 Serve with vanilla ice cream and enjoy!
26c08dc0-31c1-4850-aa58-a3895c5d778b Gather the ingredients.
26c08dc0-31c1-4850-aa58-a3895c5d778b Place a mesh sieve over a bowl and, from the canned pineapple, strain the pineapple juice into the bowl. Set the juice aside.
26c08dc0-31c1-4850-aa58-a3895c5d778b Measure 6 tablespoons (about 1/3 cup) of crushed pineapple into a small bowl and set aside. Refrigerate or freeze any remaining crushed pineapple and juice for another use, if desired.
26c08dc0-31c1-4850-aa58-a3895c5d778b Add butter to a large bowl. Using an electric mixer, cream the butter until smooth and pale. Gradually beat in the confectioners' sugar. Continue beating until light and fluffy.
26c08dc0-31c1-4850-aa58-a3895c5d778b Stir in the 6 tablespoons of crushed pineapple and just enough of the reserved pineapple juice to make it spreadable. Beat to blend thoroughly.
26c08dc0-31c1-4850-aa58-a3895c5d778b Spread over cake layers or cupcakes. If desired, add more crushed pineapple and spoon the mixture over a Bundt cake.
2306ecf2-929b-48cb-b46e-2d2f83752035 Heat the oven to 325 F/165 C/Gas 3. Grease and flour a 9-by-5-by-3-inch loaf pan.
2306ecf2-929b-48cb-b46e-2d2f83752035 Cream sugar and butter; beat in the mashed bananas, eggs, and vanilla.
2306ecf2-929b-48cb-b46e-2d2f83752035 Combine dry ingredients and stir into the first mixture just until moistened.
2306ecf2-929b-48cb-b46e-2d2f83752035 Fold in chocolate chips until well incorporated.
2306ecf2-929b-48cb-b46e-2d2f83752035 Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan. Cover the pan loosely with a tent of aluminum foil.
2306ecf2-929b-48cb-b46e-2d2f83752035 Bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes. Remove foil and continue baking for 30 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted tests done.
2306ecf2-929b-48cb-b46e-2d2f83752035 Cool in the pan on a rack for 10 minutes and then remove the bread from the pan to cool completely before slicing.
7e207e6e-9d56-4450-9950-64a250e3da42 Gather the ingredients.
7e207e6e-9d56-4450-9950-64a250e3da42 Place candied fruit, ginger, raisins, currants, cherries, walnuts or lemon rind, orange marmalade, lemon juice, brandy or orange juice, and vanilla and almond extracts in a large bowl; toss well, cover and let stand overnight at room temperature.
7e207e6e-9d56-4450-9950-64a250e3da42 Grease, then line the bottom of a 10-inch tube pan with wax paper. Preheat oven to 250 F.
7e207e6e-9d56-4450-9950-64a250e3da42 Sift together twice the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, mace, cloves, allspice, baking powder, and salt, and set aside.
7e207e6e-9d56-4450-9950-64a250e3da42 Cream butter until light, add sugar gradually, and continue creaming until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
