7e207e6e-9d56-4450-9950-64a250e3da42 Add to dry ingredients, about 1 cup at a time, beating just to blend. (Note: Unless you have an extra-large mixing bowl, you will have to transfer batter to a large kettle at this point.) Mix in the fruit mixture.
7e207e6e-9d56-4450-9950-64a250e3da42 Spoon batter into the pan and, if you wish, decorate the top with halved candied cherries and walnuts. Place on center oven rack; half fill a roasting pan with water and place on the rack below. Bake uncovered, 4 1/4 hours until cake shrinks slightly from sides of the pan and a metal skewer inserted midway between the edge and the central tube comes out clean.
7e207e6e-9d56-4450-9950-64a250e3da42 Cool cake upright in pan on a wire rack for one hour. Carefully turn out, peel off the wax paper, turn right-side-up and cool thoroughly.
7e207e6e-9d56-4450-9950-64a250e3da42 Wrap in brandy or rum soaked cheesecloth then in foil, and store in an airtight container about 3 weeks to ripen. If you wish to store it longer, sprinkle cheesecloth wrapping with 2 to 3 tablespoons brandy or rum at 3-week intervals.
7e207e6e-9d56-4450-9950-64a250e3da42 Enjoy!
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Gather the ingredients.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Place the fruit in a large bowl with the orange juice and brandy. Stir gently and set aside for a few hours.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Generously butter the bottom and sides of two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans and line them with parchment paper. Butter the paper thoroughly. You can use brown paper for this if you don't have parchment paper.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Sift the flour with the spices twice. Add the baking powder and salt, then sift again.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Put the butter in a large mixing bowl and cream with a heavy-duty electric mixer until smooth. Add sugar, then cream until light and fluffy.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Beat the egg yolks slightly and then add them to the bowl. Mix the batter well.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Stir the batter as you add the flour and spice mix, a little at a time, stirring well after each addition. When the dry ingredients are thoroughly incorporated, add the molasses and stir.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Stir in the fruit, along with any soaking liquid left in the bowl.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Put the egg whites in a stainless steel or glass bowl and beat with a clean beater to stiff peaks.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Fold them into the batter thoroughly and then spoon the batter into the prepared pans.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Cover pans loosely with a clean cloth and let the batter sit overnight in a cool place to mellow.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a The next day, heat the oven to 250 F. Place the uncovered pans on the middle rack of the oven and bake for a total of 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a After 1 1/2 hours, cover the pans with a piece of brown paper (do not use foil) or set the pans in a paper bag and return them to the oven.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a When the cakes have baked for 3 1/2 hours, test them with a toothpick or cake tester. If the tester comes out of the center of the cakes clean, the cakes are done. Leave them in their pans and set on a wire rack to cool.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a When the cakes are completely cooled, turn out of the pans, leaving the paper lining on the cakes.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Wrap the cakes with parchment, then foil, and pack them in a tin. Homemade fruitcakes need air, so punch a few holes in the lid of the tin or set the cover loosely on the tin.
1317457e-f1e6-4ca7-81fd-4bb7be51c08a Set the tin in a cool, undisturbed place, and every three or four days before serving, open the foil and drizzle a small amount of brandy or bourbon over the cakes. The liquor will keep them moist and flavorful and help preserve them as well.
d90fc4eb-cc83-4bcf-b443-a22b0ec3a724 Gather the ingredients.
d90fc4eb-cc83-4bcf-b443-a22b0ec3a724 Preheat the oven to 400 F. Line a large baking sheet with parchment and set aside.
d90fc4eb-cc83-4bcf-b443-a22b0ec3a724 In a medium mixing bowl, toss the strawberries with the 2 tablespoons of sugar until well coated. Cover and place in the refrigerator for about 20 to 30 minutes.
d90fc4eb-cc83-4bcf-b443-a22b0ec3a724 Meanwhile, make the biscuits. In a food processor, mix together the remaining 1/4 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and salt until well-mixed.
d90fc4eb-cc83-4bcf-b443-a22b0ec3a724 Add the dairy-free soy margarine, pulsing until the mixture resembles fine crumbs.
d90fc4eb-cc83-4bcf-b443-a22b0ec3a724 With the machine still running, add the non-dairy milk alternative gradually, until the dough just begins to hold together and pull away from the sides of the bowl.
d90fc4eb-cc83-4bcf-b443-a22b0ec3a724 On a lightly floured surface, turn out the dough and pat into 8 small round biscuits.
d90fc4eb-cc83-4bcf-b443-a22b0ec3a724 Transfer the biscuits to the prepared baking sheet, sprinkle lightly with sugar, and bake about 18 to 22 minutes, or until golden.
d90fc4eb-cc83-4bcf-b443-a22b0ec3a724 Allow the biscuits to cool on the baking sheet.
d90fc4eb-cc83-4bcf-b443-a22b0ec3a724 To serve, place two biscuits on each plate with a scoop of dairy-free vanilla ice cream and a helping of the sugared strawberries.
d90fc4eb-cc83-4bcf-b443-a22b0ec3a724 Enjoy!
79208ace-bf5b-4fdb-b260-1712b5687f64 In a mixing bowl combine the flour, baking powder, salt, and cinnamon. Stir in brown sugar, breaking up large lumps. With a pastry blender or hands, cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Stir in chopped pecans.
79208ace-bf5b-4fdb-b260-1712b5687f64 In a cup or small bowl, whisk the egg with the milk. Add the milk and egg mixture to first mixture; stir with a fork until blended.
79208ace-bf5b-4fdb-b260-1712b5687f64 Turn two 8- or 9-inch round cake pans upside-down and grease bottoms. Lightly dust with flour.
79208ace-bf5b-4fdb-b260-1712b5687f64 Spread half the dough on each bottom to within about 1/2-inch of edge.
79208ace-bf5b-4fdb-b260-1712b5687f64 Sprinkle the dough lightly with a cinnamon sugar mixture, if desired.
79208ace-bf5b-4fdb-b260-1712b5687f64 Bake at 425 F for about 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown and then let cool.
79208ace-bf5b-4fdb-b260-1712b5687f64 Peel, slice, and sweeten peaches with about 1 1/2 cups sugar or to taste. In a small bowl, whip cream with the vanilla or almond extract until stiff.
79208ace-bf5b-4fdb-b260-1712b5687f64 Carefully place one shortcake on a plate, top with about half of the peaches and whipped cream. Top with second shortcake and remaining peaches and whipped cream.
a0478861-356a-4051-8fb1-3e7a9a88ed78 Gather the ingredients.
a0478861-356a-4051-8fb1-3e7a9a88ed78 Grease and flour a 9-inch square baking pan. Heat oven to 375 F/190 C/Gas 5.
a0478861-356a-4051-8fb1-3e7a9a88ed78 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer beat the 4 tablespoons of butter with 3/4 cup granulated sugar until creamy; add the egg and vanilla and continue to beat until smooth and well blended.
a0478861-356a-4051-8fb1-3e7a9a88ed78 Combine the 2 cups of flour, baking powder, and salt in a small bowl.
a0478861-356a-4051-8fb1-3e7a9a88ed78 Add the flour mixture to the butter mixture, alternating with 1/2 cup of milk and beating until smooth after each addition. Gently fold the blueberries into the batter.
a0478861-356a-4051-8fb1-3e7a9a88ed78 Spread the batter in the prepared baking pan.
a0478861-356a-4051-8fb1-3e7a9a88ed78 In a medium bowl, combine the 4 tablespoons of room temperature butter with the brown sugar, 1/3 cup of flour, and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon; blend well with a pastry blender, fork, or fingers to form crumbs.
a0478861-356a-4051-8fb1-3e7a9a88ed78 Sprinkle topping crumbs over the batter. Bake the cake in the preheated oven for 35 minutes.
a0478861-356a-4051-8fb1-3e7a9a88ed78 Remove the cake from the oven and allow it to cool. Slice it into squares and serve.
76945506-3778-49f0-8e12-94176256dd99 Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
76945506-3778-49f0-8e12-94176256dd99 Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water; stir in reserved pineapple juice. Chill until slightly set, about the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
76945506-3778-49f0-8e12-94176256dd99 Stir in pineapple and blueberries. Pour into a 9 1/2 x 6 x 2-inch pan; chill until firm.
76945506-3778-49f0-8e12-94176256dd99 In a bowl, combine sour cream, cream cheese, and sugar; mix well until smooth and well blended. Spread over blueberry salad and then top with chopped pecans or walnuts.
10d3b2c4-e00a-4c7c-a243-5ea90852c742 Generously grease and flour a Bundt cake pan or tube pan. Heat the oven to 350 F.
10d3b2c4-e00a-4c7c-a243-5ea90852c742 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer combine the cake mix, cream cheese, oil, and eggs; mix on low speed until blended. Add the vanilla and beat on high speed for 1 minute. Fold in the drained blueberries; stir until well combined.
10d3b2c4-e00a-4c7c-a243-5ea90852c742 Spread the batter evenly in the prepared baking pan.
10d3b2c4-e00a-4c7c-a243-5ea90852c742 Bake the blueberry cake in the preheated oven for about 45 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
e5746e73-f650-4fdf-93bf-efdc03780a7f Gather the ingredients. Heat oven to 325 F.
e5746e73-f650-4fdf-93bf-efdc03780a7f Dump cranberry sauce into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
e5746e73-f650-4fdf-93bf-efdc03780a7f Dump apple pie filling into the pan.
e5746e73-f650-4fdf-93bf-efdc03780a7f Spread mixture evenly and sprinkle dry cake mix on top. Cut up the butter and dot the top of cake.
e5746e73-f650-4fdf-93bf-efdc03780a7f Sprinkle walnuts or pecans over the cake batter.
e5746e73-f650-4fdf-93bf-efdc03780a7f Bake for 65 to 75 minutes, or until a toothpick or cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
e5746e73-f650-4fdf-93bf-efdc03780a7f Serve and enjoy!
c54fc882-aee0-480e-99b1-19057eacf520 Gather the ingredients.
c54fc882-aee0-480e-99b1-19057eacf520 Butter a 9-by-13-by-2-inch baking dish. Heat the oven to 350 F.
c54fc882-aee0-480e-99b1-19057eacf520 Put the cubed rhubarb in the baking dish.
c54fc882-aee0-480e-99b1-19057eacf520 Top with the granulated sugar, then sprinkle the gelatin over the sugar.
c54fc882-aee0-480e-99b1-19057eacf520 Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the gelatin layer, then pour the water over the cake mix layer.
c54fc882-aee0-480e-99b1-19057eacf520 Drizzle the melted butter over all. Do not stir or mix the ingredients.
c54fc882-aee0-480e-99b1-19057eacf520 Bake in the preheated oven for about 50 to 60 minutes.
c54fc882-aee0-480e-99b1-19057eacf520 Serve the cake warm with sweetened whipped cream, ice cream, or frozen (thawed) whipped topping.
c54fc882-aee0-480e-99b1-19057eacf520 Enjoy!
992e0d64-2d89-4d4d-91ff-b99b9d9f170e Gather the ingredients.
992e0d64-2d89-4d4d-91ff-b99b9d9f170e Heat oven to 375 F (190 C). Lightly spray 4 (7- to 8-ounce) ramekins or 5 to 6 (5- or 6-ounce) ramekins or custard cups with baking spray. Alternatively, you can lightly butter the bottoms and sides.
992e0d64-2d89-4d4d-91ff-b99b9d9f170e In a medium saucepan, combine the pitted cherries, water, sugar, and cornstarch and stir to blend. Place the pan over medium heat and bring to a simmer.
992e0d64-2d89-4d4d-91ff-b99b9d9f170e Reduce heat and continue simmering, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
992e0d64-2d89-4d4d-91ff-b99b9d9f170e Divide cherry mixture among the ramekins.
992e0d64-2d89-4d4d-91ff-b99b9d9f170e In a medium bowl, combine topping ingredients.
992e0d64-2d89-4d4d-91ff-b99b9d9f170e Using your fingers, sprinkle the topping evenly over each filled ramekin.
992e0d64-2d89-4d4d-91ff-b99b9d9f170e Put ramekins in the preheated oven with a baking sheet on the rack below to catch drips. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until the topping is browned and the filling is bubbly.
992e0d64-2d89-4d4d-91ff-b99b9d9f170e Serve and enjoy!
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Gather the ingredients.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Preheat oven to 350 F.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Butter a 3 1/2-quart baking dish and line the bottom with parchment paper.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Combine 1/3 cup flour, coconut, and macadamia nuts and process until nuts are finely chopped. Set aside.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e In a medium-size bowl, whisk together remaining 2 cups flour, ground ginger, cinnamon, baking powder, salt, and baking soda until well combined.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Using an electric mixer, beat sugar and oil in large bowl to blend. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Beat in vanilla. Mix in flour-spice mixture until well combined.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Stir in the coconut-macadamia mixture, then the carrots and crushed pineapple.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Bake until tester inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean, about 40 to 45 minutes.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Cool in the baking dish for an hour.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Run a knife around edge of pan to loosen cake. Turn cake out onto racks; cool completely.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e For the frosting, beat cream cheese and butter in large bowl until smooth.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Beat in powdered sugar, then cream of coconut and both extracts.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Chill until firm enough to spread, approximately 30 minutes.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Spread a thick layer of the frosting on the top of the cake.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Top with the macadamia nuts and toasted coconut.
63c86e21-6f7c-43db-9a27-e2e100ba4f9e Serve and enjoy!
2f0e4cd5-3a06-46e5-a067-241d28514897 Gather the ingredients.
2f0e4cd5-3a06-46e5-a067-241d28514897 Heat the oven to 350 F (180° C/Gas 4). Grease and flour three 8-inch round cake pans.
2f0e4cd5-3a06-46e5-a067-241d28514897 In a mixing bowl with electric mixer, cream 2 cups of sugar and 2 sticks of butter together until light and fluffy.
2f0e4cd5-3a06-46e5-a067-241d28514897 Combine 3 cups of flour and baking powder in another bowl.
2f0e4cd5-3a06-46e5-a067-241d28514897 Add the flour mixture alternately with milk to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture, beating after each addition. Stir in the vanilla.
2f0e4cd5-3a06-46e5-a067-241d28514897 Gently fold in beaten egg whites.
2f0e4cd5-3a06-46e5-a067-241d28514897 Divide batter among the three prepared cake pans.
2f0e4cd5-3a06-46e5-a067-241d28514897 Bake for 20 minutes, or until layers test done. Remove from pans and cool.
2395b5ac-7ba4-4838-8286-117206a5767f Heat the oven to 325 F.
2395b5ac-7ba4-4838-8286-117206a5767f Generously butter a 12-cup Bundt cake pan, covering all the nooks and crannies. Dust with flour.
2395b5ac-7ba4-4838-8286-117206a5767f Combine the vegetable oil with sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
2395b5ac-7ba4-4838-8286-117206a5767f Combine the flour, salt, and baking soda together, and add to the first mixture.
2395b5ac-7ba4-4838-8286-117206a5767f Stir in the vanilla extract.
2395b5ac-7ba4-4838-8286-117206a5767f Fold in apples and nuts.
2395b5ac-7ba4-4838-8286-117206a5767f Spoon the batter into the prepared cake pan, and spread it evenly.
2395b5ac-7ba4-4838-8286-117206a5767f Bake in the preheated oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 hour and 20 minutes. A toothpick inserted into the cake should come out clean.
2395b5ac-7ba4-4838-8286-117206a5767f Cool the cake on a rack for 10 minutes in the pan; invert the cake onto a rack, and place it on a large sheet of foil or parchment paper.
2395b5ac-7ba4-4838-8286-117206a5767f When the cake has cooled completely, drizzle with your favorite icing or glaze, such as our caramel icing.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 Gather the ingredients.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 Heat the oven to 350 F. Generously grease and flour a tube cake pan.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 Combine the flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon; stir or whisk to blend thoroughly and then set aside.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the eggs.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 Add the granulated sugar and oil and beat for 3 minutes.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 Gradually stir in sifted dry ingredients.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 Fold in apples, walnuts, and vanilla.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 Spoon the batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350 F for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 About 5 minutes before the cake is done, combine the topping ingredients in a saucepan.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 Bring to a boil over high heat and boil for 3 minutes.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 Pour the hot topping over the cake as soon as it comes out of the oven.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 Let the cake cool and then loosen the sides, inverting the cake on a plate.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 Then invert on another plate, topping side up.
a0a2f148-9407-49f2-b9a3-fc8d85783019 Slice, serve, and enjoy!
56117b21-c3c4-4050-aef4-6ace9f956eba Gather the ingredients.
56117b21-c3c4-4050-aef4-6ace9f956eba Preheat oven to 325 F/165 C. Grease and flour a Bundt cake pan or tube cake pan.
56117b21-c3c4-4050-aef4-6ace9f956eba In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream the softened butter with the sugar.
56117b21-c3c4-4050-aef4-6ace9f956eba Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat until light and fluffy. Add and mix in the vanilla.
56117b21-c3c4-4050-aef4-6ace9f956eba Sift 2 cups flour, salt, and baking powder together.
56117b21-c3c4-4050-aef4-6ace9f956eba Add the sifted ingredients to creamed mixture and beat until well blended.
56117b21-c3c4-4050-aef4-6ace9f956eba In a medium bowl, dredge berries in remaining 1/2 cup flour.
56117b21-c3c4-4050-aef4-6ace9f956eba Gently fold floured berries into the batter. Spread the batter in the prepared baking pan.
56117b21-c3c4-4050-aef4-6ace9f956eba Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.
23efa581-8f81-4405-b4f8-adfe0d2fd2e2 Heat the oven to 350 F. Grease and flour an 8-inch square baking pan.
23efa581-8f81-4405-b4f8-adfe0d2fd2e2 In a bowl, combine the sifted flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt. Stir to blend thoroughly.
23efa581-8f81-4405-b4f8-adfe0d2fd2e2 In a separate mixing bowl, whisk the milk with the egg and melted butter. Add the dry mixture and beat for 2 minutes.
23efa581-8f81-4405-b4f8-adfe0d2fd2e2 Spoon the batter into the prepared baking pan and spread evenly. Top with the sliced strawberries.
23efa581-8f81-4405-b4f8-adfe0d2fd2e2 Make the crumb topping: In a bowl, combine the flour and sugar; cut in the butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add chopped pecans or walnuts, if using.
23efa581-8f81-4405-b4f8-adfe0d2fd2e2 Sprinkle the crumb topping mixture over the strawberries.
23efa581-8f81-4405-b4f8-adfe0d2fd2e2 Bake in the preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into the center of the cake.
59589e69-862c-45ac-9c08-7e8e04c9fbfa Heat the oven to 350 F/180 C/Gas 4. Butter a 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
59589e69-862c-45ac-9c08-7e8e04c9fbfa Peel and core the apples. Chop them into 1/2-inch dice.
59589e69-862c-45ac-9c08-7e8e04c9fbfa In a bowl mix the chopped apples with 1 cup of sugar and the cinnamon; transfer to the prepared baking dish. Dot with the small pieces of butter.
59589e69-862c-45ac-9c08-7e8e04c9fbfa In a medium mixing bowl, whisk the egg. In another bowl combine the flour, 1/2 cup of sugar, and baking powder; blend thoroughly. Add the flour mixture to the beaten egg along with the melted butter. Stir until well blended.
59589e69-862c-45ac-9c08-7e8e04c9fbfa Using a teaspoon, spoon the topping batter evenly over the apple filling.
59589e69-862c-45ac-9c08-7e8e04c9fbfa Bake the apple crunch in the preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until the apples are tender and the topping is browned.
d3a34647-650a-4a91-ac6c-ffbb4eb07dda Gather the ingredients.
d3a34647-650a-4a91-ac6c-ffbb4eb07dda Preheat oven to 350 F.
d3a34647-650a-4a91-ac6c-ffbb4eb07dda Grease and flour a 9x13x2-inch baking pan.
d3a34647-650a-4a91-ac6c-ffbb4eb07dda In a large mixing bowl, combine the sugar, vegetable oil or shortening, eggs, and vanilla; beat until smooth and creamy.
d3a34647-650a-4a91-ac6c-ffbb4eb07dda Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, and nutmeg; slowly beat into egg mixture. Blend well.
d3a34647-650a-4a91-ac6c-ffbb4eb07dda Stir in pecans, raisins, and tomatoes.
d3a34647-650a-4a91-ac6c-ffbb4eb07dda Pour into the prepared baking pan. Top with coconut if desired.
d3a34647-650a-4a91-ac6c-ffbb4eb07dda Bake for 55 to 65 minutes, or until a wooden pick or cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
d3a34647-650a-4a91-ac6c-ffbb4eb07dda Serve and enjoy!
fd60d185-af88-4509-a0fd-32b2a5511e18 Gather the ingredients.
fd60d185-af88-4509-a0fd-32b2a5511e18 Preheat oven to 375 F. Butter an 8-inch square baking dish.
fd60d185-af88-4509-a0fd-32b2a5511e18 Peel the peaches and remove the pits. Slice the peaches and arrange them in the prepared baking dish.
fd60d185-af88-4509-a0fd-32b2a5511e18 In a medium bowl, combine the flour, sugar, salt, and cinnamon. Mix to blend thoroughly.
fd60d185-af88-4509-a0fd-32b2a5511e18 Cut butter into the flour mixture with pastry blender or fingers until mixture resembles coarse meal. Sprinkle the crumbs evenly over the peaches in baking dish.
fd60d185-af88-4509-a0fd-32b2a5511e18 Bake the peach crisp for 45 to 50 minutes, or until the topping, is golden brown and the peaches are tender.
fd60d185-af88-4509-a0fd-32b2a5511e18 Serve peach crisp warm with cream, whipped topping, or vanilla ice cream.
334cad54-8fab-4edd-94fc-9877387ea2f7 Heat the oven to 350 F.
334cad54-8fab-4edd-94fc-9877387ea2f7 Mix together 1/2 cup butter, 1 cup brown sugar, and 2 tablespoons evaporated milk or cream; spread in bottom of an 8-inch square baking pan.
334cad54-8fab-4edd-94fc-9877387ea2f7 Arrange sliced apples on the brown sugar mixture.
334cad54-8fab-4edd-94fc-9877387ea2f7 Sift together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt. Cream shortening with sugar; beat in the egg then add sifted ingredients alternately with 1/2 cup milk and the vanilla extract.
334cad54-8fab-4edd-94fc-9877387ea2f7 Pour batter over apples. Bake in the preheated oven for 35 to 45 minutes, or until the cake is done.
54261900-4645-4af1-90a7-f6aeb9b8b80e Heat the oven to 250 F.
54261900-4645-4af1-90a7-f6aeb9b8b80e Grease and flour a 10-inch tube cake pan.
54261900-4645-4af1-90a7-f6aeb9b8b80e In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, cream the butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
54261900-4645-4af1-90a7-f6aeb9b8b80e Add the eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
54261900-4645-4af1-90a7-f6aeb9b8b80e Dissolve the baking soda in buttermilk and add it to the first mixture.
54261900-4645-4af1-90a7-f6aeb9b8b80e Place the flour in large bowl and add dates, orange slice candy, and nuts. Stir to coat all pieces thoroughly.
54261900-4645-4af1-90a7-f6aeb9b8b80e Add the flour mixture and coconut to the creamed mixture. At this point, the batter will be stiff. It might be easier to mix with your hands or a sturdy spoon.
54261900-4645-4af1-90a7-f6aeb9b8b80e Spoon the batter into the prepared cake pan and spread evenly.
54261900-4645-4af1-90a7-f6aeb9b8b80e Bake in the preheated oven for 2 1/2 hours.
54261900-4645-4af1-90a7-f6aeb9b8b80e Just before the cake comes out of the oven, make the topping. In a medium bowl, combine the orange juice and confectioners' sugar. Stir until smooth and well blended. Gradually pour the juice mixture over hot cake as soon as it comes out of the oven. Use a toothpick to prick the cake in several places, if desired. Let the orange slice cake stand in the pan overnight.
54261900-4645-4af1-90a7-f6aeb9b8b80e Carefully invert the cake onto a cake plate; slice and serve.
87083927-b4d3-4255-9115-aa16da6726a5 Heat the oven to 350 F. Grease a deep-dish pie plate or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
87083927-b4d3-4255-9115-aa16da6726a5 Place a fine-mesh sieve over a bowl and drain the peaches. Set the peaches and the reserved liquids aside.
87083927-b4d3-4255-9115-aa16da6726a5 In a bowl with an electric mixer, mix the flour, instant pudding, softened butter, egg, and milk until smooth and blended. Spread the batter over the bottom of the prepared pie plate or baking dish. Arrange the drained peaches over batter.
87083927-b4d3-4255-9115-aa16da6726a5 In another bowl, beat the cream cheese, sugar, and 3 tablespoons of the reserved peach juice until smooth, about 2 minutes.
87083927-b4d3-4255-9115-aa16da6726a5 Spread the cream cheese mixture over peaches, leaving a 1-inch border.
87083927-b4d3-4255-9115-aa16da6726a5 In a small bowl, combine the cinnamon and sugar and then sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
87083927-b4d3-4255-9115-aa16da6726a5 Bake the peach dessert for 45 minutes in the preheated oven, or until the topping is lightly browned and set.
87083927-b4d3-4255-9115-aa16da6726a5 Cool before serving. Store leftovers in the refrigerator.
2c169dc7-367c-4cc6-8ccd-27472aa32468 Combine all ingredients except sweetened condensed milk.
2c169dc7-367c-4cc6-8ccd-27472aa32468 Mix well to blend.
2c169dc7-367c-4cc6-8ccd-27472aa32468 Add milk.
2c169dc7-367c-4cc6-8ccd-27472aa32468 Blend milk in thoroughly.
2c169dc7-367c-4cc6-8ccd-27472aa32468 Press with hands into waxed paper-lined pans.
2c169dc7-367c-4cc6-8ccd-27472aa32468 Chill.
2c169dc7-367c-4cc6-8ccd-27472aa32468 Cut into small pieces (very rich!).
33ebd359-5000-4c70-bd03-af5fe94eb86e Heat oven to 325 F. Butter a 9-inch square cake pan or spray with baking spray.
33ebd359-5000-4c70-bd03-af5fe94eb86e Core the apples and cut into wedges; peel and slice thinly. Combine apple slices with the brown sugar, 1 scant teaspoon of cinnamon and 4 tablespoons of melted butter. Arrange the apple mixture in the prepared baking pan.
33ebd359-5000-4c70-bd03-af5fe94eb86e Combine the flour, salt, baking powder and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a bowl.
33ebd359-5000-4c70-bd03-af5fe94eb86e In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat butter with the sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla extract. Add the flour mixture to the first mixture, alternating with the milk, beating just until blended. Spoon the batter evenly over the apple slices; gently spreading to cover.
33ebd359-5000-4c70-bd03-af5fe94eb86e Bake for 55 to 65 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean.
33ebd359-5000-4c70-bd03-af5fe94eb86e Invert the hot cake onto a platter or cake plate and let stand for about 5 minutes. Remove the pan and scrape up any fruit slices clinging to the pan and arrange them over the cake.
023da31e-29a4-497b-8963-3503df7d2586 Preheat oven to 350 F.
023da31e-29a4-497b-8963-3503df7d2586 In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, 1/2 cup cream of coconut, 1/2 cup rum, oil, and eggs.
023da31e-29a4-497b-8963-3503df7d2586 Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
023da31e-29a4-497b-8963-3503df7d2586 Stir in drained crushed pineapple.
023da31e-29a4-497b-8963-3503df7d2586 Pour into a well greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake for 50-55 minutes.
023da31e-29a4-497b-8963-3503df7d2586 Cool slightly; remove from pan.
023da31e-29a4-497b-8963-3503df7d2586 With a table knife or skewer poke holes about 1 inch apart in cake almost to bottom. Combine remaining cream of coconut and rum; pour over cake.
023da31e-29a4-497b-8963-3503df7d2586 Chill thoroughly then garnish. Store in refrigerator.
797b3176-2c73-43de-8441-aff01d2de53d Gather the ingredients.
797b3176-2c73-43de-8441-aff01d2de53d Preheat oven to 375 F. Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
797b3176-2c73-43de-8441-aff01d2de53d In the pan, mix apples and nuts with 2 teaspoons cinnamon, nutmeg, and sugar.
797b3176-2c73-43de-8441-aff01d2de53d Spread evenly in the pan and cover with apple cider.
797b3176-2c73-43de-8441-aff01d2de53d Sprinkle dry cake mix over apple mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon.
797b3176-2c73-43de-8441-aff01d2de53d Pour melted butter over top.
797b3176-2c73-43de-8441-aff01d2de53d Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.
797b3176-2c73-43de-8441-aff01d2de53d Serve and enjoy!
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 Heat the oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4). Butter and flour two 9-inch cake pans.
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 In a large mixing bowl beat the 1 1/2 cups of butter and the granulated sugar. Add mashed bananas; beat well with electric mixer for 1 minute.
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 Add flavorings and 1/2 cup of chopped walnuts or pecans.
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 In a bowl, combine the cake flour, baking powder, soda, and salt; beat into creamed mixture alternating with the sour milk or buttermilk, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients. Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed of electric mixer.
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 Divide the batter evenly between the two prepared cake pans.
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 Bake in the preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 Cool on wire racks for 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool the layers thoroughly on racks.
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 While the cake is cooling, make the frosting.
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, 6 tablespoons of butter, a dash of salt, and 1/2 cup of milk; bring to a boil over medium heat.
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 When it comes to a full boil, begin timing it. Boil for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove the mixture from heat; let stand 8 to 10 minutes.
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 Gradually add the powdered sugar to the mixture, beating with an electric mixer. Continue beating until the frosting reaches a good spreading consistency; add vanilla and blend well.
51af102f-93ea-43d7-ac1f-64fca6f9cfb6 Frost the cake layers and sprinkle with the 1/2 cup of chopped walnuts or pecans.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 Grease and flour a 9-inch square baking pan.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, and salt; stir with a spoon or wire whisk and set aside.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat together 1 cup of brown sugar, the vegetable oil, cinnamon, and 1 tablespoon of vanilla. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add the milk and beat until the batter is smooth.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 To the batter, add the dry ingredients and stir just until blended. Fold the chopped apples into the batter.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 Bake the apple cake in the preheated oven until it is firm and springs back when touched lightly in the center with a finger, or about 30 to 40 minutes.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 Meanwhile, make the caramel topping.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 In a heavy saucepan, combine the 1/2 cup of brown sugar, 1/4 cup of butter, and the heavy cream. Place the pan over medium heat and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to low to maintain a simmer; continue cooking, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes. Remove the sauce from the heat and stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 With a fork, pierce the hot cake all over.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 Pour the hot caramel topping over the cake.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 Serve the cake warm or at room temperature with a dollop of sweetened whipped cream or whipped topping. Alternatively, serve with a scoop of ice cream.
f9412bde-1f0b-44b4-94c9-53a6f2418ab9 Store leftover cake well-wrapped or in an airtight container for about 2 to 3 days at room temperature or up to 4 to 5 days in the refrigerator.
ae0b5088-e16a-4fcb-bd6b-9d9bd032545d Gather the ingredients.
ae0b5088-e16a-4fcb-bd6b-9d9bd032545d Preheat the oven to 350 F.
ae0b5088-e16a-4fcb-bd6b-9d9bd032545d In a large mixing bowl combine first flour, butter, and brown sugar. Blend together until crumbly, using a mixer on low speed. Stir in chopped pecans. Press 2 3/4 cups of the crumb mixture into an ungreased 13X9-inch pan.
ae0b5088-e16a-4fcb-bd6b-9d9bd032545d To the remaining mixture add cinnamon, soda, salt, sour cream, vanilla, and egg. Blend well with mixer. Stir in the chopped apples. Spoon evenly over the crumb layer.
ae0b5088-e16a-4fcb-bd6b-9d9bd032545d Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
ae0b5088-e16a-4fcb-bd6b-9d9bd032545d Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired. Serve warm or cold.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 Gather the ingredients.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 Drain the peaches, reserving 2 tablespoons of the syrup.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 Add the melted butter to a 9-inch square baking pan. Add the brown sugar, reserved syrup, and coconut to the butter; stir and spread to evenly cover the bottom of the pan. Arrange peach slices, cut side up, over the coconut mixture.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 Heat the oven to 350 F.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 In mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat 1/2 cup softened butter until light and fluffy.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 Beat in granulated sugar until fluffy.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 Add eggs and blend well. Blend in vanilla.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 In another bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 Gradually beat the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture, alternating with the milk. Beat on medium speed for about 2 minutes.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 Spoon the batter evenly over peaches and then spread to cover.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 Bake in the preheated oven for 40 to 50 minutes, or until a wooden pick or cake tester inserted in center comes out with no cake batter clinging.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 Cool in pan for 5 to 8 minutes before inverting onto a serving plate.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 To invert the cake onto the plate, gently run a knife along sides of the pan. Cover the cake pan with the serving plate. Using pot holders or oven mitts and both hands, carefully turn it over so the cake will easily drop onto the plate in one piece. If some of the peach topping mixtures stick to the pan, scrape it out onto the cake.
c8f185cc-85da-4994-850c-bb584d32c7a6 Slice and serve the cake warm with whipped topping or ice cream.
75b2a221-56d5-45e4-ba30-c862a6bdd4d0 Gather the ingredients.
75b2a221-56d5-45e4-ba30-c862a6bdd4d0 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
75b2a221-56d5-45e4-ba30-c862a6bdd4d0 Melt 3 tablespoons in 2-round cake pans or all 6 tablespoons of butter in a 9 x 13 pan in the oven.
75b2a221-56d5-45e4-ba30-c862a6bdd4d0 Remove the pan(s) from the oven and sprinkle the bottom(s) with the brown sugar. Use a spoon to evenly spread it.
75b2a221-56d5-45e4-ba30-c862a6bdd4d0 Decoratively arrange the pineapple slices on top of the brown sugar. Fill in the spaces with the maraschino cherries.
75b2a221-56d5-45e4-ba30-c862a6bdd4d0 In a bowl, break the eggs. Add the coconut oil and crushed pineapple. Stir them together.
75b2a221-56d5-45e4-ba30-c862a6bdd4d0 Pour the cake mix on top of the wet ingredients. Mix for at least 2 minutes. Don’t worry if the crushed pineapple becomes even finer.
75b2a221-56d5-45e4-ba30-c862a6bdd4d0 Carefully, pour the batter in the prepared pan(s).
75b2a221-56d5-45e4-ba30-c862a6bdd4d0 Bake the cake(s) for about 40 minutes or until done.
75b2a221-56d5-45e4-ba30-c862a6bdd4d0 Remove them from the oven. Very carefully invert the cake(s) onto a serving platter or plate.
75b2a221-56d5-45e4-ba30-c862a6bdd4d0 Serve your Double Pineapple Upside-Down Cake warm or room temperature topped with whipped cream.
75b2a221-56d5-45e4-ba30-c862a6bdd4d0 Enjoy!
1de8aa1d-609f-4b6d-b0cd-a93ec4a33b24 Combine fruits and nuts in a large bowl. Pour brandy over and cover the bowl tightly. Let mixture stand overnight or up to 48 hours.
1de8aa1d-609f-4b6d-b0cd-a93ec4a33b24 Heat the oven to 250 F.
1de8aa1d-609f-4b6d-b0cd-a93ec4a33b24 Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans and two tube cake pans (or use more loaf pans). Grease a sheet of foil or parchment paper and line the pan.
1de8aa1d-609f-4b6d-b0cd-a93ec4a33b24 Beat butter until light and creamy. Beat in brown sugar until mixture is light and fluffy. Beat in eggs a few at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat until well blended.
1de8aa1d-609f-4b6d-b0cd-a93ec4a33b24 Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, and spices.
1de8aa1d-609f-4b6d-b0cd-a93ec4a33b24 Stir lemon and orange juices into the creamed mixture, then stir in flour mixture.
1de8aa1d-609f-4b6d-b0cd-a93ec4a33b24 Transfer batter to a very large pot or bowl, large enough to hold batter and all fruits and nuts. With a long-handled wooden spoon, stir in fruit and nut mixture, along with the brandy which has not been absorbed. Blend thoroughly.
1de8aa1d-609f-4b6d-b0cd-a93ec4a33b24 Turn the batter into the prepared pans.
1de8aa1d-609f-4b6d-b0cd-a93ec4a33b24 Bake in the preheated oven for about 3 hours, or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into the cake (not into fruit).
1de8aa1d-609f-4b6d-b0cd-a93ec4a33b24 Cool the cakes in pans on racks. When cool, remove them from the pans and carefully peel off the foil or paper.
1de8aa1d-609f-4b6d-b0cd-a93ec4a33b24 Wrap the cakes in cheesecloth and sprinkle generously with more of the brandy.
1de8aa1d-609f-4b6d-b0cd-a93ec4a33b24 Seal cakes in food storage bags or plastic wrap. Brush cakes once a week with more brandy and then reseal.
0f8aaaf0-dac7-4a92-87c6-f98df00fc46f Gather the ingredients.
0f8aaaf0-dac7-4a92-87c6-f98df00fc46f Preheat the oven to 350 F. Grease a 9 x 13 baking pan.
0f8aaaf0-dac7-4a92-87c6-f98df00fc46f Combine the flour and baking powder in a small bowl with a wire whisk and set aside.
0f8aaaf0-dac7-4a92-87c6-f98df00fc46f In a large bowl combine the eggs, 2 cups of sugar and the can of crushed pineapple with its juice. Mix well.
0f8aaaf0-dac7-4a92-87c6-f98df00fc46f Stir in the flour mixture and mix until just combined and no more flour is visible.
0f8aaaf0-dac7-4a92-87c6-f98df00fc46f Carefully pour the batter into the prepared pan.
0f8aaaf0-dac7-4a92-87c6-f98df00fc46f Bake the cake for 25 to 30 minutes.
0f8aaaf0-dac7-4a92-87c6-f98df00fc46f While the cake is baking, combine the remaining cup of sugar with the butter and evaporated milk in a heavy saucepan. Bring the mixture to a boil. Stir it constantly for 3 to 4 minutes.
0f8aaaf0-dac7-4a92-87c6-f98df00fc46f Remove it from the heat and stir in the pecans, coconut, vanilla and lemon juice.
0f8aaaf0-dac7-4a92-87c6-f98df00fc46f After removing the cake from the oven, poke holes in the top of the cake with a wooden spoon handle.
0f8aaaf0-dac7-4a92-87c6-f98df00fc46f Pour the hot icing over the hot cake.
0f8aaaf0-dac7-4a92-87c6-f98df00fc46f Allow the Pineapple Coconut Cake to cool completely on wire rack before serving. Optionally, serve with whipped cream.
be49432b-9af9-46db-8d74-f2ac55a218f4 In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, apricot nectar, 1/4 cup apricot brandy, and vegetable oil. Beat on medium speed until batter is smooth, about 2 minutes. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Fold in the chopped fruits and nuts.
be49432b-9af9-46db-8d74-f2ac55a218f4 Turn batter into a generously greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
be49432b-9af9-46db-8d74-f2ac55a218f4 Bake at 350 F for 50 to 55 minutes, or until cake tests done.
be49432b-9af9-46db-8d74-f2ac55a218f4 Cool for 15 minutes in the pan and then remove it to a rack to cool thoroughly.
be49432b-9af9-46db-8d74-f2ac55a218f4 For best flavor, wrap and store in the refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
cdbcd29d-a0b2-4256-bd09-271e20b30a24 Gather the ingredients.
cdbcd29d-a0b2-4256-bd09-271e20b30a24 Preheat the oven to 325 F.
cdbcd29d-a0b2-4256-bd09-271e20b30a24 Grease and flour a 9x13x2-inch baking pan.
cdbcd29d-a0b2-4256-bd09-271e20b30a24 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat eggs; add water, oil, 2 tablespoons of lime juice, instant pudding and cake mix. Beat until well blended.
cdbcd29d-a0b2-4256-bd09-271e20b30a24 Pour into the prepared baking pan.
cdbcd29d-a0b2-4256-bd09-271e20b30a24 Bake for approximately 45 to 55 minutes.
cdbcd29d-a0b2-4256-bd09-271e20b30a24 Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine the confectioners' sugar and 1/3 cup of lime juice. Stir or whisk until smooth.
cdbcd29d-a0b2-4256-bd09-271e20b30a24 About 5 to 10 minutes after the cake comes out of the oven, prick the surface all over with a fork or skewer.
cdbcd29d-a0b2-4256-bd09-271e20b30a24 Pour glaze over cake.
cdbcd29d-a0b2-4256-bd09-271e20b30a24 Cool and serve the cake from the pan.
cdbcd29d-a0b2-4256-bd09-271e20b30a24 Enjoy!
35493d7b-5da4-40ca-b385-b2c49c36707d Gather the ingredients.
35493d7b-5da4-40ca-b385-b2c49c36707d The day before baking, place the dried fruits in a large bowl, add the tea and stir well. Cover and leave overnight.
35493d7b-5da4-40ca-b385-b2c49c36707d Preheat the oven to 325 F/170 C/Gas Mark 3. Line an 8-inch round cake tin with greaseproof paper or baking parchment.
35493d7b-5da4-40ca-b385-b2c49c36707d Place the butter and sugar into a large baking bowl.
35493d7b-5da4-40ca-b385-b2c49c36707d Using an electric hand whisk or fork, cream the butter into the sugar until light, smooth, and creamy.
35493d7b-5da4-40ca-b385-b2c49c36707d Beat 1 egg into the creamed butter, then beat in a 1/4 of the flour. Repeat until all the eggs and flour are used up. Add the treacle, brandy or sherry, nutmeg, lemon juice to the cake mixture, and stir gently using a spoon or spatula. Finally, stir in the baking powder.
35493d7b-5da4-40ca-b385-b2c49c36707d Drain the dried fruits and add the ground almonds, glace cherries, and mixed peel. Stir well, then add to the cake mixture, stirring gently until all the fruits are incorporated into the mixture. Stir gently so as not to "flatten" the cake mixture.
35493d7b-5da4-40ca-b385-b2c49c36707d Spoon the mixture into the prepared cake tin and gently level the surface.
35493d7b-5da4-40ca-b385-b2c49c36707d Cook in the preheated oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until dark, golden brown.
a0aac87b-ae27-4338-bb4c-df3a4809699d Preheat the oven to 350 F. Grease and flour a Bundt pan and set aside.
a0aac87b-ae27-4338-bb4c-df3a4809699d In a medium bowl, combine the diced apples, 2 tbsp. sugar, 1 tsp. cinnamon, and nutmeg; set aside. Sift together flour, baking powder, and salt.
a0aac87b-ae27-4338-bb4c-df3a4809699d In a large bowl, combine 1 cup white sugar, brown sugar, oil, apple juice, vanilla, and eggs. Beat at high speed until smooth. Stir in flour mixture. Fold in chopped walnuts and apple mixture.
a0aac87b-ae27-4338-bb4c-df3a4809699d Pour the batter into prepared pan. Bake at 350 F for 55 to 60 minutes, or until cake is firm, well browned, and begins to pull away from pan edges. Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack and cool completely. Sprinkle with confectioners' sugar, if desired, before serving.
eee65978-bb58-4234-8b79-cb260c482fed Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F.
eee65978-bb58-4234-8b79-cb260c482fed Lightly grease and flour a loaf pan. You can also use an 8-inch diameter cake pan if you prefer.
eee65978-bb58-4234-8b79-cb260c482fed Using a fork, whip the egg replacer in 4 tablespoons of water until fluffy.
eee65978-bb58-4234-8b79-cb260c482fed Place the vegan margarine, sugar, candied fruit, whipped egg replacer, and cup water (or orange juice) in a saucepan. Bring the mixture to a boil, then allow to cool for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
eee65978-bb58-4234-8b79-cb260c482fed In a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and allspice.
eee65978-bb58-4234-8b79-cb260c482fed Mix in the boiled mixture until combined well and transfer the batter to the greased loaf tin or a greased 8-inch diameter cake tin.
eee65978-bb58-4234-8b79-cb260c482fed Bake your vegan fruitcake in the preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
eee65978-bb58-4234-8b79-cb260c482fed Let your fruitcake cool completely inside the tin or baking pan. Fruitcake is usually served room temperature or chilled. You might want to drizzle just a little vegan icing on top if you like super sweet desserts.
a090024d-b4d1-46ae-ab78-182b7082cb0b Roughly chop the nuts. Soak the nuts, raisins, and candied fruit in the rum overnight. Drain the nuts and fruit and reserve the rum.
a090024d-b4d1-46ae-ab78-182b7082cb0b Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.
a090024d-b4d1-46ae-ab78-182b7082cb0b Cream the butter with the brown sugar.
a090024d-b4d1-46ae-ab78-182b7082cb0b Gradually beat in the five egg yolks, molasses, and honey.
a090024d-b4d1-46ae-ab78-182b7082cb0b Sift the flour with the cinnamon, pie spice, and baking powder and add to the batter, alternating with the reserved rum. Stir in nuts, raisins, and fruit.
a090024d-b4d1-46ae-ab78-182b7082cb0b In a separate, clean bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form. Fold egg whites gently into the batter.
a090024d-b4d1-46ae-ab78-182b7082cb0b Pour the batter into a 9 x 5-inch bread pan, or into a 10-inch diameter by 2-inch cake pan.
a090024d-b4d1-46ae-ab78-182b7082cb0b Bake for 45 minutes, then check the cake. A toothpick inserted in the center should come out clean. If the cake is not done, return to the oven and check every 10 minutes until the toothpick comes out clean.
a090024d-b4d1-46ae-ab78-182b7082cb0b To make the icing, place 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar in a bowl. Whisk in orange juice 1 tablespoon at a time, until desired consistency, is reached. Icing should be slightly runny.
a090024d-b4d1-46ae-ab78-182b7082cb0b Drizzle icing over top of the cake, and decorate with raisins and nuts.
73494a00-10e9-47b0-9389-2b94fab0f30d Gather the ingredients.
73494a00-10e9-47b0-9389-2b94fab0f30d Grease and flour a 9x13-inch baking pan.
73494a00-10e9-47b0-9389-2b94fab0f30d Heat the oven to 350 F.
73494a00-10e9-47b0-9389-2b94fab0f30d In a mixing bowl combine the cake mix, pumpkin, 1/2 cup of brown sugar, the eggs, vegetable oil, cinnamon, nutmeg, and 1/4 cup of milk or half-and-half.
73494a00-10e9-47b0-9389-2b94fab0f30d Beat on medium speed, scraping the sides and bottom of the bowl frequently, until smooth and blended.
73494a00-10e9-47b0-9389-2b94fab0f30d Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
73494a00-10e9-47b0-9389-2b94fab0f30d Bake for 35 to 45 minutes, or until the cake springs back lightly when touched with a finger.
73494a00-10e9-47b0-9389-2b94fab0f30d Meanwhile, combine the topping ingredients in a small bowl, stirring until blended.
73494a00-10e9-47b0-9389-2b94fab0f30d Spread the topping over the warm cake and broil about 4 to 6 inches from the heat source for about 3 minutes, or until the topping is bubbly and browned.
8d7b4b2e-918f-4311-a22d-119c011010c0 Gather the ingredients.
8d7b4b2e-918f-4311-a22d-119c011010c0 Preheat oven to 350 F. Grease or paper-line 18 muffin cups.
8d7b4b2e-918f-4311-a22d-119c011010c0 In a large bowl, combine eggs, sour cream, and apple pie filling, mixing well.
8d7b4b2e-918f-4311-a22d-119c011010c0 Add cake mix to the bowl, being careful not to overmix the batter.
8d7b4b2e-918f-4311-a22d-119c011010c0 Place batter in muffin cups and sprinkle tops with ground cinnamon (optional).
8d7b4b2e-918f-4311-a22d-119c011010c0 Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into the muffin. Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing.
8d7b4b2e-918f-4311-a22d-119c011010c0 Serve warm with butter and enjoy!
5df08940-e1c0-41f4-8729-2adcda4b5160 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Spray two 8 inch round cake pans OR one 13" x 9" cake pan with nonstick baking spray containing flour and set aside.
5df08940-e1c0-41f4-8729-2adcda4b5160 Pour one portion of the cake mix into a large bowl and stir in the spices.
5df08940-e1c0-41f4-8729-2adcda4b5160 Make a well in the center of the mix and add the vanilla, oil, eggs, and milk. Beat this mixture 1 minute with an electric mixer at low speed until blended. Scrape the sides and bottom of the bowl and beat for 2 minutes longer at medium speed until batter is smooth.
5df08940-e1c0-41f4-8729-2adcda4b5160 Pour the batter into the prepared pans and bake the layer cakes at 350 F for 20 to 30 minutes, or until the cake springs back when pressed lightly in center and it begins to pull away from the edges of the pan. Bake the 9" x 13" cake for 25 to 35 minutes until the cake tests done.
7ce151c3-1ece-43cc-aa66-7f8f7eac3f6b Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F. Grease and flour one 8-inch round cake pan and one 8-inch square cake pan.
7ce151c3-1ece-43cc-aa66-7f8f7eac3f6b In a large mixing bowl, combine the cake mix, water, oil, and eggs. Blend at low speed until moistened, about 30 seconds. Scrape down the sides of the bowl and then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
7ce151c3-1ece-43cc-aa66-7f8f7eac3f6b Divide the batter evenly between the round and square baking pans. Bake for 26 to 31 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center of the cakes come out clean.
7ce151c3-1ece-43cc-aa66-7f8f7eac3f6b Cool in the pans for 10 minutes. Remove cakes from pans and cool completely on wire racks before frosting.
7ce151c3-1ece-43cc-aa66-7f8f7eac3f6b In a medium bowl, whisk together the milk, pudding mix, and powdered sugar. Beat for 2 minutes.
7ce151c3-1ece-43cc-aa66-7f8f7eac3f6b Gently stir in the whipped topping and red food coloring.
7ce151c3-1ece-43cc-aa66-7f8f7eac3f6b Leave the square cake whole. Cut the round cake in half.
7ce151c3-1ece-43cc-aa66-7f8f7eac3f6b Assemble the pieces on a serving tray in a heart shape by placing the cut side of the round cake on two of the flat sides of the square cake.
7ce151c3-1ece-43cc-aa66-7f8f7eac3f6b Frost the top and sides of the cake with the prepared topping.
7ce151c3-1ece-43cc-aa66-7f8f7eac3f6b Decorate with candies or sprinkles.
7ce151c3-1ece-43cc-aa66-7f8f7eac3f6b Enjoy!
27c9be1f-d0b4-47e3-8171-d6300fd1b43a While the baked cake is still hot, poke holes throughout the cake with a fork.
27c9be1f-d0b4-47e3-8171-d6300fd1b43a Mix the sweetened condensed milk with the cream of coconut in a measuring cup or bowl and pour over cake, making sure it goes into the poked holes. Cool the cake completely.​​
27c9be1f-d0b4-47e3-8171-d6300fd1b43a Spread the non-dairy whipped topping over the top of the cake. Sprinkle with the coconut.
64191fa8-ca1b-4dd3-abe6-e1c54bf51a70 Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray a 9x13" pan or two 9" pans with a nonstick cooking spray containing flour; set aside.
64191fa8-ca1b-4dd3-abe6-e1c54bf51a70 In large bowl, combine cake mix, whipped topping mix, water, and eggs and beat until blended. Then beat for 4 minutes at medium speed, until batter increases in volume. Pour into the prepared cake pan(s).
64191fa8-ca1b-4dd3-abe6-e1c54bf51a70 Bake the 9" pans for 25 to 30 minutes, and the 9x13" pan for 30 to 40 minutes or until cake pulls away from edges of the pan and is dark golden brown. Cool in pans for 5 minutes, then remove the 9" cakes from pans. Keep the 9x13" cake in its pan. Frost as desired.
64191fa8-ca1b-4dd3-abe6-e1c54bf51a70 Serve and enjoy!
b3540cd8-f1fc-44f0-a68f-3b8d83adb5dc Heat oven to 350 F.
b3540cd8-f1fc-44f0-a68f-3b8d83adb5dc Measure flour by lightly spooning the flour into the measuring cup, NOT by scooping the measuring cup into the flour. The scoop-and-level method is incorrect and will make this cake too dry.
b3540cd8-f1fc-44f0-a68f-3b8d83adb5dc In a large bowl, combine butter, white sugar and brown sugar and beat until mixture is light and fluffy. Add melted and cooled chocolate, beating until combined.
b3540cd8-f1fc-44f0-a68f-3b8d83adb5dc Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition until eggs combine with butter mixture (this can take some time).
b3540cd8-f1fc-44f0-a68f-3b8d83adb5dc Sift the confectioners' sugar BEFORE you measure it. Gradually add it to the batter, mixing well. By hand, stir in flour, cocoa, vanilla, and pecans until well blended.
b3540cd8-f1fc-44f0-a68f-3b8d83adb5dc Spray a 12-cup Bundt pan with nonstick baking spray combined with flour. Spoon batter into prepared pan. Bake at 350 F for 48 to 54 minutes, until crust looks dry and shiny (traditional doneness tests won't work because of the soft fudge center).
b3540cd8-f1fc-44f0-a68f-3b8d83adb5dc Cool cake in pan on a rack for 1 hour, then invert onto serving plate and remove pan. Cool completely. If you bake the cake for a shorter period of time, it will have true fudge in the center. Bake it longer for a moist tunnel in the center.
b3540cd8-f1fc-44f0-a68f-3b8d83adb5dc Make the glaze by placing the chocolate chips and oil in a small microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on 50% power for 2 minutes and then stir. Continue microwaving until chocolate is melted and the mixture is smooth.
b3540cd8-f1fc-44f0-a68f-3b8d83adb5dc Pour into a small zip-top bag. Cut a tiny piece off the corner of the bag and pipe the chocolate over the cake, using a back-and-forth motion. Let cool.
4e2de0c3-8568-451b-8f4c-d8404b256a6e Gather the ingredients. Heat oven to 325 F.
4e2de0c3-8568-451b-8f4c-d8404b256a6e Dump cranberry sauce into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
4e2de0c3-8568-451b-8f4c-d8404b256a6e Dump apple pie filling into the pan.
4e2de0c3-8568-451b-8f4c-d8404b256a6e Spread mixture evenly and sprinkle dry cake mix on top. Cut up the butter and dot the top of cake.
4e2de0c3-8568-451b-8f4c-d8404b256a6e Sprinkle walnuts or pecans over the cake batter.
4e2de0c3-8568-451b-8f4c-d8404b256a6e Bake for 65 to 75 minutes, or until a toothpick or cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
4e2de0c3-8568-451b-8f4c-d8404b256a6e Serve and enjoy!
06fd4dc8-56d9-445a-bc11-299a4d46e93d Prepare cake mix according to package directions; bake in a 13x9x2-inch pan. While still warm, puncture cake with a fork, about every 2 inches.
06fd4dc8-56d9-445a-bc11-299a4d46e93d Combine Jell-O and boiling water. Stir to dissolve. Add strawberry soda pop to Jell-O and stir. Pour over cake while warm.
06fd4dc8-56d9-445a-bc11-299a4d46e93d Spread the cool whip over the cooled strawberry cake before you serve.
06fd4dc8-56d9-445a-bc11-299a4d46e93d Serve with a few fresh strawberries for garnish.
bb6efc81-23f1-4792-b4af-8a8677c948e6 Gather the ingredients.
bb6efc81-23f1-4792-b4af-8a8677c948e6 Heat the oven to 350 F. Spray a 13x9-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
bb6efc81-23f1-4792-b4af-8a8677c948e6 In a large bowl, beat the cake mix, oil, eggs, pudding mix, and water with an electric mixer until smooth. Pour into prepared pan.
bb6efc81-23f1-4792-b4af-8a8677c948e6 Layer drained peaches on top of the batter.
bb6efc81-23f1-4792-b4af-8a8677c948e6 In a small bowl, beat the cream cheese, sugar, and 3 tablespoons of the reserved peach syrup with an electric mixer until smooth. Spread over peaches.
bb6efc81-23f1-4792-b4af-8a8677c948e6 Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
bb6efc81-23f1-4792-b4af-8a8677c948e6 Remove from the oven and serve warm or let cool completely and accompany with ice cream or sweetened whipped cream.
bb6efc81-23f1-4792-b4af-8a8677c948e6 Enjoy!
8990c712-51bf-4f69-8ab1-0ae1779284a4 Gather the ingredients.
8990c712-51bf-4f69-8ab1-0ae1779284a4 Preheat your oven to 350 F.
8990c712-51bf-4f69-8ab1-0ae1779284a4 Butter and flour two 9-inch cake pans. It can help to line the bottom with a circle of parchment paper cut to fit the pan.
8990c712-51bf-4f69-8ab1-0ae1779284a4 In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, oil, baking powder, salt, vanilla, and half the milk and mix until blended.
8990c712-51bf-4f69-8ab1-0ae1779284a4 Now add the egg whites and the rest of the milk and whisk until everything is blended.
8990c712-51bf-4f69-8ab1-0ae1779284a4 Pour the batter into your prepared pans and transfer them to the oven.
8990c712-51bf-4f69-8ab1-0ae1779284a4 Bake for about 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, or with a crumb or two attached. You can start testing after 27 minutes because it's better to check too soon than to overbake.
8990c712-51bf-4f69-8ab1-0ae1779284a4 Cool the cakes for 10 minutes in the pans on a wire rack, then loosen the edges by running a knife along the sides, turn the cakes out onto the racks and cool for at least another hour before frosting.
8990c712-51bf-4f69-8ab1-0ae1779284a4 Enjoy!
8dc78cae-b3c7-4853-854b-dbaff039e60e Heat the oven to 350 F.
8dc78cae-b3c7-4853-854b-dbaff039e60e Grease and flour a 9-by-13-by-2-inch baking pan or spray it with baking spray with flour.
8dc78cae-b3c7-4853-854b-dbaff039e60e In a large mixing bowl with electric mixer, prepare the cake mix according to package directions, using oil or melted butter and eggs, but add only 1/2 cup of water.
8dc78cae-b3c7-4853-854b-dbaff039e60e Spread the batter into a greased and floured 13x9x2-inch baking pan. Spoon cherry pie filling evenly over the batter, then swirl into the batter just enough to give a marbled effect.
8dc78cae-b3c7-4853-854b-dbaff039e60e Bake the cake in the preheated 350 F oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until the cake bounces back when lightly touched with a finger.
8dc78cae-b3c7-4853-854b-dbaff039e60e Cool the cake in the pan on a rack. Sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar or serve with ice cream or whipped topping.
1a0c0ac6-6522-4d1a-b47c-49afe1830976 Gather the ingredients.
1a0c0ac6-6522-4d1a-b47c-49afe1830976 In a very large bowl, combine flour, salt, sugar, and baking powder and mix well to blend.
1a0c0ac6-6522-4d1a-b47c-49afe1830976 Cut the butter into small pieces and place in food processor bowl along with 2 cups of the flour mixture.
1a0c0ac6-6522-4d1a-b47c-49afe1830976 Cover and process until mixture is very fine. Make sure that the butter is completely and evenly distributed in the flour mixture. If it isn't, your cakes will have uneven texture and each will turn out differently.
1a0c0ac6-6522-4d1a-b47c-49afe1830976 Return to bowl with remaining flour mixture and mix well using a wire whisk.
1a0c0ac6-6522-4d1a-b47c-49afe1830976 Divide the cake mix into three equal portions (about 4 cups each) by lightly scooping the mix into measuring cups and leveling off with the back of a knife.
1a0c0ac6-6522-4d1a-b47c-49afe1830976 Place each portion into a quart glass jar or heavy duty zip lock plastic bags. Cover tightly and store in the refrigerator for up to a month, or in the freezer for up to 3 months.
1a0c0ac6-6522-4d1a-b47c-49afe1830976 Each portion of cake mix will make two 8-inch cakes or one 9- x 13-inch cake.
8d9778b4-ac0f-40ab-8181-299f9545463f Heat the oven to 350 F.
8d9778b4-ac0f-40ab-8181-299f9545463f Grease and flour a 9 by 13 inch baking pan.
8d9778b4-ac0f-40ab-8181-299f9545463f Empty the white cake mix into a large mixing bowl with the eggs, 1 package of the pudding mix, 1 cup of vegetable oil, and the 7-Up. With an electric mixer on low, combine the ingredients. Increase the speed to medium and beat for 1 to 2 minutes. Fold in 1/2 cup of chopped pecans and 1/2 cup of coconut until well blended.
8d9778b4-ac0f-40ab-8181-299f9545463f Spoon the batter into the prepared baking pan and spread it evenly.
8d9778b4-ac0f-40ab-8181-299f9545463f Bake in the preheated oven for about 35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
8d9778b4-ac0f-40ab-8181-299f9545463f Cool the cake completely in the pan on a rack.
8d9778b4-ac0f-40ab-8181-299f9545463f When the cake has cooled completely, prepare the frosting.
8d9778b4-ac0f-40ab-8181-299f9545463f Combine the two envelopes of Dream Whip with the milk and pudding; beat with an electric mixer until soft peaks form. Add the remaining package of dry pistachio pudding mix and continue beating until well blended. Fold in the remaining 1/2 cup of chopped pecans.
8d9778b4-ac0f-40ab-8181-299f9545463f Spread the frosting over the cooled cake.
8d9778b4-ac0f-40ab-8181-299f9545463f Put the coconut in a dry skillet over medium heat. Cook, stirring constantly until the coconut is well-browned. Remove the coconut to a plate to cool and then sprinkle it over the frosting.
8d9778b4-ac0f-40ab-8181-299f9545463f Store leftover cake in the refrigerator for 4 to 6 days. According to the Kraft foodservice website, it can be stored in the refrigerator without spoilage for "several days".
97532f68-8509-46a1-9446-e69b628849b6 Gather the ingredients.
97532f68-8509-46a1-9446-e69b628849b6 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Lightly grease a 9-by-13-inch pan.
97532f68-8509-46a1-9446-e69b628849b6 In a medium saucepan, combine the peaches, sugar, 1 teaspoon ginger and cornstarch.
97532f68-8509-46a1-9446-e69b628849b6 Bring the peach mixture to a boil and cook for 1 minute.
97532f68-8509-46a1-9446-e69b628849b6 Remove the pan from stove. Pour the peach mixture into the prepared pan.
97532f68-8509-46a1-9446-e69b628849b6 Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the top.
97532f68-8509-46a1-9446-e69b628849b6 Sprinkle the remaining 2 teaspoons of ginger over the top.
97532f68-8509-46a1-9446-e69b628849b6 Take a fork to just mix the ginger into the dry cake mix. Don't disturb the peach portion.
97532f68-8509-46a1-9446-e69b628849b6 Drizzle the butter over the cake mix.
97532f68-8509-46a1-9446-e69b628849b6 Bake the cobbler for 1 hour or until the top is lightly browned and the peaches are bubbling.
97532f68-8509-46a1-9446-e69b628849b6 We like ours served with whipped or ice cream.
34621e4b-8ccf-45bf-b9d0-a01532ddd685 Gather the ingredients.
34621e4b-8ccf-45bf-b9d0-a01532ddd685 Lightly grease the crock pot; place peaches in the bottom. Sprinkle with cornstarch; toss.
34621e4b-8ccf-45bf-b9d0-a01532ddd685 Drizzle with vanilla and sprinkle brown sugar over all.
34621e4b-8ccf-45bf-b9d0-a01532ddd685 Sprinkle with cinnamon then the cake mix.
34621e4b-8ccf-45bf-b9d0-a01532ddd685 Drizzle melted butter evenly over cake mix.
34621e4b-8ccf-45bf-b9d0-a01532ddd685 Cover and cook on high for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.
34621e4b-8ccf-45bf-b9d0-a01532ddd685 Serve and enjoy!
f0bec190-04c3-449d-80da-c48c8362620d Heat oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas Mark 4).
f0bec190-04c3-449d-80da-c48c8362620d Generously butter an 8-inch square baking pan.
f0bec190-04c3-449d-80da-c48c8362620d Spread the cherry pie filling over the bottom of the prepared pan.
f0bec190-04c3-449d-80da-c48c8362620d In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, and salt; set aside.
f0bec190-04c3-449d-80da-c48c8362620d In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the butter and sugar together for about 3 to 4 minutes, until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs and the vanilla and almond extracts.
f0bec190-04c3-449d-80da-c48c8362620d Add the dry mixture in three additions, alternating with the milk and ending with the flour mixture. Blend thoroughly after each addition.
f0bec190-04c3-449d-80da-c48c8362620d Spoon the cake batter over the cherry pie filling; gently spread to cover.
f0bec190-04c3-449d-80da-c48c8362620d Bake the cake for 40 to 50 minutes, or until the cake springs back when lightly touched with finger.
f0bec190-04c3-449d-80da-c48c8362620d Let the cake cool for about 10 minutes. Loosen sides and carefully invert it onto a serving plate or cake server.
83eb5c54-da56-44d7-b1b0-0c74150326b1 Preheat oven to 325 degrees F.
83eb5c54-da56-44d7-b1b0-0c74150326b1 Lightly grease six wide mouth one-pint canning jars. Place them on a sturdy-sided baking sheet.
83eb5c54-da56-44d7-b1b0-0c74150326b1 Make cake batter by mixing ingredients for at least 2 minutes with an electric mixer. Fill jars halfway with batter. Bake jar cakes for 45 minutes.
83eb5c54-da56-44d7-b1b0-0c74150326b1 While cakes are baking, make the glaze by melting the butter in a pan. Stir in water and sugar. Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in rum. Place the pan on low to keep warm, if necessary, while canning jar cakes finish baking.
83eb5c54-da56-44d7-b1b0-0c74150326b1 Before removing cakes from oven, test for doneness with a toothpick or wooden skewer. Once baked, remove baking sheet with cakes from oven. With a meat fork, poke holes in cakes and pour warm glaze over hot cakes. Carefully with gloves, cover cakes with metal seals and lids. Screw lids on tightly, but not too tightly.
83eb5c54-da56-44d7-b1b0-0c74150326b1 Within 15 to 20 minutes the canning jars will begin popping while creating an airtight vacuum.
a29eb77f-edfb-487f-a5ef-496b857d74dc Gather the ingredients.
a29eb77f-edfb-487f-a5ef-496b857d74dc Preheat oven to 350 F. Spray two 8inch round cake pans OR one 13-by-9-inch cake pan with a nonstick baking spray containing flour and set aside.
a29eb77f-edfb-487f-a5ef-496b857d74dc Pour one portion of the cake mix into a large bowl. Make a well in the center of the mix and add vanilla, oil, egg whites, and milk. Beat mixture 1 minute with an electric mixer at low speed until blended. Scrape sides and bottom of the bowl and beat 2 minutes longer at medium speed until batter is smooth.​
a29eb77f-edfb-487f-a5ef-496b857d74dc Pour into prepared pans.
a29eb77f-edfb-487f-a5ef-496b857d74dc Bake the layer cakes at 350 F for 20 to 30 minutes, or until cake springs back when pressed lightly in center and begins to pull away from edges of the pan. Bake the 13-by-9-inch cake for 25 to 35 minutes until the cake tests done.
5f2051f7-6622-4beb-a70f-ff34d836b4b1 Lightly grease a single layer cake pan. You can use either a round or a square pan.
5f2051f7-6622-4beb-a70f-ff34d836b4b1 Pre-heat the oven to the temperature indicated on the box of your cake mix.
5f2051f7-6622-4beb-a70f-ff34d836b4b1 Dump the undrained crushed pineapple into your lightly greased cake pan and spread into an even single layer. Then, dump the pie filling on top of the crushed pineapple and again, spread into an even single layer.
5f2051f7-6622-4beb-a70f-ff34d836b4b1 Cover the pie filling and pineapple with the powdered cake mix right out of the box, then drizzle or crumble the vegan margarine on top of the cake mix.
5f2051f7-6622-4beb-a70f-ff34d836b4b1 If you'd like, you can also sprinkle the top with some nuts and brown sugar (both are optional).
5f2051f7-6622-4beb-a70f-ff34d836b4b1 Bake your pineapple dump cake according to the directions on the box of cake mix.
3f1dd3f9-8841-470e-ac33-ba86819123aa Preheat oven to 350 F.
3f1dd3f9-8841-470e-ac33-ba86819123aa Spray a 9 x 13 pan with cooking spray.
3f1dd3f9-8841-470e-ac33-ba86819123aa In a large bowl, beat the cake mix, eggs, water, oil, and vanilla until smooth.
3f1dd3f9-8841-470e-ac33-ba86819123aa Pour into prepared pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
3f1dd3f9-8841-470e-ac33-ba86819123aa Remove cake from oven and let cool completely.
3f1dd3f9-8841-470e-ac33-ba86819123aa Meanwhile, stir together the sweetened condensed milk, evaporated milk and whole milk or light cream until well blended.
3f1dd3f9-8841-470e-ac33-ba86819123aa Poke cake all over with a skewer or straw. Pour milk mixture all over the cake, pressing lightly to make sure milk is completely absorbed.
3f1dd3f9-8841-470e-ac33-ba86819123aa Refrigerate the cake for 1 to 2 hours.
3f1dd3f9-8841-470e-ac33-ba86819123aa Spread frosting over cake.
3f1dd3f9-8841-470e-ac33-ba86819123aa Cut cake into slices and spoon several tablespoons of the sauce over each slice. Top with sliced strawberries.
8b844557-d54c-4cf2-947e-e948ddbcdc0c Gather the ingredients.
8b844557-d54c-4cf2-947e-e948ddbcdc0c Preheat the oven to 350 F.
8b844557-d54c-4cf2-947e-e948ddbcdc0c In a large bowl, combine cake mix, softened butter, and egg, (plus, water for chocolate cake mix) with a mixer or a spoon until the dry ingredients are moistened and the dough is thoroughly mixed.
8b844557-d54c-4cf2-947e-e948ddbcdc0c Stir in any mix-ins (if using).
8b844557-d54c-4cf2-947e-e948ddbcdc0c Drop the dough by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
8b844557-d54c-4cf2-947e-e948ddbcdc0c Bake at 350 F for 9 to 12 minutes.
8b844557-d54c-4cf2-947e-e948ddbcdc0c Cool the cookies for 2 minutes on the cookie sheets, then use a wide and thin spatula to place them on wire racks to continue cooling.
8b844557-d54c-4cf2-947e-e948ddbcdc0c Store the cookies in an airtight container at room temperature.
ca083d29-8f89-410b-b7b4-2ed638eb463a Gather the ingredients.
ca083d29-8f89-410b-b7b4-2ed638eb463a Grease and flour a 10 to 12-cup Bundt cake pan or 10-inch tube cake pan. Preheat the oven to 325 F for a dark pan or 350 F for a light-colored pan.
ca083d29-8f89-410b-b7b4-2ed638eb463a Add the eggs and sugar to a mixing bowl. Beat with an electric mixer until light.
ca083d29-8f89-410b-b7b4-2ed638eb463a Beat in the sour cream, oil, lemon juice, and lemon zest. Continue beating until smooth.
ca083d29-8f89-410b-b7b4-2ed638eb463a With the mixer on low speed, slowly blend in the cake mix. Turn the mixer to high and beat until well blended.
ca083d29-8f89-410b-b7b4-2ed638eb463a Fold in the blueberries with a spatula or wooden spoon.
ca083d29-8f89-410b-b7b4-2ed638eb463a Spoon the batter into the prepared baking pan and smooth the top.
ca083d29-8f89-410b-b7b4-2ed638eb463a Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into the middle of the cake.
ca083d29-8f89-410b-b7b4-2ed638eb463a Dust with powdered sugar and serve with freshly whipped cream, crème fraîche , or a lemon or vanilla glaze, if desired.
e57137d4-febe-49b6-9ee7-30fd8341f89b Gather the ingredients.
e57137d4-febe-49b6-9ee7-30fd8341f89b Heat the oven to 350 F. Grease and flour a 9- x 13- x 2-inch baking pan.
e57137d4-febe-49b6-9ee7-30fd8341f89b In a mixing bowl, mix the cake mix, cherry pie filling, eggs, and flavoring by hand.
e57137d4-febe-49b6-9ee7-30fd8341f89b Pour the batter into the prepared pan.
e57137d4-febe-49b6-9ee7-30fd8341f89b Bake in the preheated oven for about 30 minutes, or until a wooden pick or cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
e57137d4-febe-49b6-9ee7-30fd8341f89b For the frosting, place sugar, butter, and milk in a saucepan.
e57137d4-febe-49b6-9ee7-30fd8341f89b Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil for one minute.
e57137d4-febe-49b6-9ee7-30fd8341f89b Remove from the heat and stir in chocolate chips until smooth.
e57137d4-febe-49b6-9ee7-30fd8341f89b Pour the frosting over the warm cake.
e57137d4-febe-49b6-9ee7-30fd8341f89b Let cool, then serve and enjoy!
75fefe9c-0ec0-4868-8b7b-7d35abb67708 Bake cake according to the mix's directions in a 9x13-inch baking pan.
75fefe9c-0ec0-4868-8b7b-7d35abb67708 While the cake is baking, mix the coconut milk and condensed milk together well.
75fefe9c-0ec0-4868-8b7b-7d35abb67708 When the cake is done, take the handle end of a wooden spoon and poke holes all over the cake.
75fefe9c-0ec0-4868-8b7b-7d35abb67708 Pour the coconut and condensed milk mixture into the holes and over top of the cake.
75fefe9c-0ec0-4868-8b7b-7d35abb67708 Place a sieve over a bowl and drain the pineapple thoroughly.
75fefe9c-0ec0-4868-8b7b-7d35abb67708 Spread the drained crushed pineapple on top of the cake along with some of the reserved liquid.
75fefe9c-0ec0-4868-8b7b-7d35abb67708 Let the cake cool and then mix the coconut, and whipped topping together and spread on top of cake; sprinkle with chopped pecans.
75fefe9c-0ec0-4868-8b7b-7d35abb67708 Refrigerate until cold before serving.
75fefe9c-0ec0-4868-8b7b-7d35abb67708 Refrigerate leftovers.
214d0b78-b93d-4602-b44a-514c0fd5591c Gather the ingredients
214d0b78-b93d-4602-b44a-514c0fd5591c Heat oven to 350 F. Use cooking spray to grease a 10-inch tube pan with a removable bottom.
214d0b78-b93d-4602-b44a-514c0fd5591c In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until thick and pale yellow.
214d0b78-b93d-4602-b44a-514c0fd5591c Add the cake mix, dry pudding mix, water, and vegetable oil. Using an electric mixer, beat at medium speed for 10 minutes.
214d0b78-b93d-4602-b44a-514c0fd5591c Pour batter into the greased pan.
214d0b78-b93d-4602-b44a-514c0fd5591c Bake the cake for about 50 minutes, or until a wooden pick or cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean. Place the pan on a wire rack and let the cake cool for about 15 minutes.
214d0b78-b93d-4602-b44a-514c0fd5591c In a saucepan, combine the lemon juice and sifted powdered sugar. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
214d0b78-b93d-4602-b44a-514c0fd5591c Remove the cake from the pan or invert it, placing it on a plate. Use a fork to prick several holes in the top of the cake.
214d0b78-b93d-4602-b44a-514c0fd5591c Drizzle the hot glaze over the top and spread over the sides of the cake. Serve and enjoy!
b65e4f72-8179-4c86-a8b7-9a926844dad5 Gather the ingredients.
b65e4f72-8179-4c86-a8b7-9a926844dad5 Prepare the cake batter according to the box directions.
b65e4f72-8179-4c86-a8b7-9a926844dad5 Pour into a greased and floured 9 by-13-inch pan.
b65e4f72-8179-4c86-a8b7-9a926844dad5 Bake according to the package directions.
b65e4f72-8179-4c86-a8b7-9a926844dad5 Let the cake cool 15 minutes.
b65e4f72-8179-4c86-a8b7-9a926844dad5 Invert onto a serving platter to cool completely.
b65e4f72-8179-4c86-a8b7-9a926844dad5 Place the cake in the freezer while you prepare the frosting (this makes the flag cake easier to frost).
b65e4f72-8179-4c86-a8b7-9a926844dad5 With an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese, whipped topping, and powdered sugar until smooth.
b65e4f72-8179-4c86-a8b7-9a926844dad5 Remove the cake from the freezer and spread the top and sides with the whipped cream frosting.
b65e4f72-8179-4c86-a8b7-9a926844dad5 To decorate your flag cake, outline a square in the top left corner with blueberries.
b65e4f72-8179-4c86-a8b7-9a926844dad5 Fill in with remaining blueberries, leaving some white space showing through. These are the stars on your flag cake.
b65e4f72-8179-4c86-a8b7-9a926844dad5 Make several lines of raspberries next to and below the blueberries. These are the stripes of your flag cake. Refrigerate the flag cake until ready to serve.
7c11bba4-038d-4c50-9f96-19667c41c53a Preheat oven to 350 F.
7c11bba4-038d-4c50-9f96-19667c41c53a Mix together all ingredients in a large bowl until well combined.
7c11bba4-038d-4c50-9f96-19667c41c53a Refrigerate dough for at least a half hour. This will help it firm up before using.
7c11bba4-038d-4c50-9f96-19667c41c53a Using a spoon, scoop dough into balls and place on an ungreased baking sheet.
7c11bba4-038d-4c50-9f96-19667c41c53a Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350 F.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 F. Line one 12-cup standard muffin tin with cupcake liners.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc In a medium bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, and salt.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc In another bowl, beat the eggs and sugar with an electric mixer until light and foamy, about 2 minutes. While beating, gradually pour in the melted butter, followed by the vanilla.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc Working in batches, alternately add the flour mixture and the milk to the egg mixture. Do not overmix.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc Divide the batter evenly into each cup of the prepared muffin tin. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until a cake tester inserted into the center of the cupcakes comes out clean.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc Cool the cupcakes in the tin on a rack for 10 minutes, then remove from the tin and cool on the rack completely.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc To prepare the frosting, beat the softened butter until smooth. Add the powdered sugar and beat until no lumps remain.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc Add the heavy cream, vanilla, and salt. Beat until combined.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc Place the frosting in a decorating bag fitted with a large star tip. Pipe a few swirls of frosting on each cupcake.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc Decorate the cupcakes with pastel colored sprinkles.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc Place a few tablespoons of pink sanding sugar on a plate. Halve each marshmallow on the diagonal, then press the cut side in the sugar to coat.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc Press two marshmallow unicorn ears in place on each cupcake. Place a gold spiral candle between the marshmallow ears on each cupcake to become the unicorn horn.
19e25ace-f894-4b84-8847-105344f3c2bc Refrigerate until ready to serve. These can be prepared and decorated up to 8 hours before serving.
9b565ee0-64b0-4350-9fa5-c78e2b09013c Gather your ingredients. Wipe the berries with paper towels and remove the hull. As these strawberries are going to be puréed, you can chop the tops off with a kitchen knife. Roughly chop the fruit, place in a mixing bowl, sprinkle with the sugar, stir and leave for 15 minutes.
9b565ee0-64b0-4350-9fa5-c78e2b09013c Transfer the strawberries into a food processor and pulse to create a thick purée. The purée can be used unstrained but if you prefer a smoother frosting, push the purée through a fine sieve (keep in mind that this will also remove some of the texture and a little flavor). Put aside.
9b565ee0-64b0-4350-9fa5-c78e2b09013c Beat the butter and 2 cups of the powdered sugar in a stand mixer using the paddle beater on low speed. Add the strawberry purée, vanilla, lemon juice, and rosewater if you are using it, and whip until light and fluffy.
9b565ee0-64b0-4350-9fa5-c78e2b09013c With the mixer turning (still on low or you may disappear into a cloud of sugar!) gradually add more powdered sugar until the mixture is the thickness you want — buttercream for frosting a cake should be stiffer than for piping onto a cupcake, for example.
9b565ee0-64b0-4350-9fa5-c78e2b09013c The buttercream is now ready to use in your recipes, it will keep tightly covered in the refrigerator for five days. It also freezes well for up to three months.
7c513201-88a5-4e2e-bbde-2948012cdabd Gather the ingredients.
7c513201-88a5-4e2e-bbde-2948012cdabd Place the coarsely chopped dark chocolate in a medium-sized bowl. Set aside.
7c513201-88a5-4e2e-bbde-2948012cdabd In a small saucepan over medium-high heat, heat the coconut milk until bubbles just begin to appear around the edges and steam rises from the surface.
7c513201-88a5-4e2e-bbde-2948012cdabd Pour the hot coconut milk over the chopped chocolate and let stand without stirring for 5 minutes.
7c513201-88a5-4e2e-bbde-2948012cdabd After 5 minutes, whisk the chocolate-coconut milk mixture until glossy and smooth (this will take about 2 minutes of gentle stirring).
7c513201-88a5-4e2e-bbde-2948012cdabd Add the vanilla extract and stir until incorporated. Use warm or slightly cooled.
7c513201-88a5-4e2e-bbde-2948012cdabd Enjoy!
1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 Gather the ingredients.
1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 Using a serrated knife, cut the angel food cake horizontally into 3 layers. Place the bottom cake layer on a serving platter; set other layers aside on a flat work surface.
1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 In a small bowl, combine the coffee and 1/4 cup of the coffee liqueur.
1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 With a long-tined fork or skewers, poke holes all over on all three layers.
1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 Drizzle mixture evenly over the tops of all three layers to soak mixture into holes.
1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 Make the filling: In bowl of electric mixer, cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar, and coffee liqueur until blended and smooth.
1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 Place bottom cake layer on serving platter. Spread with half of the filling mixture.
1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 Place a second cake layer on top of first layer and spread the top with remaining filling.
1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 Place the third cake layer on top of second cake layer. Make the Frosting. In a small bowl, stir together the powdered sugar with the instant espresso or coffee powder.
