1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 Fold mixture into the thawed whipped topping just until blended.
1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 Frost the entire cake with the whipped topping mixture. Chill cake for at least 2 hours.
1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 Before serving, stir together the fudge ice cream topping and coffee liqueur. Drizzle over chilled cake.
1a33139e-f3e6-4d65-9362-6857419ddb17 Cut cake using a serrated knife and serve.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Gather your ingredients.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Preheat the oven to 350 F. Cream the butter and sugar together in a large bowl using a hand mixer or in the bowl of a stand mixer using the whisk attachment, for ten minutes until light and fluffy.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Add the vanilla, then add the eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Sift together the remaining dry ingredients.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Alternate adding the milk and dry ingredients into the batter. Beat for another five minutes until fluffy.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Prepare a large, oven-proof mixing bowl and a cupcake tin. Grease both generously with cooking spray, then coat them with a thin layer of flour, tapping off all of the excess. You only need to prepare three or four wells in the muffin tin.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Pour three quarters of the batter into the prepared oven-proof bowl.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Fill three to four wells of the muffin tin with the remaining batter, three-quarters of the way up the sides.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Bake the cupcakes and large cake in the oven. Take the cupcakes out after about 20 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Bake the larger cake for longer, about 35 to 40 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Allow all of the cakes to cool completely, then remove them from their pans.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Gather the frosting and decorating ingredients.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Take one of the cupcakes, and crumble it up. Mix the cake crumbs with 2 tablespoons of frosting. This will form a cake ball to make the tail. You can also use one of the cupcakes as a tail, but it looks a little better to have a rounder, smaller tail in comparison to the feet.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Place the large cake on a cake stand. Trim the top of the cake before flipping it upside-down, so that it will lay flat on the plate. You can also add a layer of frosting around the base to hide any gaps.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Coat the whole cake in a layer of frosting. It doesn't have to be super-tidy, since you'll be covering it in shredded coconut as well.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Cover the entire cake in 3 cups of the coconut flakes. Pat down the areas where the tail and feet meet the cake, so they look distinct from the rest of the body.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Grind the Oreo cookies in a food processor until they become "dirt," or very fine crumbs.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Pat a circle of the Oreo cookie "dirt" around the base of the cake, so it looks like the bunny's butt is poking out of the dirt.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Dye the remaining coconut green by mixing it with a few drops of food coloring in a bowl. Place a circle around the remaining base of the cake stand to look like grass.
3d4f4eef-2e4e-4cca-b739-a714b69088c8 Use pink dyed frosting or pink jelly beans to create the pads of the feet. Then start showing it off!
957ab094-7238-428b-955b-50d73bcd8777 Gather the ingredients.
957ab094-7238-428b-955b-50d73bcd8777 Beat cream cheese until very smooth.
957ab094-7238-428b-955b-50d73bcd8777 Beat in powdered sugar.
957ab094-7238-428b-955b-50d73bcd8777 Stir in vanilla and add 3 tablespoons milk.
957ab094-7238-428b-955b-50d73bcd8777 Add more milk to get the desired consistency for drizzling.
957ab094-7238-428b-955b-50d73bcd8777 Try on your favorite cake or on another recipe. Enjoy.
b5f1672b-1a8f-472a-9f61-86e75016da44 Gather the ingredients.
b5f1672b-1a8f-472a-9f61-86e75016da44 Combine the granulated sugar, egg whites, and salt in the bowl of a stand mixer. Set the stand mixer bowl over a medium saucepan filled with 1 inch of gently simmering water (do not let the bowl touch the water). Heat, whisking constantly, until the sugar has dissolved and an instant-read thermometer registers 115 F. This will take about 5 minutes. The mixture should feel completely smooth when rubbed between your fingertips.
b5f1672b-1a8f-472a-9f61-86e75016da44 Wipe away any moisture that has accumulated on the bottom of the stand mixer bowl. Fit the bowl onto the stand mixer fitted with a whisk attachment and beat on medium-high speed until meringue is fluffy and glossy, about 8 to 10 minutes.
b5f1672b-1a8f-472a-9f61-86e75016da44 It is ready when the bottom of the bowl is completely cool to the touch and the mixture resembles a white fluffy cloud.
b5f1672b-1a8f-472a-9f61-86e75016da44 Reduce the mixer speed to medium low and add the butter, a few cubes at a time. The mixture may begin to appear curdled, but this is okay; keep the mixer running until the buttercream is smooth, glossy, and white (it will lighten in color during mixing), 10 to 15 minutes.
b5f1672b-1a8f-472a-9f61-86e75016da44 Scrape down the sides and add the vanilla extract and beat until incorporated.
b5f1672b-1a8f-472a-9f61-86e75016da44 Pipe onto cakes or cupcakes as desired.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Gather your ingredients.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Cream the butter and sugar together in the bowl of a stand mixer or a large mixing bowl with a hand mixer, about 10 minutes, until light and fluffy.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Beat in the eggs one at a time, until creamy and totally incorporated.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Whisk together the remaining dry ingredients in a large bowl. You can also sift the ingredients together.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Alternate adding the dry mixture and the milk into the sugar and butter mixture, beating after each addition. Scrape down the sides of the bowl, and mix until all ingredients are completely incorporated, with no remaining lumps.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 You'll need a square baking pan and a round, 9-inch baking pan. Prepare your cake pans by spraying them with cooking spray, then coating them with flour. You can also place a piece of parchment paper in the bottoms of the pans.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Divide the cake batter evenly between the prepared pans.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Bake them in a 375 F degree oven for 40 minutes, or until a toothpick comes clean out of the center of the cakes.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Allow the cakes to cool, then remove them from the baking pans. Cut off a half-circle from each of the ends of the cake. You are not cutting the cake in half, just slicing the ends off. You can cut one bigger than the other, so that the egg looks like one end is larger than the other (as it does in real life).
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Place the half circles onto the ends of the square cake.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Cut some of the middle of the round cake into strips to lay on the sides of the square cake.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Gather your frosting ingredients.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Trim the strips so that they are rounded appropriately. Fill in the cracks of the cake with some frosting. You can also use toothpicks to fasten the cake pieces together.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Cover the cake with a crumb coating of frosting.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Apply the final coating of frosting.
0e00879e-1f36-4756-aec2-b4957e7ada12 Place the cake in the refrigerator for a few minutes to allow the frosting to set, then apply the colored frosting using a piping bag. You can now add add jelly beans or other decorations. Decorate the edges of the egg with green-tinted coconut to look like grass.
16a4b8ae-6d19-4ab5-a279-6ade1869bd35 Gather the ingredients.
16a4b8ae-6d19-4ab5-a279-6ade1869bd35 In a medium-large mixing bowl, using an electric hand mixer, cream the confectioners' sugar with the soy margarine until mixture is thick but well combined, about 30 seconds to 1 minute.
16a4b8ae-6d19-4ab5-a279-6ade1869bd35 Add the almond milk or soy milk, cocoa powder, and vanilla and continue to mix until smooth, about 1 minute.
16a4b8ae-6d19-4ab5-a279-6ade1869bd35 Refrigerate and spread just before serving on fully-cooled cookies, cakes or cupcakes.
16a4b8ae-6d19-4ab5-a279-6ade1869bd35 Enjoy!
372ad5c6-50bc-4cc6-8f2e-0cb9b6f71653 Gather the ingredients.
372ad5c6-50bc-4cc6-8f2e-0cb9b6f71653 In a large mixing bowl using an electric hand mixer, cream the soy margarine until fluffy, or for about 2 minutes.
372ad5c6-50bc-4cc6-8f2e-0cb9b6f71653 Add the confectioners' sugar gradually, beating at a low speed until combined.
372ad5c6-50bc-4cc6-8f2e-0cb9b6f71653 Turn up the speed to high, add the remaining ingredients, and beat until the mixture is smooth and creamy.
372ad5c6-50bc-4cc6-8f2e-0cb9b6f71653 Chill slightly before using to frost Dairy-Free Cakes, Dairy-Free Cupcakes, or other desserts.
d99799f8-c005-4000-971a-09137c8b84a5 In a mixing bowl beat the butter, salt, and vanilla with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
d99799f8-c005-4000-971a-09137c8b84a5 Add the confectioners' sugar a little at a time, beating after each addition.
d99799f8-c005-4000-971a-09137c8b84a5 Add 3 tablespoons milk or light cream, beating until smooth.
d99799f8-c005-4000-971a-09137c8b84a5 Beat in more milk or cream until desired spreading consistency is reached, and the frosting is spreadable.
1b275d3b-d83e-4b0b-b62a-03cfdc553c2a Gather the ingredients.
1b275d3b-d83e-4b0b-b62a-03cfdc553c2a First, whisk together or blend together using a mixer all of the ingredients until smooth and creamy, adding more or less soy milk to achieve the desired consistency.
1b275d3b-d83e-4b0b-b62a-03cfdc553c2a Careful, though, as you don't want to add extra soy milk too soon, and add just a 1/2 teaspoon or so at a time, otherwise you run the risk of your frosting getting too thin and runny.
1b275d3b-d83e-4b0b-b62a-03cfdc553c2a Also, you might want to stick the peanut butter in the microwave for about 10 to 15 seconds or so, in order to make it easier to work with.
1b275d3b-d83e-4b0b-b62a-03cfdc553c2a Homemade peanut butter frosting is perfect for a vegan cake or cupcakes for the kids.
a615b240-ce5b-4752-af06-561009f77b88 Gather the ingredients.
a615b240-ce5b-4752-af06-561009f77b88 Add the margarine, cream cheese, and powdered sugar to a large mixing bowl.
a615b240-ce5b-4752-af06-561009f77b88 Use an electric mixer to blend all of the ingredients until creamy and fluffy (about 5 minutes).
a615b240-ce5b-4752-af06-561009f77b88 Store up to one day in an airtight container in the refrigerator until ready to use.
e1541bec-20c3-443d-9d94-d7a264c9d6e9 Gather the ingredients.
e1541bec-20c3-443d-9d94-d7a264c9d6e9 In the bowl of a standing mixer (or, alternatively, in a medium-sized mixing bowl if using a hand mixer), beat the dairy-free soy margarine until smooth and fluffy, about 1 minute. Turn the mixer speed down to low and gradually add half of the powdered sugar.
e1541bec-20c3-443d-9d94-d7a264c9d6e9 Add the vanilla coconut milk and vanilla extract, followed by the remaining powdered sugar. Once most of the powdered sugar is mixed in, turn the mixer speed up to medium and then high speed, beating until the mixture is smooth and creamy, 2 to 4 minutes more.
e1541bec-20c3-443d-9d94-d7a264c9d6e9 Use to frost dairy-free and vegan cakes and cupcakes immediately or refrigerate until ready to use.
1d8d7086-fe38-4452-a438-215938f5c749 Place the chopped chocolate into a medium stainless steel bowl.
1d8d7086-fe38-4452-a438-215938f5c749 Heat the whipping cream in a small pan over medium-high heat until it comes just to a boil. Be careful not to let it boil over because ​the burnt cream is very difficult to scour off stove elements!
1d8d7086-fe38-4452-a438-215938f5c749 When the whipping cream has come to a boil pour it slowly over the finely chopped chocolate and let stand for about 10 minutes.
1d8d7086-fe38-4452-a438-215938f5c749 Whisk the chocolate cream mixture until it is very smooth and there are no chocolate chunks left.
1d8d7086-fe38-4452-a438-215938f5c749 Whisk in the vanilla extract if you are using. You can also use orange, almond, coffee or any other flavoring you desire to get the correct flavor profile for your ganache.
1d8d7086-fe38-4452-a438-215938f5c749 Allow the chocolate ganache to cool slightly before pouring it slowly over your cake. Always start pouring the ganache in the center of the cake and work your way outward. If your ganache gets too thick to pour smoothly place the bowl over lightly simmering water to create a viscous product again taking care not to scorch it.
1d8d7086-fe38-4452-a438-215938f5c749 If you want a fluffier icing for your project you can also allow the ganache to cool completely until it is thick and then beat with a hand mixer or whisk until it is light and fluffy. The color will be lighter than if you left it alone so use very dark chocolate if you need a darker hue after whipping the ganache.
9e69d284-c3dc-4602-8af7-114bd9214bbb Gather the ingredients.
9e69d284-c3dc-4602-8af7-114bd9214bbb Combine the sifted confectioners' sugar, softened butter, vanilla extract, salt, and 3 tablespoons milk in a mixing bowl.
9e69d284-c3dc-4602-8af7-114bd9214bbb Stir until smooth and well blended.
9e69d284-c3dc-4602-8af7-114bd9214bbb Adjust for desired consistency as needed, adding more milk for drizzling or more confectioners' sugar for spreading.
9e69d284-c3dc-4602-8af7-114bd9214bbb Use immediately to top a cake, cookies, and other treats.
53887c91-7058-4303-bfa0-09bce0ff85ae In a saucepan, melt 1/2 cup butter. Add the brown sugar. Bring to a boil and lower heat to medium-low. Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
53887c91-7058-4303-bfa0-09bce0ff85ae Add the milk and bring back to a boil, stirring constantly.
53887c91-7058-4303-bfa0-09bce0ff85ae Remove the pan from the heat and let the mixture cool to lukewarm.
53887c91-7058-4303-bfa0-09bce0ff85ae Gradually add sifted confectioners' sugar while beating until thick enough to spread. If too thick, add a little hot water.
53887c91-7058-4303-bfa0-09bce0ff85ae Makes enough frosting to cover the top and sides of a 2-layer cake or a 13x9-inch cake.
08d32892-cb61-4797-93c4-6085c321a547 Gather the ingredients.
08d32892-cb61-4797-93c4-6085c321a547 Combine the butter and chocolate in a saucepan over low heat. Cook, stirring until melted. Alternatively, put the chocolate and butter in a microwave-safe bowl and microwave on medium for about 1 minute. Stir and continue to heat for about 15 seconds at a time, stirring between intervals, until the chocolate and butter are melted and smooth.
08d32892-cb61-4797-93c4-6085c321a547 Sift the powdered sugar into a small bowl.
08d32892-cb61-4797-93c4-6085c321a547 Stir the sifted powdered sugar into the melted butter and chocolate. Beat the mixture, adding small amounts of boiling water until thinned as desired. If you happen to find it too thin, add a little more powdered sugar. If too thick, add more hot water.
08d32892-cb61-4797-93c4-6085c321a547 Slowly drizzle the chocolate glaze from the pot or bowl over your cooled, finish baked good (such as a cake, cookies, brownies, doughnuts, etc.). If desired, use a spatula to evenly distribute. How long the glaze will take to harden will depend on the temperature of the glaze and the temperature of the room. Once cool, it will harden.
1e55df3e-b847-4182-a58d-488d3ec438c9 Gather the ingredients.
1e55df3e-b847-4182-a58d-488d3ec438c9 In a medium saucepan over medium heat, melt the butter with the brown sugar and maple syrup. Bring to a boil while stirring constantly.
1e55df3e-b847-4182-a58d-488d3ec438c9 Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, stirring, for about 3 to 5 minutes, or until the brown sugar has dissolved.
1e55df3e-b847-4182-a58d-488d3ec438c9 Remove the syrup mixture from the heat and let stand until completely cooled.
1e55df3e-b847-4182-a58d-488d3ec438c9 Pour the cooled syrup mixture into a mixing bowl.
1e55df3e-b847-4182-a58d-488d3ec438c9 Gradually beat in 2 1/2 cups of the powdered sugar and the cream or milk. Add the vanilla and maple flavoring (if using) and beat until smooth and fluffy. Add more confectioners' sugar or more cream or milk as needed to make a spreadable frosting.
1e55df3e-b847-4182-a58d-488d3ec438c9 Use immediately to frost a cake or cupcakes.
b828a17d-aaf1-46f9-a019-a2d1f5808476 Over low to medium heat, combine the milk and the flour in a saucepan.
b828a17d-aaf1-46f9-a019-a2d1f5808476 Stir continuously until the mixture thickens or coats the back of a spoon.
b828a17d-aaf1-46f9-a019-a2d1f5808476 Remove the pan from the heat and place on a cooling rack.
b828a17d-aaf1-46f9-a019-a2d1f5808476 Once the mixture is completely cool, cream the butter and the sugar until light and fluffy.
b828a17d-aaf1-46f9-a019-a2d1f5808476 This takes about 10 minutes with a regular mixer. If you're using a stand mixer, it will only take 5 minutes to mix.
b828a17d-aaf1-46f9-a019-a2d1f5808476 Blend in the milk mixture until it is combined with the butter mixture.
b828a17d-aaf1-46f9-a019-a2d1f5808476 Add in the vanilla.
b828a17d-aaf1-46f9-a019-a2d1f5808476 Mix until it all is combined and the frosting is of a spreadable, fluffy consistency.
35be13e1-eced-43df-871f-aab1eb1d11da Gather the ingredients.
35be13e1-eced-43df-871f-aab1eb1d11da In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat the softened cream cheese and butter together until smooth and fluffy.
35be13e1-eced-43df-871f-aab1eb1d11da With the electric mixer on low speed, add 3 cups of the confectioners' sugar a little at a time; continue beating until well blended. Beat on high speed until very smooth and creamy. Add more confectioners' sugar, as needed for thickness.
35be13e1-eced-43df-871f-aab1eb1d11da Add a pinch of salt and the vanilla extract and blend thoroughly until light and fluffy. The recipe makes enough cream cheese frosting for a small layer cake, a sheet cake, or about 12 to 18 cupcakes.
e3910e69-9b73-4787-87c9-80094a7f57c4 Gather the ingredients.
e3910e69-9b73-4787-87c9-80094a7f57c4 In a saucepan add a small amount of the milk to flour then stir to make a smooth paste. Add remaining milk.
e3910e69-9b73-4787-87c9-80094a7f57c4 Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
e3910e69-9b73-4787-87c9-80094a7f57c4 Cook, stirring, for 1 minute longer.
e3910e69-9b73-4787-87c9-80094a7f57c4 Remove from the heat and let it cool.
e3910e69-9b73-4787-87c9-80094a7f57c4 In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed, beat the butter until creamy.
e3910e69-9b73-4787-87c9-80094a7f57c4 Gradually add the sugar and salt; beat until light and fluffy, about 5 to 7 minutes, scraping the sides of the bowl frequently.
e3910e69-9b73-4787-87c9-80094a7f57c4 Add the cooled milk and flour mixture and beat until very light and fluffy; beat in the vanilla.
e3910e69-9b73-4787-87c9-80094a7f57c4 Enjoy!
f697c429-de5f-46d6-9d56-f5aac95d045e Gather the ingredients.
f697c429-de5f-46d6-9d56-f5aac95d045e In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, combine the butter, 3 cups of confectioners' sugar, and vanilla and orange extracts until well blended.
f697c429-de5f-46d6-9d56-f5aac95d045e Add the orange zest and 3 tablespoons of fresh orange juice. Beat until smooth and creamy.
f697c429-de5f-46d6-9d56-f5aac95d045e Add more confectioners' sugar or orange juice, as needed, for spreading or piping consistency. Beat in a few drops of orange food coloring, if desired.
f697c429-de5f-46d6-9d56-f5aac95d045e Use to frost a cake or cupcakes. Refrigerate leftovers, covered, for up to one month.
52edf4d1-42dd-4071-ba3f-aa3b72347013 Gather the ingredients.
52edf4d1-42dd-4071-ba3f-aa3b72347013 Heat 1 to 2 inches of water in the bottom part of the double boiler till it is boiling.
52edf4d1-42dd-4071-ba3f-aa3b72347013 In the top of a double boiler, add the brown sugar, egg whites, water, and salt. Place the double boiler over boiling water. The water itself should not come in contact with the bottom of the top of the double boiler.
52edf4d1-42dd-4071-ba3f-aa3b72347013 Beat the sugar and egg mixture with an electric beater until the frosting thickens. This should take about 7 minutes and the frosting should hold its shape when dropped from the beater.
52edf4d1-42dd-4071-ba3f-aa3b72347013 Remove the bowl from the heat and stir in the vanilla extract.
52edf4d1-42dd-4071-ba3f-aa3b72347013 Continue beating until the frosting is thick enough to spread.
52edf4d1-42dd-4071-ba3f-aa3b72347013 Spread on your favorite cake and enjoy!
b00372a4-06f0-49e3-809d-7870021792f2 Gather the ingredients.
b00372a4-06f0-49e3-809d-7870021792f2 In a stainless steel bowl or pan over hot simmering water, melt the chocolate chips with the butter.
b00372a4-06f0-49e3-809d-7870021792f2 Remove the pan or bowl from the lower pan and stir in sour cream, vanilla, and salt.
b00372a4-06f0-49e3-809d-7870021792f2 Slowly beat in confectioners sugar until desired spreading consistency is reached.
b00372a4-06f0-49e3-809d-7870021792f2 Chill until ready to use.
ff9a4668-b3b6-43d1-a7d6-06f10098205c Gather the ingredients.
ff9a4668-b3b6-43d1-a7d6-06f10098205c In a large saucepan, combine ingredients and mix well to blend. Bring to a boil; cover and cook 3 minutes.
ff9a4668-b3b6-43d1-a7d6-06f10098205c Uncover and cook to 238 F on a candy thermometer or until soft ball forms when dropped in cold water. Cool for 3 minutes.
ff9a4668-b3b6-43d1-a7d6-06f10098205c Beat until thick and spreadable. It should begin to lose its glossiness.
ff9a4668-b3b6-43d1-a7d6-06f10098205c Spread on layers and over sides of cake.
ff9a4668-b3b6-43d1-a7d6-06f10098205c Enjoy!
e3ed9d07-d29d-4b76-ba93-ab090b8fd650 In a mixing bowl with electric mixer, combine the butter with confectioners' sugar. Beat on low speed until sugar is moistened, then beat on medium to high speed for about 2 minutes.
e3ed9d07-d29d-4b76-ba93-ab090b8fd650 Add the vanilla and 1 tablespoon of milk or cream and beat until smooth. Beat in more milk or cream, as needed for spreading consistency.
bad1a883-507a-4bb2-a7ac-23ccef791841 Process all ingredients in a food processor or blender until smooth and creamy.
2a2a59a4-b708-42fa-a27c-202c4c5908e7 In a heavy saucepan, melt the butter.
2a2a59a4-b708-42fa-a27c-202c4c5908e7 Whisk in the sweetened condensed milk and the egg yolk.
2a2a59a4-b708-42fa-a27c-202c4c5908e7 While constantly stirring, bring the mixture to a boil.
2a2a59a4-b708-42fa-a27c-202c4c5908e7 Once it boils, remove from the pan from the heat.
2a2a59a4-b708-42fa-a27c-202c4c5908e7 Stir in the coconut and the pecans.
2a2a59a4-b708-42fa-a27c-202c4c5908e7 Cool the frosting to room temperature, Once cool spread it on German Chocolate Cake or some other cake of your desire.
d315b1c0-6f44-4391-99f4-b36dd5728807 Beat the powdered sugar and meringue powder together with an electric mixer.
d315b1c0-6f44-4391-99f4-b36dd5728807 Beat in 1/4 cup of the warm water. If the icing isn't smooth enough, add additional water, one tablespoon at a time until it reaches the desired consistency.
7bab8f9f-d1ee-47ab-9cb4-af71b9034da6 Blend all of the ingredients together on high speed until creamy, smooth and irresistible.
7bab8f9f-d1ee-47ab-9cb4-af71b9034da6 Use immediately or store in the refrigerator in an airtight container. Once refrigerated, the icing will become very hard and need to be thawed or warmed before using again. If you stored it in a glass container, try running the sealed container under hot water to get the warming process going.
831f7218-a1b4-4f85-843c-dfc4cb6e995c Gather the ingredients.
831f7218-a1b4-4f85-843c-dfc4cb6e995c Combine flour and sugar in top of double boiler.
831f7218-a1b4-4f85-843c-dfc4cb6e995c With a whisk, beat in the water, egg, lemon peel, and lemon juice; cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 10 to 15 minutes.
831f7218-a1b4-4f85-843c-dfc4cb6e995c Remove from the heat and add butter; refrigerate for about 1 hour, until well chilled.
831f7218-a1b4-4f85-843c-dfc4cb6e995c Just before serving, beat heavy cream until stiff peaks form; fold into the lemon sauce until blended.
831f7218-a1b4-4f85-843c-dfc4cb6e995c Makes about 2 cups of dessert sauce.
831f7218-a1b4-4f85-843c-dfc4cb6e995c Serve over pound cake, angel food cake, gingerbread, bread pudding, or other desserts.
bed80891-e26f-41b7-86b2-fba6733e840d Gather the ingredients.
bed80891-e26f-41b7-86b2-fba6733e840d In a saucepan over medium-low heat, whisk the milk, flour, and salt together.
bed80891-e26f-41b7-86b2-fba6733e840d Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until the mixture is very thick and bubbly. Remove from heat and let cool to room temperature.
bed80891-e26f-41b7-86b2-fba6733e840d In a mixing bowl, beat the sugar and room-temperature butter together until smooth and creamy. There should be no grittiness left in the mixture.
bed80891-e26f-41b7-86b2-fba6733e840d Beat in the cooled flour mixture until the mixture is light and fluffy.
bed80891-e26f-41b7-86b2-fba6733e840d Beat in the vanilla bean paste or extract.
bed80891-e26f-41b7-86b2-fba6733e840d Use to frost your favorite baked goods and enjoy.
